rapidCity.description: Enterprise MIB for the Accelar product family.

BridgeId.name: BridgeId
BridgeId.description: An identifier that identifies the Bridge Id

Timeout.name: Timeout
Timeout.description: An identifier that identifies the timeout value.

RcLongDisplayString.name: RcLongDisplayString
RcLongDisplayString.description: The semantics are identical to the standard DisplayString in RFC1213 and RFC2579, except for the longer length that is allowed with this TC.

InterfaceIndexOrZero.name: InterfaceIndexOrZero
InterfaceIndexOrZero.description: This textual convention is an extension of the InterfaceIndex convention. The latter defines a greater than zero value used to identify an interface or interface sub-layer in the managed system. This extension permits the additional value of zero. the value zero is object-specific and must therefore be defined as part of the description of any object which uses this syntax. Examples of the usage of zero might include situations where interface was unknown, or when none or all interfaces need to be referenced.

PortSet.name: PortSet
PortSet.description: The string is 88 octets long, for a total of 704 bits. Each bit corresponds to a port, as represented by its ifIndex value . When a bit has the value one(1), the corresponding port is a member of the set. When a bit has the value zero(0), the corresponding port is not a member of the set. The encoding is such that the most significant bit of octet #1 corresponds to ifIndex 0, while the least significant bit of octet #88 corresponds to ifIndex 703. In order to accommodate future uses of this the string has a max size of 255 bytes.

IdList.name: IdList
IdList.description: An identifier for a list of Ids.

VrfIdentifier.name: VrfIdentifier
VrfIdentifier.description: Virtual Router Identifier. VRFID 0 is reserved for the Administrative VRF and cannot be used to create VRF's.

Ipv6NextHdr.name: Ipv6NextHdr
Ipv6NextHdr.description: The ipv6 next header to look for.

KhiStatusValue.name: KhiStatusValue
KhiStatusValue.description: Key Health Indication status defintion green(1): normal status. yellow(2): Alert. red(3): critical state. adminDisable(4): administately disable. notApplicable(5): either not config or not applicable

rcSysCommReadWriteAll.name: rcSysCommReadWriteAll
rcSysCommReadWriteAll.description: When an SNMP message is received by this entity, the community string in the message is compared with this string first. If it matches, read-write access is granted to all items in the MIB. If it doesn't match, the rcSysCommReadWrite string is compared next.

rcSysCommReadWrite.name: rcSysCommReadWrite
rcSysCommReadWrite.description: When an SNMP message is received by this entity, the community string in the message is compared with this string second. If it matches, read-write access is granted to all items in the MIB except community strings. (Community strings appear empty when read and return a no such name error when an attempt is made to write them.) If it doesn't match, the rcSysCommReadWriteLayer3 string is compared next.

rcSysCommReadOnly.name: rcSysCommReadOnly
rcSysCommReadOnly.description: When an SNMP message is received by this entity, the community string in the message is compared with this string third. If it matches, read-only access is granted to all items in the MIB except community strings. (Community strings appear empty when read.) If it doesn't match, no access is granted, no response is sent back to the SNMP requester, and SNMP traps are sent to the SNMP trap receiver(s) if configured.

rcSysResult.name: rcSysResult
rcSysResult.description: Result from the last system action.

rcSysLastChange.name: rcSysLastChange
rcSysLastChange.description: Last management initiated configuration change since sysUpTime.

rcSysLastVlanChange.name: rcSysLastVlanChange
rcSysLastVlanChange.description: Last management initiated VLAN configuration change since sysUpTime.

rcSysLastStatisticsReset.name: rcSysLastStatisticsReset
rcSysLastStatisticsReset.description: Last management initiated statistics reset since sysUpTime.

rcSysBufferUtil.name: rcSysBufferUtil
rcSysBufferUtil.description: Buffer utilization as a percentage of the total amount of buffer space in the system. A high value indicates congestion.

rcSysBufferUtilPeak.name: rcSysBufferUtilPeak
rcSysBufferUtilPeak.description: The largest buffer utilization since sysUpTime

rcSysNVRamUsed.name: rcSysNVRamUsed
rcSysNVRamUsed.description: Non-volatile RAM in use in Kbytes

rcSysLastSaveToNVRam.name: rcSysLastSaveToNVRam
rcSysLastSaveToNVRam.description: SysUpTime of the last time when NVRAM was written to. This could be a save of the system configuration or via a file transfer of a configuration file.

rcSysLastSaveToStandbyNVRam.name: rcSysLastSaveToStandbyNVRam
rcSysLastSaveToStandbyNVRam.description: SysUpTime of the last time when the standby NVRAM (on the back-up CPU board) was written to.

rcSysRmonMemSize.name: rcSysRmonMemSize
rcSysRmonMemSize.description: Amount of RAM in bytes to allocate for RMON to use when rcSysRmonEnable is TRUE.

rcSysRmonEnable.name: rcSysRmonEnable
rcSysRmonEnable.description: Control whether the RMON feature should be enabled. To enable the RMON feature, set this variable to true. The RMON agent in the device will get started immediately if the amount of memory specified by rcSysRmonMemSize is currently available in the device. To disable the RMON feature, set this variable to false, save the new setting to NVRAM, and reboot the device. After the device is rebooted the RMON agent will not be operational.

rcSysRmonSaveConfig.name: rcSysRmonSaveConfig
rcSysRmonSaveConfig.description: Control whether RMON configuration information should be saved to NVRAM so RMON settings can be automatically reinstalled after a system reboot. Setting rcSysRmonSaveConfig to true does not immediately save the configuration information. The save happens when the rcSysAction variable is set to 'saveToNVRAM(4)'. This option is only meaningful when the rcSysRmonEnable variable is set to true.

rcSysRmonTrapOption.name: rcSysRmonTrapOption
rcSysRmonTrapOption.description: Used to indicate whether RMON traps should be sent to only the owner of the RMON alarm (i.e., the manager that created the alarm entry) or all trap recipients in the system trap receiver table.

rcSysSupportRouting.name: rcSysSupportRouting
rcSysSupportRouting.description: Used to indicate whether routing is supported in this product.

rcSysSupportWebServer.name: rcSysSupportWebServer
rcSysSupportWebServer.description: Used to indicate whether WebServer is supported in this product.

rcSysLastIpAddrChange.name: rcSysLastIpAddrChange
rcSysLastIpAddrChange.description: Last management initiated IP address change since sysUpTime. Any addition or deletion of an IP address to a single routable port or a VLAN is time-stamped by this variable.

rcSysCommReadWriteLayer3.name: rcSysCommReadWriteLayer3
rcSysCommReadWriteLayer3.description: When an SNMP message is received by this entity, the community string in the message is compared with this string third. If it matches, read-write access is granted to all Layer-3 items in the MIB except community strings. (Community strings appear empty when read and return a no such name error when an attempt is made to write them.) If it doesn't match, the rcSysCommReadWriteLayer2 string is compared next.

rcSysCommReadWriteLayer2.name: rcSysCommReadWriteLayer2
rcSysCommReadWriteLayer2.description: When an SNMP message is received by this entity, the community string in the message is compared with this string fourth. If it matches, read-write access is granted to all Layer-2 items in the MIB except community strings. (Community strings appear empty when read and return a no such name error when an attempt is made to write them.) If it doesn't match, the rcSysCommReadOnly string is compared next.

rcSysAccessPolicyEnable.name: rcSysAccessPolicyEnable
rcSysAccessPolicyEnable.description: Used to configure the system access policy feature. if 'true', the rcSysAccessPolicyTable is examined to determine which packets should be allowed or denied access to this device.

rcSysConfigFileName.name: rcSysConfigFileName
rcSysConfigFileName.description: File name used in conjunction with rcSysAction. If rcSysAction is set to 'saveRuntimeConfig' or 'saveRuntimeConfigToSlave' then this file name will be used instead of the file name specified in rcSysDefaultRuntimeConfigFileName. If rcSysAction is set to 'saveBootConfig' or 'saveBootConfigToSlave' then this file name will be used insteaad of the file name specified in rcSysDefaultBootConfigFileName. If the file name is blank (i.e., nothing is entered) then the default file name will be used.

rcSysLastRunTimeConfigSave.name: rcSysLastRunTimeConfigSave
rcSysLastRunTimeConfigSave.description: SysUpTime of the last time when the run time configuration was written to.

rcSysLastRunTimeConfigSaveToSlave.name: rcSysLastRunTimeConfigSaveToSlave
rcSysLastRunTimeConfigSaveToSlave.description: SysUpTime of the last time when the run time configuration was written to slave NVRAM.

rcSysLastBootConfigSave.name: rcSysLastBootConfigSave
rcSysLastBootConfigSave.description: SysUpTime of the last time when the boot configuration was written to.

rcSysLastBootConfigSaveOnSlave.name: rcSysLastBootConfigSaveOnSlave
rcSysLastBootConfigSaveOnSlave.description: SysUpTime of the last time when the boot configuration was written on the slave NVRAM.

rcSysRmonUtilizationMethod.name: rcSysRmonUtilizationMethod
rcSysRmonUtilizationMethod.description: Used to control whether RMON should use a half-duplex or full-duplex formula to calculate port utilization. When set to 'halfDuplex', RMON will use InOctets and the port's speed to calculate port utilization (this is the standard RMON rfc1271 convention). When set to 'fullDuplex', RMON will use InOctets and OutOctets and 2X the port's speed to calculate port utilization. Furthermore, if this variable is set to 'fullDuplex', but the port is operating in a half-duplex mode, the calculation defaults back to the rfc1271 convention.

rcSysDramMaxBlockFree.name: rcSysDramMaxBlockFree
rcSysDramMaxBlockFree.description: Dram max block free size in kilo-bytes

rcSysVirtualIpAddr.name: rcSysVirtualIpAddr
rcSysVirtualIpAddr.description: Virtual IP is an IP address that owned and advertised only by the master CPU. So whichever CPU is master registers this IP address. Unlike the management IP address, this address goes in the switch config file and not the boot config

rcSysVirtualNetMask.name: rcSysVirtualNetMask
rcSysVirtualNetMask.description: Net mask of the management virtual Ip address

rcSysReadWriteLevel.name: rcSysReadWriteLevel
rcSysReadWriteLevel.description: The status of the read/write level

rcSysMTUSize.name: rcSysMTUSize
rcSysMTUSize.description: This is the maximum transmission size of frames that all the ports on the chassis support.

rcSysClockSyncTime.name: rcSysClockSyncTime
rcSysClockSyncTime.description: Time interval at which RTC and system clocks are synchronized.

rcSysForceTrapSender.name: rcSysForceTrapSender
rcSysForceTrapSender.description: This is a flag that if user wants to configured CLIP (Circuit Less IP) as trap originator.

rcSysMrouteStrLimit.name: rcSysMrouteStrLimit
rcSysMrouteStrLimit.description: enable or disable mroute stream limit in system.

rcSysTrapRecvTable.name: rcSysTrapRecvTable
rcSysTrapRecvTable.description: The trap receiver table (0 to 25 entries). This table lists the addresses of Network Management Stations that should receive trap messages from this entity when an exception condition occurs.

rcSysTrapRecvCommunity.name: rcSysTrapRecvCommunity
rcSysTrapRecvCommunity.description: Community string used for trap messages to this trap receiver.

rcSysTrapRecvSrcAddress.name: rcSysTrapRecvSrcAddress
rcSysTrapRecvSrcAddress.description: Source IP address to use when sending traps. This IP address will be inserted into the source IP address field in the UDP trap packet.

rcSysAccessPolicyTable.name: rcSysAccessPolicyTable
rcSysAccessPolicyTable.description: Management access policy table. This table is used to permit or deny access to this device via the specified source Id.

rcSysAccessPolicyPolicyEnable.name: rcSysAccessPolicyPolicyEnable
rcSysAccessPolicyPolicyEnable.description: Indicate whether this policy is currently active.

rcSysAccessPolicyMode.name: rcSysAccessPolicyMode
rcSysAccessPolicyMode.description: Used to indicate whether a packet having a source IP address that matches this entry should be permitted to enter the device or denied access.

rcSysAccessPolicyService.name: rcSysAccessPolicyService
rcSysAccessPolicyService.description: Is represented as bitset to indicate which protocol this entry should be applied to. Value is one of multiple(logical 'OR') of the following values: telnet(1), snmp(2), tftp(4), ftp(8), http(16), rlogin(32), ssh(64), snmp-v3(128) telnet(1): enables telnet service snmp(2): enables snmp service tftp(4): enables tftp service ftp(8): enables ftp service http(16): enables http service rlogin(32): enables rlogin service ssh(64): enables ssh service snmp-v3(128): enables snmp service for v3 groups Value 0 means no service enabled.

rcSysAccessPolicyPrecedence.name: rcSysAccessPolicyPrecedence
rcSysAccessPolicyPrecedence.description: Used to indicate the precedence of this policy. The Lower the number the higher the precedence.

rcSysAccessPolicyTrustedHostAddr.name: rcSysAccessPolicyTrustedHostAddr
rcSysAccessPolicyTrustedHostAddr.description: Trusted IP address of host performing a rlogin into the device.

rcSysAccessPolicyTrustedHostUserName.name: rcSysAccessPolicyTrustedHostUserName
rcSysAccessPolicyTrustedHostUserName.description: User name on the trusted host performing a rlogin into the device.

rcSysAccessPolicyLog.name: rcSysAccessPolicyLog
rcSysAccessPolicyLog.description: Used to indicate whether logging should be performed if this policy was applied.

rcSysAccessPolicyAccessStrict.name: rcSysAccessPolicyAccessStrict
rcSysAccessPolicyAccessStrict.description: Used to restrict the access level specified in the system access policy table to exactly the same access level as specified by user. If TRUE then only the access level in the policy table is allowed access. If FALSE, then the default behavior is to assume the access level specified in policy table as the floor.

rcSysAccessPolicyTrustedHostInetAddress.name: rcSysAccessPolicyTrustedHostInetAddress
rcSysAccessPolicyTrustedHostInetAddress.description: Trusted Inet address of host performing a rlogin into the device.

rcSysAccPolSnmpGrpTable.name: rcSysAccPolSnmpGrpTable
rcSysAccPolSnmpGrpTable.description: SNMP group list for access policy

rcSysAccPolSnmpGrpEntry.name: rcSysAccPolSnmpGrpEntry
rcSysAccPolSnmpGrpEntry.description: The table entry which covers the groups under snmp service.

rcSysTrapSenderTable.name: rcSysTrapSenderTable
rcSysTrapSenderTable.description: The trap sender table (0 to 25 entries). This table lists the addresses of Network Management Stations and the Source Address that should receive trap messages from this entity when an exception condition occurs.

rcSysDnsServerListTable.name: rcSysDnsServerListTable
rcSysDnsServerListTable.description: DNS serever list table used to store the details of the DNS server configured.

rcSysDnsServerListIp.name: rcSysDnsServerListIp
rcSysDnsServerListIp.description: IP address of the DNS server

rcSysDnsServerListRequestCount.name: rcSysDnsServerListRequestCount
rcSysDnsServerListRequestCount.description: Number of request send to this server

rcSysDnsServerListSuccessCount.name: rcSysDnsServerListSuccessCount
rcSysDnsServerListSuccessCount.description: Number of request send to this server which are successful

rcSysDnsServerListRowStatus.name: rcSysDnsServerListRowStatus
rcSysDnsServerListRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete DNS server entries in rcSysDnsServerListTable.

rcSysDnsServerListAddressType.name: rcSysDnsServerListAddressType
rcSysDnsServerListAddressType.description: The address type of DNS Server.

rcSysDnsServerListAddress.name: rcSysDnsServerListAddress
rcSysDnsServerListAddress.description: The address of the DNS Server

rcSysDnsHostData.name: rcSysDnsHostData
rcSysDnsHostData.description: Host Name or Host IP Address.

rcSysMsgLogFrequency.name: rcSysMsgLogFrequency
rcSysMsgLogFrequency.description: Used to specify the maximum frequency/count of the occurence of the Log Message.

rcSysMsgLogText.name: rcSysMsgLogText
rcSysMsgLogText.description: A textual string containing the first four characters of the Log Message.

rcSysForceIpHdrSender.name: rcSysForceIpHdrSender
rcSysForceIpHdrSender.description: Flag to decide if IP header source address will be matched with SNMP header sender networks.

rcSysDnsDomainName.name: rcSysDnsDomainName
rcSysDnsDomainName.description: Default domain used for querying the DNS Server.

rcSysDnsRequestType.name: rcSysDnsRequestType
rcSysDnsRequestType.description: DNS Type: Whether it was Dns Request or a Response

rcSysSpanningTreeOperMode.name: rcSysSpanningTreeOperMode
rcSysSpanningTreeOperMode.description: This object indicates the current spanning-tree mode of the system. The meaning of specific values is: nortelStpg(1) .. The older proprietary mode which supports multiple spanning tree groups. pvst(2) ..Emulation of C***O spanning tree mode rstp(3) ..IEEE 802.1w mode mstp(4) ..IEEE 802.1s mode .

rcSysSpanningTreeAdminMode.name: rcSysSpanningTreeAdminMode
rcSysSpanningTreeAdminMode.description: This object indicates the desired spanning-tree mode of the system. The meaning of specific values is: nortelStpg(1) .. The older proprietary mode which supports multiple spanning tree groups. pvst(2) ..Emulation of C***O spanning tree mode rstp(3) ..IEEE 802.1w mode mstp(4) ..IEEE 802.1s mode . Note that depending on the current value of rcSysSpanningTreeOperMode and the value to which this object is set, the operational mode may be immediately changed, or the change may not take effect until the next system reboot.

rcSysAutoRecoverDelay.name: rcSysAutoRecoverDelay
rcSysAutoRecoverDelay.description: Time interval in seconds after which auto-recovery runs on ports to clear action taken by cp-limit, link flap or loop detect

rcSysMacFlapLimitTime.name: rcSysMacFlapLimitTime
rcSysMacFlapLimitTime.description: Time limit in milliseconds for MAC flapping for loop-detect feature

rcSysMacFlapLimitCount.name: rcSysMacFlapLimitCount
rcSysMacFlapLimitCount.description: Number of times mac flapping can happen for loop-detect feature

rcSysExtCplimitEnable.name: rcSysExtCplimitEnable
rcSysExtCplimitEnable.description: enable or disable extended CP-LIMIT in system.

rcSysExtCplimitMinCongTime.name: rcSysExtCplimitMinCongTime
rcSysExtCplimitMinCongTime.description: Minimum time for which System octapid should be congested to trigger congestion algorithm for extended CP-LIMIT in mSecs

rcSysExtCplimitMaxPorts.name: rcSysExtCplimitMaxPorts
rcSysExtCplimitMaxPorts.description: Maximum number of ports which need to be monitored for congestion in Extended CP-LIMIT

rcSysExtCplimitPortCongTime.name: rcSysExtCplimitPortCongTime
rcSysExtCplimitPortCongTime.description: Minimum time for which ingress traffic utilization rate of a monitored port should stay more than the allowed limits in order to disable the port for extended CP-LIMIT in Secs

rcSysExtCplimitTrapLevel.name: rcSysExtCplimitTrapLevel
rcSysExtCplimitTrapLevel.description: Indicates the trap level for extended CP-LIMIT

rcSysExtCplimitSysOctapidCongested.name: rcSysExtCplimitSysOctapidCongested
rcSysExtCplimitSysOctapidCongested.description: Indicates whether system octapid congestion detected for extended cp-limit

rcSysExtCplimitPortsMonitored.name: rcSysExtCplimitPortsMonitored
rcSysExtCplimitPortsMonitored.description: Indicates whether ports has been shutdown due to extended cp-limit

rcSysExtCplimitPortsShutDown.name: rcSysExtCplimitPortsShutDown
rcSysExtCplimitPortsShutDown.description: Indicates whether ports has been shutdown due to extended Cp-limit

rcSysActionL1.name: rcSysActionL1
rcSysActionL1.description: Initiate a system action for layer1 user

rcSysActionL2.name: rcSysActionL2
rcSysActionL2.description: Initiate a system action for layer2 user

rcSysActionL3.name: rcSysActionL3
rcSysActionL3.description: Initiate a system action for layer3 user

rcSysPowerUsage.name: rcSysPowerUsage
rcSysPowerUsage.description: The current power usage for the whole chassis.

rcSysPowerAvailable.name: rcSysPowerAvailable
rcSysPowerAvailable.description: The current power available for the whole chassis.

rcSysFrcMsgControlTable.name: rcSysFrcMsgControlTable
rcSysFrcMsgControlTable.description: Management Force-msg Control table. This table is used to specify the pattern for Force-msg Control

rcSysVirtualIpv6Addr.name: rcSysVirtualIpv6Addr
rcSysVirtualIpv6Addr.description: Virtual IP is an IP address that owned and advertised only by the master CPU. So whichever CPU is master registers this IP address.

rcSysVirtualIpv6PrefixLength.name: rcSysVirtualIpv6PrefixLength
rcSysVirtualIpv6PrefixLength.description: The length of the virtual ipv6 addr prefix (in bits).

rcSysConfigMode.name: rcSysConfigMode
rcSysConfigMode.description: This is used in conjunction with rcSysAction inorder to decide the mode in which the config file is going to be saved in.

rcSysLicenseTrialDaysLeft.name: rcSysLicenseTrialDaysLeft
rcSysLicenseTrialDaysLeft.description: This indicates days left before License Trial Period will expire.

rcSysFrcMsgControlPattern.name: rcSysFrcMsgControlPattern
rcSysFrcMsgControlPattern.description: Pattern for filtering the force-msg for msg control

rcTftpHost.name: rcTftpHost
rcTftpHost.description: Name of source/destination host for the TFTP transfer.

rcTftpFile.name: rcTftpFile
rcTftpFile.description: Name of file for the TFTP transfer.

rcTftpAction.name: rcTftpAction
rcTftpAction.description: The action for the TFTP transfer.

rcTftpResult.name: rcTftpResult
rcTftpResult.description: Contains result of the last Tftp action request.

rcVlanNumVlans.name: rcVlanNumVlans
rcVlanNumVlans.description: The number of VLANs currently defined in the switch.

rcVlanTable.name: rcVlanTable
rcVlanTable.description: A list of Virtual LAN entries. The number of entries is given by rcVlanNumVlans.

rcVlanEntry.name: rcVlanEntry
rcVlanEntry.description: Entry containing configuration information for a particular Virtual LAN. The relationship between the various port sets in a VLAN Entry are : o The set of ports defined by PortMembers must be a subset of the set of ports in the underlying STG of the VLAN. o The bitwise AND of PortMembers and NotAllowToJoin must be the empty set. o The bitwise OR of PortMembers and NotAllowToJoin must be the set of ports in the underlying STG of the VLAN. o The set of ports defined by StaticMembers must be a subset of the set of ports defined by PortMembers. o The bitwise XOR of PortMembers and StaticMembers defines the set of dynamic (potential) members of the VLAN. o The set of ports defined by ActiveMembers must be a subset of the set of ports defined by PortMembers.

rcVlanId.name: rcVlanId
rcVlanId.description: A value that uniquely identifies the Virtual LAN associated with this entry. This value corresponds to the lower 12 bits in the IEEE 802.1Q VLAN Tag.

rcVlanName.name: rcVlanName
rcVlanName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this VLAN.

rcVlanColor.name: rcVlanColor
rcVlanColor.description: An administratively-assigned color code for this VLAN. The value of this object is used by the VLAN Manager GUI tool to select a color when it draws this VLAN on the screen.

rcVlanHighPriority.name: rcVlanHighPriority
rcVlanHighPriority.description: A flag to note whether frames in this VLAN should be assigned a high switching priority.

rcVlanRoutingEnable.name: rcVlanRoutingEnable
rcVlanRoutingEnable.description: A flag to note whether IP routing is enabled in this VLAN.

rcVlanIfIndex.name: rcVlanIfIndex
rcVlanIfIndex.description: When rcVlanRoutingEnable is set to true(1), this value indicates the 'logical' ifIndex assigned to this VLAN. Otherwise, this value is meaningless and should be set to zero.

rcVlanResult.name: rcVlanResult
rcVlanResult.description: The result from the last VLAN action.

rcVlanStgId.name: rcVlanStgId
rcVlanStgId.description: Indicates the Spanning Tree Group (STG) used by this VLAN to determine the state of its ports. If this VLAN is not associated with any STG, this value should be set to zero.

rcVlanType.name: rcVlanType
rcVlanType.description: The type of VLAN, distinguished according to the policy used to define its port membership.

rcVlanPortMembers.name: rcVlanPortMembers
rcVlanPortMembers.description: The set of ports that are members (static or dynamic) of this VLAN.

rcVlanActiveMembers.name: rcVlanActiveMembers
rcVlanActiveMembers.description: The set of ports that are currently active in this VLAN. Active ports include all static ports and any dynamic ports where the VLAN policy was met.

rcVlanStaticMembers.name: rcVlanStaticMembers
rcVlanStaticMembers.description: The set of ports that are static members of this VLAN. A static member of a VLAN is always active and is never aged out.

rcVlanNotAllowToJoin.name: rcVlanNotAllowToJoin
rcVlanNotAllowToJoin.description: The set of ports that are not allowed to become members of this VLAN.

rcVlanProtocolId.name: rcVlanProtocolId
rcVlanProtocolId.description: The protocol identifier of this VLAN. This value is meaningful only if rcVlanType is equal to byProtocolId(3). For other VLAN types it should have the value none(0).

rcVlanSubnetAddr.name: rcVlanSubnetAddr
rcVlanSubnetAddr.description: The IP subnet address of this VLAN. This value is meaningful only if rcVlanType is equal to byIpSubnet(2). For other VLAN types it should have the value 0.0.0.0.

rcVlanSubnetMask.name: rcVlanSubnetMask
rcVlanSubnetMask.description: The IP subnet mask of this VLAN. This value is meaningful only if rcVlanType is equal to byIpSubnet(2). For other VLAN types it should have the value 0.0.0.0.

rcVlanAgingTime.name: rcVlanAgingTime
rcVlanAgingTime.description: The timeout period (in seconds) used for aging out dynamic members of this VLAN. This field is only relevant for policy-based VLANs.

rcVlanMacAddress.name: rcVlanMacAddress
rcVlanMacAddress.description: The MAC address assigned to the virtual router interface of this VLAN. This field is meaningful only if rcVlanRoutingEnable is equal to true(1).

rcVlanRowStatus.name: rcVlanRowStatus
rcVlanRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the rcVlanTable.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopEnable.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopEnable
rcVlanIgmpSnoopEnable.description: A flag to note whether IGMP Snooping is enabled on this VLAN.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopReportProxyEnable.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopReportProxyEnable
rcVlanIgmpSnoopReportProxyEnable.description: A flag to note whether IGMP Report Proxy is enabled on this VLAN.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopRobustness.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopRobustness
rcVlanIgmpSnoopRobustness.description: This variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness - 1) packet losses.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopQueryInterval.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopQueryInterval
rcVlanIgmpSnoopQueryInterval.description: The interval (in seconds) between IGMP Host-Query packets transmitted on this interface.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopMRouterPorts.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopMRouterPorts
rcVlanIgmpSnoopMRouterPorts.description: The set of ports in this VLAN that provide connectivity to an IP Multicast router.

rcVlanUserDefinedPid.name: rcVlanUserDefinedPid
rcVlanUserDefinedPid.description: When rcVlanProtocolId is set to usrDefined(15) in a protocol-based VLAN, this field represents the 16-bit user defined protocol identifier.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopActiveQuerier.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopActiveQuerier
rcVlanIgmpSnoopActiveQuerier.description: IP address of multicast querier router.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopMRouterExpiration.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopMRouterExpiration
rcVlanIgmpSnoopMRouterExpiration.description: Multicast querier router aging time out.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopQuerierPort.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopQuerierPort
rcVlanIgmpSnoopQuerierPort.description: The port on which the multicast querier router was heard.

rcVlanQosLevel.name: rcVlanQosLevel
rcVlanQosLevel.description: Used to specify the Qos level packets, carried in this VLAN, should be processed with.

rcVlanEncap.name: rcVlanEncap
rcVlanEncap.description: This is the encapsulation type for userdefined protocol based vlans. This is not meaningful for other types of vlan. The default value is null.

rcVlanFirewallVlanType.name: rcVlanFirewallVlanType
rcVlanFirewallVlanType.description: This is the firewall vlan type for port based vlans.

rcVlanFdbAging.name: rcVlanFdbAging
rcVlanFdbAging.description: The timeout period (in seconds) used for aging out fdb entries of this VLAN.

rcVlanOspfPassivePortMember.name: rcVlanOspfPassivePortMember
rcVlanOspfPassivePortMember.description: The set of ports in the vlan that are designated as ospf passive

rcVlanUnkDstMacDiscard.name: rcVlanUnkDstMacDiscard
rcVlanUnkDstMacDiscard.description: Enable/disable Unknown Destination Mac Discard on Vlan

rcVlanNlbMode.name: rcVlanNlbMode
rcVlanNlbMode.description: NLB mode set on a VLAN.

rcVlanVrfId.name: rcVlanVrfId
rcVlanVrfId.description: Indicates the Virtual Router to which the VLAN belongs

rcVlanVrfName.name: rcVlanVrfName
rcVlanVrfName.description: The Name of the Virtual Router to which the VLAN belongs

rcVlanNodalMepList.name: rcVlanNodalMepList
rcVlanNodalMepList.description: List of nodal Meps assigned to this vlan. A mep consists of Domain Name, Association name and Mep Id separated by '.'. Each meps is separated by ',': <md1>.<ma1>.<mepid1>,<md2>.<ma2>.<mepid2>,... The maximum number of nodal Mep for each vlan is 8.

rcVlanNumOfNodalMep.name: rcVlanNumOfNodalMep
rcVlanNumOfNodalMep.description: Number of nodal meps assigned to this vlan

rcVlanNodalMipLevelList.name: rcVlanNodalMipLevelList
rcVlanNodalMipLevelList.description: List of nodal Mip levels assigned to this vlan that allows Mip functionality to be enabled on a per level per vlan basis. A mip level is represented by an integer ranging from 0 to 7. The mip levels are separated by ',': <0...7>,<0...7>,... The maximum number of nodal Mip levels for each vlan is 8.

rcVlanNumOfNodalMipLevel.name: rcVlanNumOfNodalMipLevel
rcVlanNumOfNodalMipLevel.description: Number of nodal mip levels assigned to this vlan that allows MIP functionality to be enabled on a per level per vlan basis.

rcVlanIpMultinettingEnable.name: rcVlanIpMultinettingEnable
rcVlanIpMultinettingEnable.description: Indicate if the vlan is an Ip Multinetting vlan. If enabled, rcVlanAssociatedIpMultinettingVlan should be set to 0

rcVlanAssociatedIpMultinettingVlan.name: rcVlanAssociatedIpMultinettingVlan
rcVlanAssociatedIpMultinettingVlan.description: Associated Ip Multinetting vlan Id whose rcVlanIpMultinettingEnable attribute is set

rcVlanPlsbIsid.name: rcVlanPlsbIsid
rcVlanPlsbIsid.description: Plsb i-sid number assigned to a C-vlan. Default 0 value indicates that no i-sid has been assinged.

rcVlanPortTable.name: rcVlanPortTable
rcVlanPortTable.description: A table used to maintain VLAN port related information.

rcVlanPortEntry.name: rcVlanPortEntry
rcVlanPortEntry.description: Entry containing VLAN information regarding a particular port.

rcVlanPortIndex.name: rcVlanPortIndex
rcVlanPortIndex.description: An unique index used to identify a particular port in the system. This index is equal to the ifIndex of the port.

rcVlanPortNumVlanIds.name: rcVlanPortNumVlanIds
rcVlanPortNumVlanIds.description: Used to indicate the number of VLAN IDs that are stored in the rcVlanPortVlanIds variable.

rcVlanPortVlanIds.name: rcVlanPortVlanIds
rcVlanPortVlanIds.description: An array used to identify which VLANs this port is assigned to. Each VLAN ID is stored as a two octet value. The first octet in the pair holds bits 15-8 of the VLAN ID, while the second octet holds bits 7-0 of the VLAN ID. This object is now replaced by rcVlanPortVlanIdList.

rcVlanPortType.name: rcVlanPortType
rcVlanPortType.description: The type of port: access(1) or trunk(2).

rcVlanPortDiscardTaggedFrames.name: rcVlanPortDiscardTaggedFrames
rcVlanPortDiscardTaggedFrames.description: A flag used to determine how to process tagged frames received on this access port. When the flag is set, these frames are discarded by the forwarding process. When the flag is reset, these frames are processed normally. This field is meaningless when the port is not an access port and should be set to false(2).

rcVlanPortDiscardUntaggedFrames.name: rcVlanPortDiscardUntaggedFrames
rcVlanPortDiscardUntaggedFrames.description: A flag used to determine how to process untagged frames received on this trunk port. When the flag is set, these frames are discarded by the forwarding process. When the flag is reset, these frames are assigned to the VLAN specified by rcVlanPortDefaultVlanId. This field is meaningless when the port is not a trunk port and should be set to false(2).

rcVlanPortDefaultVlanId.name: rcVlanPortDefaultVlanId
rcVlanPortDefaultVlanId.description: The VLAN ID assigned to untagged frames received on this trunk port. This field is meaningless when the port is not a trunk port.

rcVlanPortPerformTagging.name: rcVlanPortPerformTagging
rcVlanPortPerformTagging.description: Enable/disable the port on the current vlan to perform tagging on the incoming and outgoing traffic.

rcVlanPortLoopDetect.name: rcVlanPortLoopDetect
rcVlanPortLoopDetect.description: Enable/disable loop detection on this port

rcVlanPortFirstPortInOpid.name: rcVlanPortFirstPortInOpid
rcVlanPortFirstPortInOpid.description: This value gives the IfIndex of the first port in the octapid. This value is used to generate an error message when changing port type from normal to uni/nni and viceversa

rcVlanPortLastPortInOpid.name: rcVlanPortLastPortInOpid
rcVlanPortLastPortInOpid.description: This value gives the IfIndex of the first port in the octapid. This value is used to generate an error message when changing port type from normal to uni/nni and viceversa

rcVlanPortUntagDefaultVlan.name: rcVlanPortUntagDefaultVlan
rcVlanPortUntagDefaultVlan.description: enable/disable Egress Tagging on the Default Vlan of the port.

rcVlanPortLoopDetectAction.name: rcVlanPortLoopDetectAction
rcVlanPortLoopDetectAction.description: This value is used to specify the action which needs to be taken once a loop is detected on a specific port.

rcVlanPortArpDetect.name: rcVlanPortArpDetect
rcVlanPortArpDetect.description: Enable/disable Arp detection on this port

rcVlanPortSpoofDetect.name: rcVlanPortSpoofDetect
rcVlanPortSpoofDetect.description: Enable/disable spoof detection on this port

rcVlanPortVlanIdList.name: rcVlanPortVlanIdList
rcVlanPortVlanIdList.description: This bitfield is used to identify which VLANs this port is assigned to. Each VLAN ID is stored as a bit. The most-significant (left-most) bit represents Vlan Id 1.

rcVlanMacTable.name: rcVlanMacTable
rcVlanMacTable.description: A table used to maintain MAC addresses assigned to a particular VLAN by MAC address.

rcVlanMacEntry.name: rcVlanMacEntry
rcVlanMacEntry.description: Entry containing VLAN information regarding a particular port.

rcVlanMacVlanId.name: rcVlanMacVlanId
rcVlanMacVlanId.description: An unique index used to identify a VLAN (by MAC address) in the system.

rcVlanMacAddr.name: rcVlanMacAddr
rcVlanMacAddr.description: An unique index used to identify a MAC address assigned to a particular VLAN.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopNumGroups.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopNumGroups
rcVlanIgmpSnoopNumGroups.description: The number of entries (rows) in the rcVlanIgmpSnoopTable.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopTable.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopTable
rcVlanIgmpSnoopTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IP multicast groups for which there are members on a particular interface on a particular VLAN (i.e., a list known multicast receivers). A row is created by the system when it receives an IGMP Join messages on a port.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopVlanId.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopVlanId
rcVlanIgmpSnoopVlanId.description: The VLAN for which this entry contains information.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopIpAddress.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopIpAddress
rcVlanIgmpSnoopIpAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains information.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopIfIndex.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopIfIndex
rcVlanIgmpSnoopIfIndex.description: The interface for which this entry contains information for this IP multicast group address (i.e., the port the Join message was received).

rcVlanIgmpSnoopMember.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopMember
rcVlanIgmpSnoopMember.description: The IP Address of the source of the membership report received for this IP Multicast group address on this interface (i.e., the address of the host sending the Join message).

rcVlanIgmpSnoopExpiration.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopExpiration
rcVlanIgmpSnoopExpiration.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopType.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopType
rcVlanIgmpSnoopType.description: The type of entry: dynamic(1) entries are created by snooping IGMP messages, static(2) entries are created via management.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticTable.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticTable
rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the statically- defined IP multicast groups for which there are members on a particular interface on a particular VLAN.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticVlanId.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticVlanId
rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticVlanId.description: The VLAN for which this entry contains information.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticIpAddress.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticIpAddress
rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticIpAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains information. The address must fall within 224.0.1.0 to 239.255.255.255.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticMemberPorts.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticMemberPorts
rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticMemberPorts.description: The set of ports in this VLAN multicast traffic for the rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticIpAddress is to be forwarded to.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticRowStatus.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticRowStatus
rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the rcVlanIgmpSnoopStaticTable.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessTable.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessTable
rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessTable.description: Table used to specify which host(s) can send and/or receive IP Multicast traffic.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessVlanId.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessVlanId
rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessVlanId.description: The VLAN for which this entry contains information.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessGrpAddr.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessGrpAddr
rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessGrpAddr.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains information.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessHostAddr.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessHostAddr
rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessHostAddr.description: The IP address of a host for which this entry contains information.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessHostMask.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessHostMask
rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessHostMask.description: The IP netmask of a host for which this entry contains information.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessMode.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessMode
rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessMode.description: Used to specify whether the host identified by rcVlanIgmpSnoopAccessHostAddr should be denied IP multicast transmit, receive, or both.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderTable.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderTable
rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IP multicast groups for which there are members on a particular interface on a particular VLAN (i.e., a list known multicast senders). A row is created by the system when it receives an IGMP Join messages on a port.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderVlanId.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderVlanId
rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderVlanId.description: The VLAN for which this entry contains information.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderIpAddress.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderIpAddress
rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderIpAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains information.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderIfIndex.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderIfIndex
rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderIfIndex.description: The interface for which this entry contains information for this IP multicast group address (i.e., the port the multicast traffic was received).

rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderMember.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderMember
rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderMember.description: The IP Address of the host sending the multicast traffic.

rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderAction.name: rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderAction
rcVlanIgmpSnoopSenderAction.description: Used to specify an action to perform on this group.

rcVlanLoopDetectedTable.name: rcVlanLoopDetectedTable
rcVlanLoopDetectedTable.description: A list of Vlans the port belongs to and the corresponding loop detected status.

rcVlanLoopDetectedVlanId.name: rcVlanLoopDetectedVlanId
rcVlanLoopDetectedVlanId.description: Gives the VlanId to which the port belongs.

rcVlanLoopDetectedValue.name: rcVlanLoopDetectedValue
rcVlanLoopDetectedValue.description: Gives the Loop Detected status of the port in a vlan.

rcVlanDsapSsapTable.name: rcVlanDsapSsapTable
rcVlanDsapSsapTable.description: A table used to maintain DSAP/SSAP values assigned to a sna802dot2 or userdefined vlan.

rcVlanDsapSsapEntry.name: rcVlanDsapSsapEntry
rcVlanDsapSsapEntry.description: An entry in the rcVlanDsapSsap table.

rcVlanDsapSsapVlanId.name: rcVlanDsapSsapVlanId
rcVlanDsapSsapVlanId.description: A unique index to identify a vlan.

rcVlanDsapSsapPid.name: rcVlanDsapSsapPid
rcVlanDsapSsapPid.description: Values of DSAP/SSAP assigned to a particular vlan.

rcVlanNewLoopDetectedTable.name: rcVlanNewLoopDetectedTable
rcVlanNewLoopDetectedTable.description: A list of Vlans the port belongs to and the corresponding loop detected status.

rcVlanNewLoopDetectedVlanId.name: rcVlanNewLoopDetectedVlanId
rcVlanNewLoopDetectedVlanId.description: Gives the VlanId to which the port belongs.

rcVlanNewLoopDetectedAction.name: rcVlanNewLoopDetectedAction
rcVlanNewLoopDetectedAction.description: This value is used to specify the action which needs to be taken once a loop is detected on a specific port.

rcVlanNewLoopDetectedSmltRemote.name: rcVlanNewLoopDetectedSmltRemote
rcVlanNewLoopDetectedSmltRemote.description: A MAC address indicate for remote learnt, either local or remote.

rcVlanClearMacRecordTable.name: rcVlanClearMacRecordTable
rcVlanClearMacRecordTable.description: Table used to clear a Vlan MAC Record.

rcVlanClearMacRecordEntry.name: rcVlanClearMacRecordEntry
rcVlanClearMacRecordEntry.description: Vlan Clear Mac Record Table Entry

rcVlanClearMacRecordAddr.name: rcVlanClearMacRecordAddr
rcVlanClearMacRecordAddr.description: Mac Address that needs to be cleared.

rcVlanClearMacRecordVlanId.name: rcVlanClearMacRecordVlanId
rcVlanClearMacRecordVlanId.description: Vlan Id where the Mac record has to be cleared.

rcVlanClearMacRecordAllVlanIds.name: rcVlanClearMacRecordAllVlanIds
rcVlanClearMacRecordAllVlanIds.description: When set to true, this will clear the MAC record on all the Vlan Ids it exists.

rcVlanClearMacRecordForceDelete.name: rcVlanClearMacRecordForceDelete
rcVlanClearMacRecordForceDelete.description: By default, when ForceDelete is set to false, MAC record will not be cleared if an ARP record is associated with this Mac Address. If ForceDelete is set to True, MAC record will be removed even when an ARP is associated with this record.

rcVlanClearMacRecordLCForceDelete.name: rcVlanClearMacRecordLCForceDelete
rcVlanClearMacRecordLCForceDelete.description: By default, when LCForceDelete (Line Card Force Delete) is set to false, if the MAC record is not found on the CP, then no message will be sent to the line-card. When LCForceDelete is set to true, a message will be sent to the line-card even when the MAC record is not found on the CP.

rcChasSerialNumber.name: rcChasSerialNumber
rcChasSerialNumber.description: Unique serial number for this chassis.

rcChasNumSlots.name: rcChasNumSlots
rcChasNumSlots.description: The number of slots in the chassis available for plug-in cards.

rcChasNumPorts.name: rcChasNumPorts
rcChasNumPorts.description: The total number of ports currently installed in the chassis.

rcChasFanTable.name: rcChasFanTable
rcChasFanTable.description: This table contains information about Fans

rcChasFanEntry.name: rcChasFanEntry
rcChasFanEntry.description: Contains information regarding a Fan Unit

rcChasFanOperStatus.name: rcChasFanOperStatus
rcChasFanOperStatus.description: Actual status of the Fan: - unknown(1) - status can not be determined. - up(2) - present and supplying power. - down(3) - present, but failure indicated.

rcChasFanAmbientTemperature.name: rcChasFanAmbientTemperature
rcChasFanAmbientTemperature.description: Used to indicate the temperature of the air entering the fan.

rcChasFanType.name: rcChasFanType
rcChasFanType.description: Type of the Fan: - unknown(1) - type can not be determined. - regularSpeed(2) - regular speed fan is present. - highSpeed(3) - high speed fan is present.

rcChasPowerSupplyTable.name: rcChasPowerSupplyTable
rcChasPowerSupplyTable.description: This table contains information about power supplies.

rcChasPowerSupplyEntry.name: rcChasPowerSupplyEntry
rcChasPowerSupplyEntry.description: Contains information regarding a power supply unit.

rcChasPowerSupplyOperStatus.name: rcChasPowerSupplyOperStatus
rcChasPowerSupplyOperStatus.description: Actual status of the power supply: - unknown(1) - status can not be determined. - empty(2) - power supply not installed. - up(3) - present and supplying power. - down(4) - present, but failure indicated.

rcChasPowerSupplyDetailTable.name: rcChasPowerSupplyDetailTable
rcChasPowerSupplyDetailTable.description: This table contains detailed information about power supplies.

rcChasPowerSupplyDetailEntry.name: rcChasPowerSupplyDetailEntry
rcChasPowerSupplyDetailEntry.description: Contains detailed info regarding a power supply unit.

rcChasPowerSupplyDetailHardwareRevision.name: rcChasPowerSupplyDetailHardwareRevision
rcChasPowerSupplyDetailHardwareRevision.description: The hardware revision of the power supply.

rcChasPowerSupplyDetailDescription.name: rcChasPowerSupplyDetailDescription
rcChasPowerSupplyDetailDescription.description: The detail description of power supply.

rcChasPowerSupplyDetailInputLineVoltage.name: rcChasPowerSupplyDetailInputLineVoltage
rcChasPowerSupplyDetailInputLineVoltage.description: The power supply Input Line voltage.

rcChasPowerSupplyDetailOperLineVoltage.name: rcChasPowerSupplyDetailOperLineVoltage
rcChasPowerSupplyDetailOperLineVoltage.description: The power supply Line voltage considered for Power Management calculation.

rcCardTable.name: rcCardTable
rcCardTable.description: A table that contains information about the cards in this chassis. For those slots that do not contain a physical card, the table may be implemented to contain a conceptual row with the type of physical module set to 'chasCardEmpty', or it may be implemented to have no conceptual row instance.

rcCardIndex.name: rcCardIndex
rcCardIndex.description: A unique value for each module within the chassis. This value is determined by the chassis slot number where the module is inserted. Valid entries are 1 to the value of rcChasNumSlots

rcCardType.name: rcCardType
rcCardType.description: Used to indicate a card types in the Accelar 1000 product families. For Accelar 1000 devices, gigabit cards use an encoded value according to the following rule: +-----+--+-+---+---+---+ bits : |31-11|10|9|8-7|6-4|3-0| +-----+--+-+---+---+---+ field : | a | b|c| d | e | f | +-----+--+-+---+---+---+ a : not-used b : 1=gigabit c : 0=non-redundant, 1=redundant d : 0=short-haul, 1=long-haul, 2=extra-distance, e : 0=work-group(a1100 & a1150) 1=back-bone(a1200 & f1250 & f2000), f : 1=1-port, 2=2-port, 4=4-port, 8=8-port

rcCardSerialNumber.name: rcCardSerialNumber
rcCardSerialNumber.description: Unique serial number for this card.

rcCardAdminStatus.name: rcCardAdminStatus
rcCardAdminStatus.description: Used to indicate the administrative status of this card

rcCardOperStatus.name: rcCardOperStatus
rcCardOperStatus.description: Used to indicate the operational status of this card.

rcCardPCMCIAType.name: rcCardPCMCIAType
rcCardPCMCIAType.description: Used to indicate the type of PCMCIA card currently installed in this CPU card, if any. For non-CPU cards, this variable has no meaning and will always be set to none.

rcPortEntry.name: rcPortEntry
rcPortEntry.description: Entry containing info. for a particular port

rcPortIndex.name: rcPortIndex
rcPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port. This value is similar to ifIndex in MIB2.

rcPortConnectorType.name: rcPortConnectorType
rcPortConnectorType.description: Type of connector installed on this port.

rcPortPerformRouting.name: rcPortPerformRouting
rcPortPerformRouting.description: Indicate whether this port should perform routing

rcPortHighPriority.name: rcPortHighPriority
rcPortHighPriority.description: Indicate whether this port should be treated with high priority

rcPortResult.name: rcPortResult
rcPortResult.description: Result from the last Vlan action.

rcPortPrimaryConnector.name: rcPortPrimaryConnector
rcPortPrimaryConnector.description: For ports configured with redundant connectors, this value is used to indicate which connector should be used as the 'active' connector on this port the next time the port is placed into the ifAdminStatus=Up.

rcPortActiveConnector.name: rcPortActiveConnector
rcPortActiveConnector.description: For ports configured with redundant connectors, this value is used to indicate which connector is currently the active one. Only one connector can be active an anytime.

rcPortBackupConnectorStatus.name: rcPortBackupConnectorStatus
rcPortBackupConnectorStatus.description: Indicate the status of the link attached to the back-up (non-active) connector.

rcPortAutoNegotiate.name: rcPortAutoNegotiate
rcPortAutoNegotiate.description: Indicate whether this port enabled for auto negotiations or not.

rcPortOperDuplex.name: rcPortOperDuplex
rcPortOperDuplex.description: Indicate this port's current duplex value.

rcPortOperSpeed.name: rcPortOperSpeed
rcPortOperSpeed.description: Indicate this port's current speed value.

rcPortMltId.name: rcPortMltId
rcPortMltId.description: Indicate which multi-link trunk (MLT) this port is assigned to. If this port is not associated with any MLT, this value will be set to zero(0).

rcPortLocked.name: rcPortLocked
rcPortLocked.description: Indicate whether this port is locked.

rcPortAutoNegotiationSupported.name: rcPortAutoNegotiationSupported
rcPortAutoNegotiationSupported.description: Indicate whether this port can support auto-negotiation.

rcPortSingleRoutablePort.name: rcPortSingleRoutablePort
rcPortSingleRoutablePort.description: Indicate whether this port is a single routable port. If this value is true, the port functions like a traditional router port.

rcPortUnknownMacDiscard.name: rcPortUnknownMacDiscard
rcPortUnknownMacDiscard.description: If rcUnknownMacDiscard is set to True, then a packet with an unknown source MAC address is dropped on that port, and other ports then will discard any packets with this MAC address in the destination field. For example, suppose 11:22:33:44:55:66 is an unknown source MAC, packets with source MAC 11:22:33:44:55 coming from this port is discarded, further more, packets with destination MAC 11:22:33:44:55:66 coming from other ports are also discarded, unless this address is later learned on another port or the restriction ages out.

rcPortAllowOversizeFrame.name: rcPortAllowOversizeFrame
rcPortAllowOversizeFrame.description: Used to specify whether over-size frames should be processed or dropped.

rcPortQosLevel.name: rcPortQosLevel
rcPortQosLevel.description: Used to specify the Qos level packets, carried on this port, should be processed with.

rcPortDiffServEnable.name: rcPortDiffServEnable
rcPortDiffServEnable.description: Used to enable/disable the Differentiated Service feature on this port.

rcPortDiffServType.name: rcPortDiffServType
rcPortDiffServType.description: Used to specify the Differentiated Service type for this port.

rcPortDiffServIeee8021POverrideEnable.name: rcPortDiffServIeee8021POverrideEnable
rcPortDiffServIeee8021POverrideEnable.description: Used to enable/disable the Differentiated Service IEEE 802.1P over-ride feature.

rcPortVendorDescr.name: rcPortVendorDescr
rcPortVendorDescr.description: Used to show the name of the vendor of this port's connector. Only applicable to ports on a GBIC cards.

rcPortOctapidId.name: rcPortOctapidId
rcPortOctapidId.description: The octapid id of the mirrored port.

rcPortWan.name: rcPortWan
rcPortWan.description: Indicatie this port's current WAN/LAN mode. Valid for 10 GE only

rcPortTransport.name: rcPortTransport
rcPortTransport.description: Indicatie this port's current tranport layer. Valid for 10 GE only

rcPortMultimediaFilterEnable.name: rcPortMultimediaFilterEnable
rcPortMultimediaFilterEnable.description: Used to enable/disable the Telephony device selected on this port

rcPortMultimediaDevSelection.name: rcPortMultimediaDevSelection
rcPortMultimediaDevSelection.description: Used to set/get the selected Multimedia & Telephony Devices on this port. The String is the name of the device in the rcIpFilterMediaDevTable

rcPortAdminRouting.name: rcPortAdminRouting
rcPortAdminRouting.description: Indicate whether the port is routable.

rcPortOperRouting.name: rcPortOperRouting
rcPortOperRouting.description: The status of the port whether is routable.

rcPortPid.name: rcPortPid
rcPortPid.description: The pid of the mirrored port.

rcPortIeee8021POverrideEnable.name: rcPortIeee8021POverrideEnable
rcPortIeee8021POverrideEnable.description: Used to enable/disable IEEE 802.1P override. If it is enabled, 802.1p value from a tagged frame may not be honored.

rcPortCpLimitShutDown.name: rcPortCpLimitShutDown
rcPortCpLimitShutDown.description: A TRUE value indicates if CP Limit shut down the interface.

rcPortMrouteStrLimit.name: rcPortMrouteStrLimit
rcPortMrouteStrLimit.description: maximum number of multicast streams that are allowed to ingress to CPU through this port.

rcPortMrouteStrTimerCheck.name: rcPortMrouteStrTimerCheck
rcPortMrouteStrTimerCheck.description: sampling period to check number of multicast streams that has ingressed CPU through this port in seconds.

rcPortMrouteStrLimitEnable.name: rcPortMrouteStrLimitEnable
rcPortMrouteStrLimitEnable.description: enable or disable mroute stream limit on port.

rcPortAutoNegAd.name: rcPortAutoNegAd
rcPortAutoNegAd.description: This object is used to specify the port speed and duplex abilities to be advertised during link negotiation. bit 0 - 10 half duplex advertised bit 1 - 10 full duplex advertised bit 2 - 100 half duplex advertised bit 3 - 100 full duplex advertised bit 4 - 1000 half duplex advertised bit 5 - 1000 full duplex advertised bit 6 - Mac PAUSE frame support advertised bit 7 - Asymmetric PAUSE frame support advertised bit 8 - No advertisements The abilities specified in this object are only used when auto-negotiation is enabled on the port. If all bits in this object are disabled, and auto-negotiation is enabled on the port, then the physical link process on the port will be disabled (if hardware supports this ability). Any change in the value of this bit map will force the PHY to restart the auto-negotiation process. This will have the same effect as physically unplugging and reattaching the cable plant attached to this port. The capabilities being advertised are either all the capabilities supported by the hardware or the user- configured capabilities which is a subset of all the capability supported by hardware. The default value for this object will be all the capabilities supported by the hardware. Note that bit 6 and bit 7 are currently not supported in ERS8600/ERS8800.

rcPortAutoRecoverPort.name: rcPortAutoRecoverPort
rcPortAutoRecoverPort.description: enable or disable auto recovery of port from action taken by cp-limit, link flap or loop detect features

rcPortExtCplimitConf.name: rcPortExtCplimitConf
rcPortExtCplimitConf.description: Indicates the port configuration for extended CP-LIMIT

rcPortExtCplimitUtilRate.name: rcPortExtCplimitUtilRate
rcPortExtCplimitUtilRate.description: Threshold for Ingress traffic utilization rate of the port for extended CP-LIMIT

rcPortBpduFilteringTimerCount.name: rcPortBpduFilteringTimerCount
rcPortBpduFilteringTimerCount.description: The remaining time the port will be disabled due to a BPDU received when BPDU filtering is enabled.

rcPortBpduFilteringTimeout.name: rcPortBpduFilteringTimeout
rcPortBpduFilteringTimeout.description: The time the port will be disabled when a BPDU is received when BPDU filtering is enabled.

rcPortBpduFilteringOperEnabled.name: rcPortBpduFilteringOperEnabled
rcPortBpduFilteringOperEnabled.description: Indicates whether BPDU filtering is actually enabled or disabled.

rcPortCpLimitEnable.name: rcPortCpLimitEnable
rcPortCpLimitEnable.description: Used to enable/disable the control packet rate limit. Specifies whether or not rate limiting is currently in operation for multicast and broadcast packets for the specified port.

rcPortIngressRateLimit.name: rcPortIngressRateLimit

rcPortVrfNameList.name: rcPortVrfNameList

rcPortBrouterVrfId.name: rcPortBrouterVrfId

rcPortLockEnable.name: rcPortLockEnable

rcPortLockLockedPorts.name: rcPortLockLockedPorts

rcPortLacpAdminEnable.description: Administratively enable/disable LACP on a port

rcPortLacpOperEnable.name: rcPortLacpOperEnable
rcPortLacpOperEnable.description: Indicates if LACP is operationally enabled or disabled on a port

rcPortLacpFastPeriodicTime.name: rcPortLacpFastPeriodicTime
rcPortLacpFastPeriodicTime.description: The number of miliseconds between periodic transmissions using Short Timeouts.

rcPortLacpSlowPeriodicTime.name: rcPortLacpSlowPeriodicTime
rcPortLacpSlowPeriodicTime.description: The number of miliseconds between periodic transmissions using LONG Timeouts.

rcPortLacpAggrWaitTime.name: rcPortLacpAggrWaitTime
rcPortLacpAggrWaitTime.description: The number of mili seconds to delay aggregation to allow multiple links to aggregate simultaneously.

rcPortLacpFastPeriodicTimeOper.name: rcPortLacpFastPeriodicTimeOper
rcPortLacpFastPeriodicTimeOper.description: The operating value of fast periodic timer on the port.

rcPortLacpSlowPeriodicTimeOper.name: rcPortLacpSlowPeriodicTimeOper
rcPortLacpSlowPeriodicTimeOper.description: The operating value of slow periodic timer on the port.

rcPortLacpTimeoutScaleOper.name: rcPortLacpTimeoutScaleOper
rcPortLacpTimeoutScaleOper.description: The operating value of timeout scale on the port.

rcPortLacpAggrWaitTimeOper.name: rcPortLacpAggrWaitTimeOper
rcPortLacpAggrWaitTimeOper.description: The operating value of aggreagate wait time on port.

rcPortVLacpEntry.name: rcPortVLacpEntry
rcPortVLacpEntry.description: Entry containing info. for a particular port

rcPortVLacpAdminEnable.name: rcPortVLacpAdminEnable
rcPortVLacpAdminEnable.description: Administratively enable/disable Virtual LACP on a port

rcPortVLacpOperEnable.name: rcPortVLacpOperEnable
rcPortVLacpOperEnable.description: Indicates if Virtual LACP is operationally enabled or disabled on a port

rcPortVLacpFastPeriodicTimer.name: rcPortVLacpFastPeriodicTimer
rcPortVLacpFastPeriodicTimer.description: The number of miliseconds between periodic transmissions using Short Timeouts

rcPortVLacpSlowPeriodicTimer.name: rcPortVLacpSlowPeriodicTimer
rcPortVLacpSlowPeriodicTimer.description: The number of miliseconds between periodic transmissions using LONG Timeouts.

rcPortVLacpTimeout.name: rcPortVLacpTimeout
rcPortVLacpTimeout.description: Timeout control value. Long or Short Timeout

rcPortVLacpTimeoutScale.name: rcPortVLacpTimeoutScale
rcPortVLacpTimeoutScale.description: Scalar value used to calculate timeout time from periodic time. Timeout = PeriodicTime * TimeoutScale

rcPortVLacpEtherType.name: rcPortVLacpEtherType
rcPortVLacpEtherType.description: VLACP Protocol Identification. The id value is in Hex. The acceptable values for this MIB is 0x0 to 0xffff

rcPortVLacpEtherMacAddress.name: rcPortVLacpEtherMacAddress
rcPortVLacpEtherMacAddress.description: Multicast Mac Address exclusively used for VLACPDU's

rcPortVLacpFlapDetectEnable.name: rcPortVLacpFlapDetectEnable
rcPortVLacpFlapDetectEnable.description: Administratively enable/disable VLACP flap detection on a port

rcPortVLacpFlapFrequency.description: The number of VLACP Flaps on a port, that if they occure within rcPortVLacpFlapInterval seconds, the port is shutdown.

rcPortVLacpFlapInterval.name: rcPortVLacpFlapInterval
rcPortVLacpFlapInterval.description: The time inteval in seconds within which VLACP flaps on a port are monitored.

rcPortVLacpTotalFlapCount.name: rcPortVLacpTotalFlapCount
rcPortVLacpTotalFlapCount.description: Total Number of VLACP flaps detected on this port since either enabling VLACP or clearing the counter.

rcPortVLacpFirstFlapTimeStamp.name: rcPortVLacpFirstFlapTimeStamp
rcPortVLacpFirstFlapTimeStamp.description: Timestamp for the first VLACP flap detected on this port since either enabling VLACP or clearing the timer.

rcPortVLacpLastFlapTimeStamp.name: rcPortVLacpLastFlapTimeStamp
rcPortVLacpLastFlapTimeStamp.description: Timestamp for the latest VLACP flap detected on this port since either enabling VLACP or clearing the timer.

rcPortVLacpFlapClearStats.name: rcPortVLacpFlapClearStats
rcPortVLacpFlapClearStats.description: Clears all VLACP flap counters and timers.

rcPortRemoteMirroringIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port. This value is similar to ifIndex in MIB2.

rcPortRemoteMirroringEnable.description: To enable remote Mirroring for the port

rcPortRemoteMirroringDstMac.name: rcPortRemoteMirroringDstMac
rcPortRemoteMirroringDstMac.description: Destination Mac of the remote mirrored packet. Packets will be bridged to this mac address. Remote mirroring packet will be send to this mac address

rcPortRemoteMirroringEtherType.name: rcPortRemoteMirroringEtherType
rcPortRemoteMirroringEtherType.description: Ethertype of the remote mirrored packet. Packets will be send with this ethertype

rcPortRemoteMirroringVlanIdListSize.name: rcPortRemoteMirroringVlanIdListSize
rcPortRemoteMirroringVlanIdListSize.description: Used to indicate the number of VLAN IDs that are assigned to this port.

rcPortRemoteMirroringVlanIdList.name: rcPortRemoteMirroringVlanIdList
rcPortRemoteMirroringVlanIdList.description: This field is used only if the port is assigned as remote mirroring termination port. Represents zero or more filter lists vlan in which the Destination Mac address resides. Each VLAN ID is stored as two bytes in this array starting from offset zero. Any unused bytes should be set to zero.

rcPortMgmtLinkTable.name: rcPortMgmtLinkTable
rcPortMgmtLinkTable.description: Port card mgmt port link table

rcPortMgmtLinkEntry.description: Entry containing info. for a particular mgmt port in I/O card

rcPortFlushMacVlanId.description: Vlan Id associated with the Mac Address.

rcChasAruMode.description: The ARU mode the chassis is operating in.

rcChasQuidMode.name: rcChasQuidMode
rcChasQuidMode.description: The Quid mode the chassis is operating in.

rcChasEocModeAdminStatus.name: rcChasEocModeAdminStatus
rcChasEocModeAdminStatus.description: Used to specify the Enforce Operational Configuration Mode(EOC) of the system. When a device is configured with hardware of different revisions, the system will initialize in some deterministic manner (e.g., the lowest common denominator that makes sense based on the hardware configuration). This is the 'default(0)' mode. The user can override this behavior by manually specifying the EOC Mode they would like.

rcChasEocModeOperStatus.name: rcChasEocModeOperStatus
rcChasEocModeOperStatus.description: Used to indicate the Enforce Operational Configuration Mode(EOC) of the system.

rcChasBrouterPorts.name: rcChasBrouterPorts
rcChasBrouterPorts.description: Used to indicate which ports in the system are configured as Brouter ports.

rcChasGlobalFilterEnable.name: rcChasGlobalFilterEnable
rcChasGlobalFilterEnable.description: Used to enable/disable global filters in the system. This variable is currently not supported.

rcChasVlanBySrcMacEnable.name: rcChasVlanBySrcMacEnable
rcChasVlanBySrcMacEnable.description: Used to enable/disable source MAC based VLANs in the system.

rcChasDiffServEcnCompatibilityEnable.name: rcChasDiffServEcnCompatibilityEnable
rcChasDiffServEcnCompatibilityEnable.description: Used to enable/disable the Explicit Congestion Notification(ECN) compatibility feature. When set to FALSE , the system will mask the ECN bits in the DS field while re-marking DSCP and will not match on ECN capable flows if filter is set on DSmatch. When set to TRUE, it will preserve the ECN bits in the DS field while re-marking and will match on full 8-bit DS field.

rcChasNewEMMode.name: rcChasNewEMMode
rcChasNewEMMode.description: This configuration is for enabling/disabling 128K mode. The change will take effect upon reboot.

rcChasEmModeError.name: rcChasEmModeError
rcChasEmModeError.description: Used to indicate the Em-mode error status

rcChasEnhancedOperMode.description: Enhanced Operational mode the switch currently has booted and will remain the same until the next reboot.

rcChasEMMode.name: rcChasEMMode
rcChasEMMode.description: EM mode the switch currently has booted and will remain the same until the next reboot.

rcChasSmltOnSingleCpEnable.description: Enable SMLT on single CP feature in the switch

rcChasVlanOptmMode.name: rcChasVlanOptmMode

rcLaunchPadClusterMgmtVlan.description: Launch pad cluster management vlan Id.

rcLaunchPadClusterSyncVlan.description: Launch pad cluster cp sync vlan Id.

rcLaunchPadClusterPortMember.description: IS cluster user port list that needs to be monitored

rcChasGlobalFilterOrderingEnable.description: Global Filter ordering in the system.

rcChasNewGlobalFilterOrderingEnable.description: This configuration is for enabling/disabling global filter ordering. The change will take effect upon reboot.

rcChasWsmDirectMode.description: This is for enabling/disabling configuration of same community strings on the WSM and 8600/8800. This is for allowing users to connect directly via SNMP to the WSM blade.

rcChasRspMode.description: This configuration is for enabling/disabling 256K mode. The change will take effect upon reboot.

rcChasRspOperMode.description: R-mode the switch currently has booted and will remain the same until the next reboot.

rcChasRspModeError.name: rcChasRspModeError
rcChasRspModeError.description: Used to indicate the r-mode error status

rcChasMcastCheckPktEnable.description: Used to enable/disable Multicast check packet in the system. This change will take effect upon reboot.

rcChasSystemMonitorEnable.description: Enable/Disable System monitoring in the switch

rcChasSysMonMonitoringEnable.description: Dyanamically Enable/Disable SystemMonitor monitoring engine in the switch

rcChasSysMonDetectionTime.name: rcChasSysMonDetectionTime
rcChasSysMonDetectionTime.description: System Monitor Detection time in seconds

rcChasNewMulticastResourceReservation.name: rcChasNewMulticastResourceReservation
rcChasNewMulticastResourceReservation.description: Used to reserve MGIDs for IP Multicast. The change will take effect upon reboot.

rcChasMulticastResourceReservation.name: rcChasMulticastResourceReservation
rcChasMulticastResourceReservation.description: MGIDs the switch currently has reserved for IP Multicast; will remain the same until the next reboot.

rcChasNewMaxVlanResourceReservation.name: rcChasNewMaxVlanResourceReservation
rcChasNewMaxVlanResourceReservation.description: A mode where all MGIDs are reserved for VLAN use only; no IPMC. The change will take effect upon reboot.

rcChasMaxVlanResourceReservation.name: rcChasMaxVlanResourceReservation
rcChasMaxVlanResourceReservation.description: Tells if all MGIDs are reserved for VLAN use. Will remain the same until the next reboot.

rcChasMgidUsageVlanCurrent.name: rcChasMgidUsageVlanCurrent
rcChasMgidUsageVlanCurrent.description: Number of MGIDs currently used for VLAN, including SMLT

rcChasMgidUsageVlanRemaining.name: rcChasMgidUsageVlanRemaining
rcChasMgidUsageVlanRemaining.description: Number of MGIDs remaining allocated for VLAN

rcChasMgidUsageMulticastCurrent.description: Number of MGIDs currently used for IPMC

rcChasMgidUsageMulticastRemaining.name: rcChasMgidUsageMulticastRemaining
rcChasMgidUsageMulticastRemaining.description: Number of MGIDs remaining allocated for IPMC

rcChasPowerManagementEnable.description: Turn on or off Chassis Power Management. The configuration will take effect upon reboot.

rcChasForceTopologyIpFlagEnable.name: rcChasForceTopologyIpFlagEnable
rcChasForceTopologyIpFlagEnable.description: Used to enable/disable flag which is used to set the CLIP-ip as topology ip

rcChasCircuitlessIpId.name: rcChasCircuitlessIpId
rcChasCircuitlessIpId.description: The Clip-Id set by the user to be used as Topology-ip

rcChasPowerManagementOriginalEnable.name: rcChasPowerManagementOriginalEnable
rcChasPowerManagementOriginalEnable.description: On or off value of Chassis Power Management which the switch has currently booted. It will remain the same until the next reboot.

rcChasPowerManagementFanCheck.name: rcChasPowerManagementFanCheck
rcChasPowerManagementFanCheck.description: Turn on or off the Fan Check functionility of Chassis Power Management. The value takes effect only on reboot.

rcChasTakeIOCardOfflineEnable.name: rcChasTakeIOCardOfflineEnable
rcChasTakeIOCardOfflineEnable.description: Enable/Disable IO Card to go offline when F2E sees excessive resets.

rcChasAutoResetFabricEnable.name: rcChasAutoResetFabricEnable
rcChasAutoResetFabricEnable.description: Enable/Disable fabric to be reset automatically on fab mem full error.

rcAgentEntry.name: rcAgentEntry
rcAgentEntry.description: Entry containing info. for a particular agent

rcMirrorSaveConfig.name: rcMirrorSaveConfig
rcMirrorSaveConfig.description: Control whether Mirror configuration information should be saved to NVRAM so mirror settings can be automatically reinstalled after a system reboot. Setting rcMirrorSaveConfig to true does not immediately save the configuration information. The save happens when the rcSysAction variable is set to 'saveToNVRAM(4)'.

rcMirrorByPortEnable.name: rcMirrorByPortEnable
rcMirrorByPortEnable.description: Used to indicate whether the mirror by port feature is active. The system can only support mirroring on two ports. When this feature is active, all packets received on the port(s) specified by rcMirrorSrcPortOne and/or rcMirrorSrcPortTwo are copied to rcMirrorDstPort. The mirroring operation is non-intrusive.

rcMirrorByPortMirrorPort.name: rcMirrorByPortMirrorPort
rcMirrorByPortMirrorPort.description: The ifIndex of the port to forward mirrored frames to.

rcMirrorByPortEnableMirroredPortOne.name: rcMirrorByPortEnableMirroredPortOne
rcMirrorByPortEnableMirroredPortOne.description: Used to indicate whether the port specified in rcMirrorByPortMirroredPortOne should be mirrored.

rcMirrorByPortMirroredPortOne.name: rcMirrorByPortMirroredPortOne
rcMirrorByPortMirroredPortOne.description: The ifIndex of the port to be mirrored. That is, traffic received on this port will be sent to the mirror port.

rcMirrorByPortEnableMirroredPortTwo.name: rcMirrorByPortEnableMirroredPortTwo
rcMirrorByPortEnableMirroredPortTwo.description: Used to indicate whether the port specified in rcMirrorByPortMirroredPortTwo should be mirrored.

rcMirrorByPortMirroredPortTwo.name: rcMirrorByPortMirroredPortTwo
rcMirrorByPortMirroredPortTwo.description: The ifIndex of the port to be mirrored. That is, traffic received on this port will be sent to the mirror port.

rcIsolateUnconfigPorts.name: rcIsolateUnconfigPorts
rcIsolateUnconfigPorts.description: Used to indicate whether ports that are unconfigured should be assigned to the 'isolated' VLAN. Ports assigned to the 'isolated' VLAN can only communicate with the CP port. If this option is not specified, unconfigured ports will be assigned to the 'default' VLAN

rcUseFactorySettings.name: rcUseFactorySettings
rcUseFactorySettings.description: Used to indicate whether the system should ignore the configuration information stored in NVRAM when the system is booted.

rcHighPriorityMode.name: rcHighPriorityMode
rcHighPriorityMode.description: Used to indicate whether the system is configured to operate in a high priority mode. The switch can operate in either a 'best effort' or 'high priority' mode. In the 'best effort' setting, the maximum queue thresholds for the QUIDs are set to 768/768 buffers. In the 'high priority' mode the setting is 512/768. This means that in 'high priority' mode the normal priority queue can't have more than 512 buffers, while the high priority queue can have up to 768.

rcTblRmonStatSize.name: rcTblRmonStatSize
rcTblRmonStatSize.description: Used to indicate the current size of the RMON Statistic table.

rcTblArVlanByPortDeleted.description: Used to indicate the number of VLAN by port entries that are deleted from the Address Translation (AR) table.

rcTblArVlanByProtocolAdded.description: Used to indicate the number of Vlans by Protocol Type entries that are added to the Address Translation (AR) table.

rcTblArVlanByProtocolDeleted.name: rcTblArVlanByProtocolDeleted
rcTblArVlanByProtocolDeleted.description: Used to indicate the number of Vlans by Protocol Type entries that are deleted from the Address Translation (AR) table.

rcTblArVlanByIpSubnetAdded.name: rcTblArVlanByIpSubnetAdded
rcTblArVlanByIpSubnetAdded.description: Used to indicate the number of VLAN by Ip entries that are added to the Address Translation (AR) table.

rcTblArVlanByIpSubnetDeleted.description: Used to indicate the number of VLAN by Ip entries that are deleted from the Address Translation (AR) table.

rcTblArIpSubnetsAdded.description: Used to indicate the number of Ip subnet entries that are added to the Address Translation (AR) table.
