rcIpPolicyOspfAnnouncePrecedence.name: rcIpPolicyOspfAnnouncePrecedence
rcIpPolicyOspfAnnouncePrecedence.description: Is used while comparing this policy rule with other policy that a given route may match. A rule with a higher precedence value will be chosen over one with a smaller value. In the case of a tie, the PolicyId is used (larger wins).

rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceRouteSource.name: rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceRouteSource
rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceRouteSource.description: Is represented as bit map to indicate route sources. It can contain one or more route sources. If the route source is in this bit map, then a route from that source that meets the other criteria of this policy will match the policy.

rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceAdvertiseNetListId.name: rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceAdvertiseNetListId
rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceAdvertiseNetListId.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the AdvertiseNetList that are configured for this policy. This has meaning only if the Action is set to 'announce'. It is useful to send or advertise networks that differ from actual network in the routing table. Also allows advertisement of an aggregate or default along with the actual network. Aggregation is useful if a number of routes in the table falls in a certain range. Can save space by sending aggregate route instead of the individual routes. Actual network/route is included in the update only if there is a match or there there is an entry (address & mask pair) 255.255.255.255/255.255.255.255 in the list.

rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceAction.name: rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceAction
rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceAction.description: It indicates whether the route should be announced or not.

rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceExtMetricType.name: rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceExtMetricType
rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceExtMetricType.description: Ospf External metric type. It is used to indicate what type of the external metric it is. 'type1' means to the cost is 'internal ospf cost + ExtMetric'. 'type2' means the ospf-metric is equal to 'type2'.

rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceExtMetric.name: rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceExtMetric
rcIpPolicyOspfAnnounceExtMetric.description: OSPF External metric. The value is meaningful only if the action is set to 'announce'. This is optional export metric to use when advertising a route that matches this policy. Value '0' is used to indicate that route's actual cost is used to announce.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptTableSize.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptTableSize
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the rcIpPolicyRipAcceptTable.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptTable.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptTable
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptTable.description: A table used to store set of accept policies configured for RIP routing protocol. The Number of entries is given by rcIpPolicyNumRipPolicies.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptEntry.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptEntry
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptEntry.description: Entry containing configuration information for a particular accept policy.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptId.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptId
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptId.description: A value that uniquely identifies the policy associated with this entry.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptName.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptName
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this policy.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptEnable.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptEnable
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptEnable.description: It indicates whether this policy is enabled or not. The policy should be applied only if it is set to 'true'.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptExactNetListId.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptExactNetListId
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptExactNetListId.description: Used to indicate the number of 'exact' type entries that are configured for this policy. An entry with type 'exactNet' or 'rangeNet' represents the network list. This indicates which networks will match a particular accept policy. An entry with a 'exact' type means to only match the specific network advertisement (netaddr & mask). An 'exact' entry with addr=0.0.0.0 and mask=0.0.0.0 means 'match the default route'.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptRangeNetListId.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptRangeNetListId
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptRangeNetListId.description: Used to indicate zero or more 'range' network entries that are associated with this policy. An entry with a 'range' type means to match any network number that falls in the range indicated by the addr & mask. A 'range' entry with addr=0.0.0.0 and mask=0.0.0.0 means 'match any route'. A null list means 'match any route'.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptRipGatewayListId.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptRipGatewayListId
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptRipGatewayListId.description: Used to identify the RIP-gatewayList in the PolicyListTable that iares associated with this policy. The list contains the addresses of one or more routers that could send RIP updates to this router. If a router address is included in this list, this policy applies to RIP advertisements from that router. If set to '0', this policy applies to RIP updates from any router.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptRipInterfaceListId.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptRipInterfaceListId
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptRipInterfaceListId.description: Used to indicate ListId defined for RipInterfaceList in the rcIpPolicyListTable that is assiciated with this policy. The list contains the addresses of one or more interfaces on this router. If an interface address is included in the list, this policy applies to RIP advertisements received on that interface. If set to '0', this policy applies to RIP updates received on any interface.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptPrecedence.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptPrecedence
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptPrecedence.description: Is used while comparing this policy rule with other policy that a given route may match. A rule with a higher precedence value will be chosen over one with a smaller value. In the case of a tie, the PolicyId is used (larger wins).

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptAction.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptAction
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptAction.description: It indicates whether the route should be acceptd or not.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptInjectNetListId.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptInjectNetListId
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptInjectNetListId.description: Used to indicate the ListId of the InjectNetList in the rcIpPolicyListTable entry that is assiciated with for this policy. If teh action is 'accept' and if it is desired to insert networks into the routing table that differ from the actual advertised network. For instance, if a number of networks in a certain range are learned and an aggregate advertisement could be inserted instead of the individual networks. Upon receiving a route that matches this policy, all networks in this list will be considered for inclusion in the routing table. If the list is empty or if the value of the ListId is '0' then the actual received network is considered. An encoding of 255.255.255.255/255.255.255.255 means 'match the actual received network.'. This allows insertion of an aggregate or default along with the actual netowrk.

rcIpPolicyRipAcceptApplyMask.name: rcIpPolicyRipAcceptApplyMask
rcIpPolicyRipAcceptApplyMask.description: If the 'action' is set to 'accept' and the actual received network will be considered, this is an optional IP address mask that will be applied to the network number from the RIP update. This is used to override the interface's subnet mask in the presence of networks with variable length subnet masks.

rcIpPolicyOspfAcceptTableSize.name: rcIpPolicyOspfAcceptTableSize
rcIpPolicyOspfAcceptTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the rcIpPolicyOspfAcceptTable.

rcIpPolicyOspfAcceptTable.name: rcIpPolicyOspfAcceptTable
rcIpPolicyOspfAcceptTable.description: A table used to store set of accept policies configured for RIP routing protocol. The Number of entries is given by rcIpPolicyNumRipPolicies.

rcIpPolicyOspfAcceptExtType.name: rcIpPolicyOspfAcceptExtType
rcIpPolicyOspfAcceptExtType.description: Used to indicate the ospf external type. This parameter describes which types of OSPF ASE routes match this policy. 'any' means 'match either ASE type 1 or 2'. 'type1' means 'match any external type 1'. 'type2' means 'match any external type 2

rcIpPolicyNetListTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the rcIpPolicyNetListTable.

rcIpPolicyNetListId.name: rcIpPolicyNetListId
rcIpPolicyNetListId.description: A value that uniquely identifies this list of rcIpPolicyNetListEntry.

rcIpPolicyNetListName.name: rcIpPolicyNetListName
rcIpPolicyNetListName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this list.

rcIpPolicyNetListIdListSize.name: rcIpPolicyNetListIdListSize
rcIpPolicyNetListIdListSize.description: Used to indicate the number of rcIpPolicyNetEntry id(s) in the rcIpPolicyNetListIdList variable.

rcIpPolicyNetListIdList.name: rcIpPolicyNetListIdList
rcIpPolicyNetListIdList.description: Used to indicate zero or more NetListId that are associated to this list. Each NetList identifier is stored as two bytes in this array starting from offset zero. Any unused bytes should be set to zero.

rcIpPolicyNetListPolicyIdListSize.name: rcIpPolicyNetListPolicyIdListSize
rcIpPolicyNetListPolicyIdListSize.description: Used to indicate the number of policy id(s) in the Policy Id list. That are referring to this list.

rcIpPolicyNetListPolicyIdList.name: rcIpPolicyNetListPolicyIdList
rcIpPolicyNetListPolicyIdList.description: Used to indicate zero or more policies that are referring to this entry. Each policy identifier is stored as two bytes in this array starting from offset zero. Any unused bytes should be set to zero.

rcIpDvmrpGlobalEnable.name: rcIpDvmrpGlobalEnable
rcIpDvmrpGlobalEnable.description: The enabled status of IP Multicast Dvmrp routing on this router.

rcIpDvmrpGlobalRouteExpireTimeOut.name: rcIpDvmrpGlobalRouteExpireTimeOut
rcIpDvmrpGlobalRouteExpireTimeOut.description: This parameter defines the route expiration timeout in seconds.

rcIpDvmrpGlobalFwdCacheTimeOut.name: rcIpDvmrpGlobalFwdCacheTimeOut
rcIpDvmrpGlobalFwdCacheTimeOut.description: This is the Forward Cache Value in second. This value is going to be used in aging prune entries in seconds.

rcIpDvmrpGlobalRouteDiscardTimeOut.name: rcIpDvmrpGlobalRouteDiscardTimeOut
rcIpDvmrpGlobalRouteDiscardTimeOut.description: This parameter defines time to garbage collect route in seconds.

rcIpDvmrpGlobalRouteSwitchTimeOut.name: rcIpDvmrpGlobalRouteSwitchTimeOut
rcIpDvmrpGlobalRouteSwitchTimeOut.description: This parameter defines the route discard timeout in seconds.

rcIpDvmrpGlobalGenerateTrap.name: rcIpDvmrpGlobalGenerateTrap
rcIpDvmrpGlobalGenerateTrap.description: Enabling the dvmrp to generate trap.

rcIpDvmrpGlobalGenerateLog.name: rcIpDvmrpGlobalGenerateLog
rcIpDvmrpGlobalGenerateLog.description: Enabling the dvmrp to generate log.

rcIpDvmrpTable.name: rcIpDvmrpTable
rcIpDvmrpTable.description: Dvmrp Interface extension table. This table augments the standard dvmrpInterfaceTable defined in <draft-thaler-dvmrp-mib-09.txt>.

rcIpDvmrpTableEntry.name: rcIpDvmrpTableEntry
rcIpDvmrpTableEntry.description: Entry containing Proprietary DVMRP interface information. An entry is automatically created in this table when an ip address is configured on an interface.

rcIpDvmrpTableIfIndex.name: rcIpDvmrpTableIfIndex
rcIpDvmrpTableIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcIpDvmrpTableEnable.name: rcIpDvmrpTableEnable
rcIpDvmrpTableEnable.description: The administrative status of DVMRP in the router. The value 'enabled' denotes that the DVMRP is enableed on the interface; 'disabled' disables it on the interface.

rcIpDvmrpTableAdvSelf.name: rcIpDvmrpTableAdvSelf
rcIpDvmrpTableAdvSelf.description: Used to indicate whether the switch can advertise this local network

rcIpDvmrpTableLocalAddr.name: rcIpDvmrpTableLocalAddr
rcIpDvmrpTableLocalAddr.description: The IP address of this interface.

rcIpDvmrpTableInPolicyName.name: rcIpDvmrpTableInPolicyName
rcIpDvmrpTableInPolicyName.description: Dvmrp Accept Policy name that is configured on this interface.

rcIpDvmrpTableOutPolicyName.name: rcIpDvmrpTableOutPolicyName
rcIpDvmrpTableOutPolicyName.description: Dvmrp Announce Policy name that is configured on this interface.

rcIpDvmrpTableDefRtLis.name: rcIpDvmrpTableDefRtLis
rcIpDvmrpTableDefRtLis.description: Used to indicate whether the switch can learn DVMRP default route over this interface

rcIpDvmrpTableDefRtSup.name: rcIpDvmrpTableDefRtSup
rcIpDvmrpTableDefRtSup.description: Used to indicate whether the switch should supply DVMRP default route over this interface

rcIpDvmrpTableDefRtMet.name: rcIpDvmrpTableDefRtMet
rcIpDvmrpTableDefRtMet.description: Used to specify the cost of the DVMRP default route that this interface generates and supplies when it is configured to supply default route

rcIpUdpProtocolTableSize.name: rcIpUdpProtocolTableSize
rcIpUdpProtocolTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the rcIpUdpProtocolTable.

rcIpUdpProtocolTable.name: rcIpUdpProtocolTable
rcIpUdpProtocolTable.description: list of UDP protocols. Used to determine whether to forward the UDP broadcast packet or not.

rcIpUdpProtocolEntry.name: rcIpUdpProtocolEntry
rcIpUdpProtocolEntry.description: Used to include a particular UDP port in the table. An entry in this table indicates that the box might do forwarding of UDP broadcast packets if there is a matching entry for this packet in the rcIpUdpPortFwdTable.

rcIpUdpProtocolPortNumber.name: rcIpUdpProtocolPortNumber
rcIpUdpProtocolPortNumber.description: well-known UDP Port number. Pre-assigned port number for this protocol. Port used by the server process as its contact port. It cannot be BOOTP/DHCP port#s 67, 68.

rcIpUdpProtocolName.name: rcIpUdpProtocolName
rcIpUdpProtocolName.description: Used to indicate the name of the protocol that is running on top of UDP protocol. cannot change the name once created. This should be set while creating the entry.

rcIpUdpPortFwdTableSize.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdTableSize
rcIpUdpPortFwdTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the rcIpUdpPortFwdTable.

rcIpUdpPortFwdEntry.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdEntry
rcIpUdpPortFwdEntry.description: An entry is configured to specify forwarding policy parameters.

rcIpUdpPortFwdDestPort.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdDestPort
rcIpUdpPortFwdDestPort.description: The well-known port number defined for UDP/TCP depending on the value of IpProtoType field in this entry. This port number has to be defined in the rcIpUdpProtoTable. In order to select this policy the destination port number has to match the DestPort value.

rcIpUdpPortFwdDestAddr.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdDestAddr
rcIpUdpPortFwdDestAddr.description: Destination IP address. The IP addres to which the UDP/TCP broadcast should be forwarded. This IP address can be any IP server address or subnet broadcast address. If the IP address is one of the routable interface's address on the router, the frame will be rebroadcast out as a limited broadcast. If the Ip address is that of a server then the received broadcast packet will be sent as a unicast packet to this address.

rcIpUdpPortFwdId.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdId
rcIpUdpPortFwdId.description: Identifier of this entry. Used internally to identify this entry.

rcIpUdpPortFwdFwdListIdListSize.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdFwdListIdListSize
rcIpUdpPortFwdFwdListIdListSize.description: Used to indicate the number of id(s) in the rcIpUdpPortFwdListId variable.

rcIpUdpPortFwdFwdListIdList.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdFwdListIdList
rcIpUdpPortFwdFwdListIdList.description: Used to indicate zero or more rcIpUdpPortFwdListEntry(s) that are referring to this entry. Each list-id identifier is stored as two bytes in this array starting from offset zero. Any unused bytes should be set to zero.

rcIpUdpPortFwdNumFwdPackets.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdNumFwdPackets
rcIpUdpPortFwdNumFwdPackets.description: The total number of UDP/TCP broadcast packets forwarded using this policy.

rcIpUdpPortFwdNumDropPacketsTtlExpired.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdNumDropPacketsTtlExpired
rcIpUdpPortFwdNumDropPacketsTtlExpired.description: The total number of UDP/TCP broadcast packets dropped because the TTL has expired.

rcIpUdpPortFwdNumDropPacketsDestUnreach.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdNumDropPacketsDestUnreach
rcIpUdpPortFwdNumDropPacketsDestUnreach.description: The total number of UDP/TCP broadcast packets dropped because the rcIpUdpPortFwdDestAddr specified in this policy was unreachable.

rcIpUdpPortFwdListTableSize.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdListTableSize
rcIpUdpPortFwdListTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the rcIpUdpPortFwdListTable.

rcIpUdpPortFwdListTable.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdListTable
rcIpUdpPortFwdListTable.description: A table used to group rcIpUdpPortFwdEntry(s) into a list.

rcIpUdpPortFwdListId.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdListId
rcIpUdpPortFwdListId.description: A value that uniquely identifies this list of rcIpUdpPortFwdListEntry.

rcIpUdpPortFwdListName.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdListName
rcIpUdpPortFwdListName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this list.

rcIpUdpPortFwdListFwdIdListSize.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdListFwdIdListSize
rcIpUdpPortFwdListFwdIdListSize.description: Used to indicate the number of rcIpUdpPortFwdNetEntry id(s) in the rcIpUdpPortFwdListIdList variable.

rcIpUdpPortFwdListFwdIdList.name: rcIpUdpPortFwdListFwdIdList
rcIpUdpPortFwdListFwdIdList.description: Used to indicate zero or more UdpPortFwd entries that are associated to this list. Each entry identifier is stored as two bytes in this array starting from offset zero. Any unused bytes should be set to zero.

rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfTableSize.name: rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfTableSize
rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the rcIpUdpBroadcastIntfTable.

rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfEntry.name: rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfEntry
rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfEntry.description: Used to configure UDP broadcast forward on a particular interface.

rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfLocalIfAddr.name: rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfLocalIfAddr
rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfLocalIfAddr.description: The ip address of the local interface that is partipating in the forwarding UDP broadcast packets.

rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfUdpPortFwdListId.name: rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfUdpPortFwdListId
rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfUdpPortFwdListId.description: Used to indicate the number UDP ports that this interface is configured to forward. A value of '0' indicates that this interface will not forward any UDP broadcast packets. This is a required field to create an entry.

rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfMaxTtl.name: rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfMaxTtl
rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfMaxTtl.description: Used to indicate the maximum number of hops an IP broadcast packet can take from the source device to the destination device.

rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumRxPkts.name: rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumRxPkts
rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumRxPkts.description: The total number of UDP/TCP broadcast packets received by this local interface.

rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumFwdPkts.name: rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumFwdPkts
rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumFwdPkts.description: The total number of UDP/TCP broadcast packets forwarded.

rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumDropPktsMaxTt.name: rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumDropPktsMaxTtlExpired
rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumDropPktsMaxTt.description: The total number of UDP/TCP broadcast packets dropped because the TTL has expired.

rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumDropPktsDestU.name: rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumDropPktsDestUnreach
rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumDropPktsDestU.description: The total number of UDP broadcast packets dropped because the destination was unreachable.

rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumDropPktsUnkno.name: rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumDropPktsUnknownPort
rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfNumDropPktsUnkno.description: The total number of UDP/TCP broadcast packets dropped because the destination port/protocol specified has no matching forwarding policy.

rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfBroadCastMask.name: rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfBroadCastMask
rcIpUdpConfBroadcastIntfBroadCastMask.description: The subnet mask of the local interface that is used for broadcasting the UDP broadcast packets.

rcIpTosRuleAndMask.name: rcIpTosRuleAndMask
rcIpTosRuleAndMask.description: And Mask. The Ip ToS byte in the Ip header is logically ANDed with this value, and then logically ORed with the one of the OrRules below.

rcIpTosRuleOrRule1.name: rcIpTosRuleOrRule1
rcIpTosRuleOrRule1.description: Quid/Gid Or rule #1. The Ip ToS byte in the Ip header is logically ORed with this value.

rcIpTosRuleOrRule2.name: rcIpTosRuleOrRule2
rcIpTosRuleOrRule2.description: Quid/Gid Or rule #2. The Ip ToS byte in the Ip header is logically ORed with this value.

rcIpTosRuleOrRule3.name: rcIpTosRuleOrRule3
rcIpTosRuleOrRule3.description: Quid/Gid Or rule #3. The Ip ToS byte in the Ip header is logically ORed with this value.

rcIpStaticRouteTableSize.name: rcIpStaticRouteTableSize
rcIpStaticRouteTableSize.description: size of Ip Static Route Table.

rcIpStaticRouteTable.name: rcIpStaticRouteTable
rcIpStaticRouteTable.description: This table is used to add static IP routes to the device. Routes added into this table will automatically show-up in the 'rcIpRouteTable' when the device is actively using the route to forward IP traffic.

rcIpStaticRouteEntry.name: rcIpStaticRouteEntry
rcIpStaticRouteEntry.description: A static route to a particular destination.

rcIpStaticRouteDest.name: rcIpStaticRouteDest
rcIpStaticRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. An entry with a value of 0.0.0.0 is considered a default route. Multiple routes to a single destination can appear in the table, but access to such multiple entries is dependent on the table- access mechanisms defined by the network management protocol in use.

rcIpStaticRouteMask.name: rcIpStaticRouteMask
rcIpStaticRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the rcIpRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the rcIpRouteMask by determining whether the value of the correspondent rcIpRouteDest field belong to a class-A, B, or C network, and then using one of: mask network 255.0.0.0 class-A 255.255.0.0 class-B 255.255.255.0 class-C If the value of the rcIpRouteDest is 0.0.0.0 (a default route), then the mask value is also 0.0.0.0. It should be noted that all IP routing subsystems implicitly use this mechanism.

rcIpStaticRouteNextHop.name: rcIpStaticRouteNextHop
rcIpStaticRouteNextHop.description: The IP address of the next hop of this route. (In the case of a route bound to an interface which is realized via a broadcast media, the value of this field is the agent's IP address on that interface).

rcIpStaticRouteMetric.name: rcIpStaticRouteMetric
rcIpStaticRouteMetric.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's rcIpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

rcIpStaticRouteIfIndex.name: rcIpStaticRouteIfIndex
rcIpStaticRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcIpStaticRoutePreference.name: rcIpStaticRoutePreference
rcIpStaticRoutePreference.description: Used to indicate the route preference of this entry. If there are more than one route that can be used to forward IP traffic, the route that has a highest preference will be used instead of a lower preference one. The higher the number, the higher the preference.

rcIpStaticRouteStatus.name: rcIpStaticRouteStatus
rcIpStaticRouteStatus.description: Used to indicate the current status of this entry.

rcIpStaticRouteLocalNextHop.name: rcIpStaticRouteLocalNextHop
rcIpStaticRouteLocalNextHop.description: Used to enable/disable this entry. True indicate that the static route becomes active only if switch has a local route to the network. False indicates that the static route becomes active if switch has a local route or dynamic route.

rcIpStaticRouteBfdTableSize.name: rcIpStaticRouteBfdTableSize
rcIpStaticRouteBfdTableSize.description: size of IP static route BFD table.

rcIpStaticRouteBfdTable.name: rcIpStaticRouteBfdTable
rcIpStaticRouteBfdTable.description: This table is used to hold next hop addresses on which BFD is enabled.

rcIpStaticRouteBfdEntry.name: rcIpStaticRouteBfdEntry
rcIpStaticRouteBfdEntry.description: An IP address of the next hop of the BFD session.

rcIpStaticRouteBfdNextHop.name: rcIpStaticRouteBfdNextHop
rcIpStaticRouteBfdNextHop.description: The IP address of the next hop of the BFD session.

rcIpPimGlobalMbr.name: rcIpPimGlobalMbr
rcIpPimGlobalMbr.description: enable/disable pim multicast border router feature

rcIpPimGlobalRegisterSuppTimer.name: rcIpPimGlobalRegisterSuppTimer
rcIpPimGlobalRegisterSuppTimer.description: Each source's DR maintains, per (S,G), a Register- Suppression-timer in seconds. The Register- Suppression-timer is started by the Register-Stop message; upon expiration, the source's DR resumes sending data packets to the RP, encapsulated in the Register message.

rcIpPimGlobalUniRouteChgTimeOut.name: rcIpPimGlobalUniRouteChgTimeOut
rcIpPimGlobalUniRouteChgTimeOut.description: This timer allows a better tuning on how fast the routing information is going to get updated from RTM (the frequency at which the RTM is polled for routing information updates).

rcIpPimGlobalDiscardDataTimeOut.name: rcIpPimGlobalDiscardDataTimeOut
rcIpPimGlobalDiscardDataTimeOut.description: This timer is used to discard data until the Join is received from the RP. A ipmc discard record is created and deleted once the timer expires and/or when a Join is received.

rcIpPimGlobalCRPADVTimeOut.name: rcIpPimGlobalCRPADVTimeOut
rcIpPimGlobalCRPADVTimeOut.description: Routers configured as candidate RPs use this timer to periodically send C-RP-Adv messages. Upon expiry, a C-RP-Adv message is sent to the elected BSR.

rcIpPimGlobalBootStrapPeriod.name: rcIpPimGlobalBootStrapPeriod
rcIpPimGlobalBootStrapPeriod.description: At the elected BSR, this is the interval between originating Bootstrap messages.

rcIpPimGlobalActivityChkInterval.name: rcIpPimGlobalActivityChkInterval
rcIpPimGlobalActivityChkInterval.description: Activity check interval for polling PIM SG traffic activity information.

rcIpPimGlobalFwdCacheTimeOut.name: rcIpPimGlobalFwdCacheTimeOut
rcIpPimGlobalFwdCacheTimeOut.description: PIM forward cache expiry value in seconds.This value is going to be used in aging PIM mroutes in seconds.

rcIpPimGlobalStaticRPSpecificRt.name: rcIpPimGlobalStaticRPSpecificRt
rcIpPimGlobalStaticRPSpecificRt.description: Enable/Disable Static RP specific route feature.

rcIpPimEntry.name: rcIpPimEntry
rcIpPimEntry.description: An entry of Ip Pim Table.

rcIpPimInterfaceEntry.name: rcIpPimInterfaceEntry
rcIpPimInterfaceEntry.description: An entry of Ip Pim Interface Table.

rcIpPimInterfaceOperState.name: rcIpPimInterfaceOperState
rcIpPimInterfaceOperState.description: The current operational state of this PIM interface. This object is deprecated in favor of ifOperStatus.

rcIpPimInterfaceCBSREnable.name: rcIpPimInterfaceCBSREnable
rcIpPimInterfaceCBSREnable.description: Enable/disable Candidate BSR on pim local interface.

rcIpPimStaticRPTable.name: rcIpPimStaticRPTable
rcIpPimStaticRPTable.description: The table lists all the RPs configured statically for various IP multicast groups.

rcIpPimStaticRPEntry.name: rcIpPimStaticRPEntry
rcIpPimStaticRPEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the rcIpPimStaticRPTable.

rcIpPimStaticRPGroupAddress.name: rcIpPimStaticRPGroupAddress
rcIpPimStaticRPGroupAddress.description: The IP multicast group address which, when combined with rcIpPimStaticRPGroupMask, identifies a group prefix for which rcIpPimStaticRPAddress is a static-RP.

rcIpPimStaticRPGroupMask.name: rcIpPimStaticRPGroupMask
rcIpPimStaticRPGroupMask.description: The multicast group address mask which, when combined with rcIpPimStaticRPGroupAddress, identifies a group prefix for which rcIpPimStaticRPAddress is a static-RP.

rcIpPimStaticRPRowStatus.name: rcIpPimStaticRPRowStatus
rcIpPimStaticRPRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

rcIpPimVirtualNbrTable.name: rcIpPimVirtualNbrTable
rcIpPimVirtualNbrTable.description: Table listing the router's virtual PIM neighbors

rcIpPimVirtualNbrEntry.name: rcIpPimVirtualNbrEntry
rcIpPimVirtualNbrEntry.description: An entry in the virtual PIM neighbors' table.

rcIpPimVirtualNbrAddress.name: rcIpPimVirtualNbrAddress
rcIpPimVirtualNbrAddress.description: The IP address of the virtual PIM neighbor for which this entry contains information.

rcIpPimVirtualNbrIfIndex.name: rcIpPimVirtualNbrIfIndex
rcIpPimVirtualNbrIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the PIM interface in which this virtual neighbor is created. This value is mandatory while trying to create a virtual PIM neighbor.

rcIpPimVirtualNbrRowStatus.name: rcIpPimVirtualNbrRowStatus
rcIpPimVirtualNbrRowStatus.description: To create/delete an entry in the virtual PIM neighbors' table.

rcIpMulticastArpEntry.name: rcIpMulticastArpEntry
rcIpMulticastArpEntry.description: An entry of Ip Multicast Arp Table.

rcIpMulticastEntry.name: rcIpMulticastEntry
rcIpMulticastEntry.description: Entry containing Proprietary Ip Multicast information.

rcIpMulticastMulticastIp.name: rcIpMulticastMulticastIp
rcIpMulticastMulticastIp.description: IP Address on this IfIndex to be used for all Multicast protocols running on this interface.

rcIpRipInterfaceEntry.name: rcIpRipInterfaceEntry
rcIpRipInterfaceEntry.description: An entry of Ip Rip Interface Table.

rcIpRipInterfaceHolddown.name: rcIpRipInterfaceHolddown
rcIpRipInterfaceHolddown.description: Used to indicate the rip holddown timer for this interface

rcIpRipInterfaceTimeout.name: rcIpRipInterfaceTimeout
rcIpRipInterfaceTimeout.description: Used to indicate the rip timeout interval for this interface

rcIpMulticastTimedPruneTable.name: rcIpMulticastTimedPruneTable
rcIpMulticastTimedPruneTable.description: This feature provides the ability for the user to create (S,G) Forwarding Entries that would not be pruned until a configurable timer expires. This feature is targeted for Passport 8600/8800. Currently the timer value is set to 0.

rcIpMulticastTimedPruneEntry.name: rcIpMulticastTimedPruneEntry
rcIpMulticastTimedPruneEntry.description: An entry of Ip Multicast Timed Prune Table.

rcIpMulticastTimedPruneGroupAddress.name: rcIpMulticastTimedPruneGroupAddress
rcIpMulticastTimedPruneGroupAddress.description: This field indicates the IP Multicast Group Address associated with the IP multicast stream.

rcIpMulticastTimedPruneSourceAddress.name: rcIpMulticastTimedPruneSourceAddress
rcIpMulticastTimedPruneSourceAddress.description: This is the Source Subnet IP address of the sender of the IP multicast stream.

rcIpMulticastTimedPruneSrcSubnetMask.name: rcIpMulticastTimedPruneSrcSubnetMask
rcIpMulticastTimedPruneSrcSubnetMask.description: This is the Source Subnet Mask IP address of the sender of the IP multicast stream.

rcIpMulticastTimedPruneAgingTimer.name: rcIpMulticastTimedPruneAgingTimer
rcIpMulticastTimedPruneAgingTimer.description: This field represents the amount of time (in minutes) this timed prune entry will be kept in the forwarding table when there are no more receivers. After this timer expires, this timed prune entry would be treated as a normal DVMRP/PIM forwarding entry. Aging Timer value of 0 (infinite time) indicates this timed prune entry will not be deleted even when there are no more receivers.

rcIpMulticastTimedPruneTimeLeft.name: rcIpMulticastTimedPruneTimeLeft
rcIpMulticastTimedPruneTimeLeft.description: This read-only field represents the remaining time for which this timed prune entry will be kept in the forwarding table. After this timer expires, this timed prune entry would be treated as a normal DVMRP/PIM forwarding entry. 0 in this field indicates that this entry would not be aged out.

rcIpMulticastTimedPruneLastActivity.name: rcIpMulticastTimedPruneLastActivity
rcIpMulticastTimedPruneLastActivity.description: This read-only field represents the actual time since the traffic has come from this Source, Group pair.

rcIpConfIcmpRdiscTable.name: rcIpConfIcmpRdiscTable
rcIpConfIcmpRdiscTable.description: A table used to maintain ICMP Route discovery information for a particular interface.

rcIpConfIcmpRdiscEntry.name: rcIpConfIcmpRdiscEntry
rcIpConfIcmpRdiscEntry.description: Entry containing ICMP Rdisc information. An entry is automatically created in this table when routing is enabled for an interface -or- when an ip address is configured on an interface.

rcIpConfIcmpRdiscIfIndex.name: rcIpConfIcmpRdiscIfIndex
rcIpConfIcmpRdiscIfIndex.description: An unique value to identify a physical interface or a logical interface (VLAN).

rcIpConfIcmpRdiscAdvAddress.name: rcIpConfIcmpRdiscAdvAddress
rcIpConfIcmpRdiscAdvAddress.description: Advertisement address to which the route discovery advertisements transmitted on this interface.

rcIpConfIcmpRdiscAdvFlag.name: rcIpConfIcmpRdiscAdvFlag
rcIpConfIcmpRdiscAdvFlag.description: Flag to indicate whether or not the address is to be advertised on this interface.

rcIpConfIcmpRdiscAdvLifetime.name: rcIpConfIcmpRdiscAdvLifetime
rcIpConfIcmpRdiscAdvLifetime.description: The value to be placed in the lifetime field of Router Advertisements sent from the interface.

rcIpConfIcmpRdiscMaxAdvInterval.name: rcIpConfIcmpRdiscMaxAdvInterval
rcIpConfIcmpRdiscMaxAdvInterval.description: The maximum time allowed between sending Router Advertisements from this interface.

rcIpConfIcmpRdiscMinAdvInterval.name: rcIpConfIcmpRdiscMinAdvInterval
rcIpConfIcmpRdiscMinAdvInterval.description: The minimum time allowed between sending Router Advertisements from this interface.

rcIpConfIcmpRdiscPreferenceLevel.name: rcIpConfIcmpRdiscPreferenceLevel
rcIpConfIcmpRdiscPreferenceLevel.description: Preferability of the router address as a default Router

rcIpMulticastSoftwareForwardingThreshold.name: rcIpMulticastSoftwareForwardingThreshold
rcIpMulticastSoftwareForwardingThreshold.description: Threshold to switch from software forwarding to hardware forwarding. Unit = pkt per second

rcIpMrouteHwTable.name: rcIpMrouteHwTable
rcIpMrouteHwTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing hardware entries of multicast routing information for all the Group Address.

rcIpMrouteHwEntry.name: rcIpMrouteHwEntry
rcIpMrouteHwEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing hardware entries of multicast routing information for a particular Group Address.

rcIpMrouteHwGroupAddress.name: rcIpMrouteHwGroupAddress
rcIpMrouteHwGroupAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

rcIpMrouteHwSubnet.name: rcIpMrouteHwSubnet
rcIpMrouteHwSubnet.description: The network address from where the source is sending the stream of traffic for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

rcIpMrouteHwInvlan.name: rcIpMrouteHwInvlan
rcIpMrouteHwInvlan.description: The Ingress vlan Id from where the traffic is coming for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

rcIpMrouteHwPruned.name: rcIpMrouteHwPruned
rcIpMrouteHwPruned.description: This is to show weather the entry containing multicast routing information has received Prune message or not.

rcIpMrouteHwIndex.name: rcIpMrouteHwIndex
rcIpMrouteHwIndex.description: This Index value keep tracks of the hardware record that has been accessed for displaying the entry containing multicast routing information.

rcIpMrouteHwPrunesTable.name: rcIpMrouteHwPrunesTable
rcIpMrouteHwPrunesTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing prune entries of multicast routing information for the Group Address.

rcIpMrouteHwPrunesEntry.name: rcIpMrouteHwPrunesEntry
rcIpMrouteHwPrunesEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing prune entries of multicast routing information for a particular Group Address.

rcIpMrouteHwPrunesGroupAddress.name: rcIpMrouteHwPrunesGroupAddress
rcIpMrouteHwPrunesGroupAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

rcIpMrouteHwPrunesSubnet.name: rcIpMrouteHwPrunesSubnet

rcIpRoutePolicyApply.description: Used to apply Ip Route Policy

rcIpRoutePolicyEntry.name: rcIpRoutePolicyEntry
rcIpRoutePolicyEntry.description: An entry of Ip Route Map Table.

rcIpRoutePolicyId.name: rcIpRoutePolicyId
rcIpRoutePolicyId.description: Index used to identify a group of policies in the route policy tableRoute map id

rcIpRoutePolicySequenceNumber.name: rcIpRoutePolicySequenceNumber
rcIpRoutePolicySequenceNumber.description: second index used to identify a specific policy with in the route policy group (grouped by Id). This field allows users to specify different MATCH, SET parameters and an action.

rcIpRoutePolicyName.name: rcIpRoutePolicyName
rcIpRoutePolicyName.description: Is used to group a set of policies with different sequence number. Id & Name have one-on-one relationship. Different policy groups can contain same sequence number, whereas with in a group the sequence number must be different.

rcIpRoutePolicyEnable.name: rcIpRoutePolicyEnable
rcIpRoutePolicyEnable.description: Value specified here indicate whether this policy is enabled or not. If disabled policy sould not be used.

rcIpRoutePolicyMode.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMode
rcIpRoutePolicyMode.description: specifies the action to be taken when this policy is selected for a specific route. This can be permit or deny or continue. Permit indicates allow the route, deny indicates ignore the route. Continue means continue checking the next match criteria set in the next policy seq, if none take the default action in the given context.

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchProtocol.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchProtocol
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchProtocol.description: Match protocol. Used for RIP and DVMRP announce policy only. Value is one of multiple (logical 'OR) of the following values: direct(1), static(2), rip(4), ospf(8), ebgp(16), dvmrp(32), ibgp(64), isis(128), any(255) direct(1): enables direct match-protocol static(2): enables static match-protocol rip(4): enables rip match-protocol ospf(8): enables ospf match-protocol ebgp(16): enables ebgp match-protocol dvmrp(32): enables dvmrp match-protocol ibgp(64): enables ibgp match-protocol isis(128): enables isis match-protocol any(255): enables all match-protocols

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchAsPath.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchAsPath
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchAsPath.description: Applicable to BGP protocol only. Match the BGP autonomous system path. This will override the BGP neighbor filter list info.

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchCommunity.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchCommunity
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchCommunity.description: Applicable to BGP protocol only. Filter incoming/outgoing updates based on communities.

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchCommunityExact.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchCommunityExact
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchCommunityExact.description: If enabled indicates the match has be an exact (i.e., all of the communities specified in the path has to be matched).

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchNetwork.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchNetwork
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchNetwork.description: can specify one or more prefix list name or id(s)

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchIpRouteSource.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchIpRouteSource
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchIpRouteSource.description: In case of Rip routes this is equivalent to RipInterface. In case of DVMRP routes this is equivalent to DVMRP gateway. Can specify one or more prefix list name(s) or id(s) seperated by comma.

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchNextHop.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchNextHop
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchNextHop.description: In case of Rip routes this is equivalent to RipInterface. In case of DVMRP routes this is equivalent to DVMRP gateway. Can specify one or more prefix list name(s) or id(s) seperated by comma.

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchInterface.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchInterface
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchInterface.description: Match received interface. Only for rip routes. Ignored in all other cases.

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchRouteType.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchRouteType
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchRouteType.description: For BGP this choice refers to locally generated routes external routes learned via ebgp nbr. For OSPF internal refers to intra and inter area routes (belongs to local autonomous system). External (type1|type2) refers to the routes learned from other ASs and imported as either type1 or type2. if type1/type2 is specified then match only type1/type2.

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchMetric.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchMetric
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchMetric.description: Match mec field in the incoming advertisement.

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchTag.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchTag
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchTag.description: specifies a list of tag(s), that will be used during the match criteria process.contains one or more tag values..

rcIpRoutePolicySetRoutePreference.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetRoutePreference
rcIpRoutePolicySetRoutePreference.description: if non-zero specifies the route preference value to be assigned to the routes that applies this policy.contains one or more tag values..

rcIpRoutePolicySetAsPath.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetAsPath
rcIpRoutePolicySetAsPath.description: The AS path vaule to be used whether the SetAsPathMode is Tag or Prepend.as-path string..

rcIpRoutePolicySetAsPathMode.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetAsPathMode
rcIpRoutePolicySetAsPathMode.description: It can be either tag or prepend tag. applicable only while redistributing routes to BGP.Converts the tag of a route into AS path.

rcIpRoutePolicySetCommunityNumber.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetCommunityNumber
rcIpRoutePolicySetCommunityNumber.description: this value can be a number (1..42949672000) or no-export or no-advertise. Applicable to BGP advertisments.community number.

rcIpRoutePolicySetCommunityMode.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetCommunityMode
rcIpRoutePolicySetCommunityMode.description: this value can be either append or none unchanged - keep the community attribute in the route path as it is. none - remove the community in the route path additive - adds the community-number specified in SetCommunityNumber to the community list attribute. Applicable to BGP advertisments.

rcIpRoutePolicySetMetricTypeInternal.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetMetricTypeInternal
rcIpRoutePolicySetMetricTypeInternal.description: Indicates to set the MED value for routes advertised to ebgp nbrs to the IGP metric value.

rcIpRoutePolicySetMetric.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetMetric
rcIpRoutePolicySetMetric.description: Value of the metric to be used while sending an update for the routes that match the matching criteria in this route policy. Default - 0 indicates the internal value defined for protocol

rcIpRoutePolicySetMetricType.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetMetricType
rcIpRoutePolicySetMetricType.description: Metric type for the routes to be imported into OSPF routing protocol, which passed the matching criteria configured in this route policy.

rcIpRoutePolicySetNextHop.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetNextHop
rcIpRoutePolicySetNextHop.description: IpAddress of the next hop router. Ignored for DVMRP routes.

rcIpRoutePolicySetOrigin.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetOrigin
rcIpRoutePolicySetOrigin.description: igp/egp/incomplete Applicable to BGP protocol only. If not set uses the route origin from the Ip routing table (protocol).

rcIpRoutePolicySetLocalPref.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetLocalPref
rcIpRoutePolicySetLocalPref.description: this value will be used during route decision process in the BGP protocol. Applicable to BGP only.

rcIpRoutePolicySetOriginEgpAs.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetOriginEgpAs
rcIpRoutePolicySetOriginEgpAs.description: indicates the Remote autonomous sys number. Applicable to BGP only.

rcIpRoutePolicySetTag.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetTag
rcIpRoutePolicySetTag.description: Value to be used for setting tag of the destination routing protocol. If not specified forward the tag value in the source routing protocol. Value 0 indicates not set

rcIpRoutePolicySetWeight.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetWeight
rcIpRoutePolicySetWeight.description: Should be using with match as-path condition. Weight value for the routing table. For BGP this value will override the weight configured through NetworkTableEntry or FilterListWeight or NeighborWeight. Used for BGP only.Value 0 indicates not set

rcIpRoutePolicySetInjectNetList.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetInjectNetList
rcIpRoutePolicySetInjectNetList.description: specifies the prefix list to be used either for injecting the routes into the routing table or to include the networks in the advertisement. Ignored for DVMRP.

rcIpRoutePolicyNssaPbit.name: rcIpRoutePolicyNssaPbit
rcIpRoutePolicyNssaPbit.description: Set/Reset P bit in specified type 7 LSA. By default P bit is always set in case user set it to disable state for particular route policy than all type 7 LSAs associated with that route policy will have P bit cleared, with this intact NSSA ABR will not perform translation of these LSAs to type 5.

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchVrf.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchVrf
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchVrf.description: An array used to identify which source VRFs have leaked routes to the local VRF

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchExtCommunity.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchExtCommunity
rcIpRoutePolicyMatchExtCommunity.description: Filter incoming/outgoing updates based on communities

rcIpRoutePolicySetExtCommunityMode.name: rcIpRoutePolicySetExtCommunityMode
rcIpRoutePolicySetExtCommunityMode.description: This value can be either additive, unchanged or overwrite.

rcIpRoutePolicyMatchIpRouteDest.name: rcIpRoutePolicyMatchIpRouteDest
