rcIpMplsIfTable.name: rcIpMplsIfTable
rcIpMplsIfTable.description: A table used to maintain MPLS information for a particular interface.

rcIpMplsIfEntry.name: rcIpMplsIfEntry
rcIpMplsIfEntry.description: Entry containing MPLS information. An entry is automatically created in this table when MPLS is enabled for an interface -or- when an ip address is configured on an interface.

rcIpMplsIfIfIndex.name: rcIpMplsIfIfIndex
rcIpMplsIfIfIndex.description: An unique value to identify a physical interface or a logical interface (VLAN).

rcIpMplsIfLdpAdminState.name: rcIpMplsIfLdpAdminState
rcIpMplsIfLdpAdminState.description: Indicates whether LDP is enabled on the interface.

rcIpMplsIfLdpSessionKeepAlive.name: rcIpMplsIfLdpSessionKeepAlive
rcIpMplsIfLdpSessionKeepAlive.description: Configures the LDP Session keep alive on the interface. The value 0 is used to indicate a global value. If 0 the interface will use the LDP global value. If greater than 0 this value will override the LDP global value.

rcIpMplsIfLdpHelloHoldTime.name: rcIpMplsIfLdpHelloHoldTime
rcIpMplsIfLdpHelloHoldTime.description: Configures the LDP hello hold time on the interface. If 0 the interface will use the LDP global value. If greater than 0 this value will override the LDP global value.

rcIpMplsIfLdpTransportAddr.name: rcIpMplsIfLdpTransportAddr
rcIpMplsIfLdpTransportAddr.description: Configures the transport address of the LDP lsp. If not set then transport address will be the MPLS router id.

rcIpMplsIfLdpImportPolicy.name: rcIpMplsIfLdpImportPolicy
rcIpMplsIfLdpImportPolicy.description: Configures the LDP import policy behavior. If set to host-only then only host will import policies. If set to all then all interfaces will import policies.

rcIpMplsIfRsvpAdminState.name: rcIpMplsIfRsvpAdminState
rcIpMplsIfRsvpAdminState.description: Indicates whether RSVP is enabled on the interface.

rcIpMplsIfRefreshReduction.name: rcIpMplsIfRefreshReduction
rcIpMplsIfRefreshReduction.description: Indicates whether RSVP refresh reduction is enabled or not. If set to global, refresh reduction will take the global RSVP refresh reduction value.

rcIpMplsIfRefreshInterval.name: rcIpMplsIfRefreshInterval
rcIpMplsIfRefreshInterval.description: Configures the RSVP refresh interval on the interface. If set to zero, the refresh interval will default to the global rsvp refresh interval.

rcIpMplsIfRefreshMultiplier.name: rcIpMplsIfRefreshMultiplier
rcIpMplsIfRefreshMultiplier.description: Configures the RSVP refresh multiplier for the interface. If set to zero, the refresh interval will default to to global rsvp refresh multiplier.

rcIpMplsIfRsvpHelloInterval.name: rcIpMplsIfRsvpHelloInterval
rcIpMplsIfRsvpHelloInterval.description: Configures the RSVP hello interval on the interface. If 0 the interface will use the RSVP global value. If greater than 0 this value will override the RSVP global value.

rcIpMplsIfMessageBundling.name: rcIpMplsIfMessageBundling
rcIpMplsIfMessageBundling.description: Indicates whether RSVP message bundling is enabled or not. If set to global, message bundling will take the global RSVP message bundling value.

rcIpMplsIfMtu.name: rcIpMplsIfMtu
rcIpMplsIfMtu.description: Configures the mtu of the mpls interface. The value cannot exceed that of the system mtu size.

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteTableSize.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteTableSize
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteTableSize.description: size of Ip Static Route Table.

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteTable.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteTable
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteTable.description: This table is used to add static IP routes to the device. Routes added into this table will automatically show-up in the 'rcIpRouteTable' when the device is actively using the route to forward IP traffic.

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteEntry.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteEntry
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteEntry.description: A static route to a particular destination.

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteOwnerVrfId.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteOwnerVrfId
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteOwnerVrfId.description: Owner VRF id of the static route

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteDest.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteDest
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. An entry with a value of 0.0.0.0 is considered a default route. Multiple routes to a single destination can appear in the table, but access to such multiple entries is dependent on the table- access mechanisms defined by the network management protocol in use.

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteMask.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteMask
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the rcIpRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the rcIpRouteMask by determining whether the value of the correspondent rcIpRouteDest field belong to a class-A, B, or C network, and then using one of: mask network 255.0.0.0 class-A 255.255.0.0 class-B 255.255.255.0 class-C If the value of the rcIpRouteDest is 0.0.0.0 (a default route), then the mask value is also 0.0.0.0. It should be noted that all IP routing subsystems implicitly use this mechanism.

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteNextHop.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteNextHop
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteNextHop.description: The IP address of the next hop of this route. (In the case of a route bound to an interface which is realized via a broadcast media, the value of this field is the agent's IP address on that interface).

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteMetric.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteMetric
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteMetric.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's rcIpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteIfIndex.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteIfIndex
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcIpInterVrfStaticRoutePreference.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRoutePreference
rcIpInterVrfStaticRoutePreference.description: Used to indicate the route preference of this entry. If there are more than one route that can be used to forward IP traffic, the route that has a highest preference will be used instead of a lower preference one. The higher the number, the higher the preference.

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteStatus.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteStatus
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteStatus.description: Used to indicate the current status of this entry.

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteLocalNextHop.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteLocalNextHop
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteLocalNextHop.description: Used to enable/disable this entry. True indicate that the static route becomes active only if switch has a local route to the network. False indicates that the static route becomes active if switch has a local route or dynamic route.

rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteNextHopVrfId.name: rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteNextHopVrfId
rcIpInterVrfStaticRouteNextHopVrfId.description: Used to indicate nhVrfId in inter-VRF static-route configuration

rcIpStaticMRouteTable.name: rcIpStaticMRouteTable
rcIpStaticMRouteTable.description: This table is used by multicast routing protocols, i.e PIM-SM, PIM-SSM, MSDP and is not visible to any other L2/L3 Protocols. It provides the flexibility of separating the paths for unicast and multicast streams. Any route addition to this table will not affect the switching and/or routing of IP unicast packets.

rcIpStaticMRouteEntry.name: rcIpStaticMRouteEntry
rcIpStaticMRouteEntry.description: A static MRoute to a particular destination.

rcIpStaticMRouteIpAddressType.name: rcIpStaticMRouteIpAddressType
rcIpStaticMRouteIpAddressType.description: The address type of Static MRoute IP address.

rcIpStaticMRouteIpAddress.name: rcIpStaticMRouteIpAddress
rcIpStaticMRouteIpAddress.description: Static MRoute IP address denotes the destination network for which the route is being added.

rcIpStaticMRouteMask.name: rcIpStaticMRouteMask
rcIpStaticMRouteMask.description: Denotes the IP subnet mask of the Static MRoute.

rcIpStaticMRouteRpfAddressType.name: rcIpStaticMRouteRpfAddressType
rcIpStaticMRouteRpfAddressType.description: The address type of Static MRoute Rpf address.

rcIpStaticMRouteRpfAddress.name: rcIpStaticMRouteRpfAddress
rcIpStaticMRouteRpfAddress.description: RPF address is the same as the nexthop in unicast Static IP route table. The RPF address denotes the RPF neighbor towards RP/Source.

rcIpStaticMRoutePreference.name: rcIpStaticMRoutePreference
rcIpStaticMRoutePreference.description: Static MRoute Preference is the administrative distance for the given route. When unicast routing table and the multicast-static IP route table have different routes for the same destination network, then this administrative distance is compared with that of the protocol that contributed the route in unicast routing table. By providing administrative distance for every route, we are giving flexibility to the administrator to choose different distances for different networks.

rcIpStaticMRouteEnable.name: rcIpStaticMRouteEnable
rcIpStaticMRouteEnable.description: This denotes the status of the route in this table. It can either be enabled/disabled.

rcIpStaticMRouteRowStatus.name: rcIpStaticMRouteRowStatus
rcIpStaticMRouteRowStatus.description: Creation and deletion of the row entry.

rcIpEcmpRouteTable.name: rcIpEcmpRouteTable
rcIpEcmpRouteTable.description: This is used to get the ECMP route for a given pair of source IP and destination IP addresses.

rcIpEcmpRouteNextHopLegacy.name: rcIpEcmpRouteNextHopLegacy
rcIpEcmpRouteNextHopLegacy.description: Next-hop address if the ingress port is on a legacy card.

rcIpEcmpRouteNextHopRMod.name: rcIpEcmpRouteNextHopRMod
rcIpEcmpRouteNextHopRMod.description: Next-hop address if the ingress port is on a R-Mod card.

rcIPClearIPMCRecordTable.name: rcIPClearIPMCRecordTable
rcIPClearIPMCRecordTable.description: Table used to clear an IP MC Record.

rcIPClearIPMCRecordEntry.name: rcIPClearIPMCRecordEntry
rcIPClearIPMCRecordEntry.description: IP Clear IP MC Record Table Entry

rcIPClearIPMCRecordVlanId.name: rcIPClearIPMCRecordVlanId
rcIPClearIPMCRecordVlanId.description: Vlan Id where the IP MC record has to be cleared.

rcIPClearIPMCRecordLCForceDelete.name: rcIPClearIPMCRecordLCForceDelete
rcIPClearIPMCRecordLCForceDelete.description: By default, when LCForceDelete (Line Card Force Delete) is set to false, if the IP MC record is not found on the CP, then no message will be sent to the line-card. When LCForceDelete is set to true, a message will be sent to the line-card even when the IP MC record is not found on the CP.

rcIPClearArpRecordTable.name: rcIPClearArpRecordTable
rcIPClearArpRecordTable.description: Table used to clear an IP ARP Record.

rcIPClearArpRecordEntry.name: rcIPClearArpRecordEntry
rcIPClearArpRecordEntry.description: IP Clear ARP Record Table Entry

rcIPClearArpRecordIpAddr.name: rcIPClearArpRecordIpAddr
rcIPClearArpRecordIpAddr.description: IP Address that needs to be cleared.

rcIPClearArpRecordVlanId.name: rcIPClearArpRecordVlanId
rcIPClearArpRecordVlanId.description: Vlan Id where the ARP record has to be cleared.

rcIPClearArpRecordLCForceDelete.name: rcIPClearArpRecordLCForceDelete
rcIPClearArpRecordLCForceDelete.description: By default, when LCForceDelete (Line Card Force Delete) is set to false, if the ARP record is not found on the CP, then no message will be sent to the line-card. When LCForceDelete is set to true, a message will be sent to the line-card even when the ARP record is not found on the CP.

rcArpExtLifeTime.name: rcArpExtLifeTime
rcArpExtLifeTime.description: The lifetime in minutues of an ARP entry within the system.

rcArpExtTable.name: rcArpExtTable
rcArpExtTable.description: ARP extension table. This table augments the standard ipNetToMediaTable defined in RFC1213.

rcArpExtEntry.name: rcArpExtEntry
rcArpExtEntry.description: Entry containing Proprietary ARP information. An entry is automatically created in this table when an ip address is configured on an interface.

rcArpExtEntIfIndex.name: rcArpExtEntIfIndex
rcArpExtEntIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcArpExtEntDoProxy.name: rcArpExtEntDoProxy
rcArpExtEntDoProxy.description: Enable or disable ARP proxy responses on the specified interface.

rcArpExtEntDoResp.name: rcArpExtEntDoResp
rcArpExtEntDoResp.description: Enable or disable the sending of ARP responses on the specified interface.

rcArpExtEntDoFlood.name: rcArpExtEntDoFlood
rcArpExtEntDoFlood.description: Enable or disable flooding of ARP responses for NLBS Virtual Mac on the specified interface.

rcArpExtV2Table.name: rcArpExtV2Table
rcArpExtV2Table.description: ARP extension table. This table augments the standard ipNetToMediaTable defined in RFC1213.

rcArpExtV2Entry.name: rcArpExtV2Entry
rcArpExtV2Entry.description: Entry containing Proprietary ARP information. An entry is automatically created in this table when an ip address is configured on an interface.

rcArpExtV2EntIfIndex.name: rcArpExtV2EntIfIndex
rcArpExtV2EntIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcArpExtV2EntDoProxy.name: rcArpExtV2EntDoProxy
rcArpExtV2EntDoProxy.description: Enable or disable ARP proxy responses on the specified interface.

rcArpExtV2EntDoResp.name: rcArpExtV2EntDoResp
rcArpExtV2EntDoResp.description: Enable or disable the sending of ARP responses on the specified interface.

rcRipExtOperation.name: rcRipExtOperation
rcRipExtOperation.description: Enable or disable the operation of RIP on all Interfaces.

rcRipExtUpdateTime.name: rcRipExtUpdateTime
rcRipExtUpdateTime.description: The time between transmission of RIP updates on all interfaces.

rcRipExtTable.name: rcRipExtTable
rcRipExtTable.description: RIP extension table. This table augments the standard IfConfTable table in RFC1389.

rcRipExtEntry.name: rcRipExtEntry
rcRipExtEntry.description: Entry containing Proprietary RIP information. An entry is automatically created in this table when an ip address is configured on an interface.

rcRipExtEntIfIndex.name: rcRipExtEntIfIndex
rcRipExtEntIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcRipExtEntTalk.name: rcRipExtEntTalk
rcRipExtEntTalk.description: Enable or disable RIP transmission on the specified interface.

rcRipExtEntListen.name: rcRipExtEntListen
rcRipExtEntListen.description: Enable or disable RIP reception on the specified interface.

rcRipExtEntPoison.name: rcRipExtEntPoison
rcRipExtEntPoison.description: Enable or disable operation of poison reverse on the specified interface. If poison is disabled, split-horizon operation is enabled.

rcRipExtV2Table.name: rcRipExtV2Table
rcRipExtV2Table.description: RIP extension table. This table augments the standard IfConfTable table in RFC1389.

rcRipExtV2Entry.name: rcRipExtV2Entry
rcRipExtV2Entry.description: Entry containing Proprietary RIP information. An entry is automatically created in this table when an ip address is configured on an interface.

rcRipExtV2EntIfIndex.name: rcRipExtV2EntIfIndex
rcRipExtV2EntIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcRipExtV2EntTalk.name: rcRipExtV2EntTalk
rcRipExtV2EntTalk.description: Enable or disable RIP transmission on the specified interface.

rcRipExtV2EntListen.name: rcRipExtV2EntListen
rcRipExtV2EntListen.description: Enable or disable RIP reception on the specified interface.

rcRipExtV2EntPoison.name: rcRipExtV2EntPoison
rcRipExtV2EntPoison.description: Enable or disable operation of poison reverse on the specified interface. If poison is disabled, split-horizon operation is enabled.

rcTestExtTable.name: rcTestExtTable
rcTestExtTable.description: Test extension table. This table augments the standard ifTestTable table in RFC1573.

rcTestExtIfIndex.name: rcTestExtIfIndex
rcTestExtIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcTestExtPassCount.name: rcTestExtPassCount
rcTestExtPassCount.description: The number of iterations of the test case that completed successfully.

rcTestExtFailCount.name: rcTestExtFailCount
rcTestExtFailCount.description: The number of iterations of the test case that failed.

rcStatTable.name: rcStatTable
rcStatTable.description: A table used to store port statistics.

rcStatPortIndex.name: rcStatPortIndex
rcStatPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port. This value is similar to ifIndex in MIB2.

rcStatFrameTooShorts.name: rcStatFrameTooShorts
rcStatFrameTooShorts.description: The total number of frames that are too short that were encountered on this interface.

rcStatBridgeInUnicastFrames.name: rcStatBridgeInUnicastFrames
rcStatBridgeInUnicastFrames.description: The total number of incoming unicast frames that were bridged.

rcStatBridgeInMulticastFrames.name: rcStatBridgeInMulticastFrames
rcStatBridgeInMulticastFrames.description: The total number of incoming multicast frames that were bridged.

rcStatBridgeInBroadcastFrames.name: rcStatBridgeInBroadcastFrames
rcStatBridgeInBroadcastFrames.description: The total number of incoming broadcast frames that were bridged.

rcStatBridgeInDiscards.name: rcStatBridgeInDiscards
rcStatBridgeInDiscards.description: The total number of frames that were discarded by the bridging entity.

rcStatBridgeOutUnicastFrames.name: rcStatBridgeOutUnicastFrames
rcStatBridgeOutUnicastFrames.description: The total number of outgoing unicast frames that were bridged.

rcStatBridgeOutMulticastFrames.name: rcStatBridgeOutMulticastFrames
rcStatBridgeOutMulticastFrames.description: The total number of outgoing multicast frames that were bridged.

rcStatBridgeOutBroadcastFrames.name: rcStatBridgeOutBroadcastFrames
rcStatBridgeOutBroadcastFrames.description: The total number of outgoing broadcast frames that were bridged.

rcStatRouteInUnicastFrames.name: rcStatRouteInUnicastFrames
rcStatRouteInUnicastFrames.description: The total number of incoming unicast frames that were routed.

rcStatRouteInMulticastFrames.name: rcStatRouteInMulticastFrames
rcStatRouteInMulticastFrames.description: The total number of incoming multicast frames that were routed.

rcStatRouteInDiscards.name: rcStatRouteInDiscards
rcStatRouteInDiscards.description: The total number of frames that were discarded by the routing entity.

rcStatRouteOutUnicastFrames.name: rcStatRouteOutUnicastFrames
rcStatRouteOutUnicastFrames.description: The total number of outgoing unicast frames that were routed.

rcStatRouteOutMulticastFrames.name: rcStatRouteOutMulticastFrames
rcStatRouteOutMulticastFrames.description: The total number of outgoing multicast frames that were routed.

rcStatStgForwardTransitions.name: rcStatStgForwardTransitions
rcStatStgForwardTransitions.description: The number of times this port has transitioned from the Learning state to the Forwarding state.

rcStatBridgeOutFrames.name: rcStatBridgeOutFrames
rcStatBridgeOutFrames.description: Used by the Accelar 8000 product family to account for all transmitted bridge unicast, broadcast, and multicast packets. The individual counters are not supported.

rcStatGigTable.name: rcStatGigTable
rcStatGigTable.description: A table used to store Gigport error statistics.

rcStatGigPortIndex.name: rcStatGigPortIndex
rcStatGigPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port. This value is similar to ifIndex in MIB2.

rcStatGigLinkFailures.name: rcStatGigLinkFailures
rcStatGigLinkFailures.description: The total number of link failures encountered on this interface.

rcStatGigPacketErrors.name: rcStatGigPacketErrors
rcStatGigPacketErrors.description: The total number of packet errors encountered on this interface.

rcStatGigCarrierErrors.name: rcStatGigCarrierErrors
rcStatGigCarrierErrors.description: The total number of carrier errors encountered on this interface.

rcStatGigLinkInactiveErrors.name: rcStatGigLinkInactiveErrors
rcStatGigLinkInactiveErrors.description: The total number of link inactive errors encountered on this interface.

rcStatGigInFlowCtrlPkts.name: rcStatGigInFlowCtrlPkts
rcStatGigInFlowCtrlPkts.description: The total number of flow control packets received by this interface.

rcStatGigOutFlowCtrlPkts.name: rcStatGigOutFlowCtrlPkts
rcStatGigOutFlowCtrlPkts.description: The total number of flow control packets transmitted by this interface.

rcStatOspfBuffersAllocated.name: rcStatOspfBuffersAllocated
rcStatOspfBuffersAllocated.description: Used to indicate the number of buffers allocated for OSPF.

rcStatOspfBuffersFreed.name: rcStatOspfBuffersFreed
rcStatOspfBuffersFreed.description: Used to indicate the number of buffers that are freed by the OSPF.

rcStatOspfBufferAllocFailures.name: rcStatOspfBufferAllocFailures
rcStatOspfBufferAllocFailures.description: Used to indicate the number of times that OSPF has failed to allocate buffers.

rcStatOspfBufferFreeFailures.name: rcStatOspfBufferFreeFailures
rcStatOspfBufferFreeFailures.description: Used to indicate the number of times that OSPF has failed to free buffers.

rcStatOspfTxPackets.name: rcStatOspfTxPackets
rcStatOspfTxPackets.description: Used to indicate the number of packets transmitted by OSPF.

rcStatOspfRxPackets.name: rcStatOspfRxPackets
rcStatOspfRxPackets.description: Used to indicate the number of packets received by OSPF.

rcStatOspfTxDropPackets.name: rcStatOspfTxDropPackets
rcStatOspfTxDropPackets.description: Used to indicate the number of packets dropped before transmitted by OSPF.

rcStatOspfRxDropPackets.name: rcStatOspfRxDropPackets
rcStatOspfRxDropPackets.description: Used to indicate the number of packets dropped before received by OSPF.

rcStatOspfRxBadPackets.name: rcStatOspfRxBadPackets
rcStatOspfRxBadPackets.description: Used to indicate the number of packets received by OSPF that are bad.

rcStatOspfSpfRuns.name: rcStatOspfSpfRuns
rcStatOspfSpfRuns.description: Used to indicate the total number of SPF calculatations performed by OSPF, which also includes the number of partial route table calculation for Incremental Updates.

rcStatOspfLastSpfRun.name: rcStatOspfLastSpfRun
rcStatOspfLastSpfRun.description: Used to indicate the time(SysUpTime) since the last spf calculated by OSPF.

rcStatOspfLsdbTblSize.name: rcStatOspfLsdbTblSize
rcStatOspfLsdbTblSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the linkstate database table.

rcStatOspfRoutes.name: rcStatOspfRoutes
rcStatOspfRoutes.description: Used to indicate the number of OSPF routes added to RTM.

rcStatOspfAdjacencies.name: rcStatOspfAdjacencies
rcStatOspfAdjacencies.description: Used to indicate the number of adjacencies existing.

rcStatOspfAreas.name: rcStatOspfAreas
rcStatOspfAreas.description: Used to indicate the number of areas configured

rcStatIgmpInMsgs.name: rcStatIgmpInMsgs
rcStatIgmpInMsgs.description: Used to indicate the number of Igmp packets received by the device.

rcStatIgmpInErrors.name: rcStatIgmpInErrors
rcStatIgmpInErrors.description: Used to indicate the number of Igmp packets received that are with checksum errors.

rcStatIgmpInQueries.name: rcStatIgmpInQueries
rcStatIgmpInQueries.description: Used to indicate the number of Igmp queries received by the device.

rcStatIgmpInReports.name: rcStatIgmpInReports
rcStatIgmpInReports.description: Used to indicate the number of Igmp reports received by the device.

rcStatIgmpInLeaves.name: rcStatIgmpInLeaves
rcStatIgmpInLeaves.description: Used to indicate the number of Igmp Leaves received by the device.

rcStatIgmpInvalid.name: rcStatIgmpInvalid
rcStatIgmpInvalid.description: Used to indicate the number of Igmp packets received by the device that contained invalid type.

rcStatIgmpOutMsgs.name: rcStatIgmpOutMsgs
rcStatIgmpOutMsgs.description: Used to indicate the number of Igmp queries sent by the device.

rcStatOspfIfTable.name: rcStatOspfIfTable
rcStatOspfIfTable.description: A table used to store OSPF interface statistics.

rcStatOspfIfIndex.name: rcStatOspfIfIndex
rcStatOspfIfIndex.description: An unique value that is used to identify a physical interface.

rcStatOspfIfRxHellos.name: rcStatOspfIfRxHellos
rcStatOspfIfRxHellos.description: Used to indicate the number hello packets received by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfRxDBDescrs.name: rcStatOspfIfRxDBDescrs
rcStatOspfIfRxDBDescrs.description: Used to indicate the number database descriptor packets received by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfRxLSUpdates.name: rcStatOspfIfRxLSUpdates
rcStatOspfIfRxLSUpdates.description: Used to indicate the number Link state update packets received by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfRxLSReqs.name: rcStatOspfIfRxLSReqs
rcStatOspfIfRxLSReqs.description: Used to indicate the number Link state request packets received by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfRxLSAcks.name: rcStatOspfIfRxLSAcks
rcStatOspfIfRxLSAcks.description: Used to indicate the number Link state acknowlege packets received by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfTxHellos.name: rcStatOspfIfTxHellos
rcStatOspfIfTxHellos.description: Used to indicate the number hello packets transmitted by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfTxDBDescrs.name: rcStatOspfIfTxDBDescrs
rcStatOspfIfTxDBDescrs.description: Used to indicate the number database descriptor packets transmitted by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfTxLSUpdates.name: rcStatOspfIfTxLSUpdates
rcStatOspfIfTxLSUpdates.description: Used to indicate the number Link state update packets transmitted by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfTxLSReqs.name: rcStatOspfIfTxLSReqs
rcStatOspfIfTxLSReqs.description: Used to indicate the number Link state request packets transmitted by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfTxLSAcks.name: rcStatOspfIfTxLSAcks
rcStatOspfIfTxLSAcks.description: Used to indicate the number Link state acknowlege packets transmitted by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfVersionMismatches.name: rcStatOspfIfVersionMismatches
rcStatOspfIfVersionMismatches.description: Used to indicate the number version mismatches received by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfAreaMismatches.name: rcStatOspfIfAreaMismatches
rcStatOspfIfAreaMismatches.description: Used to indicate the number area mismatches received by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfAuthTypeMismatches.name: rcStatOspfIfAuthTypeMismatches
rcStatOspfIfAuthTypeMismatches.description: Used to indicate the number AuthType mismatches received by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfAuthFailures.name: rcStatOspfIfAuthFailures
rcStatOspfIfAuthFailures.description: Used to indicate the number Authentication failures.

rcStatOspfIfNetMaskMismatches.name: rcStatOspfIfNetMaskMismatches
rcStatOspfIfNetMaskMismatches.description: Used to indicate the number net mask mismatches received by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfHelloIntervalMismatches.name: rcStatOspfIfHelloIntervalMismatches
rcStatOspfIfHelloIntervalMismatches.description: Used to indicate the number hello interval mismatches received by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfDeadIntervalMismatches.name: rcStatOspfIfDeadIntervalMismatches
rcStatOspfIfDeadIntervalMismatches.description: Used to indicate the number dead interval mismatches received by this interface.

rcStatOspfIfOptionMismatches.name: rcStatOspfIfOptionMismatches
rcStatOspfIfOptionMismatches.description: Used to indicate the number options mismatches received by this interface.

rcStatMltIfExtnTable.name: rcStatMltIfExtnTable
rcStatMltIfExtnTable.description: A table used to store Mlt interface statistics.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInOctets.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInOctets
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the MLT interface, including framing characters.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInUcastPkts.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInUcastPkts
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInUcastPkts.description: The number of packets delivered by this MLT to a higher MLT that were not addressed to a nulticast or broadcase address at this sublayer.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInMulticastPkt.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInMulticastPkt
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInMulticastPkt.description: The number of packets delivered to this MLT that were addressed to a nulticast address at this sublayer. For a MAC layer protocol, this number includes both Group and Functional addresses.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInBroadcastPkt.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInBroadcastPkt
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCInBroadcastPkt.description: The number of packets delivered to this MLT that were addressed to a broadcast address at this sublayer.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutOctets.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutOctets
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the MLT interface, including framing characters.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutUcastPkts.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutUcastPkts
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutUcastPkts.description: The number of packets that hight-level protocols requested be transmitted that were not addressed to a multicast address at this MLT. This total number includes those packets discarded or unsent.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutMulticast.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutMulticast
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutMulticast.description: The total number of packets that hight-level protocols requested be transmitted, and that were addressed to a multicast address at this MLT, including those that were discarded or not sent. For a MAC layer protocol, this number includes both Group and Functional addresses.

rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutBroadcast.name: rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutBroadcast
rcStatMltIfExtnIfHCOutBroadcast.description: The total number of packets that hight-level protocols requested be transmitted, and that were addressed to a broadcase address at this MLT, including those that were discarded or not sent.

rcStatMltEtherTable.name: rcStatMltEtherTable
rcStatMltEtherTable.description: A table used to store Mlt Ethernet statistics.

rcStatMltEtherMltId.name: rcStatMltEtherMltId
rcStatMltEtherMltId.description: A value that uniquely identifies the Multi-Link Trunk associated with this entry.

rcStatMltEtherAlignmentErrors.name: rcStatMltEtherAlignmentErrors
rcStatMltEtherAlignmentErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular MLT that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the alignmentError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions occur are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

rcStatMltEtherFCSErrors.name: rcStatMltEtherFCSErrors
rcStatMltEtherFCSErrors.description: A count of frames received on an MLT that are an integral number of octets in length but do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameCheckError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions occur are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

rcStatMltEtherSingleCollFrames.name: rcStatMltEtherSingleCollFrames
rcStatMltEtherSingleCollFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular MLT for which transmission is inhibited by exactly one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this objects is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts, ifOutMulticastPkts, or ifOutBroadcastPkts, and it not counted by the corresponding instance of the MultipleCollisionFrames object.

rcStatMltEtherMultipleCollFrames.name: rcStatMltEtherMultipleCollFrames
rcStatMltEtherMultipleCollFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular MLT for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts, ifOutMulticastPkts, or ifOutBroadcastPkts, and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the SingleCollisionFrames objects.

rcStatMltEtherSQETestError.name: rcStatMltEtherSQETestError
rcStatMltEtherSQETestError.description: A count of times that the SQE TEST ERROR message is generated by the PLS sublayer for a particular MLT. SQE stands for Signal Quality Error.

rcStatMltEtherDeferredTransmiss.name: rcStatMltEtherDeferredTransmiss
rcStatMltEtherDeferredTransmiss.description: A count of frames for which the first transmission attempt on a particular MLT is delayed because the medium is busy. The count represented by an instance of this object does not include frames involved in collisions.

rcStatMltEtherLateCollisions.name: rcStatMltEtherLateCollisions
rcStatMltEtherLateCollisions.description: The number of times that a collision is detected on a particular MLT later than 512 bit-times (64 octets) into the transmission of a packet. Five hundred and twelve bit-times corresponds to 51.2 microseconds on a 10 mb/s system. A (late) collision included in a count represented by an instance of this object is also considered as a (generic) collision for purposes of other collision-related statistics.

rcStatMltEtherExcessiveCollis.name: rcStatMltEtherExcessiveCollis
rcStatMltEtherExcessiveCollis.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular MLT fails due to excessive collisions.

rcStatMltEtherIMacTransmitError.name: rcStatMltEtherIMacTransmitError
rcStatMltEtherIMacTransmitError.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular MLT fails due to an internal MAC sublayer transmit error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the LateCollisions object, the ExcessiveCollisions object, or the CarrierSenseError object.

rcStatMltEtherCarrierSenseError.name: rcStatMltEtherCarrierSenseError
rcStatMltEtherCarrierSenseError.description: The number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame on a particular MLT. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented at most once per transmission attempt, even if the carrier sense condition fluctuates during a transmission attempt.

rcStatMltEtherFrameTooLong.name: rcStatMltEtherFrameTooLong
rcStatMltEtherFrameTooLong.description: A count of frames received on a particular MLT that exceed the maximum permitted size (1518 octets). The count represented by an instance os this object is incremented when the frame TooLong status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions occur are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

rcStatMltEtherIMacReceiveError.name: rcStatMltEtherIMacReceiveError
rcStatMltEtherIMacReceiveError.description: A count of frames for which reception on a particular MLT fails due to an internal MAC sublayer receive error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the FrameTooLongs object, the AlignmentErrors object, of the FCSErrors objects. The precise meaning of the count represented by an instance of this object is implementation specific. In particular, an instance of this object may represent a count of receive errors on a particular interface that are not otherwise counted.

When this threshold is reached, a new IP Multicast Receiver that needs new Egress Forwarding Record (PepStrem Record) will not be programmed to receive the subscribing multicast stream.

rcStgMaxStgs.name: rcStgMaxStgs
rcStgMaxStgs.description: The maximum number of spanning tree groups this device can support concurrently.

rcStgNumStgs.name: rcStgNumStgs
rcStgNumStgs.description: The number of spanning tree groups that are currently defined.

rcStgUnassignedPorts.name: rcStgUnassignedPorts
rcStgUnassignedPorts.description: A bitfield used to identify which ports in the system currently not assigned to any STG. The bitfield is 32 octets long representing ports 0 to 255 (inclusive).

rcStgTable.name: rcStgTable
rcStgTable.description: A table used to store Spanning Tree Group (STG) information. Each row in the table specifies a different STG in the device.

rcStgId.name: rcStgId
rcStgId.description: An identifier used to identify a STG in the device.

rcStgTaggedBpduAddress.name: rcStgTaggedBpduAddress
rcStgTaggedBpduAddress.description: The MAC address to be assigned to the destination mac address field in tagged BPDUs. The default address is the well known multicast group address 01-80-c2-00-00-00.

rcStgTaggedBpduVlanId.name: rcStgTaggedBpduVlanId
rcStgTaggedBpduVlanId.description: The VLAN ID to be used for tagging BPDUs.

rcStgBridgeAddress.name: rcStgBridgeAddress
rcStgBridgeAddress.description: The MAC address used by this bridge when it must be referred to in a unique fashion. It is recommended that this be the numerically smallest MAC address of all ports that belong to this bridge. However it is only required to be unique. When concatenated with rcStgPriority a unique BridgeIdentifier is formed which is used in the Spanning Tree Protocol.

rcStgNumPorts.name: rcStgNumPorts
rcStgNumPorts.description: The number of ports controlled by this bridging entity.

rcStgProtocolSpecification.name: rcStgProtocolSpecification
rcStgProtocolSpecification.description: An indication of what version of the Spanning Tree Protocol is being run. The value 'decLb100(2)' indicates the DEC LANbridge 100 Spanning Tree protocol. IEEE 802.1d implementations will return 'ieee8021d(3)'. If future versions of the IEEE Spanning Tree Protocol are released that are incompatible with the current version a new value will be defined.

rcStgPriority.name: rcStgPriority
rcStgPriority.description: The value of the write-able portion of the Bridge ID, i.e., the first two octets of the (8 octet long) Bridge ID. The other (last) 6 octets of the Bridge ID are given by the value of rcStgBridgeAddress.

rcStgTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: rcStgTimeSinceTopologyChange
rcStgTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last time a topology change was detected by the bridge entity.

rcStgTopChanges.name: rcStgTopChanges
rcStgTopChanges.description: The total number of topology changes detected by this bridge since the management entity was last reset or initialized.

rcStgDesignatedRoot.name: rcStgDesignatedRoot
rcStgDesignatedRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node. This value is used as the Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this node.

rcStgRootCost.name: rcStgRootCost
rcStgRootCost.description: The cost of the path to the root as seen from this bridge.

rcStgRootPort.name: rcStgRootPort
rcStgRootPort.description: The port number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this bridge to the root bridge.

rcStgMaxAge.name: rcStgMaxAge
rcStgMaxAge.description: The maximum age of Spanning Tree Protocol information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

rcStgHelloTime.name: rcStgHelloTime
rcStgHelloTime.description: The amount of time between the transmission of Configuration bridge PDUs by this node on any port when it is the root of the spanning tree or trying to become so, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

rcStgHoldTime.name: rcStgHoldTime
rcStgHoldTime.description: This time value determines the interval length during which no more than two Configuration bridge PDUs shall be transmitted by this node, in units of hundredths of a second.

rcStgForwardDelay.name: rcStgForwardDelay
rcStgForwardDelay.description: This time value, measured in units of hundredths of a second, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the Forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in each of the Listening and Learning states, which precede the Forwarding state. This value is also used, when a topology change has been detected and is underway, to age all dynamic entries in the Forwarding Database. [Note that this value is the one that this bridge is currently using, in contrast to rcStgBridgeForwardDelay which is the value that this bridge and all others would start using if/when this bridge were to become the root.]

rcStgBridgeMaxAge.name: rcStgBridgeMaxAge
rcStgBridgeMaxAge.description: The value that all bridges use for MaxAge when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1D-1990 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of rcStgBridgeHelloTime. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

rcStgBridgeHelloTime.name: rcStgBridgeHelloTime
rcStgBridgeHelloTime.description: The value that all bridges use for HelloTime when this bridge is acting as the root. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D- 1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

rcStgBridgeForwardDelay.name: rcStgBridgeForwardDelay
rcStgBridgeForwardDelay.description: The value that all bridges use for ForwardDelay when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1D-1990 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of rcStgBridgeMaxAge. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

rcStgEnableStp.name: rcStgEnableStp
rcStgEnableStp.description: Indicate whether the spanning tree protocol should be active in this STG.

rcStgStpTrapEnable.name: rcStgStpTrapEnable
rcStgStpTrapEnable.description: Indicate whether traps relating to the spanning tree protocol should be sent for this STG.

rcStgPortMembers.name: rcStgPortMembers
rcStgPortMembers.description: A bitfield used to identify which ports in the system are members this STG. The bitfield is 32 octets long representing ports 0 to 255 (inclusive).

rcStgPortStpState.name: rcStgPortStpState
rcStgPortStpState.description: Every 2 bitfields used to identify a port state in this STG. Port state is cataloged as non-stp(0), blocking(1), learning(2), and forwarding(3).

rcStgNtStgEnable.name: rcStgNtStgEnable
rcStgNtStgEnable.description: Indicates whether this STG is Operating in Nortel Mode or in Cisco Mode. true = Nortel Mode false = Cisco Mode.

rcStgPortTable.name: rcStgPortTable
rcStgPortTable.description: A table used to store Spanning Tree Group (STG) port related information. If a port is associated with more than one STGs, the port will have one entry in this table for each STG it assigned to.

rcStgPort.name: rcStgPort
rcStgPort.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains Spanning Tree Protocol management information.

rcStgPortStgId.name: rcStgPortStgId
rcStgPortStgId.description: The STG identifier this port is assigned to.

rcStgPortPriority.name: rcStgPortPriority
rcStgPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) octet of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of rcStgPort.

rcStgPortState.name: rcStgPortState
rcStgPortState.description: The port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action a port takes on reception of a frame. If the bridge has detected a port that is malfunctioning it will place that port into the broken(6) state. For ports which are disabled (see rcStgPortEnable), this object will have a value of disabled(1).

rcStgPortEnableStp.name: rcStgPortEnableStp
rcStgPortEnableStp.description: The enabled/disabled status of the port.

rcStgPortFastStart.name: rcStgPortFastStart
rcStgPortFastStart.description: When this flag is set, the port is moved straight to the forwarding(5) state upon being enabled.

rcStgPortPathCost.name: rcStgPortPathCost
rcStgPortPathCost.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. 802.1D-1990 recommends that the default value of this parameter be in inverse proportion to the speed of the attached LAN.

rcStgPortDesignatedRoot.name: rcStgPortDesignatedRoot
rcStgPortDesignatedRoot.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the Bridge recorded as the Root in the Configuration BPDUs transmitted by the Designated Bridge for the segment to which the port is attached.

rcStgPortDesignatedCost.name: rcStgPortDesignatedCost
rcStgPortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge PDUs.

rcStgPortDesignatedBridge.name: rcStgPortDesignatedBridge
rcStgPortDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

rcStgPortDesignatedPort.name: rcStgPortDesignatedPort
rcStgPortDesignatedPort.description: The Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

rcStgPortForwardTransitions.name: rcStgPortForwardTransitions
rcStgPortForwardTransitions.description: The number of times this port has transitioned from the Learning state to the Forwarding state.

rcStgPortInConfigBpdus.name: rcStgPortInConfigBpdus
rcStgPortInConfigBpdus.description: The number of Config BPUDs received by this port.

rcStgPortInTcnBpdus.name: rcStgPortInTcnBpdus
rcStgPortInTcnBpdus.description: The number of Topology Change Notification BPUDs received by this port.

rcStgPortInBadBpdus.name: rcStgPortInBadBpdus
rcStgPortInBadBpdus.description: The number of Bad BPUDs received by this port.

rcStgPortOutConfigBpdus.name: rcStgPortOutConfigBpdus
rcStgPortOutConfigBpdus.description: The number of Config BPUDs transmitted by this port.

rcStgPortOutTcnBpdus.name: rcStgPortOutTcnBpdus
rcStgPortOutTcnBpdus.description: The number of Topology Change Notification BPUDs transmitted by this port.

rcStgPortChangeDetection.name: rcStgPortChangeDetection
rcStgPortChangeDetection.description: If disabled, topology change notifications are not sent for the port.

rcStgPortPathCost32.name: rcStgPortPathCost32
rcStgPortPathCost32.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. 802.1D-1998 recommends that the default value of this parameter be in inverse proportion to the speed of the attached LAN. Replacement for deprecated object dot1dStpPortPathCost.

rcStgNotAllowedPorts.name: rcStgNotAllowedPorts
rcStgNotAllowedPorts.description: A bitfield used to identify which ports in the system that cannot be assigned to any STG (i.e., which ports are single routable ports). The bitfield is 32 octets long representing ports 0 to 255 (inclusive).

rcBridgeFdbTable.name: rcBridgeFdbTable
rcBridgeFdbTable.description: This table is an replacement to the standard dot1dTpFdbTable in rfc1493.

rcBridgeFdbEntry.name: rcBridgeFdbEntry
rcBridgeFdbEntry.description: Information about a specific unicast MAC address for which the bridge has some forwarding information.

rcBridgeFdbStatus.name: rcBridgeFdbStatus
rcBridgeFdbStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

rcBridgeFdbAddress.name: rcBridgeFdbAddress
rcBridgeFdbAddress.description: A unicast MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

rcBridgeFdbPort.name: rcBridgeFdbPort
rcBridgeFdbPort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port on which a frame having a source address equal to the value of the corresponding instance of rcBridgeFdbAddress has been seen. A value of '0' indicates that the port number has not been learned but that the bridge does have some forwarding/filtering information about this address (e.g. in the dot1dStaticTable). Implementors are encouraged to assign the port value to this object whenever it is learned even for addresses for which the corresponding value of rcBridgeFdbStatus is not learned(3).

rcBridgeFdbMonitor.name: rcBridgeFdbMonitor
rcBridgeFdbMonitor.description: Used to indicate whether monitoring should be performed on this unicast MAC address. If monitoring is enabled, any packet received with a matching destination MAC address will be forwarded to the port configured to receive monitor traffic.

rcBridgeFdbPriority.name: rcBridgeFdbPriority
rcBridgeFdbPriority.description: Used to indicate the priority of the incoming frames with this destination Mac Address.

rcBridgeFdbQosLevel.name: rcBridgeFdbQosLevel
rcBridgeFdbQosLevel.description: Used to indicate the qos level of the incoming frames with this destination Mac Address.

rcBridgeFdbSmltRemote.name: rcBridgeFdbSmltRemote
rcBridgeFdbSmltRemote.description: A MAC address indicate for remote learnt, either local or remote.

rcBridgeFdbTblSize.name: rcBridgeFdbTblSize
rcBridgeFdbTblSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the bridge forwarding database table.

rcBridgeStaticTable.name: rcBridgeStaticTable
rcBridgeStaticTable.description: This table is a proprietary replacement to the standard dot1dStaticTable in rfc1493.

rcBridgeStaticEntry.name: rcBridgeStaticEntry
rcBridgeStaticEntry.description: A table containing forwarding information about unicast entries configured into the bridge by management. This information is used by the transparent bridging function in determining how to propagate a received frame.

rcBridgeStaticAddress.name: rcBridgeStaticAddress
rcBridgeStaticAddress.description: The MAC address of this entry.

rcBridgeStaticPort.name: rcBridgeStaticPort
rcBridgeStaticPort.description: Port on which the MAC address is found.

rcBridgeStaticMonitor.name: rcBridgeStaticMonitor
rcBridgeStaticMonitor.description: Used to indicate whether monitoring should be performed on incoming packets that match this entry.

rcBridgeStaticPriority.name: rcBridgeStaticPriority
rcBridgeStaticPriority.description: Used to indicate forwarding priority of incoming packets that match this entry.

rcBridgeStaticStatus.name: rcBridgeStaticStatus
rcBridgeStaticStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. The default value is permanent(3).

rcBridgeStaticQosLevel.name: rcBridgeStaticQosLevel
rcBridgeStaticQosLevel.description: Used to indicate the qos level.

rcBridgeStaticTblSize.name: rcBridgeStaticTblSize
rcBridgeStaticTblSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the bridge static table.

rcBridgeFilterTable.name: rcBridgeFilterTable
rcBridgeFilterTable.description: This table is a proprietary replacement to the standard dot1dStaticTable (Filtering information) in rfc1493.

rcBridgeFilterEntry.name: rcBridgeFilterEntry
rcBridgeFilterEntry.description: A table containing filtering information configured into the bridge by management specifying a dest- ination address on a specific port and a set of incoming ports. Frames received from one of the incoming ports and containing the specific destination addresses are not allowed to be forwarded.

rcBridgeFilterAddress.name: rcBridgeFilterAddress
rcBridgeFilterAddress.description: The MAC address of this entry. This address is used to match the destination address of incoming packets.

rcBridgeFilterPort.name: rcBridgeFilterPort
rcBridgeFilterPort.description: Port on which this MAC address is found.

rcBridgeFilterNotAllowedFrom.name: rcBridgeFilterNotAllowedFrom
rcBridgeFilterNotAllowedFrom.description: Used to indicate a set of ports. Traffic arriving on any of the specified ports is not forwarded to this MAC address.

rcBridgeFilterStatus.name: rcBridgeFilterStatus
rcBridgeFilterStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. The default value is permanent(3).

rcBridgeFilterPcap.name: rcBridgeFilterPcap
rcBridgeFilterPcap.description: To enable pcap for the fdb-filter

rcBridgeFilterDestDiscard.name: rcBridgeFilterDestDiscard
rcBridgeFilterDestDiscard.description: Used to indicate a set of ports. Traffic arriving on any of the specified ports from this MAC address.

rcBridgeFilterSrcDiscard.name: rcBridgeFilterSrcDiscard
rcBridgeFilterSrcDiscard.description: Used to indicate a set of ports. Traffic arriving on any of the specified ports is not forwarded to this MAC address.

rcBridgeFilterTblSize.name: rcBridgeFilterTblSize
rcBridgeFilterTblSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the bridge filter table.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardTable.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardTable
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardTable.description: This table is used to configure the 'unknown mac discard' feature. This feature applies to layer 2 and layer 3 packets coming from or going out to a specific physical port.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardEntry.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardEntry
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardEntry.description: A table containing information configuring the 'unknown mac discard' feature.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardIfIndex.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardIfIndex
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardIfIndex.description: Port on which this 'unknown mac discard' configuration applied to.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardAutoLearnEnable.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardAutoLearnEnable
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardAutoLearnEnable.description: This variable is used to enable/disable the auto-learn capability of a specific port. The default value is auto-learn disabled.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardAutoLearnMode.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardAutoLearnMode
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardAutoLearnMode.description: This variable is used to control the auto-learn mode to either one-shot or continuous. In one-shot mode, the first n MAC addresses will be learned. The number n is dependents on the system's available resource. In continuous mode, MAC address is continuous learned until the resource limit is reached. After that the subsequent MAC will be disallowed until one of the original learned MAC is aged out. The default value is one-shot mode.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardAutoLearnTableM.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardAutoLearnTableMode
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardAutoLearnTableM.description: This MIB variable is used to lock or unlock the auto-learn MAC table. When the auto-learn table is lock neither new MAC will be learned nor the original learned MAC will be aged out. User needs to lock the auto-learn table before MAC addresses can be save to the NVRAM. The whole auto-learn table will be flushed when the setting change from lock to unlock mode. The default value is unlock mode.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardLogViolations.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardLogViolations
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardLogViolations.description: This variable controls the logging action that the system will take when a MAC address violation event was detected. The value 'enable' means a log record will be written to the system log file when a violation event was detected. The default value is enable.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardSendTrap.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardSendTrap
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardSendTrap.description: This variable controls the send trap action that system will take when a MAC address violation event was detected. The value 'enable' means a SNMP trap packet will be send to the management station when a violation event was detected. The default value is disable.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardDisablePort.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardDisablePort
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardDisablePort.description: This variable controls the 'disable-port' action that system will take when a MAC address violation event was detected. The value 'enable' means the specific port will be disabled when the violation event was detected. It needs user manually to bring the port back once it was disabled. The default value is disable.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardDefaultAutoLear.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardDefaultAutoLearnMonitor
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardDefaultAutoLear.description: This variable controls the default monitor setting of an auto-learn MAC address. The value 'monitor' means a copy of packet that send from or to the auto-learned MAC address will be forwarded to the designated monitoring port on the system. The default value is none.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardDefaultAutoLear.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardDefaultAutoLearnPriority
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardDefaultAutoLear.description: This variable controls the default priority setting of an auto-learn MAC address. The value 'low' means packets send from the MAC address is forwarded at low priority. The value 'high' means packets send from the MAC address is forwarded at high priority. The default value is low.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardMacCountMax.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardMacCountMax
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardMacCountMax.description: This variable represents the maxium number of MACc that can be added to some port.

rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardMacCountCur.name: rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardMacCountCur
rcBridgeUnknownMacDiscardMacCountCur.description: This variable represents the current number of MACs that have been added to some port.

rcBridgeManualEditTable.name: rcBridgeManualEditTable
rcBridgeManualEditTable.description: This table is used to specify what MAC addresses can be learned on each port.

rcBridgeManualEditEntry.name: rcBridgeManualEditEntry
rcBridgeManualEditEntry.description: A table containing information of MAC addresses that can be learned.

rcBridgeManualEditAddress.name: rcBridgeManualEditAddress
rcBridgeManualEditAddress.description: This variable contains the source MAC address of an entry.

rcBridgeManualEditPorts.name: rcBridgeManualEditPorts
rcBridgeManualEditPorts.description: This variable contains the allowed ports on which the MAC address of this entry can be learned.

rcBridgeManualEditMonitor.name: rcBridgeManualEditMonitor
rcBridgeManualEditMonitor.description: This variable specifies the monitoring setting of the MAC address. The value 'true' means a copy of packet frame that send from or to the MAC address is forwarded to the designated monitoring port on the system. The default value is false.

rcBridgeManualEditPriority.name: rcBridgeManualEditPriority
rcBridgeManualEditPriority.description: This variable specifies the priority setting of the MAC address. The value 'low' means packet frames send from the MAC address is forwarded at low priority. The default value is low.

rcBridgeManualEditStatus.name: rcBridgeManualEditStatus
rcBridgeManualEditStatus.description: The variable controls the status of a MAC address in the table. The value 'active' is used to add the MAC address entry into the table. The value 'invalid' is used to delete the MAC address from the table.

rcBridgeManualEditTblSize.name: rcBridgeManualEditTblSize
rcBridgeManualEditTblSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the manual edit table.

rcBridgeAutoLearnTable.name: rcBridgeAutoLearnTable
rcBridgeAutoLearnTable.description: This table contains information of auto-learned MAC address when the 'unknow MAC discard' table's auto-learn is enabled. User must explicitly lock and save the table into NVRAM in order to have this table has the same configuration cross the system reset.

rcBridgeAutoLearnEntry.name: rcBridgeAutoLearnEntry
rcBridgeAutoLearnEntry.description: Entries in this table are created automatically when the user explicitly does a lock operation on the auto-learn-table (i.e., when 'AutoLearnTableMode' is set to lock(2)).

rcBridgeAutoLearnAddress.name: rcBridgeAutoLearnAddress
rcBridgeAutoLearnAddress.description: This variable contains the source MAC address of the entries.

rcBridgeAutoLearnPort.name: rcBridgeAutoLearnPort
rcBridgeAutoLearnPort.description: This variable contains the port where the MAC address was learned.

rcBridgeAutoLearnMonitor.name: rcBridgeAutoLearnMonitor
rcBridgeAutoLearnMonitor.description: This variable contains the monitor setting of the MAC address. The value 'true' means a copy of packet frame that send from or to the MAC address is forwarded to the designated monitoring port on the system. This value should be synchronized with the setting of 'unknow MAC discard' table's 'Default AutoLearnMonitor' setting when the MAC address was learned.

rcBridgeAutoLearnPriority.name: rcBridgeAutoLearnPriority
rcBridgeAutoLearnPriority.description: This variable contains the priority setting of the MAC address. The value 'low' means packet frames send from the MAC address is forwarded at low priority. The value 'high' means packet frames send from the MAC address is forwarded at high priority. This value should be synchronized with the setting of 'unknow MAC discard' table's 'DefaultAutoLearnPriority' setting when the MAC address was learned.

rcBridgeAutoLearnAction.name: rcBridgeAutoLearnAction
rcBridgeAutoLearnAction.description: This variable is for converting an auto-learned MAC address entry to a manual edit MAC address entry. This variable provides a mechanism for user to move a MAC address entry from auto-learn table to manual edit table.

rcBridgeAutoLearnTblSize.name: rcBridgeAutoLearnTblSize
rcBridgeAutoLearnTblSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the auto learn table.

rcBridgeStaticMulticastMltIds.name: rcBridgeStaticMulticastMltIds
rcBridgeStaticMulticastMltIds.description: list of mlts this mac will be forwarded on

rcBridgeStaticMulticastTblSize.name: rcBridgeStaticMulticastTblSize
rcBridgeStaticMulticastTblSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the static multicast table.

rcRateLimitIfAllowedRate.name: rcRateLimitIfAllowedRate
rcRateLimitIfAllowedRate.description: Allowed traffic rate. If chassis type is 8100.

rcRateLimitIfEnable.name: rcRateLimitIfEnable
rcRateLimitIfEnable.description: Turn on/off rate limiting on this interface.

rcRateLimitIfAllowedRatePps.name: rcRateLimitIfAllowedRatePps
rcRateLimitIfAllowedRatePps.description: Allowed traffic rate packets per second. If chassis type is 8600/8800.

rcRateLimitIfAllowedRateKbps.name: rcRateLimitIfAllowedRateKbps
rcRateLimitIfAllowedRateKbps.description: Allowed traffic rate Kbits per second. If chassis type is R-module.

rcBridgeStaticMcastMltIds.name: rcBridgeStaticMcastMltIds
rcBridgeStaticMcastMltIds.description: list of mlts this mac will be forwarded on

rcBridgeFdbProtectTable.name: rcBridgeFdbProtectTable
rcBridgeFdbProtectTable.description: This table gives information about the mac learning limits on a particular port.

rcBridgeFdbProtectEntry.name: rcBridgeFdbProtectEntry
rcBridgeFdbProtectEntry.description: Information about a specific MAC address learning limits of a specific port.

rcBridgeFdbProtectPortNum.name: rcBridgeFdbProtectPortNum
rcBridgeFdbProtectPortNum.description: This object is the interface on which MAC address learning limit is applied.

rcBridgeFdbProtectMaxMacCount.name: rcBridgeFdbProtectMaxMacCount
rcBridgeFdbProtectMaxMacCount.description: Used to indicate maximum number of MAC address that can be learnt on the port.

rcBridgeFdbProtectMinMacCount.name: rcBridgeFdbProtectMinMacCount
rcBridgeFdbProtectMinMacCount.description: Used to indicate minimum number of MAC address learnt which mac address learning will be re-enabled on the port.

rcBridgeFdbProtectEnable.name: rcBridgeFdbProtectEnable
rcBridgeFdbProtectEnable.description: Used to enable or disable MAC learning limit feature on the port.

rcBridgeFdbProtectCurrentMacCount.name: rcBridgeFdbProtectCurrentMacCount
rcBridgeFdbProtectCurrentMacCount.description: This object indicates the current number of MAC address learnt on the port.

rcBridgeFdbProtectMacLearning.name: rcBridgeFdbProtectMacLearning
rcBridgeFdbProtectMacLearning.description: This object indicates whether the port can currrently learn new MAC addresses or not.

rcBridgeFdbProtectViolationLogTrap.name: rcBridgeFdbProtectViolationLogTrap
rcBridgeFdbProtectViolationLogTrap.description: Used to enable or disable logging and sending of snmp trap, once MAC learning limit is reached for the port.

rcBridgeFdbProtectViolationDownPort.name: rcBridgeFdbProtectViolationDownPort
rcBridgeFdbProtectViolationDownPort.description: Used to enable or disable the action of disabling the port, once MAC learning limit is reached for the port.

rcBridgeNewFdbTable.name: rcBridgeNewFdbTable
rcBridgeNewFdbTable.description: This table is an replacement to the standard dot1dTpFdbTable in rfc1493.

rcBridgeNewFdbEntry.name: rcBridgeNewFdbEntry
rcBridgeNewFdbEntry.description: Information about a specific unicast MAC address for which the bridge has some forwarding information.

rcBridgeNewFdbStatus.name: rcBridgeNewFdbStatus
rcBridgeNewFdbStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

rcBridgeNewFdbAddress.name: rcBridgeNewFdbAddress
rcBridgeNewFdbAddress.description: A unicast MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

rcBridgeNewFdbPort.name: rcBridgeNewFdbPort
rcBridgeNewFdbPort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port on which a frame having a source address equal to the value of the corresponding instance of rcBridgeNewFdbAddress has been seen. A value of '0' indicates that the port number has not been learned but that the bridge does have some forwarding/filtering information about this address (e.g. in the dot1dStaticTable). Implementors are encouraged to assign the port value to this object whenever it is learned even for addresses for which the corresponding value of rcBridgeNewFdbStatus is not learned(3).

rcBridgeNewFdbMonitor.name: rcBridgeNewFdbMonitor
rcBridgeNewFdbMonitor.description: Used to indicate whether monitoring should be performed on this unicast MAC address. If monitoring is enabled, any packet received with a matching destination MAC address will be forwarded to the port configured to receive monitor traffic.

rcBridgeNewFdbQosLevel.name: rcBridgeNewFdbQosLevel
rcBridgeNewFdbQosLevel.description: Used to indicate the qos level of the incoming frames with this destination Mac Address.

rcBridgeNewFdbSmltRemote.name: rcBridgeNewFdbSmltRemote
rcBridgeNewFdbSmltRemote.description: A MAC address indicate for remote learnt, either local or remote.

rcBridgeNewFdbVlanId.name: rcBridgeNewFdbVlanId
rcBridgeNewFdbVlanId.description: Used to indicate the Vlan ID for this MAC address.

rcBridgeRemoteMacTable.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacTable
rcBridgeRemoteMacTable.description: This table is for PLSB cvlan UNI remote mac entries

rcBridgeRemoteMacEntry.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacEntry
rcBridgeRemoteMacEntry.description: Information about a specific cvlan UNI remote MAC address for which the bridge has the forwarding information.

rcBridgeRemoteMacVlanId.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacVlanId
rcBridgeRemoteMacVlanId.description: Used to indicate the Vlan ID for this MAC address.

rcBridgeRemoteMacAddr.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacAddr
rcBridgeRemoteMacAddr.description: A customer MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

rcBridgeRemoteMacStatus.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacStatus
rcBridgeRemoteMacStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

rcBridgeRemoteMacDestAddr.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacDestAddr
rcBridgeRemoteMacDestAddr.description: A provider MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

rcBridgeRemoteMacPrimaryBVlanId.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacPrimaryBVlanId
rcBridgeRemoteMacPrimaryBVlanId.description: Used to indicate the BVlan ID for this MAC address.

rcBridgeRemoteMacPrimaryDestSysName.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacPrimaryDestSysName
rcBridgeRemoteMacPrimaryDestSysName.description: Primary System name of the node where MAC address entry come from.

rcBridgeRemoteMacPrimaryPort.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacPrimaryPort
rcBridgeRemoteMacPrimaryPort.description: Either the value '0', or the primary port on which a frame came from.

rcBridgeRemoteMacSecondaryBVlanId.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacSecondaryBVlanId
rcBridgeRemoteMacSecondaryBVlanId.description: Used to indicate the BVlan ID for this MAC address.

rcBridgeRemoteMacSecondaryDestSysName.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacSecondaryDestSysName
rcBridgeRemoteMacSecondaryDestSysName.description: Secondary System name of the node where MAC address entry come from.

rcBridgeRemoteMacSecondaryPort.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacSecondaryPort
rcBridgeRemoteMacSecondaryPort.description: Either the value '0', or the secondary port on which a frame came from.

rcBridgeRemoteMacSmltRemote.name: rcBridgeRemoteMacSmltRemote
rcBridgeRemoteMacSmltRemote.description: A MAC address indicate for remote learnt from ist peer

rcBootFlashSwVersion.name: rcBootFlashSwVersion
rcBootFlashSwVersion.description: BootFlashSwVersion indicates the software version in the Flash.

rcBootPcmciaSwVersion.name: rcBootPcmciaSwVersion
rcBootPcmciaSwVersion.description: BootPcmciaSwVersion indicate the software version in the Pcmcia card.

rcBootLastBootSource.name: rcBootLastBootSource
rcBootLastBootSource.description: Indicates the boot source of the last the system boot.

rcBootPrimary.name: rcBootPrimary
rcBootPrimary.description: BootPrimary is indicator for the primary source to boot the system.

rcBootSecondary.name: rcBootSecondary
rcBootSecondary.description: BootSecondary indicates the second choice of the boot source.

rcBootTertiary.name: rcBootTertiary
rcBootTertiary.description: BootTertiary indicates the third choice of boot source.

rcDeviceLastBootSource.name: rcDeviceLastBootSource
rcDeviceLastBootSource.description: Used to indicate the source of the software image the system was last booted with.

rcDevicePrimarySource.name: rcDevicePrimarySource
rcDevicePrimarySource.description: Used to indicate the primary choice to get a system software image.

rcDevicePrimarySourceFileName.name: rcDevicePrimarySourceFileName
rcDevicePrimarySourceFileName.description: Used to indicate a file number, if applicable.

rcDeviceSecondarySource.name: rcDeviceSecondarySource
rcDeviceSecondarySource.description: Used to indicate the secondary choice to get a system software image.

rcDeviceSecondarySourceFileName.name: rcDeviceSecondarySourceFileName
rcDeviceSecondarySourceFileName.description: Used to indicate a file name, if applicable.

rcDeviceTertiarySource.name: rcDeviceTertiarySource
rcDeviceTertiarySource.description: Used to indicate the tertiary choice to get a system software image.

rcDeviceTertiarySourceFileName.name: rcDeviceTertiarySourceFileName
rcDeviceTertiarySourceFileName.description: Used to indicate a file name, if applicable.

rcDeviceConfigSource.name: rcDeviceConfigSource
rcDeviceConfigSource.description: Used to indicate the location to get a system configuration file during system boot.

rcDeviceConfigSourceFileName.name: rcDeviceConfigSourceFileName
rcDeviceConfigSourceFileName.description: Used to indicate a file name, if applicable.

rcDeviceFlashBytesUsed.name: rcDeviceFlashBytesUsed
rcDeviceFlashBytesUsed.description: Used to indicate the number of bytes used in the system's configuration flash device.

rcDeviceFlashBytesFree.name: rcDeviceFlashBytesFree
rcDeviceFlashBytesFree.description: Used to indicate the number of bytes available in the system's configuration flash device.

rcDevicePcmciaBytesUsed.name: rcDevicePcmciaBytesUsed
rcDevicePcmciaBytesUsed.description: Used to indicate the number of bytes used in the system's PCMCIA device.

rcDevicePcmciaBytesFree.name: rcDevicePcmciaBytesFree
rcDevicePcmciaBytesFree.description: Used to indicate the number of bytes available in the system's PCMCIA device.

rcDeviceAction.name: rcDeviceAction
rcDeviceAction.description: Used to specify a particular action to perform on one of the system's device.

rcDeviceResult.name: rcDeviceResult
rcDeviceResult.description: Used to indicate the result of the last action performed on one of the system's device.

rcDeviceFlashNumFiles.name: rcDeviceFlashNumFiles
rcDeviceFlashNumFiles.description: Used to indicate the number of files available in the system's configuration flash device.

rcDevicePcmciaNumFiles.name: rcDevicePcmciaNumFiles
rcDevicePcmciaNumFiles.description: Used to indicate the number of files available in the system's PCMCIA device.

rcDeviceFlashEntry.name: rcDeviceFlashEntry
rcDeviceFlashEntry.description: An entry in the system's flash table.

rcDeviceFlashFileNum.name: rcDeviceFlashFileNum
rcDeviceFlashFileNum.description: Used to indicate a particular file in flash.

rcDeviceFlashFileName.name: rcDeviceFlashFileName
rcDeviceFlashFileName.description: Used to indicate a flash file's name.

rcDeviceFlashFileVersion.name: rcDeviceFlashFileVersion
rcDeviceFlashFileVersion.description: Used to indicate the flash file's version.

rcDeviceFlashFileType.name: rcDeviceFlashFileType
rcDeviceFlashFileType.description: Used to indicate the flash file's type.

rcDeviceFlashFileMode.name: rcDeviceFlashFileMode
rcDeviceFlashFileMode.description: Used to indicate the flash file's mode.

rcDeviceFlashFileSize.name: rcDeviceFlashFileSize
rcDeviceFlashFileSize.description: Used to indicate the flash file's size.

rcDeviceFlashFileCrc.name: rcDeviceFlashFileCrc
rcDeviceFlashFileCrc.description: Used to indicate the flash file's CRC.

rcDeviceFlashFileStatus.name: rcDeviceFlashFileStatus
rcDeviceFlashFileStatus.description: Used to indicate the flash file's status. A file that has been marked for deletion, but who's space has not been reclaimed yet is marked as 'deleted'.

rcDevicePcmciaEntry.name: rcDevicePcmciaEntry
rcDevicePcmciaEntry.description: An entry in the system's PCMCIA table.

rcDevicePcmciaFileNum.name: rcDevicePcmciaFileNum
rcDevicePcmciaFileNum.description: Used to indicate a particular file in PCMCIA.

rcDevicePcmciaFileName.name: rcDevicePcmciaFileName
rcDevicePcmciaFileName.description: Used to indicate the PCMCIA file's name.

rcDevicePcmciaFileVersion.name: rcDevicePcmciaFileVersion
rcDevicePcmciaFileVersion.description: Used to indicate the PCMCIA file's version.

rcDevicePcmciaFileType.name: rcDevicePcmciaFileType
rcDevicePcmciaFileType.description: Used to indicate the PCMCIA file's type.

rcDevicePcmciaFileMode.name: rcDevicePcmciaFileMode
rcDevicePcmciaFileMode.description: Used to indicate a particular file in mode.

rcDevicePcmciaFileSize.name: rcDevicePcmciaFileSize
rcDevicePcmciaFileSize.description: Used to indicate the PCMCIA file's size.

rcDevicePcmciaFileCrc.name: rcDevicePcmciaFileCrc
rcDevicePcmciaFileCrc.description: Used to indicate the PCMCIA file's CRC.

rcDevicePcmciaFileStatus.name: rcDevicePcmciaFileStatus
rcDevicePcmciaFileStatus.description: Used to indicate the PCMCIA file's status. A file that has been marked for deletion, but who's space has not been reclaimed yet is marked as 'deleted'.

rcMltNumMlts.name: rcMltNumMlts
rcMltNumMlts.description: The number of MLTs currently defined in the switch.

rcMltPotentialMembers.name: rcMltPotentialMembers
rcMltPotentialMembers.description: The set of ports that are not members of any MLT.

rcMltTable.name: rcMltTable
rcMltTable.description: A list of Multi-Link Trunk entries. The number of entries is given by rcMltNumMlts.

rcMltEntry.name: rcMltEntry
rcMltEntry.description: Entry containing configuration information for a particular Multi-Link Trunk.

rcMltId.name: rcMltId
rcMltId.description: A value that uniquely identifies the Multi-Link Trunk associated with this entry.

rcMltName.name: rcMltName
rcMltName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this MLT.

rcMltPortMembers.name: rcMltPortMembers
rcMltPortMembers.description: The set of ports that are members of this MLT.

rcMltPortType.name: rcMltPortType
rcMltPortType.description: The type of MLT port: access(1) or trunk(2).

rcMltNumVlanIds.name: rcMltNumVlanIds
rcMltNumVlanIds.description: Used to indicate the number of VLAN IDs that are stored in the rcMltVlanIds variable.

rcMltVlanIds.name: rcMltVlanIds
rcMltVlanIds.description: An array used to identify which VLANs this MLT is associated with. Each VLAN ID is stored as a two octet value. The first octet in the pair holds bits 15-8 of the VLAN ID, while the second octet holds bits 7-0 of the VLAN ID. This object is now replaced by rcMltVlanIdList.

rcMltRowStatus.name: rcMltRowStatus
rcMltRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the rcMltTable.

rcMltDistributionAlgorithm.name: rcMltDistributionAlgorithm
rcMltDistributionAlgorithm.description: none(1), ... It will be fill later

rcMltIfIndex.name: rcMltIfIndex
rcMltIfIndex.description: Used to indicate the 'logical' ifIndex assigned to this MLT.

rcMltAggregatable.name: rcMltAggregatable
rcMltAggregatable.description: Enable/Disable link aggregation on a MLT.

rcMltClearLinkAggregate.name: rcMltClearLinkAggregate
rcMltClearLinkAggregate.description: clear link aggregate, equivalent to disable and re-enable aggregatable on the MLT.

rcMltNtStgEnable.name: rcMltNtStgEnable
rcMltNtStgEnable.description: Indicates whether this MLT is operating in Nortel Mode or in Cisco Mode. true = Nortel Mode false = Cisco Mode.

rcMltDesignatedPort.name: rcMltDesignatedPort
rcMltDesignatedPort.description: Indicates the Designated port for the MLT.

rcMltAggOperState.name: rcMltAggOperState
rcMltAggOperState.description: Link aggregation state on a MLT.

rcMltAggTimeOfLastOperChange.name: rcMltAggTimeOfLastOperChange
rcMltAggTimeOfLastOperChange.description: The time value since the interface entered its current operational state.

rcMltAggMinLink.name: rcMltAggMinLink
rcMltAggMinLink.description: If number of active links goes below configured minimum-link number, the entire LAG is declared down.

rcMltVlanIdList.name: rcMltVlanIdList
rcMltVlanIdList.description: This bitfield is used to identify which VLANs this MLT is associated with. Each VLAN ID is stored as a bit. The most-significant (left-most) bit represents Vlan Id 1.

rcMltMcastDistributionEnable.name: rcMltMcastDistributionEnable
rcMltMcastDistributionEnable.description: Used to enable/disable this feature to distribute multicast traffic on MLT ports. All the cards in the system must be E-Tickets. Cannot perform distribution in a mixed mode.

rcMltMcastDistributionGrpMask.name: rcMltMcastDistributionGrpMask
rcMltMcastDistributionGrpMask.description: Group Mask. Create a MLT abstraction layer to distribute traffic basd on (source, group) information of the multicast packet. The algorithm to pick the actual port nedds to generate a fairly random number for different combinations but a lways generate the same number for a given (source, group) pair.
