By default, the number of active ports of the MLT is used to MOD the pseudo-random number generated by the XOR of each byte of the masked group address with the masked source address.

rcMltAggTrapEvent.name: rcMltAggTrapEvent
rcMltAggTrapEvent.description: It indicates three trap events: local down(1), remote down(2), up(3).

rcMltIstStpEnable.name: rcMltIstStpEnable
rcMltIstStpEnable.description: Used to enable/disable mlt ist stp functionality.

rcSltPortEntry.name: rcSltPortEntry
rcSltPortEntry.description: Entry containing configuration information for a particular Multi-Link Trunk.

rcSltPortSmltId.name: rcSltPortSmltId
rcSltPortSmltId.description: A uniquely identifies the Single-Link Trunk associated with this entry.

rcSltPortOperType.name: rcSltPortOperType
rcSltPortOperType.description: The current operate type of the port normal or smlt.

rcSltPortRowStatus.name: rcSltPortRowStatus
rcSltPortRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries of the Table.

rcWebEnableServer.name: rcWebEnableServer
rcWebEnableServer.description: Control whether the web server should be enabled. Setting this variable to true will make the server operational. Setting this variable to false will disable server.

rcWebRWAUserName.name: rcWebRWAUserName
rcWebRWAUserName.description: User name for the read-write-all web-server account.

rcWebRWAPassword.name: rcWebRWAPassword
rcWebRWAPassword.description: Password for the read-write-all web-server account.

rcWebRWUserName.name: rcWebRWUserName
rcWebRWUserName.description: User name for the read-write web-server account.

rcWebRWPassword.name: rcWebRWPassword
rcWebRWPassword.description: Password for the read-write web-server account.

rcWebROUserName.name: rcWebROUserName
rcWebROUserName.description: User name for the read-only web-server account.

rcWebROPassword.name: rcWebROPassword
rcWebROPassword.description: Password for the read-only web-server account.

rcWebLastChange.name: rcWebLastChange
rcWebLastChange.description: Last web-browser initiated configuration change since sysUpTime.

rcWebNumHits.name: rcWebNumHits
rcWebNumHits.description: Number of hits to the web-server

rcWebNumAccessChecks.name: rcWebNumAccessChecks
rcWebNumAccessChecks.description: Number of access checks performed by the web-server

rcWebNumAccessBlocks.name: rcWebNumAccessBlocks
rcWebNumAccessBlocks.description: Number of accesses blocked by the web-server

rcWebNumRxErrors.name: rcWebNumRxErrors
rcWebNumRxErrors.description: Number of receive errors encountered by the web-server

rcWebNumTxErrors.name: rcWebNumTxErrors
rcWebNumTxErrors.description: Number of transmit errors encountered by the web-server

rcWebNumSetRequest.name: rcWebNumSetRequest
rcWebNumSetRequest.description: Number of set-request to the web-server

rcWebRWL3UserName.name: rcWebRWL3UserName
rcWebRWL3UserName.description: user name for the L3 web server account

rcWebRWL3Password.name: rcWebRWL3Password
rcWebRWL3Password.description: password for the L3 web server account

rcWebRWL2UserName.name: rcWebRWL2UserName
rcWebRWL2UserName.description: user name for the L2 web server account

rcWebRWL2Password.name: rcWebRWL2Password
rcWebRWL2Password.description: password for the L2 web server account

rcWebDefaultDisplayRows.name: rcWebDefaultDisplayRows
rcWebDefaultDisplayRows.description: default display rows in html page.

rcWebHelpTftpSourceDir.name: rcWebHelpTftpSourceDir
rcWebHelpTftpSourceDir.description: tftp source directory for help files

rcWebHttpPort.name: rcWebHttpPort
rcWebHttpPort.description: the HTTP port for web access

rcWebSecureOnly.name: rcWebSecureOnly
rcWebSecureOnly.description: Control whether the secure only should be enabled. Setting this variable to true will make the server support HTTPS only. Setting this variable to false will make the server support both HTTP & HTTPS

rcWebHttpsPort.name: rcWebHttpsPort
rcWebHttpsPort.description: the HTTPs port for web access

rcCliRWAUserName.name: rcCliRWAUserName
rcCliRWAUserName.description: User name for the read-write-all CLI account.

rcCliRWAPassword.name: rcCliRWAPassword
rcCliRWAPassword.description: Password for the read-write-all CLI account.

rcCliRWUserName.name: rcCliRWUserName
rcCliRWUserName.description: User name for the read-write CLI account.

rcCliRWPassword.name: rcCliRWPassword
rcCliRWPassword.description: Password for the read-write CLI account.

rcCliRWL3UserName.name: rcCliRWL3UserName
rcCliRWL3UserName.description: User name for the read-write layer-3 CLI account.

rcCliRWL3Password.name: rcCliRWL3Password
rcCliRWL3Password.description: Password for the read-write layer-3 CLI account.

rcCliRWL2UserName.name: rcCliRWL2UserName
rcCliRWL2UserName.description: User name for the read-write layer-2 CLI account.

rcCliRWL2Password.name: rcCliRWL2Password
rcCliRWL2Password.description: Password for the read-write layer-2 CLI account.

rcCliROUserName.name: rcCliROUserName
rcCliROUserName.description: User name for the read-only CLI account.

rcCliROPassword.name: rcCliROPassword
rcCliROPassword.description: Password for the read-only CLI account.

rcCliMaxTelnetSessions.name: rcCliMaxTelnetSessions
rcCliMaxTelnetSessions.description: Used to indicate the maximum number of telnet sessions the system will support.

rcCliMaxRloginSessions.name: rcCliMaxRloginSessions
rcCliMaxRloginSessions.description: Used to indicate the maximum number of rlogin sessions the system will support.

rcCliTimeout.name: rcCliTimeout
rcCliTimeout.description: Used to indicate the amount of idle time, in seconds to wait before timing out telnet and rlogin sessions.

rcCliNumAccessViolations.name: rcCliNumAccessViolations
rcCliNumAccessViolations.description: Used to indicate the number of CLI access violations detected by the system.

rcCliRWL1UserName.name: rcCliRWL1UserName
rcCliRWL1UserName.description: User name for the read-write layer-1 CLI account.

rcCliRWL1Password.name: rcCliRWL1Password
rcCliRWL1Password.description: Password for the read-write layer-1 CLI account.

rcCliPasswordChange.name: rcCliPasswordChange
rcCliPasswordChange.description: Used to indication which password is changed when sending a rcCliPasswordChange trap.

rcCliPassChangeResult.name: rcCliPassChangeResult
rcCliPassChangeResult.description: Used to indication the result of changing password when sending a rcPasswordChange trap.

rcCliRWEnable.name: rcCliRWEnable
rcCliRWEnable.description: Enable/Disable for the read-write CLI account.

rcCliRWL1Enable.name: rcCliRWL1Enable
rcCliRWL1Enable.description: Enable/Disable for the read-write-layer1 CLI account.

rcCliRWL2Enable.name: rcCliRWL2Enable
rcCliRWL2Enable.description: Enable/Disable for the read-write-layer2 CLI account.

rcCliRWL3Enable.name: rcCliRWL3Enable
rcCliRWL3Enable.description: Enable/Disable for the read-write-layer3 CLI account.

rcCliROEnable.name: rcCliROEnable
rcCliROEnable.description: Enable/Disable for the read-only CLI account.

rcErrorLevel.name: rcErrorLevel
rcErrorLevel.description: Error level indicator for the last error reported in the system. The meaning of this value are : 0 = Informative Information 1 = Warning Condition 2 = Error Condition 3 = Manufacturing Information 4 = Fatal Condition

rcErrorCode.name: rcErrorCode
rcErrorCode.description: Error code indicator for the last error reported in the system. This is an encoded value that identifies the software module that generated the error message as well as a specific error condition within that module. This value is transparent to the user. This value is intended to help Accelar support and development staff to isolate system problems.

rcErrorText.name: rcErrorText
rcErrorText.description: Error string of the last error reported in the system.

IpAddressOriginTC.name: IpAddressOriginTC
IpAddressOriginTC.description: The origin of the address. manual(2) indicates that the address was manually configured to a specified address, e.g. by user configuration. dhcp(4) indicates an address that was assigned to this system by a DHCP server. linklayer(5) indicates an address created by IPv6 stateless auto-configuration. random(6) indicates an address chosen by the system at random, e.g. an IPv4 address within 169.254/16, or an RFC 3041 privacy address.

IpAddressStatusTC.name: IpAddressStatusTC
IpAddressStatusTC.description: The status of an address. Most of the states correspond to states from the IPv6 Stateless Address Autoconfiguration protocol [5]. The preferred(1) state indicates that this is a valid address that can appear as the destination or source address of a packet. The deprecated(2) state indicates that this is a valid but deprecated address that should no longer be used as a source address in new communications, but packets addressed to such an address are processed as expected. The invalid(3) state indicates that this isn't a valid address and it shouldn't appear as the destination or source address of a packet. The inaccessible(4) state indicates that the address is not accessible because the interface to which this address is assigned is not operational. The unknown(5) state indicates that the status can not be determined for some reason. The tentative(6) state indicates the uniqueness of the address on the link is being verified. Addresses in this state should not be used for general communication and should only be used to determine the uniqueness of the address. The duplicate(7) state indicates the address has been determined to be non-unique on the link and so must not be used. In the absence of other information, an IPv4 address is always preferred(1).

rcIpv6IcmpErrorInterval.name: rcIpv6IcmpErrorInterval
rcIpv6IcmpErrorInterval.description: The rate (in milliseconds) at which ICMP error messages can be sent out. A value of zero means not be send any.

rcIpv6MulticastAdminStatus.name: rcIpv6MulticastAdminStatus
rcIpv6MulticastAdminStatus.description: This indicates the global admin status for multicast.

rcIpv6IcmpNetUnreach.name: rcIpv6IcmpNetUnreach
rcIpv6IcmpNetUnreach.description: Used to set icmp net unreach feature enable/ disable.

rcIpv6IcmpRedirectMsg.name: rcIpv6IcmpRedirectMsg
rcIpv6IcmpRedirectMsg.description: Used to set icmp redirect feature enable/ disable.

rcIpv6IcmpErrorQuota.name: rcIpv6IcmpErrorQuota
rcIpv6IcmpErrorQuota.description: The number of icmp error messages that can be sent during the icmp error interval. A value of zero means not be send any.

rcIpv6InterfaceTable.name: rcIpv6InterfaceTable
rcIpv6InterfaceTable.description: This table contains list of IPv6 interfaces and per-interface IPv6-specific information.

rcIpv6InterfaceEntry.name: rcIpv6InterfaceEntry
rcIpv6InterfaceEntry.description: An entry of ipv6 interface In Table containing per-interface information.

rcIpv6InterfaceIfIndex.name: rcIpv6InterfaceIfIndex
rcIpv6InterfaceIfIndex.description: An unique value to identify a physical interface or a logical interface (VLAN). For the brouter port it is the ifindex of the port and in the case of the vlan it is the ifindex of the vlan.

rcIpv6InterfaceIdentifier.name: rcIpv6InterfaceIdentifier
rcIpv6InterfaceIdentifier.description: IPv6 address interface identifiers. This is a binary string of up to 8 octets in network byte-order.

rcIpv6InterfaceIdentifierLength.name: rcIpv6InterfaceIdentifierLength
rcIpv6InterfaceIdentifierLength.description: The length of the Interface Identifier in bits.

rcIpv6InterfaceDescr.name: rcIpv6InterfaceDescr
rcIpv6InterfaceDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string may be set by network management system.

rcIpv6InterfaceVlanId.name: rcIpv6InterfaceVlanId
rcIpv6InterfaceVlanId.description: A value that uniquely identifies the Virtual LAN associated with this entry. This value corresponds to the lower 12 bits in the IEEE 802.1Q VLAN Tag.

rcIpv6InterfaceReasmMaxSize.name: rcIpv6InterfaceReasmMaxSize
rcIpv6InterfaceReasmMaxSize.description: MTU for this IPv6 interface, this value should be same for all the ip addresses defined on this interface.

rcIpv6InterfacePhysAddress.name: rcIpv6InterfacePhysAddress
rcIpv6InterfacePhysAddress.description: The media-dependent `physical' address, for the ethernet media it is the MAC address

rcIpv6InterfaceAdminStatus.name: rcIpv6InterfaceAdminStatus
rcIpv6InterfaceAdminStatus.description: The indication of whether IPv6 is enabled (up) or disabled (down) on this interface. This object does not affect the state of the interface itself, only its connection to an IPv6 stack.

rcIpv6InterfaceReachableTime.name: rcIpv6InterfaceReachableTime
rcIpv6InterfaceReachableTime.description: The time (in milliseconds) a neighbor is considered reachable after receiving a reachability confirmation. REFERENCE RFC2461, Section 6.3.2

rcIpv6InterfaceRetransmitTime.name: rcIpv6InterfaceRetransmitTime
rcIpv6InterfaceRetransmitTime.description: The time (in milliseconds) between retransmissions of Neighbor Solicitation messages to a neighbor when resolving the address or when probing the reachability of a neighbor. REFERENCE RFC2461, Section 6.3.2

rcIpv6InterfaceMulticastAdminStatus.name: rcIpv6InterfaceMulticastAdminStatus
rcIpv6InterfaceMulticastAdminStatus.description: This indicates the admin status for multicast for this interface.

rcIpv6InterfaceDhcpEnabled.name: rcIpv6InterfaceDhcpEnabled
rcIpv6InterfaceDhcpEnabled.description: Enable or disable DHCP on the specified interface.

rcIpv6InterfaceMacOffset.name: rcIpv6InterfaceMacOffset
rcIpv6InterfaceMacOffset.description: Used to request a particular MAC for an IPv6 VLAN. Analogous to rcIpAdEntMacOffset in rcIpAddrTable. The system has 512 mac addresses of which 0-507 are reserved for Boardwalk box. 508-511 is reserved for MG. One can either mention a mac offset while configuring IPv6 on a vlan or it can be alloted by the system within the above range.

rcIpv6AddressTable.name: rcIpv6AddressTable
rcIpv6AddressTable.description: This table contains addressing information relevant to the entity's interfaces. This table does not contain multicast address information. Tables for such information should be contained in multicast specific MIBs such as RFC3019. While this table is writable the user will note that several objects, such as rcIpv6AddressOrigin, are not. The intention in allowing a user to write to this table is to allow them to add or remove any entry that isn't permanent. The user should be allowed to modify objects and entries when that would not cause inconsistencies within the table. Allowing write access to objects such as rcIpv6AddressOrigin could allow a user to insert an entry and then label it incorrectly.

rcIpv6AddressEntry.name: rcIpv6AddressEntry
rcIpv6AddressEntry.description: An address mapping for a particular interface. Note that when an address is added to an interface the resulted prefix is added to that interface.

rcIpv6AddressIfIndex.name: rcIpv6AddressIfIndex
rcIpv6AddressIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of the IfIndex field in the rcIpv6InterfaceIfIndex.

rcIpv6AddressAddr.name: rcIpv6AddressAddr
rcIpv6AddressAddr.description: The IPv6 address to which this entry's addressing information pertains. This is one of the ipv6 addresses that this interface(identified by the rcIpv6AddressIfIndex) has. Implementors need to be aware that if the size of ipAddressAddr exceeds 116 octets then OIDS of instances of columns in this row will have more than 128 sub-identifiers and cannot be accessed using SNMPv1, SNMPv2c or SNMPv3.

rcIpv6AddressType.name: rcIpv6AddressType
rcIpv6AddressType.description: The type of address. It is either unicast or anycast IPv6 addresses (RFC3513).

rcIpv6AddressPrefixLength.name: rcIpv6AddressPrefixLength
rcIpv6AddressPrefixLength.description: Prefix Length value for this address. Cannot be changed after the creation. This field MUST be provided in order to create an entry in this table.

rcIpv6AddressPrefix.name: rcIpv6AddressPrefix
rcIpv6AddressPrefix.description: A pointer to the row in the prefix table to which this address belongs. May be { 0 0 } if there is no such row.

rcIpv6AddressOrigin.name: rcIpv6AddressOrigin
rcIpv6AddressOrigin.description: The origin of the address. The origin of the address, one of: other(1),manual(2), dhcp(4),linklayer(5), random(6)

rcIpv6AddressStatus.name: rcIpv6AddressStatus
rcIpv6AddressStatus.description: The status of the address, describing if the address can be used for communication. It will One of: preferred(1), deprecated(2),invalid(3),inaccessible(4),unknown(5), tentative(6), duplicate(7)

rcIpv6AddressCreated.name: rcIpv6AddressCreated
rcIpv6AddressCreated.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this entry was created. If this entry was created prior to the last re- initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

rcIpv6AddressLastChanged.name: rcIpv6AddressLastChanged
rcIpv6AddressLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this entry was last updated. If this entry was updated prior to the last re- initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

rcIpv6AddressRowStatus.name: rcIpv6AddressRowStatus
rcIpv6AddressRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. The RowStatus TC requires that this DESCRIPTION clause states under which circumstances other objects in this row can be modified. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified. A conceptual row can not be made active until the rcIpv6AddressIfIndex has been set to a valid index. Only createAndGo and Delete vlaues are supported.

rcIpv6PrefixTable.name: rcIpv6PrefixTable
rcIpv6PrefixTable.description: This table allows the user to determine the source of an IP address or set of IP addresses and allows other tables to share the information via pointer rather than by copying. For example when the node configures both a unicast and anycast address for a prefix the ipAddressPrefix objects for those addresses will point to a single row in this table. This table primarily provides support for IPv6 prefixes and several of the objects are less meaningful for IPv4. The table continues to allow IPv4 addresses to allow future flexibility. In order to promote a common configuration this document includes suggestions for default values for IPv4 prefixes. Each of these values may be overridden if an object is meaningful to the node. All prefixes used by this entity should be included in this table independent of how the entity learned the prefix. (This table isn't limited to prefixes learned from router advertisements.)

rcIpv6PrefixEntry.name: rcIpv6PrefixEntry
rcIpv6PrefixEntry.description: An entry of ipv6 prefix In the Table.

rcIpv6PrefixIfIndex.name: rcIpv6PrefixIfIndex
rcIpv6PrefixIfIndex.description: An unique value to identify an ipv6 interface. For the brouter port it is the ifindex of the port and in the case of the vlan it is the ifindex of the vlan.

rcIpv6PrefixAddr.name: rcIpv6PrefixAddr
rcIpv6PrefixAddr.description: Prefix to create an ipv6 address in ipv6 interface table.

rcIpv6PrefixLength.name: rcIpv6PrefixLength
rcIpv6PrefixLength.description: Mask to create an ipv6 prefix entry either will be advertised or suppressed

rcIpv6PrefixVlanId.name: rcIpv6PrefixVlanId
rcIpv6PrefixVlanId.description: A value that uniquely identifies the Virtual LAN associated with this entry. This value corresponds to the lower 12 bits in the IEEE 802.1Q VLAN Tag.

rcIpv6PrefixUseDefaultVal.name: rcIpv6PrefixUseDefaultVal
rcIpv6PrefixUseDefaultVal.description: Select one of the value to set/use it's value to default value. This is a bitmask field, setting all the bits means that all the options will be reverted to default values.

rcIpv6PrefixAtValidLife.name: rcIpv6PrefixAtValidLife
rcIpv6PrefixAtValidLife.description: Is the date and time, upon reaching this value the prefix will be expired, if configured this option will be included in the neighbor advertisement for this prefix.

rcIpv6PrefixAtPreferredLife.name: rcIpv6PrefixAtPreferredLife
rcIpv6PrefixAtPreferredLife.description: Is the date and time, upon reaching this value the prefix will be expired, if configured this option will be included in the neighbor advertisement for this prefix.

rcIpv6PrefixOnLinkFlag.name: rcIpv6PrefixOnLinkFlag
rcIpv6PrefixOnLinkFlag.description: if set then this prefix can be used for onlink determination. This value be placed in the L-bit field in the prefix information option. It is a 1 bit flag.

rcIpv6PrefixAutoFlag.name: rcIpv6PrefixAutoFlag
rcIpv6PrefixAutoFlag.description: if set then this prefix can be used for autonomous address config. This value be placed in the auto-flag field in the prefix information option. It is a 1 bit flag.

rcIpv6PrefixAddressEui.name: rcIpv6PrefixAddressEui
rcIpv6PrefixAddressEui.description: Use an EUI-64 interface ID in the low-order 64bits of the address when not specified in the address field. If enabled use EUI, otherwise use EUI-64 and complement U/L (Universal/Local bit). This operation should be allowed for both global and link local addresses. Once the entry is create cannot modify this field. This will be valid to use only when the PrefixLength is 64 or less

rcIpv6PrefixNoAdvertise.name: rcIpv6PrefixNoAdvertise
rcIpv6PrefixNoAdvertise.description: if set then this prefix can not be included in the neighbor advertisement.

rcIpv6PrefixValidLifetime.name: rcIpv6PrefixValidLifetime
rcIpv6PrefixValidLifetime.description: Valid lifetime in seconds, indicates how long this prefix advertised in the nbr advertisement is valid. Value of 4294967295 represents infinity.

rcIpv6PrefixPreferredLifetime.name: rcIpv6PrefixPreferredLifetime
rcIpv6PrefixPreferredLifetime.description: Preferred lifetime in seconds, indicates how long this prefix advertised in advertisemt for this prefix. Value of 4294967295 represents infinity.

rcIpv6RouterAdvertTable.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertTable
rcIpv6RouterAdvertTable.description: The table containing information used to construct router advertisements.

rcIpv6RouterAdvertEntry.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertEntry
rcIpv6RouterAdvertEntry.description: An entry containing information used to construct router advertisements.

rcIpv6RouterAdvertIfIndex.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertIfIndex
rcIpv6RouterAdvertIfIndex.description: An unique value to identify an ipv6 interface. For the brouter port it is the ifindex of the port and in the case of the vlan it is the ifindex of the vlan.

rcIpv6RouterAdvertSendAdverts.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertSendAdverts
rcIpv6RouterAdvertSendAdverts.description: A flag indicating whether or not the router sends periodic router advertisements and responds to router solicitations on this interface. REFERENCE RFC2461 Section 6.2.1

rcIpv6RouterAdvertUseDefaultVal.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertUseDefaultVal
rcIpv6RouterAdvertUseDefaultVal.description: Select one of the value to set/use it's value to default value, or set all the bits to indicate all the options will be set to their default value.

rcIpv6RouterAdvertMaxInterval.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertMaxInterval
rcIpv6RouterAdvertMaxInterval.description: Configure the max interval (in seconds) at which the transmission of route advertisments can occur on this interface. This must be no less than 4 seconds and no greater than 1800.

rcIpv6RouterAdvertMinInterval.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertMinInterval
rcIpv6RouterAdvertMinInterval.description: Configure the min interval (in seconds) at which the transmission of route advertisments can occur on this interface. This must be no less than 3 seconds and no greater than .75* max-interval.

rcIpv6RouterAdvertReachableTime.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertReachableTime
rcIpv6RouterAdvertReachableTime.description: The value (in milliseconds) to be placed in the router advertisement message sent by the router. The value zero means unspecified (by this router). Used to configure the amount of time that a remote IPv6 node is considered reachable after some reachability confirmation event has occured. REFERENCE RFC2461 Section 6.2.1

rcIpv6RouterAdvertRetransmitTimer.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertRetransmitTimer
rcIpv6RouterAdvertRetransmitTimer.description: The value (in milliseconds) to be placed in the retransmit timer field in router advertisement message sent from this interface. The value zero means unspecified (by this router). Used to configure the amount of time that router should wait for the transmit to occur. REFERENCE RFC2461 Section 6.2.1

rcIpv6RouterAdvertDefaultLifeTime.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertDefaultLifeTime
rcIpv6RouterAdvertDefaultLifeTime.description: The value to be placed in the router lifetime field of router advertisements sent from this interface. This value MUST be either 0 or between rcIpv6RouterAdvertMaxInterval and 9000 seconds. A value of zero indicates that the router is not to be used as a default router. The default is 3 * rcIpv6RouterAdvertMaxInterval. REFERENCE RFC2461 Section 6.2.1

rcIpv6RouterAdvertCurHopLimit.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertCurHopLimit
rcIpv6RouterAdvertCurHopLimit.description: The default value to be placed in the current hop limit field in router advertisements sent from this interface. The value should be set to the current diameter of the Internet. A value of zero in the router advertisement indicates that the advertisement isn't specifying a value for curHopLimit. The default should be set to the value specified in the IANA web pages (www.iana.org) at the time of implementation. REFERENCE RFC2461 Section 6.2.1

rcIpv6RouterAdvertManagedFlag.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertManagedFlag
rcIpv6RouterAdvertManagedFlag.description: if true then the M-bit(Managed address configureation) in the router adverisement will be set. REFERENCE RFC2461 Section 6.2.1

rcIpv6RouterAdvertOtherConfigFlag.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertOtherConfigFlag
rcIpv6RouterAdvertOtherConfigFlag.description: if true then the O-bit (Other stateful Configuration) in the router adverisement will be set. REFERENCE RFC2461 Section 6.2.1

rcIpv6RouterAdvertDadNsNum.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertDadNsNum
rcIpv6RouterAdvertDadNsNum.description: The number of neighbor solicitation messages for DAD (Duplicate address detection). A value 0 is used to disable DAD process on this interface. A value 1 is used to send one advertisment without any retransmissions.

rcIpv6RouterAdvertLinkMTU.name: rcIpv6RouterAdvertLinkMTU
rcIpv6RouterAdvertLinkMTU.description: The value to be placed in MTU options sent by the router on this interface. A value of zero indicates that no MTU options are sent. REFERENCE RFC2461 Section 6.2.1

rcIpv6StaticRouteTable.name: rcIpv6StaticRouteTable
rcIpv6StaticRouteTable.description: This table contains list of routes that are created by the user to destination networks.

rcIpv6StaticRouteEntry.name: rcIpv6StaticRouteEntry
rcIpv6StaticRouteEntry.description: An entry in the static route table for IPv6 can be created for a destination with a specific prefix length; multiple entries to the same destination are created either by specifying the next-hop or interfaceIndex or both to reach the destination. However if the nexthop Ipv6 address is a link-local address then IfIndex must be supplied.

rcIpv6StaticRouteDest.name: rcIpv6StaticRouteDest
rcIpv6StaticRouteDest.description: The destination IPv6 address of this route. The values for the index objects rcIpv6StaticRouteDest and rcIpv6StaticRoutePrefixLength must be consistent. When the value of rcIpv6StaticRouteDest (excluding the zone index, if one is present) is x, then the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the mask formed from the corresponding index object rcIpv6StaticRoutePrefixLength MUST be equal to x. If not, then the index pair is not consistent and an inconsistentName error must be returned on SET or CREATE requests.

rcIpv6StaticRoutePrefixLength.name: rcIpv6StaticRoutePrefixLength
rcIpv6StaticRoutePrefixLength.description: Indicates the number of leading one bits which form the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the rcIpv6StaticRouteDestAddr field.

rcIpv6StaticRouteNextHop.name: rcIpv6StaticRouteNextHop
rcIpv6StaticRouteNextHop.description: Next hop IPv6 address for this destination. On remote routes, the address of the next system en route. For non-remote routes, a zero length string.

rcIpv6StaticRouteIfIndex.name: rcIpv6StaticRouteIfIndex
rcIpv6StaticRouteIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. A value of 0 is valid and represents the scenario where no interface is specified.

rcIpv6StaticRouteDistance.name: rcIpv6StaticRouteDistance
rcIpv6StaticRouteDistance.description: cost/distance to reach the destination for this node.

rcIpv6StaticRouteStatus.name: rcIpv6StaticRouteStatus
rcIpv6StaticRouteStatus.description: (1)notReachable means the route is not reachable and no neighbor request entry is built to resolved the next-hop. It happens when there is no route or neighbor to reach the static route's next-hop. (2)tryToResolve means the route is not reachable but a neighbor request entry is built to resolved the next-hop. It happens when there is a local equivelent route in system to reach the next-hop but the neighor is not learnt yet (3)reachableNotInRtm means the static route is reachable but it is not in RTM. It happens when the static route is reachable, but it is not the best among alternative static route. (4)reachableInRtm means the static route is reachable and it is in RTM. It happens when the static route is reachable, and it is the best among alternative static route to be added into RTM.

rcIpv6StaticRoutePreference.name: rcIpv6StaticRoutePreference
rcIpv6StaticRoutePreference.description: Used to indicate the route preference of this entry. If there are more than one route that can be used to forward IP traffic, the route that has a highest preference will be used instead of a lower preference one. The higher the number, the higher the preference.

rcIpv6NetToPhysicalTable.name: rcIpv6NetToPhysicalTable
rcIpv6NetToPhysicalTable.description: The IP Address Translation table used for mapping from IP addresses to physical addresses. The Address Translation tables contain the IP address to 'physical' address equivalences. Some interfaces do not use translation tables for determining address equivalences (e.g., DDN-X.25 has an algorithmic method); if all interfaces are of this type, then the Address Translation table is empty, i.e., has zero entries. While many protocols may be used to populate this table, ARP [10] and Neighbor Discovery [4] are the most likely options.

rcIpv6NetToPhysicalEntry.name: rcIpv6NetToPhysicalEntry
rcIpv6NetToPhysicalEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP address to `physical' address equivalence.

rcIpv6NetToPhysicalIfIndex.name: rcIpv6NetToPhysicalIfIndex
rcIpv6NetToPhysicalIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of the IfIndex field in the rcIpv6InterfaceIfIndex.

rcIpv6NetToPhysicalNetAddress.name: rcIpv6NetToPhysicalNetAddress
rcIpv6NetToPhysicalNetAddress.description: The IP Address corresponding to the media-dependent `physical' address. The address type of this object is specified in rcIpv6NetToPhysicalAddressType. Implementors need to be aware that if the size of rcIpv6NetToPhysicalNetAddress exceeds 115 octets then OIDS of instances of columns in this row will have more than 128 sub-identifiers and cannot be accessed using SNMPv1, SNMPv2c or SNMPv3.

rcIpv6NetToPhysicalPhysAddress.name: rcIpv6NetToPhysicalPhysAddress
rcIpv6NetToPhysicalPhysAddress.description: The media-dependent `physical' address. As the entries in this table are typically not persistent when this object is written the entity SHOULD NOT save the change to non-volatile storage. In the ethernet case it is a MAC address.

rcIpv6NetToPhysicalInterface.name: rcIpv6NetToPhysicalInterface
rcIpv6NetToPhysicalInterface.description: The field represents either a physical port id or the MLT port id. This entry is associated either with a port or with a MLT in a VLAN/Brouter port. If the value is 0 then the interface is CP port.

rcIpv6NetToPhysicalLastUpdated.name: rcIpv6NetToPhysicalLastUpdated
rcIpv6NetToPhysicalLastUpdated.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this entry was last updated. If this entry was updated prior to the last re- initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

rcIpv6NetToPhysicalType.name: rcIpv6NetToPhysicalType
rcIpv6NetToPhysicalType.description: The type of mapping. The 'dynamic(2)' type indicates that the IP address to physical addresses mapping has been dynamically resolved using e.g. IPv4 ARP or the IPv6 Neighbor Discovery protocol. The 'static(3)' type indicates that the mapping has been statically configured. Both of these refer to entries that provide mappings for other entities addresses. The 'local(4)' type indicates that the mapping is provided for an entity's own interface address. As the entries in this table are typically not persistent when this object is written the entity SHOULD NOT save the change to non-volatile storage.

rcIpv6NetToPhysicalState.name: rcIpv6NetToPhysicalState
rcIpv6NetToPhysicalState.description: The Neighbor Unreachability Detection [4] state for the interface when the address mapping in this entry is used. If Neighbor Unreachability Detection is not in use (eg. for IPv4), this object is always unknown(6). REFERENCE RFC2461

rcIpv6NetToPhysicalRowStatus.name: rcIpv6NetToPhysicalRowStatus
rcIpv6NetToPhysicalRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. The RowStatus TC requires that this DESCRIPTION clause states under which circumstances other objects in this row can be modified. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified. A conceptual row can not be made active until the rcIpv6NetToPhysicalPhysAddress object has been set. Note that if the rcIpv6NetToPhysicalType is set to 'invalid' the managed node may delete the entry independent of the state of this object. Only createandGo and Delete operations are supported

rcIpv6PrefixListTableSize.name: rcIpv6PrefixListTableSize
rcIpv6PrefixListTableSize.description: Size of Ipv6 Prefix List Table

rcIpv6PrefixListEntry.name: rcIpv6PrefixListEntry
rcIpv6PrefixListEntry.description: An entry of Ipv6 Prefix List Table.

rcIpv6PrefixListId.name: rcIpv6PrefixListId
rcIpv6PrefixListId.description: Id of an IPv6 Prefix List

rcIpv6PrefixListPrefix.name: rcIpv6PrefixListPrefix
rcIpv6PrefixListPrefix.description: Is a member of a specific ipv6 prefix list. Adding the prefix to the given ipv6 prefix list

rcIpv6PrefixListPrefixMaskLen.name: rcIpv6PrefixListPrefixMaskLen
rcIpv6PrefixListPrefixMaskLen.description: Mask length of the ipv6 prefix added to the prefix list

rcIpv6PrefixListMaskLenFrom.name: rcIpv6PrefixListMaskLenFrom
rcIpv6PrefixListMaskLenFrom.description: Lower bound of mask length of the ipv6 prefix added to the prefix list

rcIpv6PrefixListMaskLenUpto.name: rcIpv6PrefixListMaskLenUpto
rcIpv6PrefixListMaskLenUpto.description: Higher bound of mask length of the ipv6 prefix added to the prefix list

rcIpv6PrefixListName.name: rcIpv6PrefixListName
rcIpv6PrefixListName.description: Name of the Ipv6 prefix list

rcIpv6PrefixListRowStatus.name: rcIpv6PrefixListRowStatus
rcIpv6PrefixListRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the ipv6 prefix list table

UpToRefreshInterval.name: UpToRefreshInterval
UpToRefreshInterval.description: The values one might be able to configure for variables bounded by the Refresh Interval

RouterDeadRange.name: RouterDeadRange
RouterDeadRange.description: The range of intervals in seconds that a routers hello must have not been seen before a neighbor declares the router down

rcOspfv3RouterId.name: rcOspfv3RouterId
rcOspfv3RouterId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the router in the Autonomous System. To ensure uniqueness, this may default to the value of one of the router's IPv4 interface addresses if IPv4 is configured on the router.

rcOspfv3AdminStat.name: rcOspfv3AdminStat
rcOspfv3AdminStat.description: The administrative status of OSPFv3 in the router. The value 'enabled' denotes that the OSPFv3 Process is active on at least one inter- face; 'disabled' disables it on all inter- faces.

rcOspfv3VersionNumber.name: rcOspfv3VersionNumber
rcOspfv3VersionNumber.description: The version number of OSPF for IPv6 is 3.

rcOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.name: rcOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus
rcOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 3 Splitting the AS into Areas
rcOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.description: A flag to note whether this router is an area border router.

rcOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus.name: rcOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus
rcOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 3.3 Classification of routers
rcOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus.description: A flag to note whether this router is config- ured as an Autonomous System border router.

rcOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount.name: rcOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount
rcOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount.description: The number of AS-Scope (e.g. AS-External) link-state advertisements in the link-state database.

rcOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum.name: rcOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum
rcOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the LS checksums of the AS-scoped link-state advertisements con- tained in the link-state database. This sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link-state database of two routers.

rcOspfv3OriginateNewLsas.name: rcOspfv3OriginateNewLsas
rcOspfv3OriginateNewLsas.description: The number of new link-state advertisements that have been originated. This number is in- cremented each time the router originates a new LSA.

rcOspfv3RxNewLsas.name: rcOspfv3RxNewLsas
rcOspfv3RxNewLsas.description: The number of link-state advertisements re- ceived determined to be new instantiations. This number does not include newer instantia- tions of self-originated link-state advertise- ments.

rcOspfv3ExtLsaCount.name: rcOspfv3ExtLsaCount
rcOspfv3ExtLsaCount.description: The number of External(LS type 0x4005) in the link- state database

rcOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.name: rcOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit
rcOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.description: The maximum number of non-default AS- external-LSAs entries that can be stored in the link-state database. If the value is -1, then there is no limit. When the number of non-default AS-external-LSAs in a router's link-state database reaches rcOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit, the router enters Overflow- State. The router never holds more than rcOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit non-default AS-external-LSAs in its database. OspfExtAreaLsdbLimit MUST be set identically in all routers attached to the OSPFv3 backbone and/or any regular OSPFv3 area. (i.e., OSPFv3 stub areas and NSSAs are excluded).

rcOspfv3MulticastExtensions.name: rcOspfv3MulticastExtensions
rcOspfv3MulticastExtensions.description: A Bit Mask indicating whether the router is forwarding IPv6 multicast datagrams based on the algorithms defined in the Multi- cast Extensions to OSPF. If intraAreaMulticast set, indicates that the router can forward IPv6 multicast datagrams in the router's directly attached areas (called intra-area mul- ticast routing). If interAreaMulticast set, indicates that the router can forward IPv6 multicast datagrams between OSPFv3 areas (called inter-area multicast routing). If interAsMulticast set, indicates that the router can forward IPv6 multicast datagrams between Auto- nomous Systems (called inter-AS multicast rout- ing). Only certain combinations of bit settings are allowed, namely: - All bits cleared (no multicasting) - intraAreaMulticast only, - intraAreaMulticast and interAreaMulticast, - intraAreaMulticast and interAsMulticast - intraAreaMulticast, interAreaMulticast and interAsMulticast By default, all bits are cleared.

rcOspfv3ExitOverflowInterval.name: rcOspfv3ExitOverflowInterval
rcOspfv3ExitOverflowInterval.description: The number of seconds that, after entering OverflowState, a router will attempt to leave OverflowState. This allows the router to again originate non-default AS-External-LSAs. When set to 0, the router will not leave Overflow- State until restarted.

rcOspfv3DemandExtensions.name: rcOspfv3DemandExtensions
rcOspfv3DemandExtensions.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix on Demand Routing
rcOspfv3DemandExtensions.description: The router's support for demand routing.

rcOspfv3TrafficEngineeringSupport.name: rcOspfv3TrafficEngineeringSupport
rcOspfv3TrafficEngineeringSupport.description: The router's support for traffic engineering extensions.

rcOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth.name: rcOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth
rcOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth.description: Reference bandwidth in kilobits/second for calculating default interface metrics. The default value is 100,000 KBPS (100 MBPS)

rcOspfv3RestartSupport.name: rcOspfv3RestartSupport
rcOspfv3RestartSupport.description: The router's support for OSPF hitless restart. Options include: no restart support, only planned restarts or both planned and unplanned restarts.

rcOspfv3RestartInterval.name: rcOspfv3RestartInterval
rcOspfv3RestartInterval.description: Configured OSPF hitless restart timeout interval.

rcOspfv3RestartStatus.name: rcOspfv3RestartStatus
rcOspfv3RestartStatus.description: Current status of OSPF hitless restart.

rcOspfv3RestartAge.name: rcOspfv3RestartAge
rcOspfv3RestartAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPF hitless restart interval.

rcOspfv3RestartExitReason.name: rcOspfv3RestartExitReason
rcOspfv3RestartExitReason.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at a hitless restart. If the value is 'none', no restart has yet been attempted. If the value is 'inProgress', a restart attempt is currently underway.

rcOspfv3BadLsaIgnore.name: rcOspfv3BadLsaIgnore
rcOspfv3BadLsaIgnore.description: The administrative status of OSPFv3 in the router. The value 'enabled' denotes that the OSPFv3 Process is active on at least one inter- face; 'disabled' disables it on all inter- faces.

rcOspfv3AreaTable.name: rcOspfv3AreaTable
rcOspfv3AreaTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 6 The Area Data Struc- ture
rcOspfv3AreaTable.description: Information describing the configured parame- ters and cumulative statistics of the router's attached areas.

rcOspfv3AreaEntry.name: rcOspfv3AreaEntry
rcOspfv3AreaEntry.description: Information describing the configured parame- ters and cumulative statistics of one of the router's attached areas.

rcOspfv3AreaId.name: rcOspfv3AreaId
rcOspfv3AreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
rcOspfv3AreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an area. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPFv3 backbone.

rcOspfv3ImportAsExtern.name: rcOspfv3ImportAsExtern
rcOspfv3ImportAsExtern.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
rcOspfv3ImportAsExtern.description: Indicates whether an area is a Stub area, NSSA, or standard area. AS-scope LSAs are not imported into Stub Areas or NSSAs. NSSAs import AS-External data as Type-7 LSAs which have Area-scope

rcOspfv3AreaSpfRuns.name: rcOspfv3AreaSpfRuns
rcOspfv3AreaSpfRuns.description: The number of times that the intra-area route table has been calculated using this area's link-state database. This is typically done using Dijkstra's algorithm.

rcOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount.name: rcOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount
rcOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount.description: The total number of area border routers reach- able within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each SPF Pass.

rcOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount.name: rcOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount
rcOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount.description: The total number of Autonomous System border routers reachable within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each SPF Pass.

rcOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount.name: rcOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount
rcOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Area-Scope link-state advertisements in this area's link-state database.

rcOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum.name: rcOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum
rcOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Area-Scope link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this area's link-state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link-state database of two routers.

rcOspfv3AreaSummary.name: rcOspfv3AreaSummary
rcOspfv3AreaSummary.description: The variable rcOspfv3AreaSummary controls the im- port of Inter-Area LSAs into stub areas. It has no effect on other areas. If it is noAreaSummary, the router will neither originate nor propagate Inter-Area LSAs into the stub area. It will rely entirely on its de- fault route. If it is sendAreaSummary, the router will both summarize and propagate Inter-Area LSAs.

rcOspfv3AreaStatus.name: rcOspfv3AreaStatus
rcOspfv3AreaStatus.description: This variable controls the status of the en- try. The use of RowStatus is covered in more detail in [6].

rcOspfv3StubMetric.name: rcOspfv3StubMetric
rcOspfv3StubMetric.description: The metric value advertised for the default route into Stub and NSSA areas.

rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole.name: rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole
rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole.description: Indicates an NSSA Border router's ability to perform NSSA translation of type-7 LSAs into type-5 LSAs.

rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState.name: rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState
rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState.description: Indicates if and how an NSSA Border router is performing NSSA translation of type-7 LSAs into type-5 LSAs. When this object is set to enabled, the NSSA Border router's rcOspfv3AreaNssTranslatorRole has been set to always. When this object is set to elected, a candidate NSSA Border router is translating type-7 LSAs into type-5. When this object is set to disabled, a candidate NSSA Border router is NOT translating type-7 LSAs into type-5.

rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabilityInter.name: rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabilityInterval
rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabilityInter.description: The number of seconds after an elected translator determines its services are no longer required, that it should continue to perform its translation duties.

rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents.name: rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents
rcOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents.description: Indicates the number of Translator State changes that have occurred since the last boot-up.

rcOspfv3AreaStubMetricType.name: rcOspfv3AreaStubMetricType
rcOspfv3AreaStubMetricType.description: This variable displays the type of metric ad- vertised as a default route.

rcOspfv3AsLsdbTable.name: rcOspfv3AsLsdbTable
rcOspfv3AsLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's AS-Scope Link State Database.

rcOspfv3AsLsdbEntry.name: rcOspfv3AsLsdbEntry
rcOspfv3AsLsdbEntry.description: A single AS-Scope Link State Advertisement.

rcOspfv3AsLsdbType.name: rcOspfv3AsLsdbType
rcOspfv3AsLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertise- ment format. AS-Scope LSAs not recognized by the router may be stored in the database.

rcOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.name: rcOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId
rcOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters
rcOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

rcOspfv3AsLsdbLsid.name: rcOspfv3AsLsdbLsid
rcOspfv3AsLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.

rcOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.name: rcOspfv3AsLsdbSequence
rcOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number
rcOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and dupli- cate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

rcOspfv3AsLsdbAge.name: rcOspfv3AsLsdbAge
rcOspfv3AsLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state adver- tisement in seconds.

rcOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum.name: rcOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum
rcOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connec- tionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

rcOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement.name: rcOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement
rcOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.

rcOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown.name: rcOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown
rcOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown.description: Is the LSA type recognized by this Router?

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbTable.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbTable
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's Area-Scope Link State Database.

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry.description: A single Area-Scope Link State Advertisement.

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.description: The 32 bit identifier of the Area from which the LSA was received.

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbType.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbType
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertise- ment format. Area-Scope LSAs unrecognized by the router are also stored in this database.

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbLsid.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbLsid
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and dupli- cate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbAge.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbAge
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state adver- tisement in seconds.

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connec- tionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown.description: Is the LSA type recognized by this Router?

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbTable.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbTable
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's Link-Scope Link State Database.

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry.description: A single Link-Scope Link State Advertisement.

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex.description: The identifier of the link from which the LSA was received.

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbType.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbType
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertise- ment format. Link-Scope LSAs unrecognized by the router are also stored in this database.

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbLsid.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbLsid
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and dupli- cate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbAge.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbAge
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connec- tionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown.description: Indicates whether the LSA type is recognized by this Router.

rcOspfv3HostTable.name: rcOspfv3HostTable
rcOspfv3HostTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.6 Host route param- eters
rcOspfv3HostTable.description: The list of Hosts, and their metrics, that the router will advertise as host routes.

rcOspfv3HostEntry.name: rcOspfv3HostEntry
rcOspfv3HostEntry.description: A metric to be advertised when a given host is reachable.

rcOspfv3HostAddressType.name: rcOspfv3HostAddressType
rcOspfv3HostAddressType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.6 Host route parame- ters
rcOspfv3HostAddressType.description: The address type of rcOspfv3HostAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

rcOspfv3HostAddress.name: rcOspfv3HostAddress
rcOspfv3HostAddress.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.6 Host route parame- ters
rcOspfv3HostAddress.description: The IPv6 Address of the Host. Must be a Global or Site-local address.

rcOspfv3HostMetric.name: rcOspfv3HostMetric
rcOspfv3HostMetric.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.6 Host route parame- ters

rcOspfv3HostStatus.name: rcOspfv3HostStatus
rcOspfv3HostStatus.description: This variable controls the status of the en- try. The use of RowStatus is covered in more detail in [6].

rcOspfv3HostAreaID.name: rcOspfv3HostAreaID
rcOspfv3HostAreaID.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
rcOspfv3HostAreaID.description: The Area the Host Entry is to be found within. By default, the area that a subsuming OSPFv3 in- terface is in, or 0.0.0.0

rcOspfv3IfTable.name: rcOspfv3IfTable
rcOspfv3IfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.3 Router interface parameters
rcOspfv3IfTable.description: The OSPFv3 Interface Table describes the inter- faces from the viewpoint of OSPFv3.

rcOspfv3IfEntry.name: rcOspfv3IfEntry
rcOspfv3IfEntry.description: The OSPFv3 Interface Entry describes one inter- face from the viewpoint of OSPFv3.

rcOspfv3IfIndex.name: rcOspfv3IfIndex
rcOspfv3IfIndex.description: The interface index of this OSPFv3 interface. It corresponds to the interface index of the IPv6 interface on which OSPFv3 is configured.

rcOspfv3IfAreaId.name: rcOspfv3IfAreaId
rcOspfv3IfAreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the area to which the interface connects. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPFv3 backbone.

rcOspfv3IfAdminStat.name: rcOspfv3IfAdminStat
rcOspfv3IfAdminStat.description: The OSPFv3 interface's administrative status. The value formed on the interface, and the in- terface will be advertised as an internal route to some area. The value 'disabled' denotes that the interface is external to OSPFv3.

rcOspfv3IfRtrPriority.name: rcOspfv3IfRtrPriority
rcOspfv3IfRtrPriority.description: The priority of this interface. Used in multi-access networks, this field is used in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the router is not eligi- ble to become the designated router on this particular network. In the event of a tie in this value, routers will use their Router ID as a tie breaker.

rcOspfv3IfTransitDelay.name: rcOspfv3IfTransitDelay
rcOspfv3IfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link state update packet over this interface.

rcOspfv3IfRetransInterval.name: rcOspfv3IfRetransInterval
rcOspfv3IfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link-state ad- vertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database descrip- tion and link-state request packets.

rcOspfv3IfHelloInterval.name: rcOspfv3IfHelloInterval
rcOspfv3IfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the in- terface. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

rcOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval.name: rcOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval
rcOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neigh- bors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

rcOspfv3IfPollInterval.name: rcOspfv3IfPollInterval
rcOspfv3IfPollInterval.description: The larger time interval, in seconds, between the Hello packets sent to an inactive non- broadcast multi- access neighbor.

rcOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter.name: rcOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter
rcOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter.description: The Router ID of the Designated Router.

rcOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter.name: rcOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter
rcOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter.description: The Router ID of the Backup Designated Router.

rcOspfv3IfEvents.name: rcOspfv3IfEvents
rcOspfv3IfEvents.description: The number of times this OSPF interface has changed its state, or an error has occurred.

rcOspfv3IfStatus.name: rcOspfv3IfStatus
rcOspfv3IfStatus.description: This variable controls the status of the en- try. The use of RowStatus is covered in more detail in [6].

rcOspfv3IfMulticastForwarding.name: rcOspfv3IfMulticastForwarding
rcOspfv3IfMulticastForwarding.description: The way multicasts should forwarded on this interface; not forwarded, forwarded as data link multicasts, or forwarded as data link uni- casts. Data link multicasting is not meaning- ful on point to point and NBMA interfaces, and setting rcOspfv3MulticastForwarding to 0 effective- ly disables all multicast forwarding.

rcOspfv3IfDemand.name: rcOspfv3IfDemand
rcOspfv3IfDemand.description: Indicates whether Demand OSPFv3 procedures (hel- lo suppression to FULL neighbors and setting the DoNotAge flag on propagated LSAs) should be per- formed on this interface.

rcOspfv3IfMetricValue.name: rcOspfv3IfMetricValue
rcOspfv3IfMetricValue.description: The metric assigned to this interface. The default value of the Metric is Reference Bandwidth / ifSpeed. The value of the reference bandwidth is configured by the rcOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth object. A value of '0' means the metric value of this interface will depend on the speed of the interface, when the state of the interface is up. The default (0) metric for Vlan and Tunnel is 10.

rcOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount.name: rcOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount
rcOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Link-Scope link-state advertisements in this link's link-state database.

rcOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum.name: rcOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum
rcOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Link-Scope link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this link's link-state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link-state database of two routers.

rcOspfv3IfInstId.name: rcOspfv3IfInstId
rcOspfv3IfInstId.description: Enables multiple instances of OSPFv3 to be run over a single link. Each protocol instance would be assigned a separate ID. This ID has local link significance only.

rcOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbe.name: rcOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbe
rcOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbe.description: Indicates whether or not neighbor probing is enabled to determine whether or not the neighbor is inactive. Neighbor probing is disabled by default.

rcOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeRetxLimit.name: rcOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeRetxLimit
rcOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeRetxLimit.description: The number of consecutive LSA retransmissions before the neighbor is deemed inactive and the neighbor adjacency is brought down.

rcOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeInterval.name: rcOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeInterval
rcOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeInterval.description: Defines how often the neighbor will be probed.

rcOspfv3VirtIfTable.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfTable
rcOspfv3VirtIfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.4 Virtual link parameters
rcOspfv3VirtIfTable.description: Information about this router's virtual inter- faces.

rcOspfv3VirtIfEntry.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfEntry
rcOspfv3VirtIfEntry.description: Information about a single Virtual Interface.

rcOspfv3VirtIfAreaId.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfAreaId
rcOspfv3VirtIfAreaId.description: The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not 0.0.0.0

rcOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor
rcOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the Virtual Neighbor.

rcOspfv3VirtIfIndex.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfIndex
rcOspfv3VirtIfIndex.description: The interface ID assigned to this OSPFv3 virtual interface. It is advertised in Hello's sent over the virtal link and in the router's router-LSAs.

rcOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay
rcOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link- state update packet over this interface.

rcOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval
rcOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link-state ad- vertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database descrip- tion and link-state request packets. This value should be well over the expected round- trip time.

rcOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval
rcOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the in- terface. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

rcOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval
rcOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neigh- bors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for the virtual neigh- bor.

rcOspfv3VirtIfEvents.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfEvents
rcOspfv3VirtIfEvents.description: The number of state changes or error events on this Virtual Link

rcOspfv3VirtIfStatus.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfStatus
rcOspfv3VirtIfStatus.description: This variable controls the status of the en- try. The use of RowStatus is covered in more detail in [6].

rcOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount
rcOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Link-Scope link-state advertisements in this virtual link's link-state database.

rcOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum
rcOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Link-Scope link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this virtual link's link-state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link-state database of two routers.

rcOspfv3NbrTable.name: rcOspfv3NbrTable
rcOspfv3NbrTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure
rcOspfv3NbrTable.description: A table of non-virtual neighbor information.

rcOspfv3NbrEntry.name: rcOspfv3NbrEntry
rcOspfv3NbrEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure
rcOspfv3NbrEntry.description: The information regarding a single neighbor.

rcOspfv3NbrIfIndex.name: rcOspfv3NbrIfIndex
rcOspfv3NbrIfIndex.description: The local link ID of the link over which the neighbor can be reached.

rcOspfv3NbrRtrId.name: rcOspfv3NbrRtrId
rcOspfv3NbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer (represented as a type IpAd- dress) uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

rcOspfv3NbrAddressType.name: rcOspfv3NbrAddressType
rcOspfv3NbrAddressType.description: The address type of rcOspfv3NbrAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

rcOspfv3NbrAddress.name: rcOspfv3NbrAddress
rcOspfv3NbrAddress.description: The IPv6 address of the neighbor associated with the local link.

rcOspfv3NbrOptions.name: rcOspfv3NbrOptions
rcOspfv3NbrOptions.reference: OSPF Version 3, Appendix A.2 the Options field
rcOspfv3NbrOptions.description: A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's op- tions field.

rcOspfv3NbrPriority.name: rcOspfv3NbrPriority
rcOspfv3NbrPriority.description: The priority of this neighbor in the designat- ed router election algorithm. The value 0 sig- nifies that the neighbor is not eligible to be- come the designated router on this particular network.

rcOspfv3NbrState.name: rcOspfv3NbrState
rcOspfv3NbrState.description: The State of the relationship with this Neigh- bor.

rcOspfv3NbrEvents.name: rcOspfv3NbrEvents
rcOspfv3NbrEvents.description: The number of times this neighbor relationship has changed state, or an error has occurred.

rcOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen.name: rcOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen
rcOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.

rcOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed.name: rcOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed
rcOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor

rcOspfv3NbrIfId.name: rcOspfv3NbrIfId
rcOspfv3NbrIfId.description: The interface ID that the neighbor advertises in its Hello Packets on this link, that is, the neighbor's local interface index.

rcOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus.name: rcOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus
rcOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a hitless restart helper for the neighbor.

rcOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge.name: rcOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge
rcOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPF hitless restart interval, if the router is acting as a restart helper for the neighbor.

rcOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitReason.name: rcOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitReason
rcOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitReason.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at acting as a hitless restart helper for the neighbor.

rcOspfv3NbmaNbrTable.name: rcOspfv3NbmaNbrTable
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrTable.description: A table of configured non-virtual neighbor information and neighbors dynamically discovered by lower-level protocols such as Inverse Neighbor Discovery.

rcOspfv3NbmaNbrEntry.name: rcOspfv3NbmaNbrEntry
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrEntry.description: The information regarding a single configured neighbor or neighbor discovered by lower-level protocols such as Inverse Neighbor Discovery.

rcOspfv3NbmaNbrIfIndex.name: rcOspfv3NbmaNbrIfIndex
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrIfIndex.description: The local link ID of the link over which the neighbor can be reached.

rcOspfv3NbmaNbrAddress.name: rcOspfv3NbmaNbrAddress
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrAddress.description: The IPv6 address of the neighbor associated with the local link.

rcOspfv3NbmaNbrPriority.name: rcOspfv3NbmaNbrPriority
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrPriority.description: The priority of this neighbor in the designat- ed router election algorithm. The value 0 sig- nifies that the neighbor is not eligible to be- come the designated router on this particular network.

rcOspfv3NbmaNbrRtrId.name: rcOspfv3NbmaNbrRtrId
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer (represented as a type IpAd- dress) uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System. A value of 0.0.0.0 is returned until a Hello is received from the configured neighbor.

rcOspfv3NbmaNbrState.name: rcOspfv3NbmaNbrState
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrState.description: The State of the relationship with this Neigh- bor.

rcOspfv3NbmaNbrStorageType.name: rcOspfv3NbmaNbrStorageType
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar objects in the row. Manually configured entries will have a storage type of nonVolatile while entries dynamically created as a result of a lower-level protocol such as Inverse Neighbor Discovery will have a storage type of volatile.

rcOspfv3NbmaNbrStatus.name: rcOspfv3NbmaNbrStatus
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrStatus.description: This variable controls the status of the en- try. The use of RowStatus is covered in more detail in [6].

rcOspfv3VirtNbrTable.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrTable
rcOspfv3VirtNbrTable.description: A table of virtual neighbor information.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId
rcOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex
rcOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex.description: The local interface ID for the virtual link over which the neighbor can be reached.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType
rcOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType.description: The address type of rcOspfv3VirtNbrAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrAddress.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrAddress
rcOspfv3VirtNbrAddress.description: The IPv6 address advertised by this Virtual Neighbor. It must be a Site-Local or Global scope address.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrOptions
rcOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.reference: OSPF Version 3, Appendix A.2 the Options field
rcOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.description: A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's op- tions field.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrState.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrState
rcOspfv3VirtNbrState.description: The state of the Virtual Neighbor Relation- ship.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrEvents.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrEvents
rcOspfv3VirtNbrEvents.description: The number of times this virtual link has changed its state, or an error has occurred.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen
rcOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed
rcOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor

rcOspfv3VirtNbrIfId.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrIfId
rcOspfv3VirtNbrIfId.description: The interface ID that the neighbor advertises in its Hello Packets on this virtual link, that is, the neighbor's local interface ID.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus
rcOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a hitless restart helper for the neighbor.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge
rcOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPF hitless restart interval, if the router is acting as a restart helper for the neighbor.

rcOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitReason.name: rcOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitReason
rcOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitReason.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at acting as a hitless restart helper for the neighbor.

rcOspfv3AreaAggregateTable.name: rcOspfv3AreaAggregateTable
rcOspfv3AreaAggregateTable.description: A range of IPv6 prefixes specified by a prefix/prefix length pair. Note that if ranges are configured such that one range sub- sumes another range the most specific match is the preferred one.

rcOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.name: rcOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry
rcOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
rcOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.description: A range of IPv6 prefixes specified by a prefix/prefix length pair. Note that if ranges are configured such that one range sub- sumes another range the most specific match is the preferred one.

rcOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID.name: rcOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID
rcOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
rcOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID.description: The Area the Address Aggregate is to be found within.

rcOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.name: rcOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType
rcOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.4.1 The Link State Advertisement header
rcOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.description: The type of the Address Aggregate. This field specifies the Area Lsdb type that this Address Ag- gregate applies to.

rcOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix.name: rcOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix
rcOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters

rcOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.name: rcOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength
rcOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
rcOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix (in bits). A prefix can not be shorter than 3 bits.

rcOspfv3AreaAggregateStatus.name: rcOspfv3AreaAggregateStatus
rcOspfv3AreaAggregateStatus.description: This variable controls the status of the en- try. The use of RowStatus is covered in more detail in [6].

rcOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect.name: rcOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect
rcOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect.description: Prefixes subsumed by ranges either trigger the advertisement of the indicated aggregate (ad- vertiseMatching), or result in the prefix not being advertised at all outside the area.

rcOspfv3AreaAggregateRouteTag.name: rcOspfv3AreaAggregateRouteTag
rcOspfv3AreaAggregateRouteTag.description: This tag is advertised only in the summarized As-External LSA when summarizing from type-7 to type-5.

rcOspfv3AreaAggregateAdvertiseMetric.name: rcOspfv3AreaAggregateAdvertiseMetric
rcOspfv3AreaAggregateAdvertiseMetric.description: Used to specify a metric for a Summary LSA (type 3) generated by OSPF through an area range. If this metric is set to 0, OSPF uses the cost to the farthest point in the networks being summarized as the metric.

rcOspfv3StatsTxPackets.name: rcOspfv3StatsTxPackets
rcOspfv3StatsTxPackets.description: Used to indicate the number of packets transmitted by OSPF.

rcOspfv3StatsRxPackets.name: rcOspfv3StatsRxPackets
rcOspfv3StatsRxPackets.description: Used to indicate the number of packets received by OSPF.

rcOspfv3StatsTxDropPackets.name: rcOspfv3StatsTxDropPackets
rcOspfv3StatsTxDropPackets.description: Used to indicate the number of packets dropped before transmitted by OSPF.

rcOspfv3StatsRxDropPackets.name: rcOspfv3StatsRxDropPackets
rcOspfv3StatsRxDropPackets.description: Used to indicate the number of packets dropped before received by OSPF.

rcOspfv3StatsRxBadPackets.name: rcOspfv3StatsRxBadPackets
rcOspfv3StatsRxBadPackets.description: Used to indicate the number of packets received by OSPF that are bad.

rcOspfv3StatsSpfRuns.name: rcOspfv3StatsSpfRuns
rcOspfv3StatsSpfRuns.description: Used to indicate the total number of SPF calculations performed by OSPF, which also includes the number of partial route table calculation for Incremental Updates.

rcOspfv3StatsLastSpfRun.name: rcOspfv3StatsLastSpfRun
rcOspfv3StatsLastSpfRun.description: Used to indicate the time(SysUpTime) since the last spf calculated by OSPF.

rcOspfv3StatsLsdbTblSize.name: rcOspfv3StatsLsdbTblSize
rcOspfv3StatsLsdbTblSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the linkstate database table.

rcOspfv3StatsBadLsReqs.name: rcOspfv3StatsBadLsReqs
rcOspfv3StatsBadLsReqs.description: Used to indicate the number of bad ls requests.

rcOspfv3StatsSeqMismatches.name: rcOspfv3StatsSeqMismatches
rcOspfv3StatsSeqMismatches.description: Used to indicate the number of sequence mismatched packets.

rcOspfv3BasicGroup.name: rcOspfv3BasicGroup
rcOspfv3BasicGroup.description: These objects are required for OSPFv3 systems.

rcOspfv3AreaGroup.name: rcOspfv3AreaGroup
rcOspfv3AreaGroup.description: These objects are required for OSPFv3 systems supporting areas.

rcOspfv3AsLsdbGroup.name: rcOspfv3AsLsdbGroup
rcOspfv3AsLsdbGroup.description: These objects are required for OSPFv3 systems that display their AS-scope link state database.

rcOspfv3AreaLsdbGroup.name: rcOspfv3AreaLsdbGroup
rcOspfv3AreaLsdbGroup.description: These objects are required for OSPFv3 systems that display their Area-scope link state database.

rcOspfv3LinkLsdbGroup.name: rcOspfv3LinkLsdbGroup
rcOspfv3LinkLsdbGroup.description: These objects are required for OSPFv3 systems that display their Link-scope link state database.

rcOspfv3HostGroup.name: rcOspfv3HostGroup
rcOspfv3HostGroup.description: These objects are required for OSPFv3 systems that support attached hosts.

rcOspfv3IfGroup.name: rcOspfv3IfGroup
rcOspfv3IfGroup.description: These interface objects are required for OSPFv3 systems.

rcOspfv3VirtIfGroup.name: rcOspfv3VirtIfGroup
rcOspfv3VirtIfGroup.description: These virtual interface objects are required for OSPFv3 systems.

rcOspfv3NbrGroup.name: rcOspfv3NbrGroup
rcOspfv3NbrGroup.description: These neighbor objects are required for OSPFv3 systems.

rcOspfv3NbmaNbrGroup.name: rcOspfv3NbmaNbrGroup
rcOspfv3NbmaNbrGroup.description: These NBMA neighbor objects are required for OSPFv3 systems.
