rcnIgmpNewGroupMember.description: An IgmpNewGroupMember trap signifies that a new member has come on an interface.

rcIgmpLossGroupMember.name: rcIgmpLossGroupMember
rcIgmpLossGroupMember.description: An IgmpLossGroupMember trap signifies that a group member has been lost on an interface.

rcnIgmpLossGroupMember.name: rcnIgmpLossGroupMember
rcnIgmpLossGroupMember.description: An IgmpLossGroupMember trap signifies that a group member has been lost on an interface.

rcIgmpNewQuerier.name: rcIgmpNewQuerier
rcIgmpNewQuerier.description: An igmpNewQuerier trap signifies that a new querier has come up on an interface.

rcnIgmpNewQuerier.name: rcnIgmpNewQuerier
rcnIgmpNewQuerier.description: An igmpNewQuerier trap signifies that a new querier has come up on an interface.

rcIgmpQuerierChange.name: rcIgmpQuerierChange
rcIgmpQuerierChange.description: An rcIgmpQuerierChange trap signifies that the querier has changed.

rcnIgmpQuerierChange.name: rcnIgmpQuerierChange
rcnIgmpQuerierChange.description: An rcIgmpQuerierChange trap signifies that the querier has changed.

rcDvmrpIfStateChange.name: rcDvmrpIfStateChange
rcDvmrpIfStateChange.description: A rcDvmrpIfStateChange trap signifies that there has been a change in the state of a DVMRP interface.

rcnDvmrpIfStateChange.name: rcnDvmrpIfStateChange
rcnDvmrpIfStateChange.description: A rcDvmrpIfStateChange trap signifies that there has been a change in the state of a DVMRP interface.

rcDvmrpNewNbrChange.name: rcDvmrpNewNbrChange
rcDvmrpNewNbrChange.description: A rcDvmrpNewNbrChange trap signifies that a new neighbor has come up on a DVMRP interface.

rcnDvmrpNewNbrChange.name: rcnDvmrpNewNbrChange
rcnDvmrpNewNbrChange.description: A rcDvmrpNewNbrChange trap signifies that a new neighbor has come up on a DVMRP interface.

rcDvmrpNbrLossChange.name: rcDvmrpNbrLossChange
rcDvmrpNbrLossChange.description: A rcDvmrpNbrLossChange trap signifies that a new neighbor has gone down on a DVMRP interface.

rcnDvmrpNbrLossChange.name: rcnDvmrpNbrLossChange
rcnDvmrpNbrLossChange.description: A rcDvmrpNbrLossChange trap signifies that a new neighbor has gone down on a DVMRP interface.

rcnFdbProtectViolation.name: rcnFdbProtectViolation
rcnFdbProtectViolation.description: The rcFdbProtectViolation trap signifies that the has violated the user configured limit for total number of fdb-entries learned on that port.

rcnLogMsgControl.name: rcnLogMsgControl
rcnLogMsgControl.description: A rcMsgControl trap signifies whether the number of times of repeatation of the particular Log message has exceeded the particular frequency/count or not.

rcnSaveConfigFile.name: rcnSaveConfigFile
rcnSaveConfigFile.description: A rcSaveConfig trap signifies that either the runtime config or the boot config has been saved on the switch

rcnDNSRequestResponse.name: rcnDNSRequestResponse
rcnDNSRequestResponse.description: A rcDnsRequestResponse trap signifies that the switch had sent a query to the DNS server or it had received a successful response from the DNS Server

rcnDuplicateIpAddress.name: rcnDuplicateIpAddress
rcnDuplicateIpAddress.description: A rcDuplicateIpAddress trap signifies that a duplicate IP address is detected on the subnet.

rcnLoopDetectPortDown.name: rcnLoopDetectPortDown
rcnLoopDetectPortDown.description: A rcLoopDetectPortDown trap signifies that a loop has been detected on a port and the port is going to shut down.

rcnLoopDetectMacDiscard.name: rcnLoopDetectMacDiscard
rcnLoopDetectMacDiscard.description: A rcLoopDetectMacDiscard trap signifies that a loop has been Detected on a port and the mac address will be discarded on all ports in that vlan

rcnAutoRecoverPort.name: rcnAutoRecoverPort
rcnAutoRecoverPort.description: A rcnAutoRecoverPort trap signifies that autorecover has re-enabled a port disabled by link flap or cp limit

rcnAutoRecoverLoopDetectedPort.name: rcnAutoRecoverLoopDetectedPort
rcnAutoRecoverLoopDetectedPort.description: A rcnAutoRecoverPort trap signifies that autorecover has cleared the action taken on a port by loop detect

rcnExtCpLimitShutDown.name: rcnExtCpLimitShutDown
rcnExtCpLimitShutDown.description: A rcnExtCpLimitShutDown trap signifies that port is shut down due to Extended CP-Limit.

rcnExtCpLimitSopCongestion.name: rcnExtCpLimitSopCongestion
rcnExtCpLimitSopCongestion.description: A rcnExtCpLimitSopCongestion signifies that system octapid polling finds that system octapid is congested or not. rcSysExtCplimitSysOctapidCongested signifies whether system octapid is congested or not. rcSysExtCplimitPortsMonitored signifies whether ports are selected for monitoring the ingress traffic utilization.

rcnTacacsNoServers.name: rcnTacacsNoServers
rcnTacacsNoServers.description: Unable to use any TACACS+ servers for authentication

rcnTacacsRxUnsupportedFrame.name: rcnTacacsRxUnsupportedFrame
rcnTacacsRxUnsupportedFrame.description: Received unsupported frame from TACACS+ server

rcnTacacsExceededMaxLogins.name: rcnTacacsExceededMaxLogins
rcnTacacsExceededMaxLogins.description: Attempted to exceed the maximum number of allowed TACACS+ logins

rcnBpduReceived.name: rcnBpduReceived
rcnBpduReceived.description: This notification will be generated when a BPDU is received on a port which has BPDU filtering enabled.

rcnVlacpPortDown.name: rcnVlacpPortDown
rcnVlacpPortDown.description: A rcnVlacpPortDown trap signifies that Vlacp is down on the port specified.

rcnVlacpPortUp.name: rcnVlacpPortUp
rcnVlacpPortUp.description: A rcnVlacpPortUp trap signifies that Vlacp is Up on the port specified.

rcnExtCpLimitShutDownNormal.name: rcnExtCpLimitShutDownNormal
rcnExtCpLimitShutDownNormal.description: An rcnExtCpLimitShutDownNormal trap signifies that Ports are shut down due to Extended CP-Limit in Normal mode.

rcnEapMacIntrusion.name: rcnEapMacIntrusion
rcnEapMacIntrusion.description: A rcnEapMacIntrusion trap signifies that an EAP MAC intrusion has occured on this Port.

rcnInterCpuCommStatus.name: rcnInterCpuCommStatus
rcnInterCpuCommStatus.description: A rcnInterCpuCommStatus trap signifies the current communication status between primary and secondary CPU.

rcPlugOptModTemperatureStatusTrap.name: rcPlugOptModTemperatureStatusTrap
rcPlugOptModTemperatureStatusTrap.description: Used to trap changes in the temperature status

rcPlugOptModVoltageStatusTrap.name: rcPlugOptModVoltageStatusTrap
rcPlugOptModVoltageStatusTrap.description: Used to trap changes in the voltage level

rcPlugOptModBiasStatusTrap.name: rcPlugOptModBiasStatusTrap
rcPlugOptModBiasStatusTrap.description: Used to trap changes in the laser bias status

rcPlugOptModTxPowerStatusTrap.name: rcPlugOptModTxPowerStatusTrap
rcPlugOptModTxPowerStatusTrap.description: Used to trap changes in the transmit power status

rcPlugOptModRxPowerStatusTrap.name: rcPlugOptModRxPowerStatusTrap
rcPlugOptModRxPowerStatusTrap.description: Used to trap changes in the received power status

rcPlugOptModAux1StatusTrap.name: rcPlugOptModAux1StatusTrap
rcPlugOptModAux1StatusTrap.description: Used to trap changes in the Aux1 status

rcPlugOptModAux2StatusTrap.name: rcPlugOptModAux2StatusTrap
rcPlugOptModAux2StatusTrap.description: Used to trap changes in the Aux2 status

rcnMaxRouteWarnClear.name: rcnMaxRouteWarnClear
rcnMaxRouteWarnClear.description: A rcnMaxRouteWarnClear trap signifies that the number of routes in the routing table of the Virtual Router has droped below its warning threshold.

rcnMaxRouteWarnSet.name: rcnMaxRouteWarnSet
rcnMaxRouteWarnSet.description: A rcnMaxRouteWarnSet trap signifies that the given Virtual Routers routing table is reaching its maximum size. Action should be taken to prevent this

rcnMaxRouteDropClear.name: rcnMaxRouteDropClear
rcnMaxRouteDropClear.description: A rcnMaxRouteDropClear signifies that the given Virtual Routers routing table is no longer dropping new routes as it is below its maximum size.

rcnMaxRouteDropSet.name: rcnMaxRouteDropSet
rcnMaxRouteDropSet.description: A rcnMaxRouteDropSet trap signifies that the given Virtual Routers routing table has reached its maximum size, and is now dropping all new non static routes.

rcnMstpNewCistRoot.name: rcnMstpNewCistRoot
rcnMstpNewCistRoot.description: A rcMstpNewCistRoottrap signifies that the SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role, has detected the Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol has declared the device to be the new root of the common internal spanning tree.

rcnMstpNewMstiRoot.name: rcnMstpNewMstiRoot
rcnMstpNewMstiRoot.description: A rcMstpNewMstiRoot signifies that the SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role, has detected the Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol has declared the device to be the new root of the spanning tree instance.

rcnMstpNewCistRegionalRoot.name: rcnMstpNewCistRegionalRoot
rcnMstpNewCistRegionalRoot.description: A rcMstpNewCistRegionalRoottrap signifies that the SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role, has detected the Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol has declared the device to be the new regional root of the common internal spanning tree.

rcnRstpNewRoot.name: rcnRstpNewRoot
rcnRstpNewRoot.description: A rcRstpNewRoot signifies that the SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role, has detected the Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol has declared the device to be the new root of the spanning tree.

rcnRsmltEdgePeerModified.name: rcnRsmltEdgePeerModified
rcnRsmltEdgePeerModified.description: A rcnRsmltEdgePeerModified signifies that the RSMLT Peer address is different from that of the stored address. Save config is necessary if EdgeSupport has to use this info on next reboot.

rcnTmuxParityError.name: rcnTmuxParityError
rcnTmuxParityError.description: A rcnTmuxParityError trap identifies a problem in the FAD /SWIP based on the number of parity errors.

rcnChasPowerSupplyNoRedundancy.name: rcnChasPowerSupplyNoRedundancy
rcnChasPowerSupplyNoRedundancy.description: A rcnChasPowerSupplyNoRedundancy signifies that the chassis is running on power supply without redundancy.

rcnChasPowerSupplyRedundancy.name: rcnChasPowerSupplyRedundancy
rcnChasPowerSupplyRedundancy.description: A rcnChasPowerSupplyRedundancy signifies that the chassis is running on power supply with redundancy.

rcnLicenseTrialPeriodExpired.name: rcnLicenseTrialPeriodExpired
rcnLicenseTrialPeriodExpired.description: A rcnLicenseTrialPeriodExpired signifies that Trial Period License has expired.

rcnLicenseTrialPeriodExpiry.name: rcnLicenseTrialPeriodExpiry
rcnLicenseTrialPeriodExpiry.description: A rcnLicenseTrialPeriodExpiry signifies the time remaining before License Trial Period expires in days.

rcnVrfUp.name: rcnVrfUp
rcnVrfUp.description: This notification is generated when the specified VRF's operational status is toggled from down to up.

rcnVrfDown.name: rcnVrfDown
rcnVrfDown.description: This notification is generated when the specified VRF's operational status is toggled from up to down.

rcnMrouteIngressThresholdExceeded.name: rcnMrouteIngressThresholdExceeded
rcnMrouteIngressThresholdExceeded.description: This notification is generated when the number of mroute ingress records exceeds the ingress threshold.

rcnMrouteEgressThresholdExceeded.name: rcnMrouteEgressThresholdExceeded
rcnMrouteEgressThresholdExceeded.description: This notification is generated when the number of mroute egress records exceeds the egress threshold.

rcnRemoteMirroringStatus.name: rcnRemoteMirroringStatus
rcnRemoteMirroringStatus.description: A rcRemoteMirroringStatus trap signifies whether the remote mirroring is enabled or disabled on a particular port

rcnMaxMrouteWarnSet.name: rcnMaxMrouteWarnSet
rcnMaxMrouteWarnSet.description: A rcnMaxMrouteWarnSet trap signifies that the given Virtual Routers multicast routing table is reaching its maximum size. Action should be taken to prevent this

rcnMaxMrouteDropSet.name: rcnMaxMrouteDropSet
rcnMaxMrouteDropSet.description: A rcnMaxMrouteDropSet trap signifies that the given Virtual Routers multicast routing table has reached its maximum size, and is now dropping all new non static routes

rcnMaxMrouteWarnClear.name: rcnMaxMrouteWarnClear
rcnMaxMrouteWarnClear.description: A rcnMaxMrouteWarnClear trap signifies that the number of routes in the multicast routing table of the Virtual Router has dropped below its warning threshold.

rcnMaxMrouteDropClear.name: rcnMaxMrouteDropClear
rcnMaxMrouteDropClear.description: A rcnMaxMrouteDropClear trap signifies that the given Virtual Routers multicast routing table is no longer dropping new routes as it is below its maximum size.

rcnAggLinkStateChange.name: rcnAggLinkStateChange
rcnAggLinkStateChange.description: The trap is generated when the operational state of the LAG changes; it identifies three events: local down, remote down, up.

rcnBfdSessExceedThreshold.name: rcnBfdSessExceedThreshold
rcnBfdSessExceedThreshold.description: A rcnBfdSessExceedThreshold signifies that the BFD session have exceed system limit and hence creation of new session failed.

rcnBfdStatusChange.name: rcnBfdStatusChange
rcnBfdStatusChange.description: A rcnBfdSessChange signifies that the status of BFD session changed.

rcnChasPowerSupplyRunningLow.name: rcnChasPowerSupplyRunningLow
rcnChasPowerSupplyRunningLow.description: A rcnChasPowerSupplyRunningLow signifies that the chassis is running on low power supply.

rcnIsisPlsbMetricMismatchTrap.name: rcnIsisPlsbMetricMismatchTrap
rcnIsisPlsbMetricMismatchTrap.description: A PLSB ISIS trap signifies that a LSP with a different value of l1-metric is received

rcnIsisPlsbDuplicateSysidTrap.name: rcnIsisPlsbDuplicateSysidTrap
rcnIsisPlsbDuplicateSysidTrap.description: A PLSB ISIS trap signifies that a Hello packet with a duplicate system-id is received

rcnIsisPlsbLsdbUpdateTrap.name: rcnIsisPlsbLsdbUpdateTrap
rcnIsisPlsbLsdbUpdateTrap.description: A PLSB ISIS trap signifies that LSDB information has changed

rcnChasFanCoolingLow.name: rcnChasFanCoolingLow
rcnChasFanCoolingLow.description: A rcnChasFanCoolingLow signifies that the chassis is running on low fan cooling.

rcnSmpFtpFail.name: rcnSmpFtpFail
rcnSmpFtpFail.description: A rcnSmpFtpFail trap signifies that Ftp/Tftp of a logfile has failed in SMP (System Messagin Platform). Ftp of a logfile fails when configured remote server is not reachable or remote server is not configured.

rcnSmpLogFileDeleted.name: rcnSmpLogFileDeleted
rcnSmpLogFileDeleted.description: A rcnSmpLogFileDeleted trap signifies that a logfile has been deleted from PCMCIA. Deletion of a logfile happens when either FTP of the logfile is successful or PCMCIA has no space to create another logfile.

rcnPimMaxInterfaceWarnSet.name: rcnPimMaxInterfaceWarnSet
rcnPimMaxInterfaceWarnSet.description: A rcnPimMaxInterfaceWarnSet trap signifies that the pim interface count has exceeded the maximum set limit of 200.

rcnPimMaxNeighborsWarnSet.name: rcnPimMaxNeighborsWarnSet
rcnPimMaxNeighborsWarnSet.description: A rcnPimMaxNeighborsWarnSet trap signifies that the pim neighbor count has exceeded the maximum set limit of 200.

rcnPimMaxPassiveInterfaceWarnSet.name: rcnPimMaxPassiveInterfaceWarnSet
rcnPimMaxPassiveInterfaceWarnSet.description: A rcnPimMaxPassiveInterfaceWarnSet trap signifies that the pim passive interface count has exceeded the maximum set limit of 2000.

rcnLegacyCardDetected.name: rcnLegacyCardDetected
rcnLegacyCardDetected.description: A rcnLegacyCardDetected trap signifies that a legacy card has been detected on the cahssis, rc2kCardIndex indicates the slot number of legacy card.

rcnPrFilterRspMemoryFull.name: rcnPrFilterRspMemoryFull
rcnPrFilterRspMemoryFull.description: A rcnPrFilterRspMemoryFull trap signifies that RSP memory is full for Power Ranger filter configuration. rcPrFilterAclId indicates the ACL, on which ACL RSP memory full occurs. rc2kCardIndex indicates the slot number, on which RSP memory full event occurs.

rcnPrFilterStatsCntExst.name: rcnPrFilterStatsCntExst
rcnPrFilterStatsCntExst.description: A rcnPrFilterStatsCntExst trap signifies that RSP filter stats counters have been run out. When this happens, affected filters won't get their counter updated by filter forwarding engine. rcPrFilterAclId indicates the ACL, on which filter stats counter exhaust occurs. rc2kCardIndex indicates the slot number, on which filter stats counter exhaust occurs.

rcnIsisPlsbBvidMismatchTrap.name: rcnIsisPlsbBvidMismatchTrap
rcnIsisPlsbBvidMismatchTrap.description: A PLSB ISIS trap signifies that a Hello packet with mismatched B-VIDs is received

rcnIsisPlsbSmltVirtBmacMismatchTrap.name: rcnIsisPlsbSmltVirtBmacMismatchTrap
rcnIsisPlsbSmltVirtBmacMismatchTrap.description: A PLSB ISIS trap signifies that Virtual BMAC configured in the switch is different from virtual BMAC configured in the IST peer

rcnIsisPlsbSmltPeerBmacMismatchTrap.name: rcnIsisPlsbSmltPeerBmacMismatchTrap
rcnIsisPlsbSmltPeerBmacMismatchTrap.description: A PLSB ISIS trap signifies that either the Smlt Peer BMAC configured in the IST peer is different from the ISIS SystemId of the local switch OR The Smlt peer BMAC configured in the local switch is different from the ISIS systemId of the IST peer

rcnIsisPlsbAdjStateTrap.name: rcnIsisPlsbAdjStateTrap
rcnIsisPlsbAdjStateTrap.description: A PLSB ISIS trap signifies ISIS adjacency state change.

rcnIsisPlsbDuplicateNnameTrap.name: rcnIsisPlsbDuplicateNnameTrap
rcnIsisPlsbDuplicateNnameTrap.description: A PLSB ISIS trap signifies that a LSP with duplicate nickname is received, this trap should be generated by all the switches in the network.

rcnIsisPlsbSmltSplitBebMismatchTrap.name: rcnIsisPlsbSmltSplitBebMismatchTrap
rcnIsisPlsbSmltSplitBebMismatchTrap.description: A PLSB ISIS trap signifies that the Smlt Split-Beb configured in the local switch and IST peer are same. One IST switch shoule be configured as Split-Beb primary and the IST peer should be configured as Split-Beb secondary.

rcnIsisPlsbMultiLinkAdjTrap.name: rcnIsisPlsbMultiLinkAdjTrap
rcnIsisPlsbMultiLinkAdjTrap.description: A PLSB ISIS trap signifies that multiple ISIS adjacencies are formed with the same ISIS node.

rcnVLacpFlapDetectShutDown.name: rcnVLacpFlapDetectShutDown
rcnVLacpFlapDetectShutDown.description: A rcVlacpFlapDetectShutDown trap signifies that the port is shut down because rcPortVLacpFlapFrequency number of VLACP flaps were detected within rcPortVLacpFlapInterval seconds on this port.The port can be brought UP by toggling the port admin state manually.

rcSyslogGlobalEnable.name: rcSyslogGlobalEnable
rcSyslogGlobalEnable.description: Used to enable/disable the SysLog feature. When enabled this feature will send a message to a server on a network that this configured to receive and store diagnostic messages from this device. The type of messages sent is user configurable.

rcSyslogGlobalMaxHosts.name: rcSyslogGlobalMaxHosts
rcSyslogGlobalMaxHosts.description: Maximun number of remote hosts considered 'active' and able to receive messages from the Syslog service on the router.

rcSyslogGlobalOperState.name: rcSyslogGlobalOperState
rcSyslogGlobalOperState.description: The operational state of the syslog service on the router.

rcSyslogGlobalHeader.name: rcSyslogGlobalHeader
rcSyslogGlobalHeader.description: The IP Header Type for the Syslog Packet.

rcSyslogHostTbl.name: rcSyslogHostTbl
rcSyslogHostTbl.description: Table of remote host destinations for syslog.

rcSyslogHostEntry.name: rcSyslogHostEntry
rcSyslogHostEntry.description: Entry containing information for a particular entry in rcSyslogHostTable.

rcSyslogHostUdpPort.name: rcSyslogHostUdpPort
rcSyslogHostUdpPort.description: Specifies the UDP port to use to send syslog messages to the host.

rcSyslogHostFacility.name: rcSyslogHostFacility
rcSyslogHostFacility.description: Specifies the UNIX facility used in messages to the syslog host. Default is LOCAL7.

rcSyslogHostModuleId.name: rcSyslogHostModuleId
rcSyslogHostModuleId.description: Specifies for which modules/tasks syslog messages should be sent. Default is all modules/tasks.

rcSyslogHostModuleId2.name: rcSyslogHostModuleId2
rcSyslogHostModuleId2.description: Specifies for which modules/tasks syslog messages should be sent. Default is all modules/tasks.

rcSyslogHostSeverity.name: rcSyslogHostSeverity
rcSyslogHostSeverity.description: Specifies the severity level for which syslog messages should be sent for the modules specifies in 'SyslogHostModule'. Value is one of multiple (logical 'OR') of the following: info(1), warning(2), error(4), mfg(8), fatal(16).

rcSyslogHostMapInfoSeverity.name: rcSyslogHostMapInfoSeverity
rcSyslogHostMapInfoSeverity.description: Specifies the syslog severity to use for Accelar INFO messages. Default is INFO.

rcSyslogHostMapWarningSeverity.name: rcSyslogHostMapWarningSeverity
rcSyslogHostMapWarningSeverity.description: Specifies the syslog severity to use for Accelar WARNING messages. Default is WARNING. Should be <= INFO.

rcSyslogHostMapErrorSeverity.name: rcSyslogHostMapErrorSeverity
rcSyslogHostMapErrorSeverity.description: Specifies the syslog severity to use for Accelar ERROR messages. Default is ERROR. Should be <= WARNING.

rcSyslogHostMapMfgSeverity.name: rcSyslogHostMapMfgSeverity
rcSyslogHostMapMfgSeverity.description: Specifies the syslog severity to use for Accelar Manufactoring messages. Dafault is ERROR.

rcSyslogHostMapFatalSeverity.name: rcSyslogHostMapFatalSeverity
rcSyslogHostMapFatalSeverity.description: Specifies the syslog severity to use for Accelar FATAL messages. Default is EMERGENCY. Should be <= ERROR.

rcSyslogHostMapTraceMsg.name: rcSyslogHostMapTraceMsg
rcSyslogHostMapTraceMsg.description: Specifies the syslog severity to use for syslog trace messages. Default is DEBUG.

rcSyslogHostMapTrapMsg.name: rcSyslogHostMapTrapMsg
rcSyslogHostMapTrapMsg.description: Specifies the UNIX severity code to use for syslog messages for SNMP traps sent to the syslog host. Default is INFO.

rcSyslogHostLogTraceMsgs.name: rcSyslogHostLogTraceMsgs
rcSyslogHostLogTraceMsgs.description: Indicate whether to activate the host to log the syslog trace messages.

rcSyslogHostLogTrapMsgs.name: rcSyslogHostLogTrapMsgs
rcSyslogHostLogTrapMsgs.description: Indicate whether to activate the host to log the syslog messages for SNMP traps.

rcSyslogHostEnable.name: rcSyslogHostEnable
rcSyslogHostEnable.description: Enable/Disable messages to be sent to syslog host.

rcSyslogHostRowStatus.name: rcSyslogHostRowStatus
rcSyslogHostRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the rcSyslogTable.

rcDiagMirrorByPortTable.name: rcDiagMirrorByPortTable
rcDiagMirrorByPortTable.description: This table is used to configure the Mirror By Port feature. This feature allows the device to forward a copy of each packet seen on a particular port to a different port.

rcDiagMirrorByPortEntry.name: rcDiagMirrorByPortEntry
rcDiagMirrorByPortEntry.description: Entry containing mirror by port information.

rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroredPort.name: rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroredPort
rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroredPort.description: Used to configure the 'mirrored' port. The port where packets are copied from.

rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroringPort.name: rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroringPort
rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroringPort.description: Used to configure the 'mirroring' port. The port where packets are copied to.

rcDiagMirrorByPortMode.name: rcDiagMirrorByPortMode
rcDiagMirrorByPortMode.description: Used to configure the 'mode' of the mirror operation. 'tx' means packets being transmitted on the 'mirrored' port will be copied. 'rx' means packets received on the 'mirrored' port will be copied. 'both' means all traffic on the 'mirrored' port will be copied. 'rxFilter' means packets received on the 'mirrored' port is copied only if it macthes filter criteria. 'txFilter' means packets being transmitted on the 'mirrorred' port is copied only if it matches filter criteria. 'bothFilter' means both ingress and egress traffic will be copied if it matches either ingress or egress filter on the 'mirrored' port.

rcDiagMirrorRemoteMirrorVlanId.name: rcDiagMirrorRemoteMirrorVlanId
rcDiagMirrorRemoteMirrorVlanId.description: vlan-id to which mirrored packets needs to be send for remote mirroring. If set, this vlan id is used in mirror tag of the remote mirrored packet

rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroredPortList.name: rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroredPortList
rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroredPortList.description: Used to configure the 'mirrored' port. The port where packets are copied from.

rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroringPortList.name: rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroringPortList
rcDiagMirrorByPortMirroringPortList.description: Used to configure the 'mirroring' port. The port where packets are copied from.

rcDiagMirrorMirroringMgId.name: rcDiagMirrorMirroringMgId
rcDiagMirrorMirroringMgId.description: Contains information about the MGID allocated.

rcDiagPortConvSteeringEntry.name: rcDiagPortConvSteeringEntry
rcDiagPortConvSteeringEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of Diag Port Conv Steering.

rcDiagPortConvSteeringMode.name: rcDiagPortConvSteeringMode
rcDiagPortConvSteeringMode.description: Used to specify the traffic flow that should be captured between ports one and two.

rcDiagPortConvSteeringForwardPort.name: rcDiagPortConvSteeringForwardPort
rcDiagPortConvSteeringForwardPort.description: IfIndex of the port where captured traffic should be forwarded to.

rcDiagPortConvSteeringRowStatus.name: rcDiagPortConvSteeringRowStatus
rcDiagPortConvSteeringRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the rcDiagMirrorByPortTable.

rcDiagMacConvSteeringEntry.name: rcDiagMacConvSteeringEntry
rcDiagMacConvSteeringEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of Diag Mac Conv Steering.

rcDiagMacConvSteeringForwardPort.name: rcDiagMacConvSteeringForwardPort
rcDiagMacConvSteeringForwardPort.description: IfIndex of the port where captured traffic should be forwarded to.

rcDiagMacConvSteeringRowStatus.name: rcDiagMacConvSteeringRowStatus
rcDiagMacConvSteeringRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the rcDiagMirrorByPortTable.

rcDiagSaveConfig.name: rcDiagSaveConfig
rcDiagSaveConfig.description: Used to configure whether the various mirror feature settings should be saved and restored across system reboot.

rcDiagDiagnosticsEnable.name: rcDiagDiagnosticsEnable
rcDiagDiagnosticsEnable.description: Used to enable/disable the mirroring feature for the entire device. This setting overrides any setting in the various mirroring tables.

rcDiagPcapEnable.name: rcDiagPcapEnable
rcDiagPcapEnable.description: To enable pcap in secondary CPU

rcDiagPcapBufferWrap.name: rcDiagPcapBufferWrap
rcDiagPcapBufferWrap.description: To enable buffer wrap-around when buffer is full. If set, pcap will continue to capture pkts, otherwise stops pkt storing

rcDiagPcapPcmciaWrap.name: rcDiagPcapPcmciaWrap
rcDiagPcapPcmciaWrap.description: To wrap around the PCMCIA when saving data in PCMCIA

rcDiagPcapFrameSize.name: rcDiagPcapFrameSize
rcDiagPcapFrameSize.description: Number of bytes of pkts needs to be stored

rcDiagPcapBufferSize.name: rcDiagPcapBufferSize
rcDiagPcapBufferSize.description: memory to be allocated for capturing the pkt

rcDiagPcapAutoSave.name: rcDiagPcapAutoSave
rcDiagPcapAutoSave.description: To save data automatically when buffer is full

rcDiagPcapAutoSaveFileName.name: rcDiagPcapAutoSaveFileName
rcDiagPcapAutoSaveFileName.description: Name of the file in which the pkt is to be stored

rcDiagPcapAutoSaveDevice.name: rcDiagPcapAutoSaveDevice
rcDiagPcapAutoSaveDevice.description: Where to store the captured pkts. If the option is network, the user need to enter an IP address also

rcIpxAddrVlanId.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcIpxAddrEncap.description: Specify IPX encapsulation format. It is relevent if the VLAN is port based. But it's always nice to have it.

rcIpxAddrEntryStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the rcIpxAddrEntry.

rcIpxPolicyNetTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the table.

rcIpxPolicyNetTable.description: Net Table is used to store the IPX network address range. This entry is used for Net List Table.

rcIpxPolicyNetId.description: Unique ID to represent the entry in the table.

rcIpxPolicyNetToNet.name: rcIpxPolicyNetToNet
rcIpxPolicyNetToNet.description: This is used to specify a range of IPX network addresses. This is an optional parameter. The default value is NetAddr. In that case the entry refers to a single IPX network.

rcIpxPolicyNetName.description: Unique Name to represent the entry in the table. Id & Name have one-to-one relationship.

rcIpxPolicyServTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of entries in the table.

rcIpxPolicyServTable.description: Service Table is used to store Service Type and Service Name. This is used only for SAP Updates.

rcIpxPolicyServId.description: Used to store the service Id.

rcIpxPolicyServServiceType.name: rcIpxPolicyServServiceType
rcIpxPolicyServServiceType.description: Used to store the service type.

rcIpxPolicyServServiceName.name: rcIpxPolicyServServiceName
rcIpxPolicyServServiceName.description: Used to store the service Name. This is an optional parameter. If not entered, '*' is taken as default value. This is matched to any service name. Also, '*' can be used to match wildcard characters. This is supported only at the end of the service name. For Eg: Printer* will be matched to Printer1, Printer2, Printer123 etc. Service Name matching is CASE SENSITIVE

rcIpxPolicyServName.name: rcIpxPolicyServName
rcIpxPolicyServName.description: Used to store the entry name. Id & Name have one-to-one relationship.

rcIpxPolicyListId.description: Index used to uniquely Identify a group of policies in the route policy table.

rcIpxPolicyListSeqnum.name: rcIpxPolicyListSeqnum
rcIpxPolicyListSeqnum.description: Second Index used to identify a specific policy with in the route policy group (grouped by Id). This field allows users to specify different MATCH, SET parameters and an action. Also used to resolve the tie between 2 matching policies. The policy with lower sequence number is used.

rcIpxPolicyListName.name: rcIpxPolicyListName
rcIpxPolicyListName.description: Is used to group a set of policies with different sequence number. Id & Name have one-to-one relationship Different policy groups can have same sequence number, whereas with in a group the sequence must be different.

rcIpxPolicyListEnable.name: rcIpxPolicyListEnable
rcIpxPolicyListEnable.description: value specified here indicates whether the policy is enabled or not. If disabled, the policy should not be used.

rcIpxPolicyListAction.name: rcIpxPolicyListAction
rcIpxPolicyListAction.description: This determines what to do with the RIP/SAP packet. If the value is 'permit', then only in or out the packet. Otherwise, drop the packet.

rcIpxPolicyListRouteSource.name: rcIpxPolicyListRouteSource
rcIpxPolicyListRouteSource.description: Used to specify the Route Source of the route Packet. This field is used only for announce policies. For accept policies, this field is ignored. Value is one of multiple (logical 'OR') of following values: direct(1), nlsp(2), rip(4), static(8), any(15)

rcIpxPolicyListMatchNetList.name: rcIpxPolicyListMatchNetList
rcIpxPolicyListMatchNetList.description: List of networks to which this policy is applied. The Network List Name is entered. When this is not referring to any list or the Net List Table to which it is pointing to is empty, then THIS POLICY MATCHES ALL NETWORK ADDRESSES.

rcIpxPolicyListMatchServList.name: rcIpxPolicyListMatchServList
rcIpxPolicyListMatchServList.description: List of service types and Service Names to which this policy is applied. The Service List name is entered. This field is used only for SAP out/in policies. For, RIP policies, this field is discarded. When this is not referring to any list or the Service List Table to which it is pointing to is empty, then this POLICY MATCHES ALL SERVICE TYPE AND SERVICE NAME.

rcIpxPolicyListHops.name: rcIpxPolicyListHops
rcIpxPolicyListHops.description: This value is used as Hop count for out policies. If this field is 0, then Hop count is not modified. The default value is '0'. This field is also applicable only for Out Policies.

rcRadiusServAccessChallanges.description: The number of RADIUS access-challanges packets sent to this server. This does not include retransmission.

rcRadiusGlobalSnmpReAuthenticateTimer.description: Integer value representing Re-Authenticate Timer in seconds. Timer to be used to Re- Authenticate a SNMP Session.

rcRadiusGlobalSnmpAbortSessionTimer.name: rcRadiusGlobalSnmpAbortSessionTimer
rcRadiusGlobalSnmpAbortSessionTimer.description: Integer value representing the time in seconds after which the snmp session is considered expired and Radius Accounting Stop message is sent.

rcRadiusGlobalSnmpUserName.description: User name for Radius SNMP Accounting.

rcTacacsGlobalLastAddress.description: The address of the TACACS+ server that was most recently accessed

rcTacacsAuthentication.description: Determines which application will be authenticated by tacacs+.

rcTacacsServerTable.name: rcTacacsServerTable
rcTacacsServerTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the TACACS+ servers with which the client shares a secret.

rcTacacsServerEntry.name: rcTacacsServerEntry
rcTacacsServerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a TACACS+ server with which the client shares a secret.

rcTacacsServerAddressType.name: rcTacacsServerAddressType
rcTacacsServerAddressType.description: Specifies the type of IP address used on the Tacacs+ server.

rcTacacsServerAddress.name: rcTacacsServerAddress
rcTacacsServerAddress.description: The IP address of the TACACS+ server referred to in this table entry.

rcTacacsServerPortNumber.name: rcTacacsServerPortNumber
rcTacacsServerPortNumber.description: The TCP port on which the client establishes a connection to the server. A value of 0 indicates that the system specified default value is used.

rcTacacsServerConnectionType.name: rcTacacsServerConnectionType
rcTacacsServerConnectionType.description: Specifies TCP connection type between device and TACACS+ server. Either a single open connection between a device and server (SingleConnection), or open/close connection per communication session (PerSessionConnection).

rcTacacsServerConnectionStatus.name: rcTacacsServerConnectionStatus
rcTacacsServerConnectionStatus.description: Specifies status TCP connection type between device and TACACS+ server.

rcTacacsServerTimeout.name: rcTacacsServerTimeout
rcTacacsServerTimeout.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for this TACACS+ server to reply.

rcTacacsServerKey.name: rcTacacsServerKey
rcTacacsServerKey.description: Secret key to be shared with this TACACS+ server. If the key length is zero that indicates no encryption is being used.

rcTacacsServerSourceIpInterfaceEnabled.name: rcTacacsServerSourceIpInterfaceEnabled
rcTacacsServerSourceIpInterfaceEnabled.description: Specifies whether source address specification is enabled.

rcTacacsServerSourceIpInterfaceType.name: rcTacacsServerSourceIpInterfaceType
rcTacacsServerSourceIpInterfaceType.description: Specifies the type of IP address used on the interface that connects to the Tacacs+ server. If this value is unknown(0), then a system-wide default value will be used.

rcTacacsServerSourceIpInterface.name: rcTacacsServerSourceIpInterface
rcTacacsServerSourceIpInterface.description: IP address of the interface to use with this server.

rcTacacsServerPriority.name: rcTacacsServerPriority
rcTacacsServerPriority.description: Determines the order in which the TACACS+ servers will be used, when 1 is the highest priority. If more than one server share the same priority - they will be used in lexicographic order (the order of entries in this table).

rcTacacsServerRowStatus.name: rcTacacsServerRowStatus
rcTacacsServerRowStatus.description: The row status variable, can be set to destroy or createAndGo.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnFastLeaveEnable.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnFastLeaveEnable
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnFastLeaveEnable.description: Enable fast leave on this interface.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnFastLeavePortMembers.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnFastLeavePortMembers
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnFastLeavePortMembers.description: The set of ports that are enabled for fast leave.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnDiscoveredRouterPorts.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnDiscoveredRouterPorts
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnDiscoveredRouterPorts.description: list of ports that discovered by IGMP Multicast router discovery (MRDISC) protocol.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnSnoopMRouterPorts.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnSnoopMRouterPorts
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnSnoopMRouterPorts.description: The set of ports in this interface that provide connectivity to an IP Multicast router.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnSnoopMRouterExpiratio.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnSnoopMRouterExpiration
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnSnoopMRouterExpiratio.description: Multicast querier router aging time out.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnNewQuerier.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnNewQuerier
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnNewQuerier.description: The address of the New IGMP Querier on the IP subnet to which this interface is attached.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnSnoopQuerierAddr.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnSnoopQuerierAddr
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnSnoopQuerierAddr.description: The pseudo address of the IGMP Snoop Querier.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnMvrEnable.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnMvrEnable
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnMvrEnable.description: Enable or disable mcast-vlan-registration on a vlan, it is used to specified a vlan works as a mcast-vlan, maximum 16 mcast-vlan is supported.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnMvrProxyEnable.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnMvrProxyEnable
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnMvrProxyEnable.description: enable or disable mcast-vlan-registration proxy on a vlan, you must enable mcast-vlan-registration at first.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnDynamicDowngradeEnabl.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnDynamicDowngradeEnable
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnDynamicDowngradeEnabl.description: enable dynamic downgrade the IGMP version when older version query message was received.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnCompatibilityModeEnab.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnCompatibilityModeEnable
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnCompatibilityModeEnab.description: enable v2 v3 compatible mode, which will handle the IGMP v2 message in v3 interface.

rcIgmpInterfaceExtnOperVersion.name: rcIgmpInterfaceExtnOperVersion
rcIgmpInterfaceExtnOperVersion.description: The operational version of IGMP which is running on this interface.

rcIgmpStaticGrpAddr.name: rcIgmpStaticGrpAddr
rcIgmpStaticGrpAddr.description: Ip multicast address. The GrpAddress holds the starting range for the address range. If the ToGrpAddress is not entered, the it is as good as entering a single address.

rcIgmpStaticRowStatus.name: rcIgmpStaticRowStatus
rcIgmpStaticRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the rcIgmpStaticEntry.

rcIgmpStaticToGrpAddr.name: rcIgmpStaticToGrpAddr
rcIgmpStaticToGrpAddr.description: To hold the range for the GrpAddress.

rcIgmpAccessRowStatus.name: rcIgmpAccessRowStatus
rcIgmpAccessRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the rcIgmpAccessEntry.

rcIgmpSenderState.name: rcIgmpSenderState
rcIgmpSenderState.description: Indicates if a sender exists because of an IGMP access filter or not.

rcIgmpSsmGlobalDynamicLearning.name: rcIgmpSsmGlobalDynamicLearning
rcIgmpSsmGlobalDynamicLearning.description: Enable/disable dynamic learning or source/group pair from IGMPv3 report.

rcIgmpSsmGlobalAdminAction.name: rcIgmpSsmGlobalAdminAction
rcIgmpSsmGlobalAdminAction.description: Set the admin status of all the Ssm entries to enable/disable at once.

rcIgmpSsmGlobalRangeGroup.name: rcIgmpSsmGlobalRangeGroup
rcIgmpSsmGlobalRangeGroup.description: If multicast group address & RangeMask == RangeGroup, then RangeGroup is in Ssm Range. Else it is not in the range.

rcIgmpSsmIpMulticastGrp.name: rcIgmpSsmIpMulticastGrp
rcIgmpSsmIpMulticastGrp.description: This is the IP multicast group address that has default range of 232/8. This parameter should be configured by the user.

rcIgmpSsmIpSource.name: rcIgmpSsmIpSource
rcIgmpSsmIpSource.description: This is the Source's IP address that will be sending traffic to the group source. This parameter should be configured by the user.

rcIgmpSsmLearningMode.name: rcIgmpSsmLearningMode
rcIgmpSsmLearningMode.description: This is a read only field that provides information if the entry is statically configured entry (Static) or a dynamically learned entry from IGMPv3 (Dynamic). Note that Dynamic may not be used in the first step of the implementation.

rcIgmpSsmActivity.name: rcIgmpSsmActivity
rcIgmpSsmActivity.description: This is a read only field. It provides the activity on the corresponding (S,G). If the source is active and traffic is flowing to the switch, this field value should be Active, otherwise it should say non-active. This information is useful in knowing if the group has an active source or not when the group is joined by a member on the switch.

rcIgmpSsmAdminState.name: rcIgmpSsmAdminState
rcIgmpSsmAdminState.description: The admin state provides information on whether the entry is to be used or not. If the value of this field is Enabled (default), then the entry can be used. If the state is Disabled, then the entry will not be used, but will be saved for future use.

rcIgmpNewAccessRowStatus.name: rcIgmpNewAccessRowStatus
rcIgmpNewAccessRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in the rcIgmpNewAccessEntry.

rcIgmpChannelLimitPort.name: rcIgmpChannelLimitPort
rcIgmpChannelLimitPort.description: The port belong to this vlan.

rcIgmpIgapServiceAbilityAuthSuccess.name: rcIgmpIgapServiceAbilityAuthSuccess
rcIgmpIgapServiceAbilityAuthSuccess.description: The port belong to this vlan.

rcIgmpFastLeaveMode.name: rcIgmpFastLeaveMode
rcIgmpFastLeaveMode.description: Set the fast-leave mode to be used by for all fast-leave enabled IGMP interfaces.

rcIgmpCacheExtnType.name: rcIgmpCacheExtnType
rcIgmpCacheExtnType.description: It takes up either of the two values, dynamic or static depending upon whether the entry is learnt Dynamic or is added statically.

rcIgmpCacheExtnStaticPorts.name: rcIgmpCacheExtnStaticPorts
rcIgmpCacheExtnStaticPorts.description: It displays the static ports for the static joins, this would be null for the dynamic entry.

rcIgmpSnoopTraceTable.name: rcIgmpSnoopTraceTable
rcIgmpSnoopTraceTable.description: The table listing the multicast groups traversing the snoop enabled router

rcIgmpSnoopTraceEntry.name: rcIgmpSnoopTraceEntry
rcIgmpSnoopTraceEntry.description: The entry listing the multicast groups traversing the snoop enabled router
