rcIgmpSnoopGrpAddr.description: ip mcast addr of grp traversing the router

rcIgmpSnoopSrcAddr.name: rcIgmpSnoopSrcAddr
rcIgmpSnoopSrcAddr.description: Ip src addr of the mcast grp address

rcIgmpSnoopOutVlan.name: rcIgmpSnoopOutVlan
rcIgmpSnoopOutVlan.description: Egress vlan id for the mcast group

rcIgmpSnoopInPort.name: rcIgmpSnoopInPort
rcIgmpSnoopInPort.description: Ingress port for the mcast grp

rcIgmpSnoopInVlan.name: rcIgmpSnoopInVlan
rcIgmpSnoopInVlan.description: Ingress vlan id for the mcast source

rcIgmpSnoopOutPort.name: rcIgmpSnoopOutPort
rcIgmpSnoopOutPort.description: Egress port of the mcast grp

rcIgmpNewGroupTable.name: rcIgmpNewGroupTable
rcIgmpNewGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the multicast groups configured in the device.

rcIgmpNewGroupEntry.name: rcIgmpNewGroupEntry
rcIgmpNewGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an Igmp group.

rcIgmpNewGroupIpAddress.name: rcIgmpNewGroupIpAddress
rcIgmpNewGroupIpAddress.description: Multicast group Address (Class D) that others want to join. A group address can be the same for many incoming ports.

rcIgmpNewGroupMembers.name: rcIgmpNewGroupMembers
rcIgmpNewGroupMembers.description: IP Address of a source that has sent group report wishing to join this group.

rcIgmpNewGroupInPort.name: rcIgmpNewGroupInPort
rcIgmpNewGroupInPort.description: An unique value to identify a physical interface or a logical interface (VLAN), which has received Group reports from various sources.

rcIgmpNewGroupExpiration.name: rcIgmpNewGroupExpiration
rcIgmpNewGroupExpiration.description: Time left before the group report expired on this port. Only one of this variable port. This variable is updated upon receiving a group report.

rcIgmpNewGroupIfIndex.name: rcIgmpNewGroupIfIndex
rcIgmpNewGroupIfIndex.description: An unique value to identify a physical interface or a logical interface (VLAN), which has received Group reports from various sources.

rcIgmpNewGroupMemberState.name: rcIgmpNewGroupMemberState
rcIgmpNewGroupMemberState.description: Used for IGAP, to indicated member state.

rcIgmpNewGroupSessionTime.name: rcIgmpNewGroupSessionTime
rcIgmpNewGroupSessionTime.description: Used for IGAP, to indicated the session time in seconds for the member. Session time is started after traffic is available to member. It can be also called AccountingTime since its values correspondes to the accounting duration of IGAP user session.

rcIgmpMvrGroupTable.name: rcIgmpMvrGroupTable
rcIgmpMvrGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the mcast-vlan-registration groups.

rcIgmpMvrGroupEntry.name: rcIgmpMvrGroupEntry
rcIgmpMvrGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the rcIgmpMvrGroupTable.

rcIgmpMvrGroupVlanId.name: rcIgmpMvrGroupVlanId
rcIgmpMvrGroupVlanId.description: The igmp snoop enabled vlan this group belongs to.

rcIgmpMvrVlanTable.name: rcIgmpMvrVlanTable
rcIgmpMvrVlanTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the mcast vlans in mcast-vlan-registration.

rcIgmpMvrVlanEntry.name: rcIgmpMvrVlanEntry
rcIgmpMvrVlanEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the rcIgmpMvrVlanTable.

rcIgmpMvrVlanMvrVlanProxy.name: rcIgmpMvrVlanMvrVlanProxy
rcIgmpMvrVlanMvrVlanProxy.description: working mode of this mcast-vlan, proxy or not.

rcIgmpMvrVlanSourceAddress.name: rcIgmpMvrVlanSourceAddress
rcIgmpMvrVlanSourceAddress.description: querier address for the source in this mcast-vlan.

rcIgmpMvrReceiverTable.name: rcIgmpMvrReceiverTable
rcIgmpMvrReceiverTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the mcast vlans and receiver vlans in mcast-vlan-registration.

rcIgmpMvrReceiverEntry.name: rcIgmpMvrReceiverEntry
rcIgmpMvrReceiverEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the rcIgmpMvrGroupTable.

rcIgmpMvrReceiverVlanId.name: rcIgmpMvrReceiverVlanId
rcIgmpMvrReceiverVlanId.description: The id of receiver vlan that bound to mcast-vlan.

rcIgmpGenerateTrap.name: rcIgmpGenerateTrap
rcIgmpGenerateTrap.description: Enabling the IGMP to generate trap.

rcIgmpGenerateLog.name: rcIgmpGenerateLog
rcIgmpGenerateLog.description: Enabling the IGMP to generate log.

rcPlugOptModEntry.name: rcPlugOptModEntry
rcPlugOptModEntry.description: Entry containing info. for a particular port

rcPlugOptModPortIndex.name: rcPlugOptModPortIndex
rcPlugOptModPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port on a blade or line-card.

rcPlugOptModDdmStatusMask.name: rcPlugOptModDdmStatusMask
rcPlugOptModDdmStatusMask.description: Each bit other than ddm-ok represents a specific error. Any combination of error bits is allowed.

rcPlugOptModCalibration.name: rcPlugOptModCalibration
rcPlugOptModCalibration.description: The identifier value indicates type of calibration.

rcPlugOptModPowerMeasure.name: rcPlugOptModPowerMeasure
rcPlugOptModPowerMeasure.description: The identifier value indicates type of external power.

rcPlugOptModConnectorType.name: rcPlugOptModConnectorType
rcPlugOptModConnectorType.description: The connector type is a 16 character field that contains ASCII characters, left-aligned and padded on the right with ASCII spaces. This is an assigned name that indicates some characteristic of the layer-1 interface.

rcPlugOptModVendorName.name: rcPlugOptModVendorName
rcPlugOptModVendorName.description: The vendor name is a 16 character field that contains ASCII characters, left-aligned and padded on the right with ASCII spaces. The vendor name shall be the full name of the corporation, a commonly accepted abbreviation of the name, the SCSI company code, or the stock exchange code for the corporation.

rcPlugOptModVendorPartNumber.name: rcPlugOptModVendorPartNumber
rcPlugOptModVendorPartNumber.description: The vendor part number is a 16 byte field that contains ASCII characters, left-aligned and padded on the right with ASCII spaces, defining the vendor part number or product name.

rcPlugOptModVendorRevNumber.name: rcPlugOptModVendorRevNumber
rcPlugOptModVendorRevNumber.description: The vendor revision number is a 4-byte field that contains ASCII characters, left-aligned and padded on the right with ASCII spaces, defining the vendor product revision number.

rcPlugOptModVendorSN.name: rcPlugOptModVendorSN
rcPlugOptModVendorSN.description: The vendor serial number is a 16 character field that contains ASCII characters, left-aligned and padded on the right with ASCII spaces, defining the vendor serial number for the transceiver.

rcPlugOptModVendorDateCode.name: rcPlugOptModVendorDateCode
rcPlugOptModVendorDateCode.description: The date code is an 8-byte field that contains the vendor's date code in ASCII. This field is mandatory and takes the form: YYMMDDLC where YY is the 2 low order digits of the year (00=2000), MM is the month, 01 thru 12, DD is the day, 01 thru 31, and LC is an optional vendor specific lot code.

rcPlugOptModPEC.name: rcPlugOptModPEC
rcPlugOptModPEC.description: This is a 16 byte left-justified ASCII field that records the Nortel Product Equipment Code order number for the module. Nortel part numbers are 9 bytes long, so the 10th through 16th byte should be NULL.

rcPlugOptModCLEI.name: rcPlugOptModCLEI
rcPlugOptModCLEI.description: This is a 10 byte left-justified ASCII field that records the Nortel supplied Common Language Equipment Identifier code for the device. The CLEI code is a Telcordia human-readable representation of the 1D barcode.

rcPlugOptModSupportsDDM.name: rcPlugOptModSupportsDDM
rcPlugOptModSupportsDDM.description: This boolean indicates whether or not the device supports the DDM capability.

rcPlugOptModAux1Monitoring.name: rcPlugOptModAux1Monitoring
rcPlugOptModAux1Monitoring.description: This value tells what Aux1 is measuring.The values are as follows: 0 Auxiliary monitoring not implemented 1 APD Bias Voltage mV (units of 10 mV) 2 Reserved 3 TEC Current (mA) 4 Laser Temperature 5 Laser Wavelength 6 +5V Supply Voltage 7 +3.3V Supply Voltage 8 +1.8V Supply Voltage 9 -5.2V Supply Voltage 10 +5.0V Supply Current (unit of 100 uA) 13 +3.3V Supply Current (unit of 100 uA) 14 +1.8V Supply Current (unit of 100 uA) 15 -5.2V Supply Current (unit of 100 uA)

rcPlugOptModAux2Monitoring.name: rcPlugOptModAux2Monitoring
rcPlugOptModAux2Monitoring.description: This value tells you what AUX2 is measuring.The values are as follows: 0 Auxiliary monitoring not implemented 1 APD Bias Voltage mV (units of 10 mV) 2 Reserved 3 TEC Current (mA) 4 Laser Temperature 5 Laser Wavelength 6 +5V Supply Voltage 7 +3.3V Supply Voltage 8 +1.8V Supply Voltage 9 -5.2V Supply Voltage 10 +5.0V Supply Current (unit of 100 uA) 13 +3.3V Supply Current (unit of 100 uA) 14 +1.8V Supply Current (unit of 100 uA) 15 -5.2V Supply Current (unit of 100 uA)

rcPlugOptModWaveLength.name: rcPlugOptModWaveLength
rcPlugOptModWaveLength.description: Nominal transmitter output wavelength at room temperature. It is expressed in nano-meters.

rcPlugOptModTemperature.name: rcPlugOptModTemperature
rcPlugOptModTemperature.description: This value represents the internally measured module temperature. It is expressed in units of 1/256 of a degree Celsius and can range from -40C to +125C with 0.0001 accuracy.The most significant byte is the signed integer part of the number and the least significant byte is the fraction.

rcPlugOptModTemperatureHighAlarmThreshol.name: rcPlugOptModTemperatureHighAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModTemperatureHighAlarmThreshol.description: This value represents the vendor specified high temperature threshold. If the device temperature exceeds this value, a temperature high is asserted. It is expressed in the same units as the measured temperature.

rcPlugOptModTemperatureLowAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModTemperatureLowAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModTemperatureLowAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low temperature threshold. If the device temperature falls below this value, a temperature low is asserted. It is expressed in the same units as the measured temperature.

rcPlugOptModTemperatureHighWarningThresh.name: rcPlugOptModTemperatureHighWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModTemperatureHighWarningThresh.description: This value represents the vendor specified high temperature warning threshold. If the device temperature exceeds this value, a temperature high warning is asserted. It is expressed in the same units as the measured temperature.

rcPlugOptModTemperatureLowWarningThresho.name: rcPlugOptModTemperatureLowWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModTemperatureLowWarningThresho.description: This value represents the vendor specified low temperature warning threshold. If the device temperature falls below this value, a temperature low warning is asserted. It is expressed in the same units as the measured temperature.

rcPlugOptModVoltage.name: rcPlugOptModVoltage
rcPlugOptModVoltage.description: This value represents the internally measured supply voltage. It is a positive number expressed in microvolts and can range from 0 to 65535 mV.

rcPlugOptModVoltageHighAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModVoltageHighAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModVoltageHighAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high voltage threshold. If the measured voltage exceeds this value, a high voltage is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in microvolts.

rcPlugOptModVoltageLowAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModVoltageLowAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModVoltageLowAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low voltage threshold. If the measured voltage falls below this value, a low voltage is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in microvolts.

rcPlugOptModVoltageHighWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModVoltageHighWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModVoltageHighWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high voltage warning threshold. If the measured voltage exceeds this value, a high voltage warning is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in microvolts.

rcPlugOptModVoltageLowWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModVoltageLowWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModVoltageLowWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low voltage warning threshold. If the measured voltage falls below this value, a low voltage warning is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in microvolts.

rcPlugOptModBias.name: rcPlugOptModBias
rcPlugOptModBias.description: This value represents the internally measured transmitter laser bias current. It is a positive number expressed in units of 2 microamps and can range from 0 to 131 mA with 0.0001 accuracy.

rcPlugOptModBiasHighAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModBiasHighAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModBiasHighAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high current threshold. If the measured bias current exceeds this value, a high current alarm is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of 2 microamps and can range from 0 to 131 mA with 0.0001 accuracy.

rcPlugOptModBiasLowAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModBiasLowAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModBiasLowAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low current threshold. If the measured bias current falls below this value, a low current is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of 2 microamps and can range from 0 to 131 mA with 0.0001 accuracy.

rcPlugOptModBiasHighWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModBiasHighWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModBiasHighWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high current warning threshold. If the measured bias current exceeds this value, a high current warning is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of 2 microamps and can range from 0 to 131 mA with 0.0001 accuracy.

rcPlugOptModBiasLowWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModBiasLowWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModBiasLowWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low current warning threshold. If the measured bias current falls below this value, a low current warning is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of 2 microamps and can range from 0 to 131 mA with 0.0001 accuracy.

rcPlugOptModTxPower.name: rcPlugOptModTxPower
rcPlugOptModTxPower.description: This value represents the internally measured coupled TX output power. It is a positive number expressed in units of micro watts and can range from 0 to 65.535 mW (-40 to 18.16 dBm).

rcPlugOptModTxPowerHighAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModTxPowerHighAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModTxPowerHighAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high transmit power threshold. If the measured transmitter power exceeds this value, a transmitter power high is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of micro watts and can range from 0 to 65.535 mW (-40 to 18.16 dBm).

rcPlugOptModTxPowerLowAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModTxPowerLowAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModTxPowerLowAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low transmit power threshold. If the measured transmitter power falls below this value, a transmitter power low is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of micro watts and can range from 0 to 65.535 mW (-40 to 18.16 dBm).

rcPlugOptModTxPowerHighWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModTxPowerHighWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModTxPowerHighWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high transmit power warning threshold. If the measured transmitter power exceeds this value, a transmitter power high warning is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of units of micro watts and can range from 0 to 65.535 mW (-40 to 18.16 dBm).

rcPlugOptModTxPowerLowWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModTxPowerLowWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModTxPowerLowWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low transmit power warning threshold. If the measured transmitter power falls below this value, a transmitter power low warning is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of micro watts and can range from 0 to 65.535 mW (-40 to 18.16 dBm).

rcPlugOptModRxPower.name: rcPlugOptModRxPower
rcPlugOptModRxPower.description: This value represents the internally measured received power. It is a positive number expressed in units of micro watts and can range from 0 to 65.535 mW (-40 to 18.16 dBm).

rcPlugOptModRxPowerHighAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModRxPowerHighAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModRxPowerHighAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high receiver power threshold. If the measured received power exceeds this value, a receiver power high is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of micro watts and can range from 0 to 65.535 mW (-40 to 18.16 dBm).

rcPlugOptModRxPowerLowAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModRxPowerLowAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModRxPowerLowAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low receiver power threshold. If the measured received power falls below this value, a receiver power low is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of micro watts and can range from 0 to 65.535 mW (-40 to 18.16 dBm).

rcPlugOptModRxPowerHighWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModRxPowerHighWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModRxPowerHighWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high receiver power warning threshold. If the measured received power exceeds this value, a receiver power high warning is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of units of micro watts and can range from 0 to 65.535 uW (-40 to 18.16 dBm).

rcPlugOptModRxPowerLowWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModRxPowerLowWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModRxPowerLowWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low receiver power warning threshold. If the measured received power falls below this value, a receiver power low warning is asserted. It is a positive number expressed in units of units of micro watts and can range from 0 to 65.535 mW (-40 to 18.16 dBm).

rcPlugOptModAux1.name: rcPlugOptModAux1
rcPlugOptModAux1.description: This represents the internally measured A/D value specified.

rcPlugOptModAux1HighAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModAux1HighAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModAux1HighAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high Aux1 threshold.

rcPlugOptModAux1LowAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModAux1LowAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModAux1LowAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low Aux1 threshold.

rcPlugOptModAux1HighWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModAux1HighWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModAux1HighWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high Aux1 warning threshold.

rcPlugOptModAux1LowWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModAux1LowWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModAux1LowWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low Aux1 warning threshold.

rcPlugOptModAux2.name: rcPlugOptModAux2
rcPlugOptModAux2.description: This represents the internally measured A/D value specified.

rcPlugOptModAux2HighAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModAux2HighAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModAux2HighAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high Aux1 threshold.

rcPlugOptModAux2LowAlarmThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModAux2LowAlarmThreshold
rcPlugOptModAux2LowAlarmThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low Aux1 threshold.

rcPlugOptModAux2HighWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModAux2HighWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModAux2HighWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified high Aux1 warning threshold.

rcPlugOptModAux2LowWarningThreshold.name: rcPlugOptModAux2LowWarningThreshold
rcPlugOptModAux2LowWarningThreshold.description: This value represents the vendor specified low Aux1 warning threshold.

rcPlugOptModTemperatureStatus.name: rcPlugOptModTemperatureStatus
rcPlugOptModTemperatureStatus.description: Used to indicate the current temperature status

rcPlugOptModVoltageStatus.name: rcPlugOptModVoltageStatus
rcPlugOptModVoltageStatus.description: Used to indicate the current voltage status

rcPlugOptModBiasStatus.name: rcPlugOptModBiasStatus
rcPlugOptModBiasStatus.description: Used to indicate the current laser bias status

rcPlugOptModTxPowerStatus.name: rcPlugOptModTxPowerStatus
rcPlugOptModTxPowerStatus.description: Used to indicate the current transmitter power status

rcPlugOptModRxPowerStatus.name: rcPlugOptModRxPowerStatus
rcPlugOptModRxPowerStatus.description: Used to indicate the current receiver power status

rcPlugOptModAux1Status.name: rcPlugOptModAux1Status
rcPlugOptModAux1Status.description: Used to indicate the current Aux1 status

rcPlugOptModAux2Status.name: rcPlugOptModAux2Status
rcPlugOptModAux2Status.description: Used to indicate the current Aux2 status

rcPlugOptModDdmMonitor.name: rcPlugOptModDdmMonitor
rcPlugOptModDdmMonitor.description: Enable/disable the global polling monitor for DDM

rcPlugOptModDdmMonitorInterval.name: rcPlugOptModDdmMonitorInterval
rcPlugOptModDdmMonitorInterval.description: Indicate the interval in which the DDM alert registers is polled

rcPlugOptModDdmTrapSend.name: rcPlugOptModDdmTrapSend
rcPlugOptModDdmTrapSend.description: Enable/disable the global ddm trap send to SNMP manager

rcPlugOptModDdmAlarmPortdown.name: rcPlugOptModDdmAlarmPortdown
rcPlugOptModDdmAlarmPortdown.description: Enable/disable the global portdown option when ddm alarm occurs

rcVrrpPingVirtualAddrEnable.name: rcVrrpPingVirtualAddrEnable
rcVrrpPingVirtualAddrEnable.description: Used to configure whether this device should respond to pings directed to a virtual router's IP address.

rcVrrpTrapStateTransitionType.name: rcVrrpTrapStateTransitionType
rcVrrpTrapStateTransitionType.description: Potential types of state transitions. Used by rcVrrpTrapStateTransition trap.

rcVrrpTrapStateTransitionCause.name: rcVrrpTrapStateTransitionCause
rcVrrpTrapStateTransitionCause.description: Potential types of causes that will generate a rcVrrpTrapStateTransition trap.

rcVrrpOperTable.name: rcVrrpOperTable
rcVrrpOperTable.description: Operations table for a VRRP router which consists of a sequence (i.e., one or more conceptual rows) of 'rcVrrpOperEntry' items.

rcVrrpOperEntry.name: rcVrrpOperEntry
rcVrrpOperEntry.description: An entry in the rcVrrpOperTable containing the operational characteristics of a virtual router. On a VRRP router, a given virtual router is identified by a combination of the IF index and VRID.

rcVrrpOperVrId.name: rcVrrpOperVrId
rcVrrpOperVrId.description: This object contains the Virtual Router Identifier (VRID).

rcVrrpOperIpAddr.name: rcVrrpOperIpAddr
rcVrrpOperIpAddr.description: The assigned IP addresses that a virtual router is responsible for backing up.

rcVrrpOperVirtualMacAddr.name: rcVrrpOperVirtualMacAddr
rcVrrpOperVirtualMacAddr.description: The virtual MAC address of the virtual router. This is derived as follows: 00-00-5E-00-01-<VRID>. Where the first three octets consist of the IANA's OUI; The next two octets indicate the address block of the VRRP protocol; and the remaining octets consist of the VRID. Although this object can be derived from the 'rcVrrpOperVrId' object, it is included here, for completeness, so that it is easily obtainable by a management application and can be included in VRRP-related SNMP traps.

rcVrrpOperState.name: rcVrrpOperState
rcVrrpOperState.description: The current state of the virtual router.

rcVrrpOperControl.name: rcVrrpOperControl
rcVrrpOperControl.description: This object will enable/disable the virtual router function. Setting the value to 'enabled', will transition the state of the router from 'initialize to 'backup'; Setting the value to 'disabled', will tranisition the router from 'master' or 'backup' to 'initialize'.

rcVrrpOperPriority.name: rcVrrpOperPriority
rcVrrpOperPriority.description: This object specifies the priority for the virtual router (e.g., master election) with respect to other virtual routers that are backing up a one or more associated IP addresses. Higher values imply higher priority. A priority of '0', although not settable, is used to indicate that this router has ceased to particpate in VRRP and a backup virtual router should transition \ to become a new master. A priority of 255 is used for the router that owns the associated IP address(es).

rcVrrpOperIpAddrCount.name: rcVrrpOperIpAddrCount
rcVrrpOperIpAddrCount.description: The number of IP addresses that are associated with this virtual router. This number is equal to the number of rows in the vrrpAssoIpAddrTable that correspond to a given IF index/VRID pair.

rcVrrpOperMasterIpAddr.name: rcVrrpOperMasterIpAddr
rcVrrpOperMasterIpAddr.description: The master router's real (primary) IP address. This is the IP address listed as the source in VRRP advertisement last received by this virtual router

rcVrrpOperAuthType.name: rcVrrpOperAuthType
rcVrrpOperAuthType.description: Authentication type used for VRRP protocol exchanges between virtual routers.

rcVrrpOperAuthKey.name: rcVrrpOperAuthKey
rcVrrpOperAuthKey.description: The Authentication Key. If the virtual router's Authorization Type is 'simpleTextPassword', and the key length is shorter than 8 octets, the agent will left adjust and zero fill to 8 octets. When read, rcVrrpOperAuthKey always returns an Octet String of length zero.

rcVrrpOperHMACMD5Key.name: rcVrrpOperHMACMD5Key
rcVrrpOperHMACMD5Key.description: The Authentication Key. If the virtual router's 'Authorization Type' is 'ipAuthenticationHeader', and the key length is shorter than 16 octets, the agent will left adjust and zero fill to 16 octets. When read, rcVrrpOperHMACMD5Key always returns an Octet String of length zero.

rcVrrpOperAdvertisementInterval.name: rcVrrpOperAdvertisementInterval
rcVrrpOperAdvertisementInterval.description: This is the time interval, in seconds, between sending advertisement messages. Only the master router sends VRRP advertisements.

rcVrrpOperPreemptMode.name: rcVrrpOperPreemptMode
rcVrrpOperPreemptMode.description: Controls whether a higher priority virtual router will preempt a lower priority master.

rcVrrpOperVirtualRouterUpTime.name: rcVrrpOperVirtualRouterUpTime
rcVrrpOperVirtualRouterUpTime.description: This is the time interval (in hundredths of a second) since this virtual router was initialized.

rcVrrpOperRowStatus.name: rcVrrpOperRowStatus
rcVrrpOperRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. Setting this object to 'createAndGo' results in enabling the VRRP protocol for this virtual router. The information required to actually create the conceptual row may be included in the SET primitive or may be initialized by the agent on the virtual router. Destroying the entry or setting it to 'notInService' disables VRRP on this virtual router.

rcVrrpOperCriticalIpAddr.name: rcVrrpOperCriticalIpAddr
rcVrrpOperCriticalIpAddr.description: IP address of the interface that will cause a shutdown event.

rcVrrpOperHoldDownTimer.name: rcVrrpOperHoldDownTimer
rcVrrpOperHoldDownTimer.description: Used to configure the amount of time (in seconds) to wait before preempting the current vrrp master.

rcVrrpOperHoldDownState.name: rcVrrpOperHoldDownState
rcVrrpOperHoldDownState.description: Used to indicate the hold-down state of this vrrp interface. If the hold-down timer is operational this variable will be set to 'active'. 'dormant' otherwise.

rcVrrpOperHoldDownTimeRemaining.name: rcVrrpOperHoldDownTimeRemaining
rcVrrpOperHoldDownTimeRemaining.description: Used to indicate the amount of time (in seconds) left before the rcVrrpOperHoldDownTimer will expire.

rcVrrpOperAction.name: rcVrrpOperAction
rcVrrpOperAction.description: Used to trigger an action on this vrrp interface.

rcVrrpOperCriticalIpAddrEnable.name: rcVrrpOperCriticalIpAddrEnable
rcVrrpOperCriticalIpAddrEnable.description: Indicate if an user-defined critical IP address should be enabled. 'NO' = use the default IP address (0.0.0.0). No effect if an user-defined IP address does not exist.

rcVrrpOperBackUpMaster.name: rcVrrpOperBackUpMaster
rcVrrpOperBackUpMaster.description: Enable the backup VRRP switch traffic forwarding. This will reduce the traffic in IST link in the time of SMLT.

rcVrrpOperBackUpMasterState.name: rcVrrpOperBackUpMasterState
rcVrrpOperBackUpMasterState.description: Indicate whether backup VRRP switch traffic forwarding is enabled or not.

rcVrrpOperFasterAdvInterval.name: rcVrrpOperFasterAdvInterval
rcVrrpOperFasterAdvInterval.description: This is the faster advertisement interval, in milliseconds, between sending advertisement messages. When the faster advertisement interval enable is checked, the faster advertisement interval is being used instead of the regular advertisement interval

rcVrrpOperFasterAdvIntervalEnable.name: rcVrrpOperFasterAdvIntervalEnable
rcVrrpOperFasterAdvIntervalEnable.description: Used to indicate if the Faster Advertisement Interval should be used. 'Disable' means use regular Advertisement interval.

rcVrrpTrapStateTransition.name: rcVrrpTrapStateTransition
rcVrrpTrapStateTransition.description: A rcVrrpTrapStateTransition trap signifies a state transition has occurred on a particular vrrp interface. Implementation of this trap is optional.

rcVrrpRouterStatsEntry.name: rcVrrpRouterStatsEntry
rcVrrpRouterStatsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing statistics information about a given virtual router.

rcVrrpStatsVrId.name: rcVrrpStatsVrId
rcVrrpStatsVrId.description: This object contains the Virtual Router Identifier (VRID).

rcVrrpStatsBecomeMaster.name: rcVrrpStatsBecomeMaster
rcVrrpStatsBecomeMaster.description: The total number of times that this virtual router's state has transitioned from BACKUP to MASTER.

rcVrrpStatsAdvertiseRcvd.name: rcVrrpStatsAdvertiseRcvd
rcVrrpStatsAdvertiseRcvd.description: The total number of VRRP advertisements received by this virtual router.

rcVrrpStatsAdvertiseIntervalErrors.name: rcVrrpStatsAdvertiseIntervalErrors
rcVrrpStatsAdvertiseIntervalErrors.description: The total number of VRRP advertisement packets received for which the advertisement interval is different than the one configured for the local virtual router.

rcVrrpStatsPasswdSecurityViolations.name: rcVrrpStatsPasswdSecurityViolations
rcVrrpStatsPasswdSecurityViolations.description: The total number of VRRP packets received that do not pass the simple text password authentification check.

rcVrrpStatsHmacSecurityViolations.name: rcVrrpStatsHmacSecurityViolations
rcVrrpStatsHmacSecurityViolations.description: The total number of VRRP packets received that do not pass the HMAC-MD5-96 authentification check.

rcVrrpStatsIpTtlErrors.name: rcVrrpStatsIpTtlErrors
rcVrrpStatsIpTtlErrors.description: The total number of VRRP packets received by the virtual router with IP TTL (Time-To-Live) not equal to 255.

rcVrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsRcvd.name: rcVrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsRcvd
rcVrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsRcvd.description: The total number of VRRP packets received by the virtual router with a priority of '0'.

rcVrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsSent.name: rcVrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsSent
rcVrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsSent.description: The total number of VRRP packets sent by the virtual router with a priority of '0'.

rcVrrpStatsInvalidTypePktsRcvd.name: rcVrrpStatsInvalidTypePktsRcvd
rcVrrpStatsInvalidTypePktsRcvd.description: The number of VRRP packets received by the virtual router with an invalid value in the 'type' field.

rcVrrpStatsAddressListErrors.name: rcVrrpStatsAddressListErrors
rcVrrpStatsAddressListErrors.description: Packets received address list the address list does not match the locally configured list for the virtual router.

rcVrrpStatsUnknownAuthType.name: rcVrrpStatsUnknownAuthType
rcVrrpStatsUnknownAuthType.description: Packets received with an unknown authentication type.

rcVrrpStatsAuthTypeErrors.name: rcVrrpStatsAuthTypeErrors
rcVrrpStatsAuthTypeErrors.description: Packets received with 'Auth Type' not equal to the locally configured authentication method ('vrrpOperAuthType').

rcL2RedundancyHaCpuState.name: rcL2RedundancyHaCpuState
rcL2RedundancyHaCpuState.description: Indicate the Ha-CPU state. initialization - indicate the CPU is in this state. oneWayActive - Modules that need to be synchronized have registered with the framework (either locally or a message was received from remote CPU (1). twoWayActive - Modules that need to be synchronized have registered with the framework (either locally or a message was received from remote CPU (2). synchronized - Table based synchroniztion was completed on the current CPU (3). remoteIncompatible - CPUs framework version is incompatible with the remote CPU (4). error - If an invalid event is generated in a given state the CPU enters Error state (5). disabled - High Availability is not enabled (6). peerNotConnected - no peer connection is established (7). peerConnected - peer connection is established (8). lostPeerConnection - lost connection to peer/Standby CPU (9). notSynchronized - Table Sync is not complete (10).

rcL2RedundancyHaEvent.name: rcL2RedundancyHaEvent
rcL2RedundancyHaEvent.description: Indicate the Ha event status. restart (0) - Causes the state machine to restart systemRegistrationDone (1)- Causes the CPU to transfer to One Way or Two Way Active state. Locally or message received from remote CPU. tableSynchronizationDone (2) - Causes the CPU to transfer to Synchronized state. versionIncompatible (3) - Causes the CPU to go to Remote Incompatible state noEvent (4) - Means no event has occured uptill now.

rcL2RedundancyStandbyCpu.name: rcL2RedundancyStandbyCpu
rcL2RedundancyStandbyCpu.description: Indicate if the L2 Redundancy is enabled on the standby CPU.

rcNtpGlobalInterval.name: rcNtpGlobalInterval
rcNtpGlobalInterval.description: Time interval between successive NTP updates in minutes.

rcNtpServerTable.name: rcNtpServerTable
rcNtpServerTable.description: The NTP server table. This table lists the information of a NTP server

rcNtpServerAddress.name: rcNtpServerAddress
rcNtpServerAddress.description: Server IP address of NTP time source referred to in this table entry.

rcNtpServerEnable.name: rcNtpServerEnable
rcNtpServerEnable.description: Enable or disable this server for participation in time update.

rcNtpServerAuthentication.name: rcNtpServerAuthentication
rcNtpServerAuthentication.description: Enable or disable the MD5 Authentication on this serve.

rcNtpServerKeyId.name: rcNtpServerKeyId
rcNtpServerKeyId.description: Public Key used to generate MD5 digest for this server.

rcNtpServerAccessAttempts.name: rcNtpServerAccessAttempts
rcNtpServerAccessAttempts.description: The number of NTP requests sent to this server

rcNtpServerAccessSuccess.name: rcNtpServerAccessSuccess
rcNtpServerAccessSuccess.description: The number of times this server was selected to update the time

rcNtpServerAccessFailure.name: rcNtpServerAccessFailure
rcNtpServerAccessFailure.description: The number of times this server was rejected from updating the time

rcNtpServerPrecision.name: rcNtpServerPrecision
rcNtpServerPrecision.description: NTP precision of this server in seconds

rcNtpServerSynchronized.name: rcNtpServerSynchronized
rcNtpServerSynchronized.description: Status of synchronization with this server

rcNtpKeyTable.name: rcNtpKeyTable
rcNtpKeyTable.description: The NTP key table. This table lists the private key of the public key Id

rcNtpKeyId.name: rcNtpKeyId
rcNtpKeyId.description: Public Key used to generate MD5 digest

rcNtpKeySecret.name: rcNtpKeySecret
rcNtpKeySecret.description: Private Key used to generate MD5 Digest

rcSvlanTable.name: rcSvlanTable
rcSvlanTable.description: A list of possible levels and their corresponding ether type. The number of entries is eight.

rcSvlanLevel.name: rcSvlanLevel
rcSvlanLevel.description: A value that identifies the switch level associated with this entry.

rcSvlanEtherType.name: rcSvlanEtherType
rcSvlanEtherType.description: The ether type value is used for svlan tagging.

rc2kChassisPortOperStatus.name: rc2kChassisPortOperStatus
rc2kChassisPortOperStatus.description: A bit array that contains the oper-status of the ports in the device. 2 bits are used for each port. The high order 2 bits of the first octet represent port #0, the next two bits are used for port #1, etc. The status is encoded with the following scheme : value meaning ----- ------- 0 no-link (admin=up, oper=down) 1 up (admin=up, oper=up) 2 down (admin=down, oper=down) 3 testing (admin=test, oper=test)

rc2kChassisTemperature.name: rc2kChassisTemperature
rc2kChassisTemperature.description: Used to indicate the core operating temperature of the chassis. This value represents the degree in celsius of the air inside the chassis.

rc2kChassisAmbientLowerTemperature.name: rc2kChassisAmbientLowerTemperature
rc2kChassisAmbientLowerTemperature.description: Used to indicate the temperature of the air entering the fan at the lower half of the chassis.

rc2kChassisAmbientUpperTemperature.name: rc2kChassisAmbientUpperTemperature
rc2kChassisAmbientUpperTemperature.description: Used to indicate the temperature of the air entering the fan at the upper half of the chassis.

rc2kCpuEthernetPortEntry.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortEntry
rc2kCpuEthernetPortEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of 2k CPU Ethernet Port

rc2kCpuEthernetPortAdminStatus.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortAdminStatus
rc2kCpuEthernetPortAdminStatus.description: Used to configure the admininstrative status of the port.

rc2kCpuEthernetPortOperStatus.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortOperStatus
rc2kCpuEthernetPortOperStatus.description: Used to indicate the administrative status of the port.

rc2kCpuEthernetPortAddr.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortAddr
rc2kCpuEthernetPortAddr.description: Used to configure the port's IP address

rc2kCpuEthernetPortMask.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortMask
rc2kCpuEthernetPortMask.description: Used to configure the port's net mask

rc2kCpuEthernetPortGateway.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortGateway
rc2kCpuEthernetPortGateway.description: Used to configure the the IP address of the gateway that should be used to forward IP traffic.

rc2kCpuEthernetPortNetwork.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortNetwork
rc2kCpuEthernetPortNetwork.description: Used to configure the network that can be used to remotely manage this device.

rc2kCpuEthernetPortAutoNegotiate.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortAutoNegotiate
rc2kCpuEthernetPortAutoNegotiate.description: Used to configure auto-negotiation on this port.

rc2kCpuEthernetPortAdminDuplex.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortAdminDuplex
rc2kCpuEthernetPortAdminDuplex.description: Used to configure the administrative duplex setting for this port.

rc2kCpuEthernetPortOperDuplex.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortOperDuplex
rc2kCpuEthernetPortOperDuplex.description: Used to indicate the operational duplex setting for this port.

rc2kCpuEthernetPortAdminSpeed.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortAdminSpeed

rc2kCpuEthernetPortEnableBootp.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortEnableBootp
rc2kCpuEthernetPortEnableBootp.description: Used to enable/disable the Bootp feature on this port.

rc2kCpuEthernetPortMgmtMacAddr.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortMgmtMacAddr
rc2kCpuEthernetPortMgmtMacAddr.description: Used to indicate the mac addr for this port.

rc2kCpuSerialPortEntry.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortEntry
rc2kCpuSerialPortEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of 2k CPU Serial Port

rc2kCpuSerialPortMode.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortMode
rc2kCpuSerialPortMode.description: Used to configure the mode this port should operate in.

rc2kCpuSerialPortAdminStatus.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortAdminStatus
rc2kCpuSerialPortAdminStatus.description: Used to configure the administrative status setting for this port.

rc2kCpuSerialPortOperStatus.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortOperStatus
rc2kCpuSerialPortOperStatus.description: Used to indicate the operational status setting for this port.

rc2kCpuSerialPortBaudRate.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortBaudRate
rc2kCpuSerialPortBaudRate.description: Used to configure the baud rate of this port.

rc2kCpuSerialPortDataBits.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortDataBits
rc2kCpuSerialPortDataBits.description: Used to configure the number of data bits, per byte of data, this port should send/receive.

rc2kCpuSerialPortMyAddr.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortMyAddr
rc2kCpuSerialPortMyAddr.description: Used to configure this port's IP address. Used for both 'slip' and 'ppp' modes.

rc2kCpuSerialPortPeerAddr.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortPeerAddr
rc2kCpuSerialPortPeerAddr.description: Used to configure the peer's IP address. Used for both 'slip' and 'ppp' modes.

rc2kCpuSerialPortSlipMtu.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortSlipMtu
rc2kCpuSerialPortSlipMtu.description: Used to configure the MTU for this port. Used for slip only.

rc2kCpuSerialPortSlipTxRxCompress.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortSlipTxRxCompress
rc2kCpuSerialPortSlipTxRxCompress.description: Used to enable/disable compression of TCP/IP packet headers on this port. Used for slip only.

rc2kCpuSerialPortSlipRxCompress.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortSlipRxCompress
rc2kCpuSerialPortSlipRxCompress.description: Used to enable/disable compression for receiving packets on this port. Used for slip only.

rc2kCpuSerialPortPppConfigFile.name: rc2kCpuSerialPortPppConfigFile
rc2kCpuSerialPortPppConfigFile.description: Used to configure the configuration file to use for PPP.

rc2kDeviceGlobalEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of 2k CPU Ethernet Port

rc2kDeviceSeparator1.description: This leaf is used to provide a separation between tables. No meaningful information is stored in this variable.

rc2kDeviceFlashFileEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of 2k CPU Serial Port

rc2kDevicePcmciaPresent.description: pcmcia is a slower device. This leaf is used to stop the access into pcmcia file table when it got the end of flash file table.

rc2kDevicePcmciaFileEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of 2k CPU Serial Port

rc2kDeviceSeparator2.description: This leaf is used to provide a separation between tables. No meaningful information is stored in this variable.

rc2kBootConfigSlot.description: slot number, tattoo use 3 as cpu slot, 4 is not valid cpu slot number

rc2kBootConfigEnable8616ReAutoneg.description: Enable re-autoneg for 8616SX Cards (Intel GMAC fix)

rc2kCardFrontType.name: rc2kCardFrontType
rc2kCardFrontType.description: Used to indicate card types in the Accelar 8000 product families. For Accelar 8000 devices, all cards use an encoded value according to the following rule: | 6 | 1 | 5 | 4 | 1 | 3 | 4 | 8 | +------+-------+-------+-------+------------+------+------+------+ bits : |31-26 | 25 | 24-20 | 19-16 | 15 | 14-12 | 11-8 | 7-0 | +------+-------+-------+-------+----+-------+------+------+------+ field : | a | b | c | d | e | f | g | h | +------+-------+-------+-------+----+-------+------+------+------+ a : Family type/Product line (6 bits (5 bits usuable) (was 4 bits)) MSB bit31 should not be used (MIB compiler fails) 0x0-00 = 0000-00 = Reserved 0x1-00 = 0001-00 = Monoploy non specific (e.g backplane, psu, fans) 0x2-00 = 0010-00 = Boardwalk 0x2-01 = 0010-01 = Power Ranger 0x3-00 = 0011-00 = Marvin Gardens 0x4-00 = 0100-00 = Thunderbolt (was Pacific) 0x5-00 = 0101-00 = PP8300 (was ParkPlace) 0x6-00 = 0110-00 = Central Office (only used in chassis) 0x7-00 = 0111-00 = Alteon WebSystems b : Interface / Device type variation: 1 bit (was 3 bits, 2 bits were stolen by faimly) MSB bit31 should not be used (MIB compiler fails) 0x0-00 = 0000-00 = Reserved 0x1-00 = 0001-00 = Monoploy non specific (e.g backplane, psu, fans) 0x2-00 = 0010-00 = Boardwalk 0x2-01 = 0010-01 = Power Ranger 0x3-00 = 0011-00 = Marvin Gardens 0x4-00 = 0100-00 = Thunderbolt (was Pacific) 0x5-00 = 0101-00 = PP8300 (was ParkPlace) 0x6-00 = 0110-00 = Central Office (only used in chassis) 0x7-00 = 0111-00 = Alteon WebSystems b : Interface / Device type variation: (Were 3 bits, 2 bits taken by family) 0x1 = 1 = M-module (128K RARU records) c : Interface / device type: (5 bits) 0x0 = 00000 = CPU 0x1 = 00001 = Switch fabric 0x2 = 00010 = Copper Ethernet 0x3 = 00011 = Fiber Ethernet 0x4 = 00100 = Sonet (Packets) 0x5 = 00101 = ATM 0x6 = 00110 = Token Ring 0x7 = 00111 = RMON 0x8 = 01000 = BFM (Frame or cells indicated by field 'a' above) 0x9 = 01001 = PSU 0xa = 01010 = Fan Tray 0xb = 01011 = Chassis/Backplane 0xc = 01100 = CPU Mezz 0xd = 01101 = SSL 0xe = 01110 = LaunchPad 0xf = 01111 = reserved for future 0x10 = 10000 = reserved for future 0x11 = 10001 = reserved for future 0x12 = 10010 = reserved for future 0x13 = 10011 = WSM Fiber Ethernet d : Maximum speed (highest negotiable speed) (4 bits) 0x0 = 0000 = 10 Mbit 0x1 = 0001 = 100 Mbit 0x2 = 0010 = 1 Gbit 0x3 = 0011 = 10 Gbit 0x4 = 0100 = OC-3 0x5 = 0101 = OC-12 0x6 = 0110 = OC-48 0x7 = 0111 = OC-92 0x8 = 1000 = OC-192 0x9 = 1001 = 4 Mbit (TR) 0xa = 1010 = 16 Mbit (TR) 0xb = 1011 = E3 0xc = 1100 = DS1 0xd = 1101 = DS3 0xe = 1110 = none (no PHY interfaces on board) 0xf = 1111 = Max speed indicated implicitly in field (c) (for expansion) e : AM&OM-06/28/2006: This bit was originally used to indicate port redundancy. For PR it is used as a differentiator between Boomslang (0) and Copperhead (1). 0=non-redundant, (1 bit) 1=redundant f : Card specific info. (3 bits) For Gigabit used as follows: 000=short-haul (SX) 010=long-haul (LX) 100=extra-distance (DX) 101=GBIC For 10 Gigabit used as follws 000 = 10GE WAN serial 1310nm (XLW) 001 = 10GE WAN serial 1550nm (XEW) 100 = 10GE LAN serial 1310nm (XLR) 101 = 10GE LAN serial 1550nm (XER) 011 = 10GE LAN/WAN (XZW) For ATM/Sonet used as follows 000 = multi mode 001 = single mode 010 = single or multimode 011 = not applicable (e.g., copper has no mode) For Marvin Gardens, indicates number of MDA slots 000 = none 001 = one option slots 010 = two option slots 011 = three option slots For Power Supplies: 000 = AC PSU 001 = DC PSU For CPU Mezz: 000 = MPC755/MPC107 Mezz For SSL: 000 = server offloading 001 = end to end encryption For WSM: 000 = WSM mode 001 = ASFM mode For 8003 (3 slot) chassis differentiation: 000 = ERS 8003 001 = MERS 8003-R (Triumph) 000: PP8300 48TX, 10/100/1000 without POL 001: PP8300 48TX, 10/100/1000 with POL 010: SFP 000: non SFP g : Chassis type (4 bits, possibly MSB 2 bits are extension of field b) 0x0 = 00-00 = work-group (single card switches, etc) 0x1 = 00-01 = back-bone (chassis based products) 0x2 = 00-10 = MDA (option modules) h : Number of ports (binary representation obmited) (8 bits) (for ACIM/BFM cards, this is number of octapids/blackbirds/dea) 0x00 = no ports (cpus, switch fabrics) 0x01 = 1-port, 0x02 = 2-port, 0x04 = 4-port, 0x06 = 6-port, 0x08 = 8-port, 0x0c = 12-port, 0x10 = 16-port, 0x18 = 24-port, 0x22 = 36-port, 0x30 = 48-port, 0x40 = 64-port.

rc2kCardFrontAdminStatus.name: rc2kCardFrontAdminStatus
rc2kCardFrontAdminStatus.description: Used to indicate the administrative status of this card

rc2kCardFrontOperStatus.name: rc2kCardFrontOperStatus
rc2kCardFrontOperStatus.description: Used to indicate the operational status of this card.

rc2kCardBackType.name: rc2kCardBackType
rc2kCardBackType.description: Refer to rc2kCardFrontType for the encoding scheme

rc2kCardPCMCIAType.name: rc2kCardPCMCIAType
rc2kCardPCMCIAType.description: Used to indicate the type of PCMCIA card currently installed in this CPU card, if any. For non-CPU cards, this variable has no meaning and will always be set to none(1).

rc2kCardFrontMasterIO.name: rc2kCardFrontMasterIO
rc2kCardFrontMasterIO.description: Used to indicate whether an IO card in a 8100 device is operating in the 'master' mode. This variable is not meaningful for non-IO cards and non-8100 devices.

rc2kCardSmltOnSingleCpSupported.name: rc2kCardSmltOnSingleCpSupported
rc2kCardSmltOnSingleCpSupported.description: Used to indicate whether an IO card is updated to support SMLT on single Cp feature or not.

rc2kCardMezzCard.name: rc2kCardMezzCard
rc2kCardMezzCard.description: Used to indicate the CPU Mezz card

rc2kCardMezzSerialNum.name: rc2kCardMezzSerialNum
rc2kCardMezzSerialNum.description: Used to get the serial number of the mezz

rc2kCardMezzHwVersion.name: rc2kCardMezzHwVersion
rc2kCardMezzHwVersion.description: Used to get the HW version of the mezz. The value of HW Version corresponds to the value of part number.

rc2kCardMezzPartNum.name: rc2kCardMezzPartNum
rc2kCardMezzPartNum.description: Used to get the part number of the mezz. The value of part number corresponds to the value of HW Version.

rc2kCardSlotPriority.name: rc2kCardSlotPriority
rc2kCardSlotPriority.description: Used to indicate the priority of the slot for power management. It will take effect only after reboot.

rc2kCardSlotOriginalPriority.name: rc2kCardSlotOriginalPriority
rc2kCardSlotOriginalPriority.description: Priority of the slot for power management which the swtich has currently booted with. It will remain the same until the next reboot.

rc2kCardModuleSerialNum.name: rc2kCardModuleSerialNum
rc2kCardModuleSerialNum.description: Module serial number. It is only applicable to the RS module. And it is not applicable to old version of the R module and CP

rc2kCardModulePartNumber.name: rc2kCardModulePartNumber
rc2kCardModulePartNumber.description: Module part number. It is only applicable to the RS module. And it is not applicable to old version of the R module and CP

rc2kCardModuleAssemblyDate.name: rc2kCardModuleAssemblyDate
rc2kCardModuleAssemblyDate.description: Module assemly date. It is only applicable to the RS module. And it is not applicable to old version of the R module and CP

rc2kQosQosTable.name: rc2kQosQosTable
rc2kQosQosTable.description: This table is used to define the Quality Of Service(QOS) profiles for the system. The system can support eight different QOS levels. Each QOS level can be individually configured.

rc2kQosQosRow.name: rc2kQosQosRow
rc2kQosQosRow.description: Used to uniquely identify a row in this table.

rc2kQosIngressTagToQosTable.name: rc2kQosIngressTagToQosTable
rc2kQosIngressTagToQosTable.description: This table is used to specify the 802.1P to QOS (802.1P->QOS) mapping on packet ingress.

rc2kQosIngressTagToQosRow.name: rc2kQosIngressTagToQosRow
rc2kQosIngressTagToQosRow.description: Used to uniquely identify a row in this table.

rc2kQosIngressDsFieldToQosTable.name: rc2kQosIngressDsFieldToQosTable
rc2kQosIngressDsFieldToQosTable.description: This table is used to specify the DSCP field to QOS (DsField->QOS) mapping on packet ingress.

rc2kQosIngressDsFieldToQosEntry.name: rc2kQosIngressDsFieldToQosEntry
rc2kQosIngressDsFieldToQosEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of DsField->Qos mapping

rc2kQosIngressDsFieldToQosRow.name: rc2kQosIngressDsFieldToQosRow
rc2kQosIngressDsFieldToQosRow.description: Used to uniquely identify a row in this table.

rc2kQosEgressQosToTagTable.name: rc2kQosEgressQosToTagTable
rc2kQosEgressQosToTagTable.description: This table is used to specify the QOS to 802.1P (QOS->802.1P) mapping on packet egress.

rc2kQosEgressQosToTagEntry.name: rc2kQosEgressQosToTagEntry
rc2kQosEgressQosToTagEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of Qos->Qos mapping

rc2kQosEgressQosToTagRow.name: rc2kQosEgressQosToTagRow
rc2kQosEgressQosToTagRow.description: Used to uniquely identify a row in this table.

rc2kQosEgressQosToDsFieldTable.name: rc2kQosEgressQosToDsFieldTable
rc2kQosEgressQosToDsFieldTable.description: This table is used to specify the QOS to DSCP field (QOS->DsField) mapping on packet egress.

rc2kQosEgressQosToDsFieldEntry.name: rc2kQosEgressQosToDsFieldEntry
rc2kQosEgressQosToDsFieldEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of Qos->Qos mapping

rc2kQosEgressQosToDsFieldRow.name: rc2kQosEgressQosToDsFieldRow
rc2kQosEgressQosToDsFieldRow.description: Used to uniquely identify a row in this table.

rc2kQosTrafficProfileTable.name: rc2kQosTrafficProfileTable
rc2kQosTrafficProfileTable.description: This table is used to specify traffic profiles for the system. These traffic profiles are used for policying purposes to guarantee streams of traffic do not egress the system above a certain rate. These traffic profiles are applied in the 'rcIpFilterTable'.

rc2kQosTrafficProfileEntry.name: rc2kQosTrafficProfileEntry
rc2kQosTrafficProfileEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of Qos->Qos mapping

rc2kQosTrafficProfileTranslateDscpEnable.name: rc2kQosTrafficProfileTranslateDscpEnable
rc2kQosTrafficProfileTranslateDscpEnable.description: Used to specify whether translation of the DSCP field should be performed. If enabled, the value in the DSCP field for packets that fall within the traffic profile will get translated to 'rc2kQosTrafficProfileInProfileDscp'. Packets that fall outside the traffic profile will get translated to 'rc2kQosTrafficProfileOutProfileDscp'. If disabled, no translation is performed.

rc2kQosTrafficProfileInProfileDscp.name: rc2kQosTrafficProfileInProfileDscp
rc2kQosTrafficProfileInProfileDscp.description: Used to specify the DSCP value for 'good' packets.

rc2kQosTrafficProfileOutProfileDscp.name: rc2kQosTrafficProfileOutProfileDscp
rc2kQosTrafficProfileOutProfileDscp.description: Used to specify the DSCP value for 'violation' packets.

rc2kQosTrafficProfileDiscardEnable.name: rc2kQosTrafficProfileDiscardEnable
rc2kQosTrafficProfileDiscardEnable.description: Used to specify whether packets that fall outside the traffic profile should be discarded.

rc2kQosTrafficProfileAverageRate.name: rc2kQosTrafficProfileAverageRate
rc2kQosTrafficProfileAverageRate.description: Average rate in packets per second.

rc2kQosTrafficProfilePeakRate.name: rc2kQosTrafficProfilePeakRate
rc2kQosTrafficProfilePeakRate.description: Peak rate in packets per second.

rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosTable.name: rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosTable
rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosTable.description: This table is used to specify the DSCP to QOS (Dscp->QOS) mapping on packet ingress.

rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosEntry.name: rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosEntry
rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosEntry.description: Entry containing information of Dscp->Qos mapping

rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosRow.name: rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosRow
rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosRow.description: Used to uniquely identify a row in this table.

rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosInDscp.name: rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosInDscp
rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosInDscp.description: A 6-bit value used to define the Differentiated Service Code Point(DSCP).

rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosInDscpBinaryForma.name: rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosInDscpBinaryFormat
rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosInDscpBinaryForma.description: The 'rc2kQosIngressDscpToQosInDscp' value shown in a binary format (network order).

rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpTable.name: rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpTable
rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpTable.description: This table is used to specify the QOS to DSCP field (QOS->DsField) mapping on packet egress.

rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpEntry.name: rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpEntry
rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of Qos->Qos mapping

rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpRow.name: rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpRow
rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpRow.description: Used to uniquely identify a row in this table.

rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpOutDscp.name: rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpOutDscp
rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpOutDscp.description: A 6-bit value used to define the Differentiated Service Code Point(DSCP).

rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpOutDscpBinaryForma.name: rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpOutDscpBinaryFormat
rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpOutDscpBinaryForma.description: The 'rc2kQosEgressQosToDscpOutDscp' value show in a binary format (network order).

rc2kAtmPortEntry.name: rc2kAtmPortEntry
rc2kAtmPortEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of ATM port

rc2kAtmPortNumVpiBits.name: rc2kAtmPortNumVpiBits
rc2kAtmPortNumVpiBits.description: # of vpi bits. For OC3, the max number of vpibits is 6. However, for OC12, it is 8. Both media types share the same MIB object.

rc2kAtmPvcEntry.name: rc2kAtmPvcEntry
rc2kAtmPvcEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of ATM Pvc

rc2kAtmPvcPeakCellRate.name: rc2kAtmPvcPeakCellRate
rc2kAtmPvcPeakCellRate.description: Peak cell rate in cells per second. The maximum peak cell rate is half of the line rate. The peak cell rate for MDA type OC12 must be less than 733491. However, for OC3, it is less than 182783.

rc2kAtmPvcSustainedCellRate.name: rc2kAtmPvcSustainedCellRate
rc2kAtmPvcSustainedCellRate.description: Sustained cell rate in cells per second. The maximum peak cell rate is half of the line rate. The peak cell rate for MDA type OC12 must be less than 733491. However, for OC3, it is less than 182783.

rc2kAtmPvcOamLbMgmtEnable.name: rc2kAtmPvcOamLbMgmtEnable
rc2kAtmPvcOamLbMgmtEnable.description: Indicate whether end-to-end F5 OAM loopback is enabled. When it is enabled, OAM loopback request is sent periodically

rc2kAtmPvcOamLbSendFrequency.name: rc2kAtmPvcOamLbSendFrequency
rc2kAtmPvcOamLbSendFrequency.description: Number of seconds between transmitting OAM loopback request

rc2kAtmPvcOamLbUpCount.name: rc2kAtmPvcOamLbUpCount
rc2kAtmPvcOamLbUpCount.description: Number of consecutive end-to-end F5 OAM loopback cell responses that must be received in order to change a PVC connection state to up

rc2kAtmPvcOamLbDownCount.name: rc2kAtmPvcOamLbDownCount
rc2kAtmPvcOamLbDownCount.description: Number of consecutive end-to-end F5 OAM loopback cell responses that are not received in order to change a PVC state to down.

rc2kAtmPvcOamTrapEnable.name: rc2kAtmPvcOamTrapEnable
rc2kAtmPvcOamTrapEnable.description: Indicate whether OAM trap is enabled. When it is enabled, a trap is sent to the management station when rc2kAtmPvcOamVcStatus is going up or down.

rc2kAtmPvcOamVcStatus.name: rc2kAtmPvcOamVcStatus
rc2kAtmPvcOamVcStatus.description: Indicate the status of PVC link. Not Managed--VC is not being managed by OAM. Down Verify --An OAM loopback failed. End-to-end F5 OAM loopback cells are sent at retry frequency to verify the VC is really down. After down-count unsuccessful retries, the VC goes to the down state (see definition of rc2kAtmPvcOamLoopbackDownCount). Down --VC has not received responses to by end-to-end F5 OAM loopback cells. Up Verify -- An OAM loopback was successful. End-to-end F5 OAM loopback cells are sent at retry frequency to verify the VC is really up. After up-count successive and successful loopback retries, the VC goes to the Up state (see definition of rc2kAtmPvcOamLoopbackUpCount). Up - End-to-end loopbacks are successful.

rc2kAtmPvcOamLbRequestSent.name: rc2kAtmPvcOamLbRequestSent
rc2kAtmPvcOamLbRequestSent.description: Number of OAM loopback request sent

rc2kAtmPvcOamLbReplySent.name: rc2kAtmPvcOamLbReplySent
rc2kAtmPvcOamLbReplySent.description: Number of OAM loopback reply sent

rc2kAtmPvcOamLbReplyReceived.name: rc2kAtmPvcOamLbReplyReceived
rc2kAtmPvcOamLbReplyReceived.description: Number of OAM loopback reply received

rc2kAtm1483ElanPvcIds.name: rc2kAtm1483ElanPvcIds
rc2kAtm1483ElanPvcIds.description: list of pvc-ids. each pvc-id is represented by a 32 bit value this field can contain a maximum of 64 pvc-ids.

rc2kAtm1483ElanDummyMacAddress.name: rc2kAtm1483ElanDummyMacAddress
rc2kAtm1483ElanDummyMacAddress.description: dummy mac for the other router

rc2kAtm1483ElanLocalIpAddress.name: rc2kAtm1483ElanLocalIpAddress
rc2kAtm1483ElanLocalIpAddress.description: local ip, if ConnectType is ip(2)

rc2kAtm1483ElanRemoteIpAddress.name: rc2kAtm1483ElanRemoteIpAddress
rc2kAtm1483ElanRemoteIpAddress.description: remote ip, if ConnectType is ip(2)

rc2kAtm1483ElanInArpSendEnable.name: rc2kAtm1483ElanInArpSendEnable
rc2kAtm1483ElanInArpSendEnable.description: enable arp sending on the port, if ConnectType is ip(2)

rc2kAtm1483ElanInArpSendInterval.name: rc2kAtm1483ElanInArpSendInterval
rc2kAtm1483ElanInArpSendInterval.description: interval of arp sending on the port, if ConnectType is ip(2)

rc2kAtm1483ElanIpxVlanEncapMethod.name: rc2kAtm1483ElanIpxVlanEncapMethod
rc2kAtm1483ElanIpxVlanEncapMethod.description: vlan encapsulation method, if ConnectType is ipx(3)

rc2kAtm1483ElanIpxNetworkNum.name: rc2kAtm1483ElanIpxNetworkNum
rc2kAtm1483ElanIpxNetworkNum.description: network number, if ConnectType is ipx(3)

rc2kAtm1483ElanStgId.name: rc2kAtm1483ElanStgId
rc2kAtm1483ElanStgId.description: An identifier used to identify a STG in the device, only in bridge mode

rc2kAtm1483ElanrcStgTaggedBpduVlanId.name: rc2kAtm1483ElanrcStgTaggedBpduVlanId
rc2kAtm1483ElanrcStgTaggedBpduVlanId.description: The VLAN ID to be used for tagging BPDUs, only in bridge mode.

rc2kAtmSioCardConfigEntry.name: rc2kAtmSioCardConfigEntry
rc2kAtmSioCardConfigEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of 2kAtm Sio Card Config.

rc2kAtmSioCardConfigStatsPollPeriod.name: rc2kAtmSioCardConfigStatsPollPeriod
rc2kAtmSioCardConfigStatsPollPeriod.description: Time interval after which Elan statistics would be polled

rc2kAtmPortStatsEntry.name: rc2kAtmPortStatsEntry
rc2kAtmPortStatsEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of ATM port statistics

rc2kAtmPortStatsInCells.name: rc2kAtmPortStatsInCells
rc2kAtmPortStatsInCells.description: Number of Cells received from ATM interface

rc2kAtmPortStatsOutCells.name: rc2kAtmPortStatsOutCells
rc2kAtmPortStatsOutCells.description: Number of Cells transmitted by ATM interface

rc2kAtmPortStatsInHecCorrected.name: rc2kAtmPortStatsInHecCorrected
rc2kAtmPortStatsInHecCorrected.description: Number of received cells in which HCS was corrected

rc2kAtmPortStatsInHecUncorrected.name: rc2kAtmPortStatsInHecUncorrected
rc2kAtmPortStatsInHecUncorrected.description: Number of received cells dropped because HCS couldn't be corrected

rc2kAtmPortStatsInUnknownProtos.name: rc2kAtmPortStatsInUnknownProtos
rc2kAtmPortStatsInUnknownProtos.description: Number of received cells dropped with wrong VPI/VCI

rc2kAtmPortStatsInPkts.name: rc2kAtmPortStatsInPkts
rc2kAtmPortStatsInPkts.description: Number of AAL5 CPCS PDUs received

rc2kAtmPortStatsOutPkts.name: rc2kAtmPortStatsOutPkts
rc2kAtmPortStatsOutPkts.description: Number of AAL5 CPCS PDUs transmitted

rc2kAtmPortStatsInDroppedPkts.name: rc2kAtmPortStatsInDroppedPkts
rc2kAtmPortStatsInDroppedPkts.description: Number of AAL5 CPCS PDUs dropped due to resource exhaustion

rc2kAtmPortStatsOutDroppedPkts.name: rc2kAtmPortStatsOutDroppedPkts
rc2kAtmPortStatsOutDroppedPkts.description: Number of AAL5 CPCS PDUs dropped because the transmitter closed the channel

rc2kAtmVPortStatsEntry.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsEntry
rc2kAtmVPortStatsEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of ATM Elan statistics

rc2kAtmVPortStatsInOctets.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsInOctets
rc2kAtmVPortStatsInOctets.description: AAL5 CPCS PDU octects received from ATM interface

rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutOctets.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutOctets
rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutOctets.description: AAL5 CPCS PDU octects transmitted out of ATM interface

rc2kAtmVPortStatsInErrors.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsInErrors
rc2kAtmVPortStatsInErrors.description: AAL5 CPCS PDUs received with errors from ATM interface. These errors include CRC-32 errors,SAR time-out errors And oversized SDU errors

rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutErrors.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutErrors
rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutErrors.description: Number of AAL5 CPCS PDUs that couldn't be transmitted due to errors

rc2kAtmVPortStatsInDiscards.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsInDiscards
rc2kAtmVPortStatsInDiscards.description: Number of received AAL5 CPCS PDUs discarded

rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutDiscards.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutDiscards
rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutDiscards.description: Number of AAL5 CPCS PDUs which are to be transmitted but discarded

rc2kAtmVPortStatsInUcastPkts.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsInUcastPkts
rc2kAtmVPortStatsInUcastPkts.description: Received ethernet/IP/IPX packets whose destination address is neither a multicast nor a broadcast address

rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutUcastPkts.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutUcastPkts
rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutUcastPkts.description: Forwarded ethernet/IP/IPX packets whose destination address is neither a multicast nor a broadcast address

rc2kAtmVPortStatsInMulticastPkts.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsInMulticastPkts
rc2kAtmVPortStatsInMulticastPkts.description: Received ethernet/IP/IPX packets whose destination MAC address(or IP address in case of IP ELAN type) is multicast MAC address or class D IP address (in case of IP ELAN type)

rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutMulticastPkts.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutMulticastPkts
rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutMulticastPkts.description: Forwarded ethernet/IP/IPX packets whose destination MAC address(or IP address in case of IP ELAN type) is multicast MAC address or class D IP address (in case of IP ELAN type)

rc2kAtmVPortStatsInBroadcastPkts.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsInBroadcastPkts
rc2kAtmVPortStatsInBroadcastPkts.description: Received ethernet/IP/IPX packets whose destination address in broadcast address

rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutBroadcastPkts.name: rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutBroadcastPkts
rc2kAtmVPortStatsOutBroadcastPkts.description: Forwarded ethernet/IP/IPX packets whose destination address in broadcast address

rc2kMdaCardEntry.name: rc2kMdaCardEntry
rc2kMdaCardEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of Mda card

rc2kMdaCardMdaNum.name: rc2kMdaCardMdaNum
rc2kMdaCardMdaNum.description: MDA number within slot. MDAs are numbered from left to right.

rc2kMdaCardType.name: rc2kMdaCardType
rc2kMdaCardType.description: Refer to rc2kCardFrontType for the encoding scheme

rc2kMdaCardDeviations.name: rc2kMdaCardDeviations
rc2kMdaCardDeviations.description: hardware deviation infomation of mda card

rc2kMdaCardMacAddr.name: rc2kMdaCardMacAddr
rc2kMdaCardMacAddr.description: base mac address of mda card

rc2kMdaCardNumPorts.name: rc2kMdaCardNumPorts
rc2kMdaCardNumPorts.description: number of ports on mda card

rc2kMdaCardFirstIfIndex.name: rc2kMdaCardFirstIfIndex
rc2kMdaCardFirstIfIndex.description: first ifindex number on mda card

rc2kMdaCardLastIfIndex.name: rc2kMdaCardLastIfIndex
rc2kMdaCardLastIfIndex.description: last ifindex number on mda card

rc2kCpuEthernetPortRouteEntry.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortRouteEntry
rc2kCpuEthernetPortRouteEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of 2k CPU Ethernet Port

rc2kCpuEthernetPortRouteNetwork.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortRouteNetwork
rc2kCpuEthernetPortRouteNetwork.description: Used to configure the network that can be used to remotely manage this device.

rc2kCpuEthernetPortRouteGateway.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortRouteGateway
rc2kCpuEthernetPortRouteGateway.description: Used to configure the the IP address of the gateway that should be used to forward IP traffic.

rc2kCPUTypePrimary.name: rc2kCPUTypePrimary
rc2kCPUTypePrimary.description: Used to identify the type of primary CPU

rc2kCPUTypeSecondary.name: rc2kCPUTypeSecondary
rc2kCPUTypeSecondary.description: Used to identify the type of secondary CPU

rc2kCPUTypePrimaryMemory.name: rc2kCPUTypePrimaryMemory
rc2kCPUTypePrimaryMemory.description: Used to get the memory size of Primary CPU

rc2kCPUTypeSecondaryMemory.name: rc2kCPUTypeSecondaryMemory
rc2kCPUTypeSecondaryMemory.description: Used to get the memory size of Secondary CPU

rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteTable.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteTable
rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteTable.description: 2k CPU Ethernet Port Route table for Ipv6

rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteEntry.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteEntry
rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteEntry.description: Entry containing information of 2k CPU Ethernet Port Ipv6

rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteNetwork.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteNetwork
rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteNetwork.description: Used to configure the ipv6 network that can be used to remotely manage this device.

rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RoutePrefixLength.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RoutePrefixLength
rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RoutePrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix (in bits).

rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteGateway.name: rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteGateway
rc2kCpuEthernetPortIpv6RouteGateway.description: Used to configure the the IPv6 address of the gateway that should be used to forward IPv6 traffic.

rcWisSonetTrapType.name: rcWisSonetTrapType
rcWisSonetTrapType.description: Used to indicate a particular type of 10GE Sonet trap.

rcWisSonetTrapIndication.name: rcWisSonetTrapIndication
rcWisSonetTrapIndication.description: Used to indicate an indication for a 10GE Sonet trap.

rcTengDot3StatsTable.name: rcTengDot3StatsTable
rcTengDot3StatsTable.description: Statistics for a collection of ethernet-like interfaces attached to a particular system.

rcTengDot3StatsEntry.name: rcTengDot3StatsEntry
rcTengDot3StatsEntry.description: Statistics for a particular interface to an ethernet-like medium.

rcTengDot3StatsIndex.name: rcTengDot3StatsIndex
rcTengDot3StatsIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface to an ethernet-like medium. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcTengDot3StatsAlignmentErrors.name: rcTengDot3StatsAlignmentErrors
rcTengDot3StatsAlignmentErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the alignmentError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

rcTengDot3StatsFCSErrors.name: rcTengDot3StatsFCSErrors
rcTengDot3StatsFCSErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that are an integral number of octets in length but do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameCheckError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

rcTengDot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames.name: rcTengDot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames
rcTengDot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by exactly one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts, ifOutMulticastPkts, or ifOutBroadcastPkts, and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the dot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames object.

rcTengDot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames.name: rcTengDot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames
rcTengDot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts, ifOutMulticastPkts, or ifOutBroadcastPkts, and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the dot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames object.

rcTengDot3StatsSQETestErrors.name: rcTengDot3StatsSQETestErrors
rcTengDot3StatsSQETestErrors.reference: ANSI/IEEE Std 802.3-1985 Carrier Sense Multiple Access with Collision Detection Access Method and Physical Layer Specifications
rcTengDot3StatsSQETestErrors.description: A count of times that the SQE TEST ERROR message is generated by the PLS sublayer for a particular interface. The SQE TEST ERROR message is defined in section 7.2.2.2.4 of ANSI/IEEE 802.3-1985 and its generation is described in section 7.2.4.6 of the same document.

rcTengDot3StatsDeferredTransmissions.name: rcTengDot3StatsDeferredTransmissions
rcTengDot3StatsDeferredTransmissions.description: A count of frames for which the first transmission attempt on a particular interface is delayed because the medium is busy. The count represented by an instance of this object does not include frames involved in collisions.

rcTengDot3StatsLateCollisions.name: rcTengDot3StatsLateCollisions
rcTengDot3StatsLateCollisions.description: The number of times that a collision is detected on a particular interface later than 512 bit-times into the transmission of a packet. Five hundred and twelve bit-times corresponds to 51.2 microseconds on a 10 Mbit/s system. A (late) collision included in a count represented by an instance of this object is also considered as a (generic) collision for purposes of other collision-related statistics.

rcTengDot3StatsExcessiveCollisions.name: rcTengDot3StatsExcessiveCollisions
rcTengDot3StatsExcessiveCollisions.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular interface fails due to excessive collisions.

rcTengDot3StatsInternalMacTransmitErrors.name: rcTengDot3StatsInternalMacTransmitErrors
rcTengDot3StatsInternalMacTransmitErrors.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular interface fails due to an internal MAC sublayer transmit error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the rcTengDot3StatsLateCollisions object, the rcTengDot3StatsExcessiveCollisions object, or the rcTengDot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors object. The precise meaning of the count represented by an instance of this object is implementation- specific. In particular, an instance of this object may represent a count of transmission errors on a particular interface that are not otherwise counted.

rcTengDot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors.name: rcTengDot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors
rcTengDot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors.description: The number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame on a particular interface. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented at most once per transmission attempt, even if the carrier sense condition fluctuates during a transmission attempt.

rcTengDot3StatsFrameTooLongs.name: rcTengDot3StatsFrameTooLongs
rcTengDot3StatsFrameTooLongs.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that exceed the maximum permitted frame size. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameTooLong status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

rcTengDot3StatsInternalMacReceiveErrors.name: rcTengDot3StatsInternalMacReceiveErrors
rcTengDot3StatsInternalMacReceiveErrors.description: A count of frames for which reception on a particular interface fails due to an internal MAC sublayer receive error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the rcTengDot3StatsFrameTooLongs object, the rcTengDot3StatsAlignmentErrors object, or the rcTengDot3StatsFCSErrors object. The precise meaning of the count represented by an instance of this object is implementation- specific. In particular, an instance of this object may represent a count of receive errors on a particular interface that are not otherwise counted.

rcTengDot3StatsEtherChipSet.name: rcTengDot3StatsEtherChipSet
rcTengDot3StatsEtherChipSet.description: This object contains an OBJECT IDENTIFIER which identifies the chipset used to realize the interface. Ethernet-like interfaces are typically built out of several different chips. The MIB implementor is presented with a decision of which chip to identify via this object. The implementor should identify the chip which is usually called the Medium Access Control chip. If no such chip is easily identifiable, the implementor should identify the chip which actually gathers the transmit and receive statistics and error indications. This would allow a manager station to correlate the statistics and the chip generating them, giving it the ability to take into account any known anomalies in the chip.

rcTengDot3StatsLinkFailures.name: rcTengDot3StatsLinkFailures
rcTengDot3StatsLinkFailures.description: The total number of link failures enCounter32ed on this interface.

rcTengDot3StatsPacketErrors.name: rcTengDot3StatsPacketErrors
rcTengDot3StatsPacketErrors.description: The total number of packet errors enCounter32ed on this interface.

rcTengDot3StatsCarrierErrors.name: rcTengDot3StatsCarrierErrors
rcTengDot3StatsCarrierErrors.description: The total number of carrier errors enCounter32ed on this interface.

rcTengDot3StatsLinkInactiveErrors.name: rcTengDot3StatsLinkInactiveErrors
rcTengDot3StatsLinkInactiveErrors.description: The total number of link inactive errors enCounter32ed on this interface.

rcTengDot3StatsInFlowCtrlPkts.name: rcTengDot3StatsInFlowCtrlPkts
rcTengDot3StatsInFlowCtrlPkts.description: The total number of flow control packets received by this interface.

rcTengDot3StatsOutFlowCtrlPkts.name: rcTengDot3StatsOutFlowCtrlPkts
rcTengDot3StatsOutFlowCtrlPkts.description: The total number of flow control packets transmitted by this interface.

rcTengDot3StatsFrameTooShorts.name: rcTengDot3StatsFrameTooShorts
rcTengDot3StatsFrameTooShorts.description: The total number of frames that are too short that were enCounter32ed on this interface.

rcTengStatTable.name: rcTengStatTable
rcTengStatTable.description: A table used to store port statistics.

rcTengStatIndex.name: rcTengStatIndex
rcTengStatIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port. This value is similar to ifIndex in MIB2.

rcTengStatBridgeInUnicastFrames.name: rcTengStatBridgeInUnicastFrames
rcTengStatBridgeInUnicastFrames.description: The total number of incoming unicast frames that were bridged.

rcTengStatBridgeInMulticastFrames.name: rcTengStatBridgeInMulticastFrames
rcTengStatBridgeInMulticastFrames.description: The total number of incoming multicast frames that were bridged.

rcTengStatBridgeInBroadcastFrames.name: rcTengStatBridgeInBroadcastFrames
rcTengStatBridgeInBroadcastFrames.description: The total number of incoming broadcast frames that were bridged.

rcTengStatBridgeInDiscards.name: rcTengStatBridgeInDiscards
rcTengStatBridgeInDiscards.description: The total number of frames that were discarded by the bridging entity.

rcTengStatBridgeOutUnicastFrames.name: rcTengStatBridgeOutUnicastFrames
rcTengStatBridgeOutUnicastFrames.description: The total number of outgoing unicast frames that were bridged.

rcTengStatBridgeOutMulticastFrames.name: rcTengStatBridgeOutMulticastFrames
rcTengStatBridgeOutMulticastFrames.description: The total number of outgoing multicast frames that were bridged.

rcTengStatBridgeOutBroadcastFrames.name: rcTengStatBridgeOutBroadcastFrames
rcTengStatBridgeOutBroadcastFrames.description: The total number of outgoing broadcast frames that were bridged.

rcTengStatRouteInUnicastFrames.name: rcTengStatRouteInUnicastFrames
rcTengStatRouteInUnicastFrames.description: The total number of incoming unicast frames that were routed.

rcTengStatRouteInMulticastFrames.name: rcTengStatRouteInMulticastFrames
rcTengStatRouteInMulticastFrames.description: The total number of incoming multicast frames that were routed.

rcTengStatRouteInDiscards.name: rcTengStatRouteInDiscards
rcTengStatRouteInDiscards.description: The total number of frames that were discarded by the routing entity.

rcTengStatRouteOutUnicastFrames.name: rcTengStatRouteOutUnicastFrames
rcTengStatRouteOutUnicastFrames.description: The total number of outgoing unicast frames that were routed.

rcTengStatRouteOutMulticastFrames.name: rcTengStatRouteOutMulticastFrames
rcTengStatRouteOutMulticastFrames.description: The total number of outgoing multicast frames that were routed.

rcTengStatStgForwardTransitions.name: rcTengStatStgForwardTransitions
