rcTengStatStgForwardTransitions.description: The number of times this port has transitioned from the Learning state to the Forwarding state.

rcTengStatBridgeOutFrames.name: rcTengStatBridgeOutFrames
rcTengStatBridgeOutFrames.description: Used by the Accelar 8000 product family to account for all transmitted bridge unicast, broadcast, and multicast packets. The individual Counter32s are not supported.

rcTengIfTable.name: rcTengIfTable
rcTengIfTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of engIfNumber.

rcTengIfEntry.name: rcTengIfEntry
rcTengIfEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface.

rcTengIfIndex.name: rcTengIfIndex
rcTengIfIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub-layer must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

rcTengIfDescr.name: rcTengIfDescr
rcTengIfDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the interface hardware/software.

rcTengIfType.name: rcTengIfType
rcTengIfType.description: The type of interface. Additional values for IfType are assigned by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority (IANA), through updating the syntax of the IANAifType textual convention.

rcTengIfMtu.name: rcTengIfMtu
rcTengIfMtu.description: The size of the largest packet which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagrams, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

rcTengIfSpeed.name: rcTengIfSpeed
rcTengIfSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth. If the bandwidth of the interface is greater than the maximum value reportable by this object then this object should report its maximum value (4,294,967,295) and ifHighSpeed must be used to report the interace's speed. For a sub-layer which has no concept of bandwidth, this object should be zero.

rcTengIfPhysAddress.name: rcTengIfPhysAddress
rcTengIfPhysAddress.description: The interface's address at its protocol sub-layer. The interface's media-specific MIB must define the bit and byte ordering and format of the value contained by this object. For interfaces which do not have such an address (e.g., a serial line), this object should contain an octet string of zero length.

rcTengIfAdminStatus.name: rcTengIfAdminStatus
rcTengIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. When a managed system initializes, all interfaces start with IfAdminStatus in the down(2) state. As a result of either explicit management action or per configuration information retained by the managed system, IfAdminStatus is then changed to either the up(1) or testing(3) states (or remains in the down(2) state).

rcTengIfOperStatus.name: rcTengIfOperStatus
rcTengIfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. If IfAdminStatus is down(2) then IfOperStatus should be down(2). If IfAdminStatus is changed to up(1) then ifOperStatus should change to up(1) if the interface is ready to transmit and receive network traffic; it should change to dormant(5) if the interface is waiting for external actions (such as a serial line waiting for an incomming connection); it should remain in the down(2) state if and only if there is a fault that prevents if from going to the up(1) state.

rcTengIfLastChange.name: rcTengIfLastChange
rcTengIfLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the interface entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

rcTengIfInOctets.name: rcTengIfInOctets
rcTengIfInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.

rcTengIfInUcastPkts.name: rcTengIfInUcastPkts
rcTengIfInUcastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were not addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer.

rcTengIfInNUcastPkts.name: rcTengIfInNUcastPkts
rcTengIfInNUcastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer. This object is deprecated in favour of IfInMulticastPkts and IfInBroadcastPkts.

rcTengIfInDiscards.name: rcTengIfInDiscards
rcTengIfInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

rcTengIfInErrors.name: rcTengIfInErrors
rcTengIfInErrors.description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of inbound transmission units that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

rcTengIfInUnknownProtos.name: rcTengIfInUnknownProtos
rcTengIfInUnknownProtos.description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of packets received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces which support protocol multiplexing the number of transmission units received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. For any interface which does not support protocol multiplexing, this counter will always be 0.

rcTengIfOutOctets.name: rcTengIfOutOctets
rcTengIfOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

rcTengIfOutUcastPkts.name: rcTengIfOutUcastPkts
rcTengIfOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were not addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent.

rcTengIfOutNUcastPkts.name: rcTengIfOutNUcastPkts
rcTengIfOutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent. This object is deprecated in favour of IfOutMulticastPkts and IfOutBroadcastPkts.

rcTengIfOutDiscards.name: rcTengIfOutDiscards
rcTengIfOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

rcTengIfOutErrors.name: rcTengIfOutErrors
rcTengIfOutErrors.description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of outbound transmission units that could not be transmitted because of errors.

rcTengIfOutQLen.name: rcTengIfOutQLen
rcTengIfOutQLen.description: The length of the output packet queue (in packets).

rcTengIfSpecific.name: rcTengIfSpecific
rcTengIfSpecific.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular media being used to realize the interface. It is recommended that this value point to an instance of a MIB object in the media-specific MIB, i.e., that this object have the semantics associated with the InstancePointer textual convention defined in RFC 1443. In fact, it is recommended that the media- specific MIB specify what value ifSpecific should/can take for values of ifType. If no MIB definitions specific to the particular media are available, the value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

rcTengIfXTable.name: rcTengIfXTable
rcTengIfXTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of ifNumber. This table contains additional objects for the interface table.

rcTengIfXEntry.name: rcTengIfXEntry
rcTengIfXEntry.description: An entry containing additional management information applicable to a particular interface.

rcTengIfXIndex.name: rcTengIfXIndex
rcTengIfXIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub-layer must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

rcTengIfName.name: rcTengIfName
rcTengIfName.description: The textual name of the interface. The value of this object should be the name of the interface as assigned by the local device and should be suitable for use in commands entered at the device's `console'. This might be a text name, such as `le0' or a simple port number, such as `1', depending on the interface naming syntax of the device. If several entries in the rcTengIfTable together represent a single interface as named by the device, then each will have the same value of rcTengIfName. If there is no local name, or this object is otherwise not applicable, then this object contains a 0-length string.

rcTengIfInMulticastPkts.name: rcTengIfInMulticastPkts
rcTengIfInMulticastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were addressed to a multicast address at this sub-layer. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses.

rcTengIfInBroadcastPkts.name: rcTengIfInBroadcastPkts
rcTengIfInBroadcastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were addressed to a broadcast address at this sub-layer.

rcTengIfOutMulticastPkts.name: rcTengIfOutMulticastPkts
rcTengIfOutMulticastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were addressed to a multicast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses.

rcTengIfOutBroadcastPkts.name: rcTengIfOutBroadcastPkts
rcTengIfOutBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were addressed to a broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent.

rcTengIfHCInOctets.name: rcTengIfHCInOctets
rcTengIfHCInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters. This object is a 64-bit version of rcTengIfInOctets.

rcTengIfHCInUcastPkts.name: rcTengIfHCInUcastPkts
rcTengIfHCInUcastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were not addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer. This object is a 64-bit version of rcTengIfInUcastPkts.

rcTengIfHCInMulticastPkts.name: rcTengIfHCInMulticastPkts
rcTengIfHCInMulticastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were addressed to a multicast address at this sub-layer. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses. This object is a 64-bit version of rcTengIfInMulticastPkts.

rcTengIfHCInBroadcastPkts.name: rcTengIfHCInBroadcastPkts
rcTengIfHCInBroadcastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were addressed to a broadcast address at this sub-layer. This object is a 64-bit version of IfInBroadcastPkts.

rcTengIfHCOutOctets.name: rcTengIfHCOutOctets
rcTengIfHCOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters. This object is a 64-bit version of rcTengIfOutOctets.

rcTengIfHCOutUcastPkts.name: rcTengIfHCOutUcastPkts
rcTengIfHCOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were not addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent. This object is a 64-bit version of rcTengIfOutUcastPkts.

rcTengIfHCOutMulticastPkts.name: rcTengIfHCOutMulticastPkts
rcTengIfHCOutMulticastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were addressed to a multicast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses. This object is a 64-bit version of rcTengIfOutMulticastPkts.

rcTengIfHCOutBroadcastPkts.name: rcTengIfHCOutBroadcastPkts
rcTengIfHCOutBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were addressed to a broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent. This object is a 64-bit version of rcTengIfOutBroadcastPkts.

rcTengIfLinkUpDownTrapEnable.name: rcTengIfLinkUpDownTrapEnable
rcTengIfLinkUpDownTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether linkUp/linkDown traps should be generated for this interface. By default, this object should have the value enabled(1) for interfaces which do not operate on 'top' of any other interface (as defined in the rcTengIfStackTable), and disabled(2) otherwise.

rcTengIfHighSpeed.name: rcTengIfHighSpeed
rcTengIfHighSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in units of 1,000,000 bits per second. If this object reports a value of `n' then the speed of the interface is somewhere in the range of `n-500,000' to `n+499,999'. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth. For a sub-layer which has no concept of bandwidth, this object should be zero.

rcTengIfPromiscuousMode.name: rcTengIfPromiscuousMode
rcTengIfPromiscuousMode.description: This object has a value of false(2) If this interface only accepts packets/frames that are addressed to this station. This object has a value of true(1) when the station accepts all packets/frames transmitted on the media. The value true(1) is only legal on certain types of media. If legal, setting this object to a value of true(1) may require the interface to be reset before becoming effective. The value of rcTengIfPromiscuousMode does not affect the reception of broadcast and multicast packets/frames by the interface.

rcTengIfConnectorPresent.name: rcTengIfConnectorPresent
rcTengIfConnectorPresent.description: This object has the value 'true(1)' if the interface sublayer has a physical connector and the value 'false(2)' otherwise.

rcRecReservTable.name: rcRecReservTable
rcRecReservTable.description: This table would display the statistics of several HW record type used. This will also let the user reserve certain number of records for each type.

rcRecReservUsed.name: rcRecReservUsed
rcRecReservUsed.description: Displayes the number of HW records actually usee by the recordType.

rcRecReservReserved.name: rcRecReservReserved
rcRecReservReserved.description: Displayes the number of HW records reserved for the recordType.

rcRecReservNewReserved.name: rcRecReservNewReserved
rcRecReservNewReserved.description: Displayes the number of HW records that w ill be reserved for this recordType after reset if the configuration is saved.

rcRecReservDefReserved.name: rcRecReservDefReserved
rcRecReservDefReserved.description: Number of records reserved for this recordType if loaded with factory default.

rcSshGlobalEnable.name: rcSshGlobalEnable
rcSshGlobalEnable.description: Enable/disable, or securely enable SSH. Securely enable turns off other daemon flag, and it takes ffect afte reboot

rcLicenseNumber.name: rcLicenseNumber
rcLicenseNumber.description: Bit position number of license bitmap

rcLicenseBitMap.name: rcLicenseBitMap
rcLicenseBitMap.description: License bit map. Bitmap number is defined in rcLicenseNumber

rcSslMipTable.name: rcSslMipTable
rcSslMipTable.description: This table would display the MIP of the SSL blade according to the slot number.

rcSslMipTableEntry.name: rcSslMipTableEntry
rcSslMipTableEntry.description: This table get the MIP of the SSL blade on which the blade is in different cluster.

rcSslMipSlot.name: rcSslMipSlot
rcSslMipSlot.description: Used as an index to find out the MIP of SSL blade.

rcSslMipMip.name: rcSslMipMip
rcSslMipMip.description: Master IP of the SSL blade.

rcLacpGlobalSystemPriority.name: rcLacpGlobalSystemPriority
rcLacpGlobalSystemPriority.description: set system priority to all the LACP enabled aggregators and prots

rcLacpGlobalFastPeriodicTime.name: rcLacpGlobalFastPeriodicTime
rcLacpGlobalFastPeriodicTime.description: The number of miliseconds between periodic transmissions using Short Timeouts. Set this value to all LACP enabled ports.

rcLacpGlobalSlowPeriodicTime.name: rcLacpGlobalSlowPeriodicTime
rcLacpGlobalSlowPeriodicTime.description: The number of miliseconds between periodic transmissions using LONG Timeouts. Set this value to all LACP enabled ports.

rcLacpGlobalTimeoutScale.name: rcLacpGlobalTimeoutScale
rcLacpGlobalTimeoutScale.description: Scalar value used to calculate timeout time from periodic time. Set this value to all LACP enabled ports.

rcLacpGlobalAggrWaitTime.name: rcLacpGlobalAggrWaitTime
rcLacpGlobalAggrWaitTime.description: The number of mili seconds to delay aggregation to allow multiple links to aggregate simultaneously.

rcLacpGlobalFastPeriodicTimeOper.name: rcLacpGlobalFastPeriodicTimeOper
rcLacpGlobalFastPeriodicTimeOper.description: The operating value of global fast periodic timer.

rcLacpGlobalSlowPeriodicTimeOper.name: rcLacpGlobalSlowPeriodicTimeOper
rcLacpGlobalSlowPeriodicTimeOper.description: The operating value of global show periodic time.

rcLacpGlobalTimeoutScaleOper.name: rcLacpGlobalTimeoutScaleOper
rcLacpGlobalTimeoutScaleOper.description: The operating value of global timeout scale.

rcLacpGlobalAggrWaitTimeOper.name: rcLacpGlobalAggrWaitTimeOper
rcLacpGlobalAggrWaitTimeOper.description: The operating value of global aggregate wait time.

rcLacpGlobalVlacpHoldTime.name: rcLacpGlobalVlacpHoldTime
rcLacpGlobalVlacpHoldTime.description: The number of seconds to hold down all vlacp enabled links

rcGlobalMacFilterTable.name: rcGlobalMacFilterTable
rcGlobalMacFilterTable.description: A list of Global Mac filter entries.

rcGlobalMacFilterEntry.name: rcGlobalMacFilterEntry
rcGlobalMacFilterEntry.description: this entry is used for global mac filtering.Any Mac address configured here will be discarded globally by the switch.

rcGlobalMacFilterAddress.name: rcGlobalMacFilterAddress
rcGlobalMacFilterAddress.description: A MAC address which will be discarded globally by the switch

rcGlobalMacFilterRowStatus.name: rcGlobalMacFilterRowStatus
rcGlobalMacFilterRowStatus.description: Used to create/delete entries in rcGlobalMacFilterTable.

LaneSet.name: LaneSet
LaneSet.description: The set of lanes that are members of this Global Policer. The string is 4 octets long, for a total of 32 bits. Each bit corresponds to a laneId. Each I/O slot has 4 laneIds. When a bit has the value one(1), the corresponding laneId is a member of the set. When a bit has the value zero(0), the corresponding laneId is not a member of the set. The encoding is such that the most significant bit of octet #1 corresponds to laneId 0, while the least significant bit of octet #4 corresponds to laneId 31.

rcPrQosPolicyNumPolicies.name: rcPrQosPolicyNumPolicies
rcPrQosPolicyNumPolicies.description: A list of Global Policer (GPID) entries. The number of entries is given by rcPrQosPolicyNumPolicies.

rcPrQosTxQueueNumTemplates.name: rcPrQosTxQueueNumTemplates
rcPrQosTxQueueNumTemplates.description: The number of egress queue templates currently defined in the switch.

rcPrQosPolicyTable.name: rcPrQosPolicyTable
rcPrQosPolicyTable.description: A list of GPID entries. The number of entries is given by rcPrQosPolicyNumPolicies.

rcPrQosPolicyEntry.name: rcPrQosPolicyEntry
rcPrQosPolicyEntry.description: Entry containing configuration information for a particular global policer.

rcPrQosPolicyGpId.name: rcPrQosPolicyGpId
rcPrQosPolicyGpId.description: A value that uniquely identifies Global Policer associated with this entry.

rcPrQosPolicyName.name: rcPrQosPolicyName
rcPrQosPolicyName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this Global Policer.

rcPrQosPolicyPeakRate.name: rcPrQosPolicyPeakRate
rcPrQosPolicyPeakRate.description: Global Policer Peak Rate in Kilobit/sec.

rcPrQosPolicySvcRate.name: rcPrQosPolicySvcRate
rcPrQosPolicySvcRate.description: Global Policer Service Rate in Kilobit/sec.

rcPrQosPolicyLaneMembers.name: rcPrQosPolicyLaneMembers
rcPrQosPolicyLaneMembers.description: The set of lanes that are members of this Global Policer. The string is 4 octets long, for a total of 32 bits. Each bit corresponds to a laneId. Each I/O slot has 4 laneIds. When a bit has the value one(1), the corresponding laneId is a member of the set. When a bit has the value zero(0), the corresponding laneId is not a member of the set. The encoding is such that the most significant bit of octet #1 corresponds to laneId 0, while the least significant bit of octet #4 corresponds to laneId 31.

rcPrQosLocalPolicyTable.name: rcPrQosLocalPolicyTable
rcPrQosLocalPolicyTable.description: A list of local (aka physical) policer entries.

rcPrQosLocalPolicyEntry.name: rcPrQosLocalPolicyEntry
rcPrQosLocalPolicyEntry.description: An entry containing configuration information for a particular local policer.

rcPrQosLocalPolicyGpId.name: rcPrQosLocalPolicyGpId
rcPrQosLocalPolicyGpId.description: A value of Global Policer ID corresponding to this local policer.

rcPrQosLocalPolicyIndex.name: rcPrQosLocalPolicyIndex
rcPrQosLocalPolicyIndex.description: A value that uniquely identifies the local Policer associated with this entry. Concatenation of tap.lane.lpid.

rcPrQosLocalPolicyPeakRate.name: rcPrQosLocalPolicyPeakRate
rcPrQosLocalPolicyPeakRate.description: Local Policer Peak Rate in Kilobit/sec. Equals to that of corresponding Global Policer ID.

rcPrQosLocalPolicySvcRate.name: rcPrQosLocalPolicySvcRate
rcPrQosLocalPolicySvcRate.description: Local Policer Service Rate in Kilobit/sec. Equals to that of corresponding Global Policer ID.

rcPrQosLocalPolicyBytesOverPeak.name: rcPrQosLocalPolicyBytesOverPeak
rcPrQosLocalPolicyBytesOverPeak.description: Local Policer Bytes over Peak Rate Count.

rcPrQosLocalPolicyBytesOverSvc.name: rcPrQosLocalPolicyBytesOverSvc
rcPrQosLocalPolicyBytesOverSvc.description: Local Policer Bytes over Service Rate Count.

rcPrQosLocalPolicyTotalPktsDropped.name: rcPrQosLocalPolicyTotalPktsDropped
rcPrQosLocalPolicyTotalPktsDropped.description: The count of Local Policer Total Packets dropped due to reasons other than policing, e.g. congestion.

rcPrQosLocalPolicyLaneMember.name: rcPrQosLocalPolicyLaneMember
rcPrQosLocalPolicyLaneMember.description: The lane that this Gpid has a local policing account on

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateTable.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateTable
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateTable.description: A list of egress queue templates. The number of templates is given by rcPrQosTxQueueNumTemplates.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateEntry.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateEntry
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateEntry.description: Entry containing configuration information for a particular egress queue template. Queue is a set of egress queues.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateId.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateId
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateId.description: A value that uniquely identifies Egress Queue Template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateName.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateName
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this egress Queue Template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateMaxQueues.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateMaxQueues
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateMaxQueues.description: Maximum number of queues in this Template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateBalancedQueues.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateBalancedQueues
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateBalancedQueues.description: Total number of Balanced Queues in this Template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateHiPriQueues.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateHiPriQueues
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateHiPriQueues.description: Total number of High Priority Queues in this Template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateLoPriQueues.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateLoPriQueues
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateLoPriQueues.description: Total number of Low Priority Queues in this Template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateTotalQueues.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateTotalQueues
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateTotalQueues.description: Total number of queues in this Template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateBalancedQList.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateBalancedQList
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateBalancedQList.description: List of Balanced Queues in this Template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateHiPriQList.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateHiPriQList
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateHiPriQList.description: List of High Priority Queues in this Template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateLoPriQList.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateLoPriQList
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateLoPriQList.description: List of Low Priority Queues in this Template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateTotalQLists.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateTotalQLists
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateTotalQLists.description: List of Total Physical Queues in this Template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateMinRateTotal.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateMinRateTotal
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateMinRateTotal.description: Sum of minimum rate guarantees for this template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateMaxRateHiPri.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateMaxRateHiPri
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateMaxRateHiPri.description: Sum of maximum rate guarantees for high priority queues of this template.

rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateApply.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateApply
rcPrQosTxQueueTemplateApply.description: When apply is issued by the administrator, the Egress Queue Set attributes are committed.

rcPrQosTxQueueTable.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTable
rcPrQosTxQueueTable.description: A list of elementary Egress queue entries.

rcPrQosTxQueueEntry.name: rcPrQosTxQueueEntry
rcPrQosTxQueueEntry.description: Entry containing configuration information for a particular elementary egress queue.

rcPrQosTxQueueTid.name: rcPrQosTxQueueTid
rcPrQosTxQueueTid.description: Template ID of the template this queue belongs to.

rcPrQosTxQueueQid.name: rcPrQosTxQueueQid
rcPrQosTxQueueQid.description: Queue Offset from the base queue for this port.

rcPrQosTxQueueName.name: rcPrQosTxQueueName
rcPrQosTxQueueName.description: An NNSC name for this egress queue. Allowed only for 8 NNSC queues.

rcPrQosTxQueueWeight.name: rcPrQosTxQueueWeight
rcPrQosTxQueueWeight.description: Egress queue weight. Applicable for balanced queues and lo-pri queues only.

rcPrQosTxQueueMinRate.name: rcPrQosTxQueueMinRate
rcPrQosTxQueueMinRate.description: Egress queue minimun rate guarantee, Kbs. Applicable for balanced queues and lo-pri queues only.

rcPrQosTxQueueBquantum.name: rcPrQosTxQueueBquantum
rcPrQosTxQueueBquantum.description: Bandwidth allocation unit. Applicable for balanced queues and lo-pri queues only.

rcPrQosTxQueueStatsTable.name: rcPrQosTxQueueStatsTable
rcPrQosTxQueueStatsTable.description: A list of elementary Egress queue stats entries.

rcPrQosTxQueueStatsEntry.name: rcPrQosTxQueueStatsEntry
rcPrQosTxQueueStatsEntry.description: Entry containing statistics information for a particular elementary egress queue.

rcPrQosTxQueueStatsPort.name: rcPrQosTxQueueStatsPort
rcPrQosTxQueueStatsPort.description: Port index of the stats table.

rcPrQosTxQueueStatsQid.name: rcPrQosTxQueueStatsQid
rcPrQosTxQueueStatsQid.description: Queue Offset from the base queue for this port.

rcPrQosTxQueueStatsTotalPages.name: rcPrQosTxQueueStatsTotalPages
rcPrQosTxQueueStatsTotalPages.description: Total pages offered to the queue.

rcPrQosTxQueueStatsDroppedPages.name: rcPrQosTxQueueStatsDroppedPages
rcPrQosTxQueueStatsDroppedPages.description: Total pages dropped by the queue.

rcPrQosIngressExpToQosTable.name: rcPrQosIngressExpToQosTable
rcPrQosIngressExpToQosTable.description: This table is used to specify the Mpls EXP to QOS (Exp bit->QOS) mapping on packet ingress.

rcPrQosIngressExpToQosEntry.name: rcPrQosIngressExpToQosEntry
rcPrQosIngressExpToQosEntry.description: Entry containing information of Exp bit->Qos mapping

rcPrQosIngressExpToQosIndex.name: rcPrQosIngressExpToQosIndex
rcPrQosIngressExpToQosIndex.description: Used to uniquely identify a row in this table.

rcPrQosEgressQosToExpTable.name: rcPrQosEgressQosToExpTable
rcPrQosEgressQosToExpTable.description: This table is used to specify the QOS to Mpls EXP bit field (QOS->Exp bit) mapping on packet egress.

rcPrQosEgressQosToExpEntry.name: rcPrQosEgressQosToExpEntry
rcPrQosEgressQosToExpEntry.description: Entry containing infomation of Qos->Exp bit mapping

rcPrQosEgressQosToExpIndex.name: rcPrQosEgressQosToExpIndex
rcPrQosEgressQosToExpIndex.description: Used to uniquely identify a row in this table.

rcPrFilterActTableSize.name: rcPrFilterActTableSize
rcPrFilterActTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of Act entries in the rcPrFilterActTable. Default table size is 0 until the administrator configures any Act entries.

rcPrFilterAclTableSize.name: rcPrFilterAclTableSize
rcPrFilterAclTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of Acl entries in the rcPrFilterAclTable. Default table size is 0 until the administrator configures any Acl entries.

rcPrFilterAceTableSize.name: rcPrFilterAceTableSize
rcPrFilterAceTableSize.description: Used to indicate the number of Ace entries in the rcPrFilterAceTable. Default table size is 0 until the administrator configures any Ace entries. The maximum size is # of Acls multiplied by # of Aces.

rcPrFilterActTable.name: rcPrFilterActTable
rcPrFilterActTable.description: A table of Acts to store information of each Act entry. This table is indexed by the Act Id.

rcPrFilterActEntry.name: rcPrFilterActEntry
rcPrFilterActEntry.description: One Act Entry holding Act information.

rcPrFilterActId.name: rcPrFilterActId
rcPrFilterActId.description: A table of Acts to store information of each Act. This table is indexed by the Act Id.

rcPrFilterActName.name: rcPrFilterActName
rcPrFilterActName.description: A descriptive name chosen by the administrator for the Act Entry.

rcPrFilterActArpAttrs.name: rcPrFilterActArpAttrs
rcPrFilterActArpAttrs.description: Value is one or multiple (logical 'OR' of the following): none(0), operation(1) none: No Arp Attrs are selected or to clear other choices. operation: Only valid option for Arp attributes.

rcPrFilterActEthernetAttrs.name: rcPrFilterActEthernetAttrs
rcPrFilterActEthernetAttrs.description: Value is one or multiple of the following: none(0), srcMac(1), dstMac(2), etherType(4), port(8), vlan(16), vlanTagPrio(32) none: If selected then unselect all other selections.

rcPrFilterActIpAttrs.name: rcPrFilterActIpAttrs
rcPrFilterActIpAttrs.description: Value is one or multiple of the following: none(0), srcIp(1), dstIp(2), ipFragFlag(4), ipOptions(8), ipProtoType(16), dscp(32) none: If selected then unselect all other selections.

rcPrFilterActProtocolAttrs.name: rcPrFilterActProtocolAttrs
rcPrFilterActProtocolAttrs.description: Value is one or multiple of the following: none(0), tcpSrcPort(1), udpSrcPort(2), tcpDstPort(4), udpDstPort(8), tcpFlags(16), icmpMsgType(32) none: If selected then unselect all other selections.

rcPrFilterActApply.name: rcPrFilterActApply
rcPrFilterActApply.description: When apply is issued by the administrator, the ACT attributes cannot be modified.

rcPrFilterActRowStatus.name: rcPrFilterActRowStatus
rcPrFilterActRowStatus.description: Create/delete operations for this entry. The entry cannot be modified or deleted while there are Acls configured with this Act entry.

rcPrFilterActIpv6Attrs.name: rcPrFilterActIpv6Attrs
rcPrFilterActIpv6Attrs.description: Value is one or multiple of the following: none(0), srcIpv6(1), dstIpv6(4), nextHdr(16), none: If selected then unselect all other selections.

rcPrFilterActPatternTable.name: rcPrFilterActPatternTable
rcPrFilterActPatternTable.description: A table of user-defined parameters of Acls to store information of each Acl. This table is indexed by the Act Id and PatternIndex.

rcPrFilterActPatternEntry.name: rcPrFilterActPatternEntry
rcPrFilterActPatternEntry.description: Entry containing Configuration information for a particular Act.

rcPrFilterActPatternActId.name: rcPrFilterActPatternActId
rcPrFilterActPatternActId.description: An index to the ActPatternEntry, a unique identifier for Act entry in the range of Table Size.

rcPrFilterActPatternIndex.name: rcPrFilterActPatternIndex
rcPrFilterActPatternIndex.description: Indexes each user defined field pattern in an Acl entry. In this release only 3 patterns are allowed per ACT but we can have multiple patterns per ACL.

rcPrFilterActPatternName.name: rcPrFilterActPatternName
rcPrFilterActPatternName.description: A descriptive name chosen by the administrator for the Acl Pattern Entry.

rcPrFilterActPatternBase.name: rcPrFilterActPatternBase
rcPrFilterActPatternBase.description: User defined fields from headers to be used in the Aces of the Acl.

rcPrFilterActPatternOffset.name: rcPrFilterActPatternOffset
rcPrFilterActPatternOffset.description: Set Offset in bits to the beginning offset of the user defined field with selected header option as base.

rcPrFilterActPatternLength.name: rcPrFilterActPatternLength
rcPrFilterActPatternLength.description: The number of bits to extract beginning from the offset is set in rcPrFilterActPatternLength. Only 1-56 are valid.

rcPrFilterAclTable.name: rcPrFilterAclTable
rcPrFilterAclTable.description: A table of Acls to store information of each Acl. This table is indexed by the Acl Id.

rcPrFilterAclEntry.name: rcPrFilterAclEntry
rcPrFilterAclEntry.description: Entry containing Configuration information for a particular Acl.

rcPrFilterAclId.name: rcPrFilterAclId
rcPrFilterAclId.description: A unique identifier for Acl entry in the range of Table Size.

rcPrFilterAclActId.name: rcPrFilterAclActId
rcPrFilterAclActId.description: A unique identifier for Act entry in the range of Table Size.

rcPrFilterAclName.name: rcPrFilterAclName
rcPrFilterAclName.description: A descriptive name chosen by the administrator for the Acl Entry.

rcPrFilterAclType.name: rcPrFilterAclType
rcPrFilterAclType.description: An Acl can be vlan-based or port-based. An Ace has a capability to match packets classified as 'ingress' and 'egress'. An ingress packet is assigned a value 'in' and an egress packet is assigned a value 'out'.

rcPrFilterAclAceListSize.name: rcPrFilterAclAceListSize
rcPrFilterAclAceListSize.description: Indicates the number of Aces in a particular Acl.

rcPrFilterAclDefaultAction.name: rcPrFilterAclDefaultAction
rcPrFilterAclDefaultAction.description: Indicates action to be taken when none of the Aces in the Acl match.

rcPrFilterAclGlobalAction.name: rcPrFilterAclGlobalAction
rcPrFilterAclGlobalAction.description: Indicates action is applied to all Aces that match in an Acl.

rcPrFilterAclState.name: rcPrFilterAclState
rcPrFilterAclState.description: Enables/Disables the state of all Aces in the Acl

rcPrFilterAclVlanList.name: rcPrFilterAclVlanList
rcPrFilterAclVlanList.description: An array used to indicate all the VLANs to be associated with this Acl Entry. At present, only 4k Vlans are supported.

rcPrFilterAclPortList.name: rcPrFilterAclPortList
rcPrFilterAclPortList.description: Indicates the ports to be added to this Acl Entry.

rcPrFilterAclRowStatus.name: rcPrFilterAclRowStatus
rcPrFilterAclRowStatus.description: Create/delete operations for the entry. Deleting a non-empty Acl results in deletion of member Aces and then the Acl.

rcPrFilterAclNumVlanIds.name: rcPrFilterAclNumVlanIds
rcPrFilterAclNumVlanIds.description: Used to Indicate the number of VLAN ID's that are stored in the rcPrFilterAclVlanList.

rcPrFilterAclPktType.name: rcPrFilterAclPktType
rcPrFilterAclPktType.description: Indicates the packet type that thsi ACL is applicable to.

rcPrFilterAclStatsTable.name: rcPrFilterAclStatsTable
rcPrFilterAclStatsTable.description: A table of Acls Statistics entries to store the Default Acl statistics for each Acl. This table is indexed by the Acl Id.

rcPrFilterAclStatsEntry.name: rcPrFilterAclStatsEntry
rcPrFilterAclStatsEntry.description: Entry containing default statistics information for a particular Acl.

rcPrFilterAclStatsAclId.name: rcPrFilterAclStatsAclId
rcPrFilterAclStatsAclId.description: A unique identifier for Acl entry in the range of Table Size.

rcPrFilterAclStatsMatchDefaultCounterPkt.name: rcPrFilterAclStatsMatchDefaultCounterPkts
rcPrFilterAclStatsMatchDefaultCounterPkt.description: Packet count of traffic not matching any of the Ace rules or hit the Default Action that have the count bit turned on in Acl Global Action.

rcPrFilterAclStatsMatchDefaultOctets.name: rcPrFilterAclStatsMatchDefaultOctets
rcPrFilterAclStatsMatchDefaultOctets.description: Byte count of traffic not matching any of the Ace rules or hit the Default Action that have the count bit turned on in Acl Global Action.

rcPrFilterAclStatsClear.name: rcPrFilterAclStatsClear
rcPrFilterAclStatsClear.description: Clear default statistics for ACL Filters.

rcPrFilterAceTable.name: rcPrFilterAceTable
rcPrFilterAceTable.description: A table of Aces to store information of each Ace in context of its parent Acl. This is indexed by AclId and AceId.

rcPrFilterAceEntry.name: rcPrFilterAceEntry
rcPrFilterAceEntry.description: One Ace entry holding Ace information. Ace is a member of one Acl.

rcPrFilterAceAclId.name: rcPrFilterAceAclId
rcPrFilterAceAclId.description: An index to the AceEntry, a unique identifier for Acl entry in the range of Table Size.

rcPrFilterAceId.name: rcPrFilterAceId
rcPrFilterAceId.description: AceId uniquely identifies one Ace entry.

rcPrFilterAceName.name: rcPrFilterAceName
rcPrFilterAceName.description: A descriptive name chosen by the administrator. System automatically assigns a name if the user has not assigned one.

rcPrFilterAceMode.name: rcPrFilterAceMode
rcPrFilterAceMode.description: Operating Mode associated with the Ace is effective on the packets matching this Ace.

rcPrFilterAceRemarkDscp.name: rcPrFilterAceRemarkDscp
rcPrFilterAceRemarkDscp.description: The 6-bit DSCP field from the ToS byte in Ipv4 header encodes the PHB information per DiffServ standards (Refer to DiffServ RFCs 2474). Set the Dscp to PHB (like EF) or PHB-class(like AF1 which includes AF11, AF12,AF13) to mark specific diffserv class traffic. Set the field value to desired integer dscp code for rcPrFilterAceRemarkDscp field to mark non-standard traffic classes and local use PHBs.

rcPrFilterAceRemarkDot1Priority.name: rcPrFilterAceRemarkDot1Priority
rcPrFilterAceRemarkDot1Priority.description: Dot1 Priority as described by Layer 2 standards, 802.1Q, 802.1P.

rcPrFilterAceRedirectNextHop.name: rcPrFilterAceRedirectNextHop
rcPrFilterAceRedirectNextHop.description: Redirect matching IP traffic to the next hop.

rcPrFilterAceRedirectUnreach.name: rcPrFilterAceRedirectUnreach
rcPrFilterAceRedirectUnreach.description: Set the desired behavior for redirected traffic in case the specified next-hop is not reachable.

rcPrFilterAcePolice.name: rcPrFilterAcePolice
rcPrFilterAcePolice.description: Policing profile Identifier. Set the desired policing profile identifier. Set the value to 0 when policing is not desired.

rcPrFilterAceAdminState.name: rcPrFilterAceAdminState
rcPrFilterAceAdminState.description: Value indicating whether the Ace is enabled. An Ace can only be modified if it is disabled.

rcPrFilterAceOperState.name: rcPrFilterAceOperState
rcPrFilterAceOperState.description: The current operational state of the Ace.

rcPrFilterAceEgressQueue.name: rcPrFilterAceEgressQueue
rcPrFilterAceEgressQueue.description: Indicates the Egress Queue for 10/100 card. If only 1 value is specified then this value is applied to Queue1g and Queue10g as well. If 2 values are specified then the first value is applied to 10/100 card and the second value is applied to 1gig and 10gig cards. If all three values are specified, then all three values are applied respectively to the appropriate Egress Queue. If value is greater than 8, it will not be applied to the 10/100 card as it only has 8 queues. However, the value will be applied to the 1gig and 10gig card types.

rcPrFilterAceEgressQueue1g.name: rcPrFilterAceEgressQueue1g
rcPrFilterAceEgressQueue1g.description: Indicates the Egress Queue for 1gig card.

rcPrFilterAceEgressQueue10g.name: rcPrFilterAceEgressQueue10g
rcPrFilterAceEgressQueue10g.description: Indicates the Egress Queue for 10gig card.

rcPrFilterAceFlags.name: rcPrFilterAceFlags
rcPrFilterAceFlags.description: Bitmask for the flags: none(0): Default value for the flags. stopOnMatch(1): set desired behavior for flag whether to stop or continue in case an Ace matching the packet is found. When this Ace is hit, match on other Aces with a lower priority is not attempted. count(2): set desired behavior for flag i.e. to enable/disable counting in case a packet matching the ace is found. copyToPrimaryCp(4): set to enable/disable copying of matching packets to primary CP. copyToSecondaryCp(8): set to enable/disable copying of matching packets to secondary CP. mirror(16): set to enable/disable mirroring the matching packets to an interface. System can mirror one port or mirror to 1 port.

rcPrFilterAceStopOnMatch.name: rcPrFilterAceStopOnMatch
rcPrFilterAceStopOnMatch.description: Value indicating whether stop-on-match option on the Ace is enabled.

rcPrFilterAceMltIndex.name: rcPrFilterAceMltIndex
rcPrFilterAceMltIndex.description: If this action is specified, it will basically override the mlt-index picked by the mlt algorithm, when a packet is being sent out on MLT ports.

rcPrFilterAceIpfixState.name: rcPrFilterAceIpfixState
rcPrFilterAceIpfixState.description: Value indicating whether ipfix option on the Ace is enabled.

rcPrFilterAceRedirectNextHopIpv6.name: rcPrFilterAceRedirectNextHopIpv6
rcPrFilterAceRedirectNextHopIpv6.description: Redirect matching IPv6 traffic to the next hop.

rcPrFilterAceDstPortList.name: rcPrFilterAceDstPortList
rcPrFilterAceDstPortList.description: Destination Port List for mirroring the packets.

VPNId.name: VPNId
VPNId.description: The purpose of a VPN-ID is to uniquely identify a VPN. The Global VPN Identifier format is: 3 octet VPN Authority, Organizationally Unique Identifier followed by 4 octet VPN index identifying VPN according to OUI
VPNId.reference: Fox, B. and Gleeson, B., 'Virtual Private Networks Identifier', RFC 2685, September 1999.

VrfRpTriggerBitCode.name: VrfRpTriggerBitCode
VrfRpTriggerBitCode.description: This object represents Routing Protocol (RP) Triggers on a Virtual Router. The BITS represent an Action-code that specifies the action on the Routing Protocols. The actions are: initiate or shutdown. When encoding the RP using the BITS construct, the value is encoded as an OCTET STRING where the first bit (bit 0) is the highest bit of the octet. Bits 0-3 may be specified in any combination to allow multiple Routing Protocols to be acted on simultaneously or individually.

rcVrfConfigNextAvailableVrfId.name: rcVrfConfigNextAvailableVrfId
rcVrfConfigNextAvailableVrfId.description: The next available Virtual Router Id (index). This object provides a hint for the rcVrfId value to use when administratively creating a new rcVrfConfigEntry. A GET of this object returns the next available rcVrfId value to be used to create an entry in the associated rcVrfConfigTable; or zero, if no valid rcVrfId value is available. A value of zero(0) indicates that it is not possible to create a new rcVrfConfigEntry. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously. Unless specified otherwise by its MAX-ACCESS and DESCRIPTION clauses, an object of this type is read-only, and a SET of such an object returns a notWritable error.

rcVrfConfigTable.name: rcVrfConfigTable
rcVrfConfigTable.description: This table is for creating the new Virtual Routers.

rcVrfConfigEntry.name: rcVrfConfigEntry
rcVrfConfigEntry.description: The entries in this table can be added/deleted using the rcVrfRowStatus.

rcVrfId.name: rcVrfId
rcVrfId.description: The unique id of this virtual router instance. A Virtual Router cannot not be created with rcVrfId = 0. VRFID 0 is reserved for the Administrative VRF.

rcVrfRowStatus.name: rcVrfRowStatus
rcVrfRowStatus.description: The status column has three defined values: - `active', which indicates that the conceptual row is available for use by the managed device; - `createAndGo', which is supplied by a management station wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row and to have its status automatically set to active, making it available for use by the managed device; - `destroy', which is supplied by a management station wishing to delete all of the instances associated with an existing conceptual row.

rcVrfName.name: rcVrfName
rcVrfName.description: The Name of the Virtual Router.

rcVrfContextName.name: rcVrfContextName
rcVrfContextName.description: The SNMPv2 Community String or SNMPv3 contextName denotes the VRF 'context' and is used to logically separate the MIB module management.

rcVrfTrapEnable.name: rcVrfTrapEnable
rcVrfTrapEnable.description: This objects is used to enable the generation of the VrfUp and VrfDown traps. true(1) - VRF Traps Enabled false(2) - VRF Traps Disabled

rcVrfMaxRoutes.name: rcVrfMaxRoutes
rcVrfMaxRoutes.description: This object specifies the maximum number of routes that this VRF can support. The default value is 10000.

rcVrfAdminStatus.name: rcVrfAdminStatus
rcVrfAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of the Virtual Router.

rcVrfVpnId.name: rcVrfVpnId
rcVrfVpnId.description: The Virtual Private Network Identifier of the Virtual Router.

rcVrfRpTrigger.name: rcVrfRpTrigger
rcVrfRpTrigger.description: This object represents Routing Protocol (RP) Triggers on a Virtual Router and it meant to be used to initiate or shutdown routing protocols on a VRF. Multiple RPs can be acted on simultaneously. Also, individual RPs can be brought up in steps, which should not affect the RPs that were running. The BITS represent an Action-code that specifies what action is to be performed for the RPs. The actions are: initiate(1) or shutdown(0). The running status of an RP shall be available in the VRF stats table's rcVrfRpStatus, which has a similar format, but represents the status. Bits 0-3 may be specified in any combination. Individual routing protocols may be enabled and disabled independently. Protocols are enabled by setting the respective BIT and are disabled by resetting the BIT. So, for example, to enable RIP and BGP protocols the rcVrfRpTrigger bits 0 and 2 need to be set, and as encoded as 10100000. All zeros should be interpreted as all protocols disable.

rcVrfMaxRoutesTrapEnable.name: rcVrfMaxRoutesTrapEnable
rcVrfMaxRoutesTrapEnable.description: This objects is used to enable the generation of the VRF Max Routes Exceeded traps. true(1) - VRF Max Routes Exceeded Traps Enabled false(2) - VRF Max Routes Exceeded Traps Disabled

rcVrfConfiguredVRFs.name: rcVrfConfiguredVRFs
rcVrfConfiguredVRFs.description: The number of VRFs configured on this network element.

rcVrfActiveVRFs.name: rcVrfActiveVRFs
rcVrfActiveVRFs.description: The number of VRFs that are active on the network element. These are VRFs for which the rcVrfStatOperStatus = up(1)

rcVrfStatTable.name: rcVrfStatTable
rcVrfStatTable.description: This table contains statistics for the Virtual Router.

rcVrfStatEntry.name: rcVrfStatEntry
rcVrfStatEntry.description: Entries in this table are per rcVrfId.

rcVrfStatRouteEntries.name: rcVrfStatRouteEntries
rcVrfStatRouteEntries.description: Total number of routes for this VRF.

rcVrfStatFIBEntries.name: rcVrfStatFIBEntries
rcVrfStatFIBEntries.description: Total number of FIB Entries for this VRF.

rcVrfStatUpTime.name: rcVrfStatUpTime
rcVrfStatUpTime.description: The time in (in hundredths of a second) since this VRF entry has been operational.

rcVrfOperStatus.name: rcVrfOperStatus
rcVrfOperStatus.description: The operational status of the Virtual Router.

rcVrfRpStatus.name: rcVrfRpStatus
rcVrfRpStatus.description: This object represents the status of Routing Protocols on this VRF corresponding to the list of RP specified in rcVrfRpTrigger. The BITS represent an Action-code that specifies the status of the RPs. The status are: initiated (1) or shutdown (0). Initiated status is indicated when the respective BIT value is 1 and indicates shutdown when the respective BIT value is 0. Bits 0-3 may appear in any combination to indicate that RPs may be enabled and disabled independently or that multiple RP are acted on simultaneously.

rcVrfRouterAddressType.name: rcVrfRouterAddressType
rcVrfRouterAddressType.description: Router Address Type of this VRF.

rcVrfRouterAddress.name: rcVrfRouterAddress
rcVrfRouterAddress.description: Router Address of this VRF. It is derived from one of the interfaces. If loopback interface is present, the loopback interface address can be used. However, loopback interface is optional.

rcIpfixConfState.name: rcIpfixConfState
rcIpfixConfState.description: Enables/Disables the state of ipfix on the box.

rcIpfixConfSlotTable.name: rcIpfixConfSlotTable
rcIpfixConfSlotTable.description: A table to store the configuration details for IPFIX for each slot. This table is indexed by slot number.

rcIpfixConfSlotEntry.name: rcIpfixConfSlotEntry
rcIpfixConfSlotEntry.description: One Entry holding IPFIX config information on slot basis.

rcIpfixConfSlotAgingIntv.name: rcIpfixConfSlotAgingIntv
rcIpfixConfSlotAgingIntv.description: Flow record aging interval (Value in seconds).

rcIpfixConfSlotActiveTimeout.name: rcIpfixConfSlotActiveTimeout
rcIpfixConfSlotActiveTimeout.description: Flow record active timeout value (Value in mins).

rcIpfixConfSlotExportIntv.name: rcIpfixConfSlotExportIntv
rcIpfixConfSlotExportIntv.description: Frequency of flow export to collector (Value in sec).

rcIpfixConfSlotTempRefIntvSec.name: rcIpfixConfSlotTempRefIntvSec
rcIpfixConfSlotTempRefIntvSec.description: Template refresh timeout. Template is sent out to the collector at least every x seconds or every y exported packets, whichever occurs first.

rcIpfixConfSlotTempRefIntvPkts.name: rcIpfixConfSlotTempRefIntvPkts
rcIpfixConfSlotTempRefIntvPkts.description: Template refresh timeout. Template is sent out to the collector at least every x seconds or every y exported packets, whichever occurs first.

rcIpfixCollectorTable.name: rcIpfixCollectorTable
rcIpfixCollectorTable.description: Table to store the configuration details for IPFIX collector for each slot. This table is indexed by slot number and ip address.

rcIpfixCollectorEntry.name: rcIpfixCollectorEntry
rcIpfixCollectorEntry.description: One entry holds IPFIX collector config information based on slot info and collector ip address.

rcIpfixCollectorSlotNum.name: rcIpfixCollectorSlotNum
rcIpfixCollectorSlotNum.description: Slot number. An index to the CollectorEntry.

rcIpfixCollectorAddressType.name: rcIpfixCollectorAddressType
rcIpfixCollectorAddressType.description: IP address type of the collector. An index to the CollectorEntry.

rcIpfixCollectorAddress.name: rcIpfixCollectorAddress
rcIpfixCollectorAddress.description: IP address of the collector. An index to the CollectorEntry.

rcIpfixCollectorProtocol.name: rcIpfixCollectorProtocol
rcIpfixCollectorProtocol.description: Protocol for export data from exporter to collector .

rcIpfixCollectorDestPort.name: rcIpfixCollectorDestPort
rcIpfixCollectorDestPort.description: Dest port to send the requests.

rcIpfixCollectorExporterIpType.name: rcIpfixCollectorExporterIpType
rcIpfixCollectorExporterIpType.description: Ip address type of the exporter for collector.

rcIpfixCollectorExporterIp.name: rcIpfixCollectorExporterIp
rcIpfixCollectorExporterIp.description: Ip address of the exporter for collector.

rcIpfixCollectorProtoVer.name: rcIpfixCollectorProtoVer
rcIpfixCollectorProtoVer.description: This specifies the protocol version for ipfix.

rcIpfixCollectorState.name: rcIpfixCollectorState
rcIpfixCollectorState.description: State of the particular collector. Enable is true by default.

rcIpfixConfPortTable.name: rcIpfixConfPortTable
rcIpfixConfPortTable.description: A table to store the configuration details for IPFIX for each port. This table is indexed by port number.

rcIpfixConfPortEntry.name: rcIpfixConfPortEntry
rcIpfixConfPortEntry.description: Entry holding IPFIX config information per port.

rcIpfixConfPortId.name: rcIpfixConfPortId
rcIpfixConfPortId.description: An index to the IpfixConfPortEntry, a unique identifier of the portId

rcIpfixConfPortSampleRate.name: rcIpfixConfPortSampleRate
rcIpfixConfPortSampleRate.description: Used to configure the sampling rate. Sample one in every N packets.

rcIpfixConfPortHashPolyCoeffs.name: rcIpfixConfPortHashPolyCoeffs
rcIpfixConfPortHashPolyCoeffs.description: Command to set hash polynomial coeffs.

rcIpfixConfPortHashPolySeed.name: rcIpfixConfPortHashPolySeed
rcIpfixConfPortHashPolySeed.description: Command to set hash polynomial seed.

rcIpfixConfPortFlush.name: rcIpfixConfPortFlush
rcIpfixConfPortFlush.description: This is used to delete all records stored in COP, or to initiate an export of all records and delete data base after the export is finished.

rcIpfixConfPortAllTraffic.name: rcIpfixConfPortAllTraffic
rcIpfixConfPortAllTraffic.description: This is used to enable/disable ipfix on all trafiic, for the specified port.

rcIpfixHashStatsTable.name: rcIpfixHashStatsTable
rcIpfixHashStatsTable.description: A table of hash Statistics entries to store the statistics for each slot. This table is indexed by the slot number.

rcIpfixHashStatsEntry.name: rcIpfixHashStatsEntry
rcIpfixHashStatsEntry.description: Entry containing hash statistics information for a particular slot.

rcIpfixHashStatsSlotNum.name: rcIpfixHashStatsSlotNum
rcIpfixHashStatsSlotNum.description: A unique identifier for the table.

rcIpfixHashStatsHashOverflows.name: rcIpfixHashStatsHashOverflows
rcIpfixHashStatsHashOverflows.description: Count of hash overflows per slot.

rcIpfixHashStatsHashDrops.name: rcIpfixHashStatsHashDrops
rcIpfixHashStatsHashDrops.description: Count of hash drops per slot.

rcIpfixHashStatsClear.name: rcIpfixHashStatsClear
rcIpfixHashStatsClear.description: Setting this object will clear hash statistics for a slot.

rcIpfixHashStatsClearTime.name: rcIpfixHashStatsClearTime
rcIpfixHashStatsClearTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the hash statistics were last cleared.

rcIpfixExporterStatsTable.name: rcIpfixExporterStatsTable
rcIpfixExporterStatsTable.description: A table of Exporter Statistics entries to store the statistics for each slot, each collector. This table is indexed by the slot number and collector address.

rcIpfixExporterStatsEntry.name: rcIpfixExporterStatsEntry
rcIpfixExporterStatsEntry.description: Entry containing Exporter statistics information for a particular slot and particular collector.

rcIpfixExporterStatsSlotNum.name: rcIpfixExporterStatsSlotNum
rcIpfixExporterStatsSlotNum.description: Index for the table, slot number.

rcIpfixExporterStatsCollectorType.name: rcIpfixExporterStatsCollectorType
rcIpfixExporterStatsCollectorType.description: Collector IP address type. This is an index for the table.

rcIpfixExporterStatsCollector.name: rcIpfixExporterStatsCollector
rcIpfixExporterStatsCollector.description: Index for the table, collector address.

rcIpfixExporterStatsClear.name: rcIpfixExporterStatsClear
rcIpfixExporterStatsClear.description: Setting this object will clear exporter statistics.

rcIpfixExporterStatsClearTime.name: rcIpfixExporterStatsClearTime
rcIpfixExporterStatsClearTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when exporter statistics were last cleared.

rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherTable.name: rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherTable
rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherTable.description: The Route Distinguisher Table is a table of entries.

rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherEntry.name: rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherEntry
rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherEntry.description: The table contains route distinguisher entry for ipvpn. A route distinguisher entry can be of two types: Type 0 and Type 1. Each type is comprised as follows: Type 0 is made of the 2-byte Autonomous System Number (globally unique) as administrator field followed by a 4-byte locally assigned number field.Type 1 is made of a 4 byte IP address globally unique followed by a 2-byte locally assigned number.

rcIpVpnVrfId.name: rcIpVpnVrfId
rcIpVpnVrfId.description: The VrfId is the unique identifier of the rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherTable. It is unique because there is only one Route-Distinguisher per Vrf i.e. there is a one-to-one mapping between the route-distinguisher and the Vrf.

rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherType.name: rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherType
rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherType.description: The route distinguisher can be of the type Ipaddress or AS number (Autonomous System) number.

rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherAddress.name: rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherAddress
rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherAddress.description: The IpAddress is required along with the Assigned number to create a route-distinguisher entry.

rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherAsNumber.name: rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherAsNumber
rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherAsNumber.description: The AS (Autonomous System) number is required along with the Assigned number to create a route-distinguisher entry.

rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherAssignedNum.name: rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherAssignedNum
rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherAssignedNum.description: The assigned number is used in combination with the IpAddress or the AS number to create an entry for the route-distinguisher.

rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherRowStatus.name: rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherRowStatus
rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherRowStatus.description: Row Status for the Route Distinguisher Table.

rcIpVpnRouteTargetTable.name: rcIpVpnRouteTargetTable
rcIpVpnRouteTargetTable.description: This table specifies per-VRF route target association.

rcIpVpnRouteTargetEntry.name: rcIpVpnRouteTargetEntry
rcIpVpnRouteTargetEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for each route target configured for a VRF supporting a MPLS/BGP VPN instance.

rcIpVpnRouteTargetIndex.name: rcIpVpnRouteTargetIndex
rcIpVpnRouteTargetIndex.description: The Route Target Index is a unique value for the rcIpVpnRouteTargetTable. It is an incremental integer value.

rcIpVpnRouteTargetType.name: rcIpVpnRouteTargetType
rcIpVpnRouteTargetType.description: The route target entry is identified on the basis of ipaddress for Autonomous System number.

rcIpVpnRouteTargetIpAddress.name: rcIpVpnRouteTargetIpAddress
rcIpVpnRouteTargetIpAddress.description: The IpAddress is required along with the Assigned number to create a route-target entry.

rcIpVpnRouteTargetAsNumber.name: rcIpVpnRouteTargetAsNumber
rcIpVpnRouteTargetAsNumber.description: The AS (Autonomous System) number is required along with the Assigned number to create a route-target entry.

rcIpVpnRouteTargetAssignedNum.name: rcIpVpnRouteTargetAssignedNum
rcIpVpnRouteTargetAssignedNum.description: The assigned number is used in combination with the IpAddress or the AS number to create an entry for the route-target table.

rcVrfIpVpnTable.name: rcVrfIpVpnTable
rcVrfIpVpnTable.description: Table required to configure vpn under ip.

rcVrfIpVpnTableEntry.name: rcVrfIpVpnTableEntry
rcVrfIpVpnTableEntry.description: Entries in this table are per rcVrfId.

rcVrfIpVpnVrfId.name: rcVrfIpVpnVrfId
rcVrfIpVpnVrfId.description: The VrfId serves as the Index for the rcIpVpnVrfTable and also for the rcIpVpnRouteDistinguisherTable. It allows to connect to the vrf table to obtain other attributes like the vrf name, rcVrfMaxRoutesTrapEnable etc.

rcVrfIpVpnImportRTList.name: rcVrfIpVpnImportRTList
rcVrfIpVpnImportRTList.description: The Import RT list is a list of all the route-targets attached to a particular vrf behaving in the import mode.

rcVrfIpVpnExportRTList.name: rcVrfIpVpnExportRTList
rcVrfIpVpnExportRTList.description: The Export RT list is a list of all the route-targets attached to a particular vrf in the export mode.

rcVrfIpVpnSvcLblAllocOpt.name: rcVrfIpVpnSvcLblAllocOpt
rcVrfIpVpnSvcLblAllocOpt.description: The service label allocation option for the ipvpn

rcVrfIpVpnIsidNumber.name: rcVrfIpVpnIsidNumber
rcVrfIpVpnIsidNumber.description: IP VPN I-SID number.Default 0 value indicates that no i-sid has been assinged.

rcSlppGlobalEnable.name: rcSlppGlobalEnable
rcSlppGlobalEnable.description: Global enable/disable for the simple loop prevention protocol.

rcSlppTransmissionInterval.name: rcSlppTransmissionInterval
rcSlppTransmissionInterval.description: The interval (in seconds) for which loop detection occurs.

rcSlppEtherType.name: rcSlppEtherType
rcSlppEtherType.description: SLPP Protocol Identification. The value is normally in Hex.

rcSlppVlanTable.name: rcSlppVlanTable
rcSlppVlanTable.description: Table of VLANs for which simple loop detection occur on.

rcSlppVlanVlanId.name: rcSlppVlanVlanId
rcSlppVlanVlanId.description: Vlan id for which simple loop detection occurs on.

rcSlppVlanSlppEnable.name: rcSlppVlanSlppEnable
rcSlppVlanSlppEnable.description: Flag to indicate whether the VLAN entry is active or not for SLPP.

rcSlppPortTable.name: rcSlppPortTable
rcSlppPortTable.description: Table of ports for which simple loop detection occurs on.

rcSlppPortIfIndex.name: rcSlppPortIfIndex
rcSlppPortIfIndex.description: Port on which simple loop detection occurs on.

rcSlppPortPktRxThreshold.name: rcSlppPortPktRxThreshold
rcSlppPortPktRxThreshold.description: Once the number of SLPP packets received on this port reaches this threshold action will be taken.Normally, the port will be shutdown.

rcSlppPortSlppEnable.name: rcSlppPortSlppEnable
rcSlppPortSlppEnable.description: Flag to indicate whether the port entry is active or not for SLPP.

rcSlppPortIncomingVlanId.name: rcSlppPortIncomingVlanId
rcSlppPortIncomingVlanId.description: Vlan id of the classified packet on the port brought down by SLPP.

rcSlppPortSrcNodeType.name: rcSlppPortSrcNodeType
rcSlppPortSrcNodeType.description: The src node type of the received slpp Pkt.

rcSlppIncomingVlanId.name: rcSlppIncomingVlanId
rcSlppIncomingVlanId.description: Vlan id of the classified packet on the port brought down by SLPP.

rcSlppSrcMacAddress.name: rcSlppSrcMacAddress
rcSlppSrcMacAddress.description: Source MAC address in the classified packet on the port brought down by SLPP.

rcSlppRxPortIndex.name: rcSlppRxPortIndex
rcSlppRxPortIndex.description: Port on which the SLPP packet is received.

rcSlppRxVlanId.name: rcSlppRxVlanId
rcSlppRxVlanId.description: Vlan on which the SLPP packet is received.

rcnSlppPortDownEvent.name: rcnSlppPortDownEvent
rcnSlppPortDownEvent.description: A port down event that has occurred due to SLPP. The user is notified of the expected Vlan ID along with the Vlan ID and source MAC address of the packet coming in on the port identified. The first two objects can be used to lookup instance info for port id and vlan id.

rcnSlppPortDownEventNew.name: rcnSlppPortDownEventNew
rcnSlppPortDownEventNew.description: A port down event that has occurred due to SLPP. The trap includes the port and its Vlan which receives the packet, and along with the Vlan ID and source MAC address of the packet coming in on the port identified.

rcMplsRouterId.name: rcMplsRouterId
rcMplsRouterId.description: IP address of the circuitless interface to be used as router-id

rcMplsLdpAdminStatus.name: rcMplsLdpAdminStatus
rcMplsLdpAdminStatus.description: State of global LDP - enabled or disabled

rcMplsLdpPenultimateHopPop.name: rcMplsLdpPenultimateHopPop
rcMplsLdpPenultimateHopPop.description: State of global LDP Penultimate Hop Popping.

rcMplsLdpHelloHoldTimer.name: rcMplsLdpHelloHoldTimer
rcMplsLdpHelloHoldTimer.description: The global Hello Hold Time in seconds.

rcMplsLdpSessionKeepAlive.name: rcMplsLdpSessionKeepAlive
rcMplsLdpSessionKeepAlive.description: The global Session Keep alive in seconds.

rcMplsLdpHopCountLimit.name: rcMplsLdpHopCountLimit
rcMplsLdpHopCountLimit.description: The global loop detect hop count limit.

rcMplsLdpEgressPolicyStatus.name: rcMplsLdpEgressPolicyStatus
rcMplsLdpEgressPolicyStatus.description: State of LDP Egress-policy enabled or disabled

rcMplsRsvpAdminStatus.name: rcMplsRsvpAdminStatus
rcMplsRsvpAdminStatus.description: State of global RSVP - enabled or disabled

rcMplsRsvpPenultimateHopPop.name: rcMplsRsvpPenultimateHopPop
rcMplsRsvpPenultimateHopPop.description: State of global RSVP Penultimate Hop Popping.

rcMplsRsvpRefreshReduction.name: rcMplsRsvpRefreshReduction
rcMplsRsvpRefreshReduction.description: State of global RSVP refresh reduction - enabled or disabled

rcMplsRsvpRefreshInterval.name: rcMplsRsvpRefreshInterval
rcMplsRsvpRefreshInterval.description: The global value for RSVP refresh interval.

rcMplsRsvpRefreshMultiplier.name: rcMplsRsvpRefreshMultiplier
rcMplsRsvpRefreshMultiplier.description: The global value for RSVP refresh multiplier.

rcMplsRsvpMessageBundling.name: rcMplsRsvpMessageBundling
rcMplsRsvpMessageBundling.description: State of global RSVP message bundling - enabled or disabled

rcMplsLspIngressStartLabel.name: rcMplsLspIngressStartLabel
rcMplsLspIngressStartLabel.description: The global ingress rsp start label.

rcMplsLspEgressStartLabel.name: rcMplsLspEgressStartLabel
rcMplsLspEgressStartLabel.description: The global egress rsp start label.

rcMplsLspIngressPktEnable.name: rcMplsLspIngressPktEnable
rcMplsLspIngressPktEnable.description: Enable/Disable ingress rsp pkt lsp stats

rcMplsLspEgressPktEnable.name: rcMplsLspEgressPktEnable
rcMplsLspEgressPktEnable.description: Enable/Disable egress rsp pkt lsp stats

rcMplsIpStaticFecTable.name: rcMplsIpStaticFecTable
rcMplsIpStaticFecTable.description: This is the table of ip-static fec mappings for both RSVP and LDP .

rcMplsIpStaticFecEntry.name: rcMplsIpStaticFecEntry
rcMplsIpStaticFecEntry.description: A static fec mapping to an rsvp lsp or ldp egress IP address.

rcMplsIpStaticFecTunnelName.name: rcMplsIpStaticFecTunnelName
rcMplsIpStaticFecTunnelName.description: The rsvp lsp tunnel name associated with rcMplsIpStaticFecTunnelId. This field will be null if the value of rcMplsIpStaticFecTunnelId is 0.

rcMplsIpStaticFecTunnelId.name: rcMplsIpStaticFecTunnelId
rcMplsIpStaticFecTunnelId.description: The rsvp lsp tunnel index (from mplsTunnelTable defined in rfc3812) if this is an rsvp Ip statically mapped address. This field will be 0 if this is an LDP Egress Address mapping.

rcMplsIpStaticFecEgressAddr.name: rcMplsIpStaticFecEgressAddr
rcMplsIpStaticFecEgressAddr.description: The LDP Egress IP Address. This field will be 0 if this is an rsvp tunnel fec mapping.

rcMplsIpStaticFecEgressMask.name: rcMplsIpStaticFecEgressMask
rcMplsIpStaticFecEgressMask.description: The LDP Egress IP Mask. This field will be 0 if this is an rsvp tunnel fec mapping.

rcMplsIpStaticFecState.name: rcMplsIpStaticFecState
rcMplsIpStaticFecState.description: Indicates the actual operational status of this static fec.

rcMplsIpStaticFecRowStatus.name: rcMplsIpStaticFecRowStatus
rcMplsIpStaticFecRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table.

rcMplsIpFtnTable.name: rcMplsIpFtnTable
rcMplsIpFtnTable.description: This is the table of mpls Ip FTN.

rcMplsIpFtnType.name: rcMplsIpFtnType
rcMplsIpFtnType.description: The FTN next hop label type.

rcMplsIpFtnOutIfIndex.name: rcMplsIpFtnOutIfIndex
rcMplsIpFtnOutIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcMplsIpFtnNextHop.name: rcMplsIpFtnNextHop
rcMplsIpFtnNextHop.description: The FTN next hop Ip Address.

rcMplsIpIlmTable.name: rcMplsIpIlmTable
rcMplsIpIlmTable.description: This is the table of mpls Incoming Label Mapping.

rcMplsIpIlmEntry.name: rcMplsIpIlmEntry
rcMplsIpIlmEntry.description: An mpls Incoming Label Map entry .

rcMplsIpIlmInIfIndex.name: rcMplsIpIlmInIfIndex
rcMplsIpIlmInIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the incoming interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcMplsIpIlmOutIfIndex.name: rcMplsIpIlmOutIfIndex
rcMplsIpIlmOutIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the outgoing interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rcMplsIngressLspStatTable.name: rcMplsIngressLspStatTable
rcMplsIngressLspStatTable.description: This is the table of mpls Incoming Label Stats.

rcMplsIngressLspStatEntry.name: rcMplsIngressLspStatEntry
rcMplsIngressLspStatEntry.description: An mpls Incoming Label Stat entry .

rcMplsIngressLspPort.name: rcMplsIngressLspPort
rcMplsIngressLspPort.description: The incoming port for the lsp.

rcMplsIngressLspPkts.name: rcMplsIngressLspPkts
rcMplsIngressLspPkts.description: Count of incoming packets for the corresponding lsp and port.

rcMplsEgressLspStatTable.name: rcMplsEgressLspStatTable
rcMplsEgressLspStatTable.description: This is the table of mpls OutGoing Label Stats.

rcMplsEgressLspStatEntry.name: rcMplsEgressLspStatEntry
rcMplsEgressLspStatEntry.description: An mpls OutGoing Label Stat entry .

rcMplsEgressLspPort.name: rcMplsEgressLspPort
rcMplsEgressLspPort.description: The OutGoing port for the lsp.

rcMplsEgressLspPkts.name: rcMplsEgressLspPkts
rcMplsEgressLspPkts.description: Count of outgoing packets for the corresponding lsp and port.

rcMplsRsvpSummaryVersion.name: rcMplsRsvpSummaryVersion
rcMplsRsvpSummaryVersion.description: This is the RSVP version number.

rcMplsRsvpSummaryState.name: rcMplsRsvpSummaryState
rcMplsRsvpSummaryState.description: This is the RSVP protocol state.

rcMplsRsvpSummaryLSPRetryTimer.name: rcMplsRsvpSummaryLSPRetryTimer
rcMplsRsvpSummaryLSPRetryTimer.description: This is the retry timer (secs) for the LSPs starting from this node, in case of failure. A value of zero means no retry on LSPs.

rcMplsRsvpSummaryLSPRetryLimit.name: rcMplsRsvpSummaryLSPRetryLimit
rcMplsRsvpSummaryLSPRetryLimit.description: This is the retry limit for the LSPs starting from this node. It indicates how many times an LSP is retried before giving up. A value of zero means try infinitely.

rcMplsRsvpSummaryLSPDecayRate.name: rcMplsRsvpSummaryLSPDecayRate
rcMplsRsvpSummaryLSPDecayRate.description: This is the decay rate (percent) for LSPs starting on this node.

rcMplsRsvpSummaryPHP.name: rcMplsRsvpSummaryPHP
rcMplsRsvpSummaryPHP.description: This is the configured RSVP PHP support on this node. Possible values are implicit-null, explicit-null, or disabled.

rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtTable.name: rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtTable
rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtTable.description: This is the table of mpls rsvp tunnels. This table supplements the mplsTunnelTable from rfc3812.

rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtEntry.name: rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtEntry
rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtEntry.description: An entry in the mpls tunnel table.

rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtIndex.name: rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtIndex
rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtIndex.description: The Tunnel Index. The value of this object should mimic the value of mplsTunnelIndex of the MplsTunnelEntry of the mpls tunnel for which this extended tunnel table entry row applies.

rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtInstance.name: rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtInstance
rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtInstance.description: The Tunnel Instance. The value of this object should mimic the value of mplsTunnelInstance of the MplsTunnelEntry of the mpls tunnel for which this extended tunnel table entry row applies.

rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtIngressLSRId.name: rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtIngressLSRId
rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtIngressLSRId.description: The Rsvp Tunnel Ingress LSR Id. The value of this object should mimic the value of the mplsTunnelIngressLSRId of the MplsTunnelEntry of the mpls tunnel for which this extended tunnel table entry row applies.

rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtEgressLSRId.name: rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtEgressLSRId
rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtEgressLSRId.description: The Rsvp Tunnel Egress LSR Id. The value of this object should mimic the value of the mplsTunnelEgressLSRId of the MplsTunnelEntry of the mpls tunnel for which this extended tunnel table entry row applies.

rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtName.name: rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtName
rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtName.description: The Name of the tunnel associated with this LSP.

rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtSwitchover.name: rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtSwitchover
rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtSwitchover.description: Switch this LSP from active status to inactive status or vice versa.

rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtActiveStatus.name: rcMplsRsvpTunnelExtActiveStatus
