rcMplsLdpStatsPeerAddress.description: This is the LDP Peer Address key for search. This value can be a valid peer address or 0.0.0.0. If 0.0.0.0 then global LDP statistics are retrieved.

rcMplsLdpStatsNotifyRecv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsNotifyRecv
rcMplsLdpStatsNotifyRecv.description: This is the count of notifications received.

rcMplsLdpStatsNotifySent.name: rcMplsLdpStatsNotifySent
rcMplsLdpStatsNotifySent.description: This is the count of notifications sent.

rcMplsLdpStatsHelloRecv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsHelloRecv
rcMplsLdpStatsHelloRecv.description: This is the count of hellos received.

rcMplsLdpStatsHelloSent.name: rcMplsLdpStatsHelloSent
rcMplsLdpStatsHelloSent.description: This is the count of hellos sent.

rcMplsLdpStatsInitRecv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsInitRecv
rcMplsLdpStatsInitRecv.description: This is the count of initializations received.

rcMplsLdpStatsInitSent.name: rcMplsLdpStatsInitSent
rcMplsLdpStatsInitSent.description: This is the count of initializations sent.

rcMplsLdpStatsKeepRecv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsKeepRecv
rcMplsLdpStatsKeepRecv.description: This is the count of keep alives received.

rcMplsLdpStatsKeepSent.name: rcMplsLdpStatsKeepSent
rcMplsLdpStatsKeepSent.description: This is the count of keep alives sent.

rcMplsLdpStatsAddrRecv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsAddrRecv
rcMplsLdpStatsAddrRecv.description: This is the count of addrs received.

rcMplsLdpStatsAddrSent.name: rcMplsLdpStatsAddrSent
rcMplsLdpStatsAddrSent.description: This is the count of addrs sent.

rcMplsLdpStatsAddrWdrRecv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsAddrWdrRecv
rcMplsLdpStatsAddrWdrRecv.description: This is the count of addr withdraws received.

rcMplsLdpStatsAddrWdrSent.name: rcMplsLdpStatsAddrWdrSent
rcMplsLdpStatsAddrWdrSent.description: This is the count of addr withdraws sent.

rcMplsLdpStatsLabelMapRecv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsLabelMapRecv
rcMplsLdpStatsLabelMapRecv.description: This is the count of label maps received.

rcMplsLdpStatsLabelMapSent.name: rcMplsLdpStatsLabelMapSent
rcMplsLdpStatsLabelMapSent.description: This is the count of label maps sent.

rcMplsLdpStatsLabelReqRecv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsLabelReqRecv
rcMplsLdpStatsLabelReqRecv.description: This is the count of label reqs received.

rcMplsLdpStatsLabelReqSent.name: rcMplsLdpStatsLabelReqSent
rcMplsLdpStatsLabelReqSent.description: This is the count of label reqs sent.

rcMplsLdpStatsLabelWdrRecv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsLabelWdrRecv
rcMplsLdpStatsLabelWdrRecv.description: This is the count of label withdraws received.

rcMplsLdpStatsLabelWdrSent.name: rcMplsLdpStatsLabelWdrSent
rcMplsLdpStatsLabelWdrSent.description: This is the count of label withdraws sent.

rcMplsLdpStatsLabelRelRecv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsLabelRelRecv
rcMplsLdpStatsLabelRelRecv.description: This is the count of label withdraws received.

rcMplsLdpStatsLabelRelSent.name: rcMplsLdpStatsLabelRelSent
rcMplsLdpStatsLabelRelSent.description: This is the count of label withdraws sent.

rcMplsLdpStatsLabelAbrRecv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsLabelAbrRecv
rcMplsLdpStatsLabelAbrRecv.description: This is the count of label aborts received.

rcMplsLdpStatsLabelAbrSent.name: rcMplsLdpStatsLabelAbrSent
rcMplsLdpStatsLabelAbrSent.description: This is the count of label aborts sent.

rcMplsLdpStatsSessionUp.name: rcMplsLdpStatsSessionUp
rcMplsLdpStatsSessionUp.description: This is the count of session up.

rcMplsLdpStatsSessionDown.name: rcMplsLdpStatsSessionDown
rcMplsLdpStatsSessionDown.description: This is the count of session down.

rcMplsLdpStatsBadLdpIdentifierErrors.name: rcMplsLdpStatsBadLdpIdentifierErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsBadLdpIdentifierErrors.description: This is the count of bad LDP ID errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsBadPduLengthErrors.name: rcMplsLdpStatsBadPduLengthErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsBadPduLengthErrors.description: This is the count of Bad PDU length errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsBadMessageLengthErrors.name: rcMplsLdpStatsBadMessageLengthErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsBadMessageLengthErrors.description: This is the count of bad message length errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsUnknownMessageErrors.name: rcMplsLdpStatsUnknownMessageErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsUnknownMessageErrors.description: This is the count of unknown message errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsUnknownTlvErrors.name: rcMplsLdpStatsUnknownTlvErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsUnknownTlvErrors.description: This is the count of unknown TLV errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsBadTlvLengthErrors.name: rcMplsLdpStatsBadTlvLengthErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsBadTlvLengthErrors.description: This is the count of bad TLV Length errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsMalformedTlvValueErrors.name: rcMplsLdpStatsMalformedTlvValueErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsMalformedTlvValueErrors.description: This is the count of Malinformed TLV value errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsHoldTimerExpErrors.name: rcMplsLdpStatsHoldTimerExpErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsHoldTimerExpErrors.description: This is the count of hold time expired errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedNoHelloErro.name: rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedNoHelloErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedNoHelloErro.description: This is the count of session reject - no hello errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedBadParmAdvE.name: rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedBadParmAdvErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedBadParmAdvE.description: This is the count of session reject - bad parameter advertisement errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedMaxPduError.name: rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedMaxPduErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedMaxPduError.description: This is the count of session reject - Max PDU Errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedBadLabelRan.name: rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedBadLabelRangeErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedBadLabelRan.description: This is the count of session reject - Bad Label Range errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedSetupAbortE.name: rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedSetupAbortErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedSetupAbortE.description: This is the count of session reject - Setup Abort errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedBadKeepaliv.name: rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedBadKeepaliveErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsSessionRejectedBadKeepaliv.description: This is the count of session reject - Bad Keepalive Errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsSessionOtherErrors.name: rcMplsLdpStatsSessionOtherErrors
rcMplsLdpStatsSessionOtherErrors.description: This is the count of other errors.

rcMplsLdpStatsClear.name: rcMplsLdpStatsClear
rcMplsLdpStatsClear.description: Clear LDP Statistics for the Peer.

rcMplsLdpStatusNotificationEnable.name: rcMplsLdpStatusNotificationEnable
rcMplsLdpStatusNotificationEnable.description: If this object is true, then it enables the generation of LDP Session Up or Down Traps, otherwise these traps are not emitted.

rcMplsLdpSessionThresholdNotificationEna.name: rcMplsLdpSessionThresholdNotificationEnable
rcMplsLdpSessionThresholdNotificationEna.description: If this object is true, then it enables the generation of LDP Session Threshold Exceeded Traps, otherwise these traps are not emitted.

rcMplsLdpPathVectorLimitNotificationEnab.name: rcMplsLdpPathVectorLimitNotificationEnable
rcMplsLdpPathVectorLimitNotificationEnab.description: If this object is true, then it enables the generation of LDP Path Vector Limit Exceeded Traps, otherwise these traps are not emitted.

rcMsdpRouteMapName.name: rcMsdpRouteMapName
rcMsdpRouteMapName.description: Route map name. Transmit only the SA messages that meet the match criteria in the route map name with a permit keyword. It is used as the policy of the redistribute filter. It can not be set when redistribute filter is disabled.

rcMsdpRedistributeFilterEnabled.name: rcMsdpRedistributeFilterEnabled
rcMsdpRedistributeFilterEnabled.description: To enable or disable the redistribute filter. This filter is used to filter the (S,G,RP) entries provided by PIM to MSDP.

rcMsdpRedistributeFilterApply.name: rcMsdpRedistributeFilterApply
rcMsdpRedistributeFilterApply.description: Each time when making changes to the redistribute filter, it will not take effect until it is applied.

rcMsdpImplicitDefaultPeerEnabled.name: rcMsdpImplicitDefaultPeerEnabled
rcMsdpImplicitDefaultPeerEnabled.description: To enable or disable the implicit default peer of MSDP. If enabled,it will accept SA messages even if the Peer RPF(Reverse Path Forwarding) rules fails, condition is that there should be only one peer configured.

rcMsdpPeerTable.name: rcMsdpPeerTable
rcMsdpPeerTable.description: A table that augments the management information in the standard IETF msdpPeerTable.

rcMsdpPeerEntry.name: rcMsdpPeerEntry
rcMsdpPeerEntry.description: A set of additional management information augmenting that of the standard IETF msdpPeerEntry.

rcMsdpPeerAsNumber.name: rcMsdpPeerAsNumber
rcMsdpPeerAsNumber.description: The AS number of the remote Peer. Value -1 indicates that AS number is not configured.

rcMsdpPeerTooShortMessages.name: rcMsdpPeerTooShortMessages
rcMsdpPeerTooShortMessages.description: The number of Short messages received from this peer.

rcMsdpPeerInBadMessages.name: rcMsdpPeerInBadMessages
rcMsdpPeerInBadMessages.description: The number of Bad MSDP messages received from this peer.

rcMsdpPeerInKeepAliveMessages.name: rcMsdpPeerInKeepAliveMessages
rcMsdpPeerInKeepAliveMessages.description: The number of keep alive messages received from this peer.

rcMsdpPeerOutKeepAliveMessages.name: rcMsdpPeerOutKeepAliveMessages
rcMsdpPeerOutKeepAliveMessages.description: The number of keep alive messages transmitted to this peer.

rcMsdpPeerInSAFilterEnabled.name: rcMsdpPeerInSAFilterEnabled
rcMsdpPeerInSAFilterEnabled.description: To enable or disable the in SA filter of a peer.

rcMsdpPeerInSAFilterRouteMapName.name: rcMsdpPeerInSAFilterRouteMapName
rcMsdpPeerInSAFilterRouteMapName.description: The route Map name of IN SA Filter. If route map name is configured, it Accepts only the SA messages that meet the match criteria in the route map map-name with a permit keyword. If access route map name is not configured, all inbound SA messages from this peer will be blocked.

rcMsdpPeerOutSAFilterEnabled.name: rcMsdpPeerOutSAFilterEnabled
rcMsdpPeerOutSAFilterEnabled.description: To enable or disable the out SA filter of a peer.

rcMsdpPeerOutSAFilterRouteMapName.name: rcMsdpPeerOutSAFilterRouteMapName
rcMsdpPeerOutSAFilterRouteMapName.description: The route Map name of OUT SA Filter. If route map name is configured, it sends only the SA messages that meet the match criteria in the route map map-name with a permit keyword. If access route map name is not configured, all outbound SA messages sent to this peer will be blocked

rcMsdpPeerDescription.name: rcMsdpPeerDescription
rcMsdpPeerDescription.description: Peer specific description. It is used to make the peer easier to be identified.

rcMsdpPeerSALimit.name: rcMsdpPeerSALimit
rcMsdpPeerSALimit.description: The SA Cache limit for this peer.

rcMsdpPeerMd5AuthEnabled.name: rcMsdpPeerMd5AuthEnabled
rcMsdpPeerMd5AuthEnabled.description: The MD5 Authentication status of this peer.

rcMsdpPeerMd5AuthPassword.name: rcMsdpPeerMd5AuthPassword
rcMsdpPeerMd5AuthPassword.description: The MD5 Authentication password of this peer.

rcMsdpPeerSAsLearnedFromThisPeer.name: rcMsdpPeerSAsLearnedFromThisPeer
rcMsdpPeerSAsLearnedFromThisPeer.description: The total number of SAs learned from this peer.

rcMsdpPeerSAsAdvertisedToThisPeer.name: rcMsdpPeerSAsAdvertisedToThisPeer
rcMsdpPeerSAsAdvertisedToThisPeer.description: The total number of SAs advertised to this peer.

rcMsdpPeerUpOrDownTime.name: rcMsdpPeerUpOrDownTime
rcMsdpPeerUpOrDownTime.description: MSDP Peer Up or Down duration.

rcMsdpPeerConnAndStatsClearedTime.name: rcMsdpPeerConnAndStatsClearedTime
rcMsdpPeerConnAndStatsClearedTime.description: The duration of connection and statistics cleared ago.

rcMsdpPeerRouteMapName.name: rcMsdpPeerRouteMapName
rcMsdpPeerRouteMapName.description: Route map name for default peer.

rcMsdpPeerAdminEnabled.name: rcMsdpPeerAdminEnabled
rcMsdpPeerAdminEnabled.description: The admin status of this peer.

rcMsdpPeerOperEnabled.name: rcMsdpPeerOperEnabled
rcMsdpPeerOperEnabled.description: The operational status of this peer.

rcMsdpPeerDefaultPeerState.name: rcMsdpPeerDefaultPeerState
rcMsdpPeerDefaultPeerState.description: The default peer has two state: Configured and Operational. MSDP node only accept SA messages from the Operational default peer. These is only one default peer can become Operational, all the Configured default peers are for redundancy.

rcMsdpPeerDefaultPeer.name: rcMsdpPeerDefaultPeer
rcMsdpPeerDefaultPeer.description: It is used to indicate whether a peer is a default peer or not.

rcMsdpSACacheTable.name: rcMsdpSACacheTable
rcMsdpSACacheTable.description: SA (Source Active) - Cache Table. This table contains foreign as well as local SA Cache entries. Foreign SA Cache entries from this table will have corresponding entries in the standard table msdpSACacheTable

rcMsdpSACacheGroupAddr.name: rcMsdpSACacheGroupAddr
rcMsdpSACacheGroupAddr.description: The group address of the SA Cache entry.

rcMsdpSACacheSourceAddr.name: rcMsdpSACacheSourceAddr
rcMsdpSACacheSourceAddr.description: The source address of the SA Cache entry.

rcMsdpSACacheOriginRP.name: rcMsdpSACacheOriginRP
rcMsdpSACacheOriginRP.description: The RP of the SA Cache entry. This field is in the INDEX in order to catch multiple RP's advertising the same source and group.

rcMsdpSACacheTypeInformation.name: rcMsdpSACacheTypeInformation
rcMsdpSACacheTypeInformation.description: This object describes the SA cache type. It can be either local cache or foreign cache.

rcMsdpSACacheOriginatorAsNumber.name: rcMsdpSACacheOriginatorAsNumber
rcMsdpSACacheOriginatorAsNumber.description: The AS number of the originator.

rcMsdpSACacheRouteType.name: rcMsdpSACacheRouteType
rcMsdpSACacheRouteType.description: The owner of the route that is used for rpf checking.

rcnMsdpMaxSACacheWarnSet.name: rcnMsdpMaxSACacheWarnSet
rcnMsdpMaxSACacheWarnSet.description: This event is generated when the SA entries in the cache database exceeds 85 % of maximum value (6K) in local cache or in foreign cache.

rcnMsdpMaxSACacheWarnClear.name: rcnMsdpMaxSACacheWarnClear
rcnMsdpMaxSACacheWarnClear.description: This event is generated when the Sa entries in the cache database drops to 80 % of the maximum value (6K).

rcnMsdpMaxSACacheErrorSet.name: rcnMsdpMaxSACacheErrorSet
rcnMsdpMaxSACacheErrorSet.description: This event is generated when the SA entries in the cache database hits 100 % of the maximum value (6K).

rcnMsdpMaxSACacheErrorClear.name: rcnMsdpMaxSACacheErrorClear
rcnMsdpMaxSACacheErrorClear.description: This event is generated when the SA entries in the cache database drops to 95% of the maximum value.

rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheWarnSet.name: rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheWarnSet
rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheWarnSet.description: This event is generated when the SA entries for this peer exceeds 85 % of maximum value configured for this peer.

rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheWarnClear.name: rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheWarnClear
rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheWarnClear.description: This event is generated when the SA entries for this peer drops to 80 % of the maximum value configured for this peer.

rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheErrorSet.name: rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheErrorSet
rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheErrorSet.description: This event is generated when the SA entries for this peer hits 100 % of the peer SA limit.

rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheErrorClear.name: rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheErrorClear
rcnMsdpMaxPeerSACacheErrorClear.description: This event is generated when the SA entries for this peer drops to 95% of the peer SA limit.

rcnMsdpEstablished.name: rcnMsdpEstablished
rcnMsdpEstablished.description: The MSDP Established event is generated when the MSDP FSM enters the ESTABLISHED state.

rcnMsdpBackwardTransition.name: rcnMsdpBackwardTransition
rcnMsdpBackwardTransition.description: The MSDPBackwardTransition Event is generated when the MSDP FSM moves from a higher-numbered state to a lower-numbered state.

rcMsdpSACacheType.name: rcMsdpSACacheType
rcMsdpSACacheType.description: This object describes the SA cache type.

rcVrrpTmpNotificationCntl.name: rcVrrpTmpNotificationCntl
rcVrrpTmpNotificationCntl.description: Indicates whether the VRRP-enabled router will generate SNMP notifications for events defined in this MIB. 'Enabled' results in SNMP notifications; 'disabled', no notifications are sent.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsTable.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsTable
rcVrrpTmpOperationsTable.description: Unified Operations table for a VRRP router which consists of a sequence (i.e., one or more conceptual rows) of 'rcVrrpTmpOperationsEntry' items which describe the operational characteristics of a virtual router.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsEntry.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsEntry
rcVrrpTmpOperationsEntry.description: An entry in the rcVrrpTmpOperationsTable containing the operational characteristics of a virtual router. On a VRRP router, a given virtual router is identified by a combination of the IP version, VRID and ifIndex. ifIndex represents a physical interface of the router. Note that rows in this table can be distinguished on a multi-stacked device running VRRP over IPv4 and IPv6 on the same physical interface. Rows in the table cannot be modified unless the value of 'rcVrrpTmpOperationsState' has transitioned to 'initialize'

rcVrrpTmpOperationsInetAddrType.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsInetAddrType
rcVrrpTmpOperationsInetAddrType.description: The IP address type of RcVrrpTmpOperationsEntry. This value applies to both rcVrrpTmpOperationsMasterIpAddr and rcVrrpTmpOperationsPrimaryIpAddr.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsVrId.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsVrId
rcVrrpTmpOperationsVrId.description: This object contains the Virtual Router Identifier (VRID).

rcVrrpTmpOperationsVirtualMacAddr.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsVirtualMacAddr
rcVrrpTmpOperationsVirtualMacAddr.description: The virtual MAC address of the virtual router. Although this object can be derived from the 'rcVrrpTmpOperationsVrId' object, it is defined so that it is easily obtainable by a management application and can be included in VRRP-related SNMP notifications.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsState.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsState
rcVrrpTmpOperationsState.description: The current state of the virtual router. This object has three defined values: - `initialize', which indicates that the virtual router is waiting for a startup event. - `backup', which indicates the virtual router is monitoring the availability of the master router. - `master', which indicates that the virtual router is forwarding packets for IP addresses that are associated with this router.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsPriority.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsPriority
rcVrrpTmpOperationsPriority.description: This object specifies the priority to be used for the virtual router master election process. Higher values imply higher priority. A priority of '0', although not settable, is sent by the master router to indicate that this router has ceased to participate in VRRP and a backup virtual router should transition to become a new master. A priority of 255 is used for the router that owns the associated IP address(es) for VRRP over IPv4 and hence not settable. A 'badValue(3)' should be returned when a user tries to set 0 or 255 for this object.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsAddrCount.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsAddrCount
rcVrrpTmpOperationsAddrCount.description: The number of IP addresses that are associated with this virtual router. This number is equal to the number of rows in the rcVrrpTmpAssociatedAddrTable that correspond to a given IP version/VRID/ifIndex.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsMasterIpAddr.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsMasterIpAddr
rcVrrpTmpOperationsMasterIpAddr.description: The master router's real IP address. Master router would set this address to rcVrrpTmpOperationsPrimaryIpAddr while transitioning to master state. For backup routers, this is the IP address listed as the source in VRRP advertisement last received by this virtual router.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsPrimaryIpAddr.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsPrimaryIpAddr
rcVrrpTmpOperationsPrimaryIpAddr.description: In the case where there are more than one IP Address (associated IP addresses) for a given `ifIndex', this object is used to specify the IP address that will become the rcVrrpTmpOperationsMasterIpAddr', should the virtual router transition from backup state to master.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsAdvInterval.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsAdvInterval
rcVrrpTmpOperationsAdvInterval.description: The time interval, in centiseconds, between sending advertisement messages. Only the master router sends VRRP advertisements.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsPreemptMode.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsPreemptMode
rcVrrpTmpOperationsPreemptMode.description: Controls whether a higher priority virtual router will preempt a lower priority master.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsAcceptMode.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsAcceptMode
rcVrrpTmpOperationsAcceptMode.description: Controls whether a virtual router in Master state will accept packets addressed to the address owner's IPv6 address as its own if it is not the IPv6 address owner. Default is False. This object is not relevant for rows representing VRRP over IPv4 and should be set to false.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsUpTime.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsUpTime
rcVrrpTmpOperationsUpTime.description: This is the value of the `sysUpTime' object when this virtual router (i.e., the `rcVrrpTmpOperationsState') transitioned out of `initialized'.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsStorageType.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsStorageType
rcVrrpTmpOperationsStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. Write access is not required. It is optional to support nonVolatile StorageType enumeration.

rcVrrpTmpOperationsRowStatus.name: rcVrrpTmpOperationsRowStatus
rcVrrpTmpOperationsRowStatus.description: The RowStatus variable should be used in accordance to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. When `rcVrrpTmpOperationsRowStatus' is set to active(1), no other objects in the conceptual row can be modified. To create a row in this table, a manager sets this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the `rcVrrpTmpOperationsRowStatus' column will be read as notReady(3). In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active(1) until (minimally) the corresponding instance of rcVrrpTmpOperationsInetAddrType, rcVrrpTmpOperationsVrId and rcVrrpTmpOperationsPrimaryIpAddr has been set and there is at least one active row in the `rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrTable' defining an associated IP address. notInService(2) should be used to administratively bring the row down. A typical order of operation to add a row is: 1. Create a row in rcVrrpTmpOperationsTable with createAndWait(5). 2. Create one or more corresponding rows in rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrTable. 3. Populate the rcVrrpTmpOperationsEntry. 4. set rcVrrpTmpOperationsRowStatus to active(1). A typical order of operation to delete an entry is: 1. Set rcVrrpTmpOperationsRowStatus to notInService(2). 2. Set the corresponding rows in rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrTable to destroy(6) to delete the entry. 3. set rcVrrpTmpOperationsRowStatus to destroy(6) to delete the entry.

rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrTable.name: rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrTable
rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrTable.description: The table of addresses associated with this virtual router.

rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrEntry.name: rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrEntry
rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrEntry.description: An entry in the table contains an IP address that is associated with a virtual router. The number of rows for a given IP version, VrID and ifIndex will equal the number of IP addresses associated (e.g., backed up) by the virtual router (equivalent to 'rcVrrpTmpOperationsIpAddrCount'). Rows in the table cannot be modified unless the value of `rcVrrpTmpOperationsState' has transitioned to `initialize'.

rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddr.name: rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddr
rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddr.description: The assigned IP addresses that a virtual router is responsible for backing up. The size of this object is either 4 or 16 depending on rcVrrpTmpOperationsInetAddrType.

rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrPrefixLength.name: rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrPrefixLength
rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrPrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix (in bits).

rcVrrpTmpAssociatedStorageType.name: rcVrrpTmpAssociatedStorageType
rcVrrpTmpAssociatedStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. Write access is not required. It is optional to support nonVolatile StorageType enumeration.

rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrRowStatus.name: rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrRowStatus
rcVrrpTmpAssociatedIpAddrRowStatus.description: The RowStatus variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. To create a row in this table, a manager sets this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Setting this object to active(1) results in the addition of an associated address for a virtual router. Setting this object to notInService(2) results in administratively bringing down the row. Destroying the entry or setting it to destroy(6) removes the associated address from the virtual router. The use of other values is implementation-dependent. Only rcVrrpTmpAssociatedStorageType can be modified when the row is in active(1) state for Implementations supporting write access to rcVrrpTmpAssociatedStorageType Implementations should not allow deletion of the last row corresponding to an active row in rcVrrpTmpOperationsTable. Refer to description of rcVrrpTmpOperationsRowStatus for a typical row creation and deletion scenarios.

rcVrrpTmpRouterChecksumErrors.name: rcVrrpTmpRouterChecksumErrors
rcVrrpTmpRouterChecksumErrors.description: The total number of VRRP packets received with an invalid VRRP checksum value.

rcVrrpTmpRouterVersionErrors.name: rcVrrpTmpRouterVersionErrors
rcVrrpTmpRouterVersionErrors.description: The total number of VRRP packets received with an unknown or unsupported version number.

rcVrrpTmpRouterVrIdErrors.name: rcVrrpTmpRouterVrIdErrors
rcVrrpTmpRouterVrIdErrors.description: The total number of VRRP packets received with an invalid VRID for this virtual router.

rcVrrpTmpRouterStatisticsEntry.name: rcVrrpTmpRouterStatisticsEntry
rcVrrpTmpRouterStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing statistics information about a given virtual router.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsMasterTransitions.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsMasterTransitions
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsMasterTransitions.description: The total number of times that this virtual router's state has transitioned to MASTER. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdAdvertisements.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdAdvertisements
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdAdvertisements.description: The total number of VRRP advertisements received by this virtual router. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsAdvIntervalErrors.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsAdvIntervalErrors
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsAdvIntervalErrors.description: The total number of VRRP advertisement packets received for which the advertisement interval is different than the one configured for the local virtual router. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsIpTtlErrors.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsIpTtlErrors
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsIpTtlErrors.description: The total number of VRRP packets received by the Virtual router with IPv4 TTL (for VRRP over IPv4) or IPv6 Hop Limit (for VRRP over IPv6) not equal to 255. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdPriZeroPackets.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdPriZeroPackets
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdPriZeroPackets.description: The total number of VRRP packets received by the virtual router with a priority of '0'. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsSentPriZeroPackets.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsSentPriZeroPackets
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsSentPriZeroPackets.description: The total number of VRRP packets sent by the virtual router with a priority of '0'. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdInvalidTypePkts.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdInvalidTypePkts
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdInvalidTypePkts.description: The number of VRRP packets received by the virtual router with an invalid value in the 'type' field. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsAddressListErrors.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsAddressListErrors
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsAddressListErrors.description: The total number of packets received for which the address list does not match the locally configured list for the virtual router. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsPacketLengthErrors.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsPacketLengthErrors
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsPacketLengthErrors.description: The total number of packets received with a packet length less than the length of the VRRP header. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdInvalidAuthentica.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdInvalidAuthentications
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRcvdInvalidAuthentica.description: The total number of packets received with an unknown authentication type.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which any one or more of this entry's counters suffered a discontinuity. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last re-initialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRefreshRate.name: rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRefreshRate
rcVrrpTmpStatisticsRefreshRate.description: The minimum reasonable polling interval for this entry. This object provides an indication of the minimum Amount of time required to update the counters in this entry.

rcVrrpTmpNewMasterReason.name: rcVrrpTmpNewMasterReason
rcVrrpTmpNewMasterReason.description: This indicates the reason for rcVrrpTmpNewMaster trap. Used by rcVrrpTmpTrapNewMaster trap. The object can be polled if the rcVrrpTmpNewMaster trap is lost to identify the reason for transmission. Backup router should return notmaster(0) when pooled.

rcVrrpTmpTrapProtoErrReason.name: rcVrrpTmpTrapProtoErrReason
rcVrrpTmpTrapProtoErrReason.description: This indicates the reason for protocol error trap. Used by rcVrrpTmpTrapProtoError trap.

rcVrrpTmpTrapNewMaster.name: rcVrrpTmpTrapNewMaster
rcVrrpTmpTrapNewMaster.description: The newMaster trap indicates that the sending agent has transitioned to 'Master' state.

rcVrrpTmpTrapProtoError.name: rcVrrpTmpTrapProtoError
rcVrrpTmpTrapProtoError.description: The error trap indicates that the sending agent has encountered the protocol error indicated by rcVrrpTmpTrapProtoErrorReason.

rcVrrpExtPingVirtualAddrEnable.name: rcVrrpExtPingVirtualAddrEnable
rcVrrpExtPingVirtualAddrEnable.description: Used to configure whether this device should respond to pings directed to a virtual router's IPv6 address.

rcVrrpExtVersionNumber.name: rcVrrpExtVersionNumber
rcVrrpExtVersionNumber.description: The version number of Vrrp for IPv6 is 3.

rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransitionType.name: rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransitionType
rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransitionType.description: Potential types of state transitions.Used by rcVrrpv3TrapStateTransition trap.

rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransitionCause.name: rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransitionCause
rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransitionCause.description: Potential types of causes that will generate a rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransition trap.

rcVrrpExtOperationsVrId.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsVrId
rcVrrpExtOperationsVrId.description: This object contains the Virtual Router Identifier (VRID).This is used in rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransition.

rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransition.name: rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransition
rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransition.description: A rcVrrpExtTrapStateTransition trap signifies a state transition has occurred on a particular vrrp interface. Implementation of this trap is optional.

rcVrrpExtOperationsTable.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsTable
rcVrrpExtOperationsTable.description: Unified Operations table for a VRRP router which consists of a sequence (i.e., one or more conceptual rows) of 'rcVrrpExtOperationsEntry'and 'rcVrrpTmpOperationsEntry' items which describe the operational characteristics of a virtual router. This table is an extention of 'rcVrrpTmpOperationsTable'.It contains the mib objects that are Nortel specific.

rcVrrpExtOperationsEntry.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsEntry
rcVrrpExtOperationsEntry.description: An entry in the rcVrrpExtOperationsTable containing the operational characteristics of a virtual router. On a VRRP router, a given virtual router is identified by a combination of the IP version, VRID and ifIndex. ifIndex represents a physical interface of the router. Note that rows in this table can be distinguished on a multi-stacked device running VRRP over IPv4 and IPv6 on the same physical interface. Rows in the table cannot be modified unless the value of 'rcVrrpTmpOperationsState' has transitioned to 'initialize'.

rcVrrpExtOperationsAction.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsAction
rcVrrpExtOperationsAction.description: Used to trigger an action on this vrrp interface.

rcVrrpExtOperationsBackUpMaster.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsBackUpMaster
rcVrrpExtOperationsBackUpMaster.description: Enable the backup VRRP switch traffic forwarding. This will reduce the traffic in IST link in the time of SMLT.

rcVrrpExtOperationsBackUpMasterState.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsBackUpMasterState
rcVrrpExtOperationsBackUpMasterState.description: Indicate whether backup VRRP switch traffic forwarding is enabled or not.

rcVrrpExtOperationsCriticalIpAddr.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsCriticalIpAddr
rcVrrpExtOperationsCriticalIpAddr.description: IP address of the interface that will cause a shutdown event.Only IPv6 address is supported as of now.

rcVrrpExtOperationsCriticalIpAddrEnabled.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsCriticalIpAddrEnabled
rcVrrpExtOperationsCriticalIpAddrEnabled.description: Indicate if an user-defined critical IP address should be enabled. 'NO' = use the default IP address (::). No effect if an user-defined IP address does not exist.

rcVrrpExtOperationsControl.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsControl
rcVrrpExtOperationsControl.description: This object will enable/disable the virtual router function. Setting the value to 'enabled', will transition the state of the router from 'initialize to 'backup'; Setting the value to 'disabled', will tranisition the router from 'master' or 'backup' to 'initialize'.

rcVrrpExtOperationsHoldDownTimer.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsHoldDownTimer
rcVrrpExtOperationsHoldDownTimer.description: Used to configure the amount of time (in seconds) to wait before preempting the current vrrp master.

rcVrrpExtOperationsHoldDownState.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsHoldDownState
rcVrrpExtOperationsHoldDownState.description: Used to indicate the hold-down state of this vrrp interface. If the hold-down timer is operational this variable will be set to 'active'. 'dormant' otherwise.

rcVrrpExtOperationsHoldDownTimeRemaining.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsHoldDownTimeRemaining
rcVrrpExtOperationsHoldDownTimeRemaining.description: Used to indicate the amount of time (in seconds) left before the rcVrrpExtOperationsHoldDownTimer will expire.

rcVrrpExtOperationsFasterAdvInterval.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsFasterAdvInterval
rcVrrpExtOperationsFasterAdvInterval.description: This is the faster advertisement interval, in milliseconds, between sending advertisement messages. When the faster advertisement interval enable is checked, the faster advertisement interval is being used instead of the regular advertisement interval.

rcVrrpExtOperationsFasterAdvIntervalEnab.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsFasterAdvIntervalEnabled
rcVrrpExtOperationsFasterAdvIntervalEnab.description: Used to indicate if the Faster Advertisement Interval should be used.'Disable' means use regular Advertisement interval.

rcVrrpExtOperationsLinkLocalAddr.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsLinkLocalAddr
rcVrrpExtOperationsLinkLocalAddr.description: The assigned Linklocal addresses to the virtual router interface. This mib object support only IPv6 address as of now.

rcVrrpExtOperationsGlobalIpAddr.name: rcVrrpExtOperationsGlobalIpAddr
rcVrrpExtOperationsGlobalIpAddr.description: The assigned Global addresses to the virtual router interface. This mib object support only IPv6 address as of now.

rcIsisGlobalAreaAuthType.name: rcIsisGlobalAreaAuthType
rcIsisGlobalAreaAuthType.description: The authentication type for the area

rcIsisGlobalAreaKeyId.name: rcIsisGlobalAreaKeyId
rcIsisGlobalAreaKeyId.description: Authentication key-id for the area. This is required if the auth-type is hmac-md5 else it is not required.

rcIsisGlobalAreaAuthKey.name: rcIsisGlobalAreaAuthKey
rcIsisGlobalAreaAuthKey.description: Authentication key, this key will be used to authenticate the LSP's received on the area

rcIsisGlobalDomainAuthType.name: rcIsisGlobalDomainAuthType
rcIsisGlobalDomainAuthType.description: The authentication type for the domain

rcIsisGlobalDomainKeyId.name: rcIsisGlobalDomainKeyId
rcIsisGlobalDomainKeyId.description: The authentication key-id for the domain. This is required if the auth-type is hmac-md5 else it is not required.

rcIsisGlobalDomainAuthKey.name: rcIsisGlobalDomainAuthKey
rcIsisGlobalDomainAuthKey.description: Authentication key, this key will be used to authenticate the LSP's received on the domain

rcIsisGlobalCsnpInt.name: rcIsisGlobalCsnpInt
rcIsisGlobalCsnpInt.description: Interval of time, in seconds, between periodic transmission of a complete set of CSNPs on multiaccess networks if this router is the designated router at this level. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior. For ResettingTimer description see the ISIS MIB

rcIsisGlobalRxmtLspInt.name: rcIsisGlobalRxmtLspInt
rcIsisGlobalRxmtLspInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between re-transmission of a LSP at this level. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior. For ResettingTimer description see the ISIS MIB

rcIsisGlobalPSNPInterval.name: rcIsisGlobalPSNPInterval
rcIsisGlobalPSNPInterval.description: Minimum interval in seconds between sending Partial Sequence Number PDUs at this level. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior. For ResettingTimer description see the ISIS MIB

rcIsisGlobalHostName.name: rcIsisGlobalHostName
rcIsisGlobalHostName.description: The hostname listed in LSP, or the system name if host name is not configured.

rcIsisGlobalIpSourceAddress.name: rcIsisGlobalIpSourceAddress
rcIsisGlobalIpSourceAddress.description: ISIS PLSB IP address. Define an existing router interface for management (ping/traceroute)

rcIsisGlobalIpSourceAddressType.name: rcIsisGlobalIpSourceAddressType
rcIsisGlobalIpSourceAddressType.description: The type of address for existing router interface for management (ping/traceroute)

rcIsisCircuitTable.name: rcIsisCircuitTable
rcIsisCircuitTable.description: Table of IS-IS Circuit, this is extension to the isisCircTable defined in ISIS MIB

rcIsisCircuitEntry.name: rcIsisCircuitEntry
rcIsisCircuitEntry.description: An entry of rcIsisCircuit Table. A Entry in table exists for each ISIS circuit created

rcIsisCircuitIndex.name: rcIsisCircuitIndex
rcIsisCircuitIndex.description: The identifier of this circuit, unique within the Intermediate System. This object follows the index behavior. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and need not have any relation to any protocol value.

rcIsisCircuitType.name: rcIsisCircuitType
rcIsisCircuitType.description: ISIS circuit type this is an extention to ISIS circuit table, this was required a standard MIB circuit type does not support passive type

rcIsisCircuitAuthType.name: rcIsisCircuitAuthType
rcIsisCircuitAuthType.description: Authentication type for IIH to be sent/reveived on the circuit/interface

rcIsisCircuitKeyId.name: rcIsisCircuitKeyId
rcIsisCircuitKeyId.description: Authentication key id related to IIH key This can be set only if the auth-type is hmac-md5

rcIsisCircuitAuthKey.name: rcIsisCircuitAuthKey
rcIsisCircuitAuthKey.description: Authentication key to be used to authenticate IIH sent/reveived on the circuit/interface

rcIsisCircuitAddr.name: rcIsisCircuitAddr
rcIsisCircuitAddr.description: IP address associated with the interface

rcIsisCircuitMask.name: rcIsisCircuitMask
rcIsisCircuitMask.description: IP mask associated with the interface

rcIsisCircuitOperState.name: rcIsisCircuitOperState
rcIsisCircuitOperState.description: This variable tells the operating state of circ

rcIsisCircuitNumUpAdj.name: rcIsisCircuitNumUpAdj
rcIsisCircuitNumUpAdj.description: Number of adjancencies which are UP

rcIsisStatsClearErrorCounters.name: rcIsisStatsClearErrorCounters
rcIsisStatsClearErrorCounters.description: Clear ISIS global and interface error counters.

rcIsisStatsClearPacketCounters.name: rcIsisStatsClearPacketCounters
rcIsisStatsClearPacketCounters.description: Clear IS-IS control packets sent and received at each level on all the interface/circuits.

rcIsisPlsbEntry.name: rcIsisPlsbEntry
rcIsisPlsbEntry.description: An entry of rcIsisPlsb Table. A Entry in table exists for each plsb instance created

rcIsisPlsbNodeNickName.name: rcIsisPlsbNodeNickName
rcIsisPlsbNodeNickName.description: PLSB node's nickname is used to calculate ISID multicast mac address.

rcIsisPlsbVlans.name: rcIsisPlsbVlans
rcIsisPlsbVlans.description: PLSB ISIS vlans for a PLSB instance.

rcIsisPlsbLsdbTrap.name: rcIsisPlsbLsdbTrap
rcIsisPlsbLsdbTrap.description: isis PLSB lsdb update trap enable on this plsb instance

rcIsisPlsbPrimaryVlan.name: rcIsisPlsbPrimaryVlan
rcIsisPlsbPrimaryVlan.description: Primary Vlan Id for this plsb instance.

rcIsisPlsbSmltSplitBEB.name: rcIsisPlsbSmltSplitBEB
rcIsisPlsbSmltSplitBEB.description: ISIS PLSB SMLT split BEB for this plsb instance.

rcIsisPlsbSmltBmac.name: rcIsisPlsbSmltBmac
rcIsisPlsbSmltBmac.description: ISIS PLSB SMLT virtual MAC for this plsb instance.

rcIsisPlsbSmltPeerSysId.name: rcIsisPlsbSmltPeerSysId
rcIsisPlsbSmltPeerSysId.description: ISIS PLSB SMLT Peer's system-id for this plsb instance.

IsisDefaultL1Metric.name: IsisDefaultL1Metric
IsisDefaultL1Metric.description: Integer sub-range for default metric for single hop. ISO 10589 provides for 4 types of metric. Only the 'default' metric is used in practice.

IsisWideL1Metric.name: IsisWideL1Metric
IsisWideL1Metric.description: Wide Metric for IS Neighbors. ISO 10589 provides a 6 bit metric. Traffic Engineering extensions provide 24 bit metrics.

rcIsisCircuitPlsbTable.name: rcIsisCircuitPlsbTable
rcIsisCircuitPlsbTable.description: Table of IS-IS Circuit PLSB instance

rcIsisCircuitPlsbEntry.name: rcIsisCircuitPlsbEntry
rcIsisCircuitPlsbEntry.description: An entry of rcIsisCircuitPlsb Table. A Entry in table exists for each PLSB instance under a ISIS circuit created

rcIsisCircuitPlsbIndex.name: rcIsisCircuitPlsbIndex
rcIsisCircuitPlsbIndex.description: The identifier of this circuit, unique within the Intermediate System. This object follows the index behavior. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and need not have any relation to any protocol value.

rcIsisCircuitPlsbState.name: rcIsisCircuitPlsbState
rcIsisCircuitPlsbState.description: PLSB functionality enable on this Plsb instance at this port

rcIsisCircuitPlsbType.name: rcIsisCircuitPlsbType
rcIsisCircuitPlsbType.description: ISIS circuit type this is an extention to ISIS circuit table, this was required a standard MIB circuit type does not support passive type

rcIsisCircuitPlsbL1Metric.name: rcIsisCircuitPlsbL1Metric
rcIsisCircuitPlsbL1Metric.description: The metric value of this circuit for this level.

rcIsisCircuitPlsbWideL1Metric.name: rcIsisCircuitPlsbWideL1Metric
rcIsisCircuitPlsbWideL1Metric.description: The metric value of this circuit for this level.

rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibTable.name: rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibTable
rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibTable.description: Table of IS-IS PLSB Unicast FIB

rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibEntry.name: rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibEntry
rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibEntry.description: An entry of rcIsisPlsbUnicastFib Table. A Entry in table exists for each PLSB unicast forwarding entry generated by ISIS SPF computation

rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibDestinationMacAddr.name: rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibDestinationMacAddr
rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibDestinationMacAddr.description: Destination Mac Address of the unicast FIB entry

rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibVlan.name: rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibVlan
rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibVlan.description: Vlan of the unicast FIB entry

rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibSysId.name: rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibSysId
rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibSysId.description: System ID of the node where unicast FIB entry come from

rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibOutgoingPort.name: rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibOutgoingPort
rcIsisPlsbUnicastFibOutgoingPort.description: Outgoing port of the unicast Fib entry.

rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibTable.name: rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibTable
rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibTable.description: Table of IS-IS PLSB Multicast FIB

rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibEntry.name: rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibEntry
rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibEntry.description: An entry of rcIsisPlsbmulticastFib Table. A Entry in table exists for each PLSB Multicast forwarding entry generated by ISIS SPF computation

rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibMcastDestMacAddr.name: rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibMcastDestMacAddr
rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibMcastDestMacAddr.description: Multicast destination Mac Address of the multicast FIB entry

rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibVlan.name: rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibVlan
rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibVlan.description: Vlan of the multicast FIB entry

rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibSysId.name: rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibSysId
rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibSysId.description: System ID of the node where multicast FIB entry come from

rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibIsid.name: rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibIsid
rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibIsid.description: Isid id of the multicast FIB entry

rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibOutgoingPorts.name: rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibOutgoingPorts
rcIsisPlsbMulticastFibOutgoingPorts.description: Nni port of the multicast Fib entry.

rcIsisPlsbIsidEntry.name: rcIsisPlsbIsidEntry
rcIsisPlsbIsidEntry.description: An entry of rcIsisPlsbIsid Table. A Entry in table exists for each PLSB i-sid configed or discovered by IS-IS

rcIsisPlsbIsidSourceName.name: rcIsisPlsbIsidSourceName
rcIsisPlsbIsidSourceName.description: nick name of node where this i-sid got configed or discovered

rcIsisPlsbIsidSysId.name: rcIsisPlsbIsidSysId
rcIsisPlsbIsidSysId.description: System ID of the node where multicast FIB entry come from

rcIsisLocalLspId.name: rcIsisLocalLspId
rcIsisLocalLspId.description: The 8 byte Local LSP ID, consisting of the SystemID, Circuit ID, and Fragment Number.

rcIsisLocall1Metric.name: rcIsisLocall1Metric
rcIsisLocall1Metric.description: l1-metric for ISIS interface on local Node.

rcIsisNgbLspId.name: rcIsisNgbLspId
rcIsisNgbLspId.description: The 8 byte neighbor LSP ID, consisting of the SystemID, Circuit ID, and Fragment Number.

rcIsisNgbl1Metric.name: rcIsisNgbl1Metric
rcIsisNgbl1Metric.description: l1-metric for ISIS interface on neighbor Node.

rcIsisTrapIndicator.name: rcIsisTrapIndicator
rcIsisTrapIndicator.description: indicates that an alarm has been Raised, or an alarm has been cleared.

rcIsisLocalPrimaryTieBrkAlg.name: rcIsisLocalPrimaryTieBrkAlg
rcIsisLocalPrimaryTieBrkAlg.description: The tie breaking algorithm applied to local primary B-VID.

rcIsisLocalSecondaryTieBrkAlg.name: rcIsisLocalSecondaryTieBrkAlg
rcIsisLocalSecondaryTieBrkAlg.description: The tie breaking algorithm applied to local seconday B-VID.

rcIsisNgbPrimaryTieBrkAlg.name: rcIsisNgbPrimaryTieBrkAlg
rcIsisNgbPrimaryTieBrkAlg.description: The neighbor tie breaking algorithm applied to primary B-VID.

rcIsisNgbSecondaryTieBrkAlg.name: rcIsisNgbSecondaryTieBrkAlg
rcIsisNgbSecondaryTieBrkAlg.description: The neighbor tie breaking algorithm applied to secondary B-VID.

rcIsisLocalVirtualBmac.name: rcIsisLocalVirtualBmac
rcIsisLocalVirtualBmac.description: The SMLT Virtual BMAC configured in the local IST switch.

rcIsisPeerVirtualBmac.name: rcIsisPeerVirtualBmac
rcIsisPeerVirtualBmac.description: The SMLT Virtual BMAC configured in the IST Peer.

rcIsisSysId.name: rcIsisSysId
rcIsisSysId.description: The isis system id configured in the local switch or IST peer.

rcIsisSmltPeerSysId.name: rcIsisSmltPeerSysId
rcIsisSmltPeerSysId.description: The SMLT Peer system-id configured in the local switch or IST Peer.

rcIsisDuplicateNnameCounter.name: rcIsisDuplicateNnameCounter
rcIsisDuplicateNnameCounter.description: indicate how many nodes in the network share the nick-name.

rcIsisLocalBvidCounter.name: rcIsisLocalBvidCounter
rcIsisLocalBvidCounter.description: indicate how many b-vid configured on local nodes.

rcIsisNgbBvidCounter.name: rcIsisNgbBvidCounter
rcIsisNgbBvidCounter.description: indicate how many b-vid configured on a neighbor nodes.

rcIsisLocalSmltSplitBeb.name: rcIsisLocalSmltSplitBeb
rcIsisLocalSmltSplitBeb.description: The SMLT Split-BEB configured in the local IST switch.

rcIsisPeerSmltSplitBeb.name: rcIsisPeerSmltSplitBeb
rcIsisPeerSmltSplitBeb.description: The SMLT Split-BEB configured in the IST Peer switch.

rcIsisPrevInterface.name: rcIsisPrevInterface
rcIsisPrevInterface.description: ISIS local interface index for previously found adj.

rcIsisAdjTable.name: rcIsisAdjTable
rcIsisAdjTable.description: Table of IS-IS Adjacency, this is extension to the isisISAdjTable defined in ISIS MIB

rcIsisAdjEntry.name: rcIsisAdjEntry
rcIsisAdjEntry.description: An entry of rcIsisAdj Table. A Entry in table exists for each ISIS adjacency

rcIsisAdjCircIndex.name: rcIsisAdjCircIndex
rcIsisAdjCircIndex.description: The identifier of this circuit, unique within the Intermediate System. This object follows the index behavior. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and need not have any relation to any protocol value.

rcIsisAdjIndex.name: rcIsisAdjIndex
rcIsisAdjIndex.description: A unique value identifying the IS adjacency from all other such adjacencies on this circuit. This value is automatically assigned by the system when the adjacency is created.

rcIsisAdjHostName.name: rcIsisAdjHostName
rcIsisAdjHostName.description: The hostname listed in LSP, or the system name if host name is not configured.

rcIsisAdjIfIndex.name: rcIsisAdjIfIndex
rcIsisAdjIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface to which this circuit corresponds.

rcIsisLSPTable.name: rcIsisLSPTable
rcIsisLSPTable.description: Table of IS-IS LSP, this is extension to the isisLSPSummaryTable defined in ISIS MIB

rcIsisLSPEntry.name: rcIsisLSPEntry
rcIsisLSPEntry.description: An entry of rcIsisLSP Table. A Entry in table exists for each ISIS LSP

rcIsisLSPLevel.name: rcIsisLSPLevel
rcIsisLSPLevel.description: At which level does this LSP appear?

rcIsisLSPID.name: rcIsisLSPID
rcIsisLSPID.description: The 8 byte LSP ID, consisting of the SystemID, Circuit ID, and Fragment Number.

rcIsisLSPSeq.name: rcIsisLSPSeq
rcIsisLSPSeq.description: The sequence number for this LSP.

rcIsisLSPHostName.name: rcIsisLSPHostName
rcIsisLSPHostName.description: The hostname listed in LSP, or the system name if host name is not configured.

rcIsisLSPLifetimeRemain.name: rcIsisLSPLifetimeRemain
rcIsisLSPLifetimeRemain.description: The remaining lifetime in seconds for this LSP.

rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibTable.name: rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibTable
rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibTable.description: Table of IS-IS PLSB IP Unicast FIB

rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibEntry.name: rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibEntry
rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibEntry.description: An entry of rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFib Table. A Entry in table exists for each PLSB IP unicast forwarding entry.

rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibVrfId.name: rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibVrfId
rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibVrfId.description: VRF ID of the IP unicast FIB entry, 0 indicates NRE.

rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibDestinationIpAddrT.name: rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibDestinationIpAddrType
rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibDestinationIpAddrT.description: The address type of destination IP Address.

rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibDestinationIpAddr.name: rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibDestinationIpAddr
rcIsisPlsbIpUnicastFibDestinationIpAddr.description: Destination IP Address of the IP unicast FIB entry. Support ipv4 size(4) and ipv6 size(16)

LldpPortIdSubtype.name: LldpPortIdSubtype
LldpPortIdSubtype.description: This TC describes the source of a particular type of Port identifier used in the LLDP MIB. The enumeration 'interfaceAlias(1)' represents a port identifier based on the ifAlias MIB object, defined in IETF RFC 2863. The enumeration 'portComponent(2)' represents a port identifier based on the value of entPhysicalAlias (defined in IETF RFC 2737) for a port component (i.e., entPhysicalClass value of 'port(10)'), within the containing chassis. The enumeration 'macAddress(3)' represents a port identifier based on a unicast source address (encoded in network byte order and IEEE 802.3 canonical bit order), which has been detected by the agent and associated with a particular port (IEEE Std 802-2001). The enumeration 'networkAddress(4)' represents a port identifier based on a network address, detected by the agent and associated with a particular port. The enumeration 'interfaceName(5)' represents a port identifier based on the ifName MIB object, defined in IETF RFC 2863. The enumeration 'agentCircuitId(6)' represents a port identifier based on the agent-local identifier of the circuit (defined in RFC 3046), detected by the agent and associated with a particular port. The enumeration 'local(7)' represents a port identifier based on a value locally assigned.

LldpPortId.name: LldpPortId
LldpPortId.description: This TC describes the format of a port identifier string. Objects of this type are always used with an associated LldpPortIdSubtype object, which identifies the format of the particular LldpPortId object instance. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of '342/200/230interfaceAlias(1)', then the octet string identifies a particular instance of the ifAlias object (defined in IETF RFC 2863). If the particular ifAlias object does not contain any values, another port identifier type should be used. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'portComponent(2)', then the octet string identifies a particular instance of the entPhysicalAlias object (defined in IETF RFC 2737) for a port or backplane component. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'macAddress(3)', then this string identifies a Particular unicast source address (encoded in network byte order and IEEE 802.3 canonical bit order) associated with the port (IEEE Std 802-2001). If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'networkAddress(4)', then this string identifies a Network address associated with the port. The first octet contains the IANA AddressFamilyNumbers enumeration value for the specific address type, and octets 2 through N contain the networkAddress address value in network byte order. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'interfaceName(5)', then the octet string identifies A particular instance of the ifName object (defined in IETF RFC 2863). If the particular ifName object does not contain any values, another port identifier type should be used. If the associated ldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'agentCircuitId(6)', then this string identifies a agent-local identifier of the circuit (defined in RFC 3046). If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of '342/200/230local(7)', then this string identifies a locally assigned port ID.

rcCfmLtrReplyTable.description: This table contains a list of Linktrace replies received by a specific MEP in response to a linktrace message.

rcCfmLtrReplySeqNumber.name: rcCfmLtrReplySeqNumber
rcCfmLtrReplySeqNumber.description: The transaction identifier/sequence number returned by a previous transmit linktrace message command, indicating which LTM's response is going to be returned.

rcCfmLtrReplyHop.name: rcCfmLtrReplyHop
rcCfmLtrReplyHop.description: The number of hops away from LTM initiator

rcCfmLtrReplyReceiveOrder.name: rcCfmLtrReplyReceiveOrder
rcCfmLtrReplyReceiveOrder.description: An index to distinguish among multiple LTRs with the same LTR Transaction Identifier field value. This value is assigned sequentially from 1, in the order that the Linktrace Initiator received the LTRs.

rcCfmLtrReplyTtl.name: rcCfmLtrReplyTtl
rcCfmLtrReplyTtl.description: Ttl field value for a returned LTR.

rcCfmLtrReplyForwarded.name: rcCfmLtrReplyForwarded
rcCfmLtrReplyForwarded.description: Indicates if a LTM was forwarded by the responding MP, as returned in the 'FwdYes' flag of the flags field.

rcCfmLtrReplyTerminalMep.name: rcCfmLtrReplyTerminalMep
rcCfmLtrReplyTerminalMep.description: A boolean value stating whether the forwarded LTM reached a MEP enclosing its MA, as returned in the Terminal MEP flag of the Flags field.

rcCfmLtrReplyLastEgressIdentifier.name: rcCfmLtrReplyLastEgressIdentifier
rcCfmLtrReplyLastEgressIdentifier.description: An octet field holding the Last Egress Identifier returned in the LTR Egress Identifier TLV of the LTR. The Last Egress Identifier identifies the MEP Linktrace Indicator that originated, or the Linktrace Responder that forwarded, the LTM to which this LTR is the response. This is the same value as the Egress Identifier TLV of that LTM.

rcCfmLtrReplyNextEgressIdentifier.name: rcCfmLtrReplyNextEgressIdentifier
rcCfmLtrReplyNextEgressIdentifier.description: An octet field holding the Next Egress Identifier returned in the LTR Egress Identifier TLV of the LTR. The Next Egress Identifier Identifies the Linktrace Responder that transmitted this LTR, and can forward the LTM to the next hop. This is the same value as the Egress Identifier TLV of the forwarded LTM, if any. If the FwdYes bit of the Flags field is false, the contents of this field are undefined, and the field is ignored by the receiver.

rcCfmLtrReplyRelayAction.name: rcCfmLtrReplyRelayAction
rcCfmLtrReplyRelayAction.description: Value returned in the Relay Action field.

rcCfmLtrReplySrcMac.name: rcCfmLtrReplySrcMac
rcCfmLtrReplySrcMac.description: Mac address of the MP that respond to the LTM request for this LTR

rcCfmLtrReplyIngressAction.name: rcCfmLtrReplyIngressAction
rcCfmLtrReplyIngressAction.description: The value returned in the Ingress Action Field of the LTM. The value ingNoTlv(5) indicates that no Reply Ingress TLV was returned in the LTM.

rcCfmLtrReplyIngressMac.name: rcCfmLtrReplyIngressMac
rcCfmLtrReplyIngressMac.description: Mac address returned in the ingress MAC address field. If the rcCfmLtrReplyIngress object contains the value ingNoTlv(5), then the contents of this object are meaningless.

rcCfmLtrReplyIngressPortIdSubtype.name: rcCfmLtrReplyIngressPortIdSubtype
rcCfmLtrReplyIngressPortIdSubtype.description: Format of the Ingress Port ID. If the rcCfmLtrReplyIngress object contains the value ingNoTlv(5), then the contents of this object are meaningless.

rcCfmLtrReplyIngressPortId.name: rcCfmLtrReplyIngressPortId
rcCfmLtrReplyIngressPortId.description: Ingress Port ID. The format of this object is determined by the value of the rcCfmLtrReplyIngressPortIdSubtype object. If the rcCfmLtrReplyIngress object contains the value ingNoTlv(5), then the contents of this object are meaningless.

rcCfmLtrReplyEgressAction.name: rcCfmLtrReplyEgressAction
rcCfmLtrReplyEgressAction.description: The value returned in the Egress Action Field of the LTM. The value egrNoTlv(5) indicates that no Reply Egress TLV was returned in the LTM.

rcCfmLtrReplyEgressMac.name: rcCfmLtrReplyEgressMac
rcCfmLtrReplyEgressMac.description: Mac address returned in the egress MAC address field. If the rcCfmLtrReplyEgress object contains the value egrNoTlv(5), then the contents of this object are meaningless.

rcCfmLtrReplyEgressPortIdSubtype.name: rcCfmLtrReplyEgressPortIdSubtype
rcCfmLtrReplyEgressPortIdSubtype.description: Format of the Egress Port ID. If the rcCfmLtrReplyEgress object contains the value egrNoTlv(5), then the contents of this object are meaningless.
